INSERT INTO `reviews` VALUES
('1a2b9f9944c7c1ac616c97c3c8c44448',279,1,4.3,'Merlot and Nero d\'Avola form the base for this easy red wine that would pair with fettuccine and meat sauce or pork roast. The quality of the fruit is clean, bright and sharp.'),
('d2be91d1b0aca24dbb9b24c4b68d72e9',277,2,4.3,'Part of the extended Calanìca series, this Grillo-Viognier blend shows aromas of honeysuckle and jasmine, backed by touches of cut grass and wild sage. In the mouth, it shows ripe yellow-fruit flavors.'),
('116e3378b63b5d51d6a212d08f141c81',271,3,4.3,'Spicy, fresh and clean, this would pair with fried seafood or spaghetti con vongole. It offers pretty citrus tones followed by a drying mineral nuance.'),
('b9e0d791130f6067527c31fa60b2d0ee',631,4,4.25,'There\'s a touch of toasted almond at the start, but then this Grillo revs up in the glass to deliver notes of citrus, stone fruit, crushed stone and lemon tart. The mouthfeel is crisp and simple.'),
('959f7ae7ff817eee7b3dc284d9958c91',5,5,4.55,'Cooked cranberry is spiced with anise, peppercorn and roasted beef slices on this bottling from a vineyard planted by three brothers who are longtime Salinas Valley farmers. The palate shows dark cranberry and raspberry, spiced up by chopped sage, thyme and bay leaf.'),
('921bae979246f465865fb8a6b8735668',284,6,4.45,'A good value, this is an easy-pleasing Syrah with vibrant notes of red plum, cherry and blueberry. Fine, dusty tannins reminiscent of cocoa powder and dried crushed berries stay after swallow alongside a hint of sweet smoke flavor.'),
('5af3a644605eea38813e6688b83d7c72',747,7,4.7,'Smoky, with bursts of sage and celery root, this is a wine that is unabashedly earthy, spicy, bold and juicy at its core. Light-bodied and delicate, the palate shows beautiful floral undertones. This is a complex and beguiling bottling that should hold well for years to come.'),
('dd0082f0338a2dbff22b416b29a36a6e',764,8,4.25,'This is a delicious and ripe-fruited wine. Dominated by Fernão Pires, it has an apple-puree texture: smooth and creamy. The wine has an edge of light acidity at the end to give it a lift. Drink now.'),
('f800b4625167a066ec49dca002a17740',60,9,4.95,'A stupendous Pinot Noir, showing how beautifully this vineyard performs in the remote Sonoma Coast above Fort Ross. Williams Selyem\'s last few vintages of Precious Mountain have been extraordinary, but this 2009 tops them all. The wine is as light as a feather in the mouth, modest in alcohol and delicately feminine, like pure satin. However, few Pinot Noirs in the world achieve this level of concentration. Wild raspberries and cherries, cola, sleek minerals, dusty baking spices and smoky oak combine for flavors that are utterly delicious. After all that, it possesses an indefinable attribute of fascination. Will age well for a long time, if you can keep your hands off it. Now–2021.'),
('5d2dcb1420299240c961615430067533',706,10,4.35,'Hay, straw, match stick and minerally aromas outweigh this wine\'s fruit scents by a measurable margin. This is chunky and a bit soft in the mouth, a reflection of 2012\'s heat. And while it\'s round as a ball, it\'s slightly vegetal and bitter tasting on the palate, with grapefruit and bell pepper flavors.'),
('ec03914f4cf9a43db495a0f9efe740fe',631,11,4.25,'There\'s a touch of toasted almond at the start, but then this Grillo revs up in the glass to deliver notes of citrus, stone fruit, crushed stone and lemon tart. The mouthfeel is crisp and simple.'),
('2d399f7cd3b4cdfc5249f92256f45b08',464,12,4.45,'Made with 80% Nasco and 20% Vermentino, this offers delicate aromas of marzipan, dried apricot and wildflower honey. On the sweet, full-bodied palate, notes of white almond back up acacia honey and tangerine zest.'),
('52c674a0282f79f427bd3169d5c60077',212,13,4.35,'Molasses, smoked bacon, beef jerky and loads of clove and exotic spice come to mind. Lamùri is a pure expression of Nero d\'Avola that also offers plum, prune and blackberry. Despite the mature fruit flavors, the wine has good acidity and crispness.'),
('64a083d0b5c0db37f0a19ecc09ed6f2f',712,14,4.4,'This is nicely balanced and easy in terms of its tannins and overall intensity, with enough structure to pair with game meat or succulent red meat. The bouquet is redolent of spice, black fruit and crushed granite.'),
('df80ffccd4a49c962d60185cbde63ad9',308,15,4.3,'Very oaky and very ripe, offering a flood of pineapple jam, pear, vanilla and toasty oak flavors. Crisp acidity provides needed balance and a clean, brisk mouthfeel.'),
('ddbee53a77e4147f22b38f70828a5107',933,16,4.45,'This blend features aromas of vanilla, sweet tobacco and cherry followed by big, masculine flavors of cassis, raspberry, tobacco and cedar. Deep spice undertones add to the dimension of the wine. Ageable and intense and best paired with more robust meat dishes.'),
('90ce660d70429f0371956c7d566ebe8c',641,17,4.5,'Campanaro is a unique blend of Fiano and Greco grapes that opens with a beautiful bouquet of stone fruit, honey, white almond and Golden Delicious apple. It a dry, crisp wine with a focused, fine feel in the mouth.'),
('8a35a526270708b434e1b6dd8b86f711',297,18,4.35,'Although this Pinot is a bit thin, it does offer plenty of elegant sophistication. The structure shows off the Sonoma Coast, with vibrant acidity and a clean, dry mouthfeel. The flavors are of cherries with bitter skins, pomegranates, rhubarb, cola and peppery spices. Drink now.'),
('dff1bb03f05ba726354254391bd3f748',547,19,4.5,'Here\'s a brilliantly golden-colored Chardonnay from sunny Sicily with aromas of mature fruit, spice, roasted nut and even a surprising note of white truffle. The mouthfeel is creamy and smooth and the wine would taste great with risotto and wild mushrooms.'),
('f0f397af9ee5b63045053fe628642f10',631,20,4.25,'This is a fresh, tonic and light Grillo that would pair with endive salad and sliced oranges or red beets in vinaigrette. The wine offers citrus, green herb and fresh kiwi aromas.'),
('fd5286ce940ae56cb2b0cee79e76e652',228,21,4.25,'This version of Calanìca (made from 60% Frappato and 40% Syrah) offers a low impact bouquet of earthy forest fruit and bramble. It\'s a light, lean wine with a touch of soft spice on the close.'),
('900e57e02a57ad5009636b3f72fa98fd',62,22,4.65,'One of Testarossa\'s best 2011 Pinot Noirs, of 14 released, this wine is, in a word, gorgeous. First off is the silky texture, as airy as a cloud. Then there are the flavors, complex and lush in raspberries, cherries, brown sugar, cinnamon and oak. The wine is so delightful to drink now, you might miss out on cellaring it until 2018 to see where it goes.'),
('48ac985f0d338581cd6d18fd8c89af65',264,23,4.3,'This value wine opens with a fresh, citrusy bouquet and features a compact, streamlined mouthfeel.'),
('a0f0e10b27b69ecca16a57152d13b486',271,24,4.3,'Inzolia is one of the most widely planted varieties in Sicily and the results are surprisingly consistent. The grape is usually vinified in stainless steel to lock in its freshness and lemon-lime aromas. This wine faithfully follows suit.'),
('69068fa01ad06dcabd79865fb67961de',249,25,4.3,'A great value wine, this fruity Syrah opens with bright blueberry, cherry and plum woven between subtle nuances of leather, spice and smoked bacon.'),
('240cdf0c2c59fe66c80fa890a1998612',708,26,4.35,'Instantly recognizable for the eye-catching purple dot on its label, this offers a slightly austere expression of Aglianico that would pair with almost any grilled meat dish. The soft mouthfeel is characterized by notes of cherry, tobacco and spice.'),
('8fd046b582c68da80b2b1c252359da77',181,27,4.55,'A proprietary blend inspired by Chateauneuf-du-Pape, the Count\'s Red is more closed than the other offerings from Tasca, showing little on the nose beyond chocolate. In the mouth, raspberry fruit begins to emerge; the wine is obviously a big, full-bodied and tannic. It\'s meant to age, and we think it will do so just fine. Try in 2008, or pair it with hearty meat dishes if you can\'t hold out that long.'),
('e6b8370aca47814fdd69468bfbfcfc22',329,28,4.5,'This winning blend of 75% Nero d\'Avola and 25% Cabernet Sauvignon is firm and structured, but coddles that structure in a layer of lushness. Briary, raspberry fruit is balanced by darker notes of cassis and chocolate. Drink now-2010.'),
('8a678f890a21a779885fa90b0e457c91',577,29,4.5,'A rich and full-boded white blended from Sauvignon Blanc and Inzolia, the Nozze d\'Oro begins with lightly buttery aromas of passionfruit, before developing melon and peach flavors in the mouth. Finishes long, with a refreshing note of bitter almond.'),
('aeca858abfc80c7ff4f111915b8b2ecb',271,30,4.3,'Spicy, fresh and clean, this would pair with fried seafood or spaghetti con vongole. It offers pretty citrus tones followed by a drying mineral nuance.'),
('a89a22e171d81422c0d7d9d388a9793e',47,31,4.55,'A brilliant Chardonnay, brimming with powerfully ripe tropical fruit and pear flavors, enriched with smoky, sweet oak. The key here is acidity and the minerality that accompanies the best Santa Lucia Chards. Drink this flamboyant wine now for maximum vibrancy.'),
('28865dc9f1bb8cab0aa4aac3af0a4b32',228,32,4.25,'Made from an interesting blend of Frappato and Syrah, this Calanìca offers the bright, fruity freshness of the first variety against the bold, soft chewiness of the second.'),
('59ac48f69513d8f5f35dfddf4d595735',632,33,4.25,'This fresh and easy Sicilian white is a blend of Insolia, Grecanico and Catarratto with easy citrus and stone fruit aromas. Pair it with Chinese chicken salad.'),
('b1edb98c45e279a5ab10a4079638233c',631,34,4.25,'Sushi, fried calamari, grilled vegetables or barbecued shrimp would all make perfect companions to this fresh, easy Sicilian white wine. It ends with citrus, lime and herbal aromas.'),
('866cd058c31814a71810f272904dc9bc',1040,35,4.4,'Juicy, sweet and fat in glycerine, this has complex flavors of blackberry and cherry pie filling. The tannins and acids give it a fine, elegant structure. Drink now.'),
('2d33aa9838db0fcec2cc814dcca3f832',641,36,4.6,'The two grapes that represent the pride of southern Italian winemaking—Fiano and Greco—are blended here to produce a creamy, rich white wine that will pair well with steamed lobster or crab. Beautifully balanced sensations of acidity and spice appear on the long finish.'),
('eab1e942853c36ad2beac81938ba3b9d',1,37,4.2,'Tastes as sweet as a dessert wine, with caramelized new oak and sugary pineapple, orange and apricot jam flavors, brightened with crisp acidity. Will appeal to those who like this style.'),
('7fc6c998af705173e971231678a0da82',554,38,4.45,'Làvico, made from Nerello Mascalese grapes harvested on the slopes of Mount Etna (with 10% Merlot), exhibits aromas of burnt coal, bramble, lead pencil, blueberry and wild strawberries. The wine moves with delicate, feminine steps but is not without power and intensity.'),
('dadd9cc38224678281eca38defec81c7',180,39,4.6,'This is one of the bigger, more powerful Chardonnays out there in the market. It\'s triumphant in ripe pineapple jam, apricot-infused crème brûlée, Meyer lemon custard, buttered toast and cinnamon spice flavors, wrapped into a creamy rich texture that finishes dry and crisp. May lack subtlety, but what immense pleasure it offers.'),
('a41ee71236fe6572b17668c046824ed2',1002,40,4.65,'Something special from the west side of the Salinas Valley, with its fogs and wind. Drinks very bright in acids and even some tannins that frame a melange of flavors, including sweet lime, green apple, and the ripest white peach. Tastes leesy and has the texture of sweet cream. This distinctive wine defines Monterey\'s interpretation of Chardonnay.'),
('21d054743eba9c736015d06d0034bb28',1002,41,4.55,'Made in the Sleepy Hollow style, extraordinarily ripe, almost botrytized in apricot and honey flavors like a dessert wine, except that it\'s bone dry. Really epitomizes this vineyard and corner of Monterey, where Chard ripens to beautifully while maintaining acidity.'),
('b51c311efde029bb9a53a1f714540b81',249,42,4.35,'Syrah finds a perfect home in Sicily. The sea breezes and sunny weather help give ripe aromas of blackberry, cherry, tobacco and smoked bacon. It exudes a spicy touch of barbecue sauce, with gritty tannins that give the wine texture, richness and power.'),
('e896f90475d54ba79b145354c53ea205',196,43,4.35,'This white blend is the quintessential seafood wine. It offers citrus, stone fruit, crushed mineral and pretty flower nuances.'),
('9a72db41a4aa5a6b36df7c65b0652749',248,44,4.35,'Fragrant and floral, with a bright golden color, this expression of Insolia shows a rich, creamy mouthfeel, with orange blossom and candied lemon flavors.'),
('1db1ad6a9dedb922ab1f898e9d5e07d8',124,45,4.55,'Duca Enrico is one of Sicily\'s most celebrated expressions of Nero d\'Avola with excellent complexity and compelling notes of licorice, black fruit and spice. It tastes clean and polished and ends on a cooling note of fresh acidity.'),
('dd5abcfef73910fb04a14329b045dc9b',78,46,4.6,'This is an absolutely lovely Pinot Noir that\'s softly refined and balanced, yet so complex. It\'s silky and dry, with waves of raspberries and cherries, red currants, mocha, red licorice and sautéed wild mushrooms. Drink now–2015 for fresh appeal.'),
('f3b0f6b5f18c35b5fdb34b5a704c2f8f',251,47,4.55,'This is a big wine that\'s not ready now—it\'s too tannic. That gives it a lockdown, numbing quality that blocks a full appreciation of the fruit. But what fruit! Blackberries pure and simple, reduced to their quintessence. Such is the inherent integrity of this wine that it should effortlessly negotiate 4 to 6 years, gradually softening.'),
('8d91699c43a62052d53eeac5f9bdb81b',297,48,4.55,'This shows the lovely balance of both the winery and the appellation, with a silky, lightly tannic mouthfeel brightened by plenty of acidity. The flavors are delicate and complex, suggesting wild raspberries, thyme, cranberries and toast. No reason to age this puppy, so drink now–2016.'),
('19dedbe9f3d52bf626312aebc7196fbd',680,49,4.4,'The opulence of this Chard comes at least as much from the buttered toast and caramel notes of oak, as it does from the underlying pineapple and tropical fruit flavors. It\'s a crowd pleaser. Drink now.'),
('a90c7a250e606c71f654d4ed89a62603',704,50,4.4,'Here\'s a rich, smooth wine for drinking now. It\'s softly luscious, packed with blackberry, cherry, anise and cedar flavors that finish with quite a bit of complexity.'),
('eafd63432c85da405b967e3a1962e6e4',52,51,4.55,'This is a softly delicious, immediately likeable Pinot. It\'s all about pie-filling raspberries and cherries and cola, with sweet toasted oak and fabulously exotic spices, leading to a dry finish. Defines in its own way coastal Pinot in its ripest, silkiest, drink-me-now incarnation.'),
('98ac9e795a357c80469efa372618896e',233,52,4.6,'This Pinot\'s immediate lusciousness belies its complexity. Your first impression is of ripe raspberries and cherries that taste like they were baked into a pie. Then layers of minerals, mushrooms, cola and earthier fruits like persimmons and rhubarbs appear, all made brisk by amazing acidity and finishing bone dry. Lovely now and over the next six years, after an hour or two in the decanter.'),
('784e1055148b760a3da7931620a4e2f6',180,53,4.55,'From a cool appellation, a wine that smells bright and clean, like the scent you get when slicing into a fresh peach. There\'s also a lot of young, toasty oak riding on top of the fruit. Long in the mouth and in the finish, this delicious wine has crisp, supporting acids.'),
('ba9b9cde559a829335ba2541c5ae8100',228,54,4.35,'Frappato and Syrah make perfect blending partners. The first grape shows light, feminine characteristics, with bright berry and cola nuances. The second delivers color, dark fruit, density and savory spice.'),
('5eddb3ec3164e069efef405bd7164adc',212,55,4.35,'Lamùri shows a food friendly side of Nero d\'Avola that would pair with veal, pork or roasted turkey. The bouquet is redolent of cherry cola, forest fruit, ginger and toasted nut. Subtle notes of smoke and spice appear on the finish.'),
('e9b9aa2a455f7b20532c4043148dd9aa',338,56,4.35,'Fresh and easy, this shows bright berry aromas, with subtle touches of forest floor and bramble. This should pair well with barbecued pork or grilled hamburgers.'),
('75b9aeab3af5bcd63c23e5af91587f8b',212,57,4.35,'Lamùri is a solid value wine from Sicily that shows fresh fruit nuances and loads of wild berry and white almond. Try it with baked salmon or creamy shellfish dishes.'),
('4bb97447294a825ee852161475e501da',344,58,4.35,'A great value choice from Sicily, this bright Nero d\'Avola is perfumed and floral, with red rose, violet and wild berry aromas. The mouthfeel is delicate, polished and fresh.'),
('4eeb7344ae967a9067716b12a2802b3c',248,59,4.35,'From the newly created Vittoria appellation in Sicily, this bright white wine opens with citrus, crushed almond, peach and exotic fruit. The mouthfeel is fresh, compact and tight.'),
('a4b594ddf3f5fb8f1f86607d1ba7635c',632,60,4.3,'Here\'s the quintessential Mediterranean fish wine that offers easy aromas of citrus, almond flower and peach. Think grilled tuna, halibut and pan roasted sea bass. The wine is light, fresh and offers a touch of piquant acidity on the close.'),
('86d8771b0600c85515649ad955ba3ee3',24,61,4.6,'A classic high-end Carmenère, with enticingly rich, chocolaty, herbal aromas. The palate is lush but balanced, with a generous texture, smooth tannins and plenty of depth. Saturated in flavor, with blackberry, herbal notes, chocolate, spiced meat and more. Drink now through 2012.'),
('34f9dbd86f8c47378931a6eceef0f86d',255,62,4.35,'Nero d\'Avola and Merlot are blended to produce a tight, crisp, cherry-driven red wine with almond and toasted pistachio overtones. Pair this wine with veal, chicken or pork.'),
('b0eaffe54d4fbb3d42435d58c641a873',183,63,4.35,'Here\'s a very pretty white wine from Sicily (made with Grillo grapes) that opens with creamy, light nuances of almond blossom, stone fruit and citrus. Pair this wine with steamed white fish.'),
('0bfed3c5fbf526424a9111335d6bf042',193,64,4.35,'Duca di Salaparuta sources fruit from vineyard sites spanning the island of Sicily. From the Passo delle Mule location, this bright Nero d\'Avola is generous in terms of its fruit-forward aromatic profile. The mouthfeel is firm, polished and crisp.'),
('7aeeadb373a5a8765c8c0da12c3fa26f',257,65,4.65,'A first-rate Pinot Noir, dry and firm in structure. There\'s a solid minerality girding the ripe cherry, red currant and cola fruit, while sweet oak provides an ample, but balanced, coating of vanilla and toast. Luscious now right out of the bottle, and should age for a good eight years.'),
('3789e38bd8fa0d85206a4a897c7d7c58',413,66,4.3,'Made from Aglianico grapes, this fresh rosé is a garnet-pink color, with savory aromas of forest floor, bramble, wild berry and white almond. A touch of sassy spice defines the finish.'),
('b84f0b02234aa33af1fab441dfd6dad9',1606,67,4.6,'The vineyard is in the northwestern, coolest part of the Highlands, which is most susceptible to the chilly winds that blow in from Monterey Bay. You can taste the salty tang of the sea, and the wine certainly is high in acidity. It\'s also deep in cherry, raspberry, currant, cola and spice flavors. Delicious now, and should mellow over the next six years.'),
('cae07fbf17cbe710bd262b308e2e14a8',1037,68,4.35,'True to this negociant\'s style, this Chardonnay offers lots of bang for the buck. It delivers true varietal character, offering flavors of pineapples, pears and oak, wrapped into a creamy texture that finishes dry and spicy.'),
('f9ca4280cad7ce335848e0fd66a314c2',82,69,4.65,'As usual with a Hirsch Pinot, the wine is young and thick and jammy, even a little heavy, and needs time to develop. The wild raspberry, sour cherry, cola and Asian spices have a touch of smoky new oak, while the tannins and acids are noticeable, providing a dry architecture for the ripe fruit. Should develop over the next decade, as everything comes together into balance.'),
('9be9ee092cca4b383e6a522499c3f9f5',249,70,4.3,'A great value wine, this fruity Syrah opens with bright blueberry, cherry and plum woven between subtle nuances of leather, spice and smoked bacon.'),
('8691dddc8dbacc8a19b6e3a74ce6b6ce',251,71,4.7,'A great Syrah, from a winery better known for Pinot. The wine shows true power in the blueberry, blackberry, mulberry, spice and smoke flavors. Yet it\'s so elegantly constructed, with fine Central Coast acidity and imposingly rich, fine tannins. An important wine that should have an interesting future over the next 6–8 years.'),
('99f5fe9b5bf885de4e5b462cdb8ab374',180,72,4.45,'A controversial wine due to its amazing power. It\'s just tremendous in apricot, peach, nectarine, marzipan and crème brûlée flavors, like some dainty from a great pastry chef. But this oversized quality makes it difficult to enjoy with food. Almost better on its own as a cocktail sipper.'),
('779f310252bfb8085528105d06f8036d',8,73,4.55,'This wine is opulent with flavors of orange, peach, mangoes and oak, with excellent acidity. Open now and pair with lobster, crab, scallops or tuna.'),
('cd8fa859cfc2ddd908e5fe94f8b4a852',180,74,4.55,'This wine shows everything that Chardonnay lovers want. It\'s enormously rich and ripe in mango, pineapple, orange and peach flavors, enriched with sweet new oak and creamy lees. Drink now.'),
('1d5dad4290cf042143097c7ad45f727f',78,75,4.65,'A very fine Pinot Noir, dry and elegantly constructed, but it needs a little time in the cellar. That\'s due to the tannins, which are thick and noticeable in the way they create an astringency through the finish. The flavors are exceptionally rich, suggesting cherries, raspberries and tobacco, with a welcome sweetness from toasty oak.'),
('843c543e28378d8af1dc9812d22a02fb',554,76,4.45,'Vajasindi Làvico is a lively expression of Nerello Mascalese that is redolent of capers, black olives, black fruit and exotic spice. The wine is sharp and intense in the mouth, with a bright personality and some chewy, ripe fruit notes on the close.'),
('d521ea9c57c9614852df9c5f704fd2b1',45,77,4.65,'Brisk acidity brightens the ripe raspberry and cherry fruit, giving it a clean, lively mouthfeel. There\'s a jacket of tannins, but it\'s fine and easy, and oak brings just the right touch of sweet toast flavor. Lovely to drink now, and it should develop bottle complexities over the next 8–10 years.'),
('2c054affbf961b8ca32265504b9466c8',368,78,4.4,'A nice Russian River Chard, firm in acidic minerals, with an edge of dried herbs and wood char to the pineapple, green apple and cream caramel flavors.'),
('0cc7be593bc0ece4e76d0eb17e44e070',82,79,4.95,'This expresses the greatness of its vintage and vineyard, offering wave after wave of raspberry and cherry pie flavors, plus notes of red currant, sweet licorice, spicy Dr. Pepper and smoky sandalwood. There\'s also something exotically briary and wild that intrigues. Even more remarkable is the texture, an amalgam of acids and tannins that rivals any Pinot Noir ever produced in California. It should age for up to 20 years.'),
('481402500408fd11885c68cdf2a93a90',60,80,4.9,'In recent years, Precious Mountain Vineyard has provided Bob Cabral with some of his most glorious fruit. Tremendous in flash and depth, it offers compelling flavors of raspberry and cherry, accented by sweet, smoky oak. There\'s such complexity in the acid and tannin structure, and in the earthy, stony, spicy nuances, that you find something new to love with every sip. This masterpiece is fabulous now, and will develop bottle complexity over the next 15 years, at least.'),
('29b99cff37b99817def662d733bdb877',545,81,4.55,'The Tasca family shows a deft hand with Cabernet Sauvignon, and has worked hard to match this international variety to the unique Sicilian territory. This beautiful vintage opens with nicely ripened dark fruit, cola, root beer, cured meat and Teriyaki sauce. The wine\'s texture is polished, smooth and firm.'),
('eb13fd6b211827cc2b0b515cdcfcc047',233,82,4.3,'Not the most successful Rosella\'s Pinot ever. The flavors are rich enough, suggesting raspberries, cherries and cola, and the wine is dry and silky. But there\'s an acidic sharpness, reminiscent of mint jelly, that deranges the palate.'),
('f2dbdacff0ebb78aaef64df165ae0f09',377,83,4.5,'This is a big, dark, full-bodied Pinot Noir, huge in fruit and quite mouthfilling in black cherries, cola and spice. It\'s a bit ungainly now due to the size, but has the balance to age. Give it a year or two to mellow out. If you drink now, decant.'),
('4eb06b2e3d4b2b695fa4bb541830153b',1,84,4.55,'Chard freaks will love this California-style version of the variety. It\'s wonderfully fruity, with ripe pineapples, tangerines and papayas, and a rich, sweet taste, like bananas sautéed in butter and drizzled with honey. The acidity is perfect. Great job for the price, and easy to find, with production of 12,700 cases.'),
('d5bd88ced5dc56fbf73e847ab8c50b69',338,85,4.35,'Here\'s a wine that delivers big, ripe fruity tones such as sticky black cherry and blackberry comfiture but that leaves just enough room for those distinctive Sardinian notes of Mediterranean herbs. Pair this wine with red meat, especially lamb, and roasts.'),
('276b22f967347a007bbef286ca8a6fb2',229,86,4.35,'This is a fragrant and creamy white wine with pretty floral tones backed by fresh fruit and citrus. Pair it with sushi or swordfish carpaccio.'),
('82cee171565da99f6e1c92862896eb36',62,87,4.7,'A very finely crafted Pinot Noir, although it\'s also very young and wants some time in the cellar. Combines great Highlands fruit power and tannic structure with a silky, delicate mouthfeel. Beautiful now for the elaborate raspberry and cherry flavors, elaborated with beautiful oak, but better after 2013.'),
('16e9d1c9ac7dd29ca9833adc87824f3d',248,88,4.35,'Fragrant and floral, with a bright golden color, this expression of Insolia shows a rich, creamy mouthfeel, with orange blossom and candied lemon flavors.'),
('192c405d91484a869cb0abd75b920fe7',294,89,4.3,'This shows a bright quality of fruit, with fine nuances of berry, tart cherry and plum. The acidity would pair with oven-roasted lasagna with a cheesy crust.'),
('a69397498061010264953d3f3a5ae201',248,90,4.35,'From the newly created Vittoria appellation in Sicily, this bright white wine opens with citrus, crushed almond, peach and exotic fruit. The mouthfeel is fresh, compact and tight.'),
('d5a8553f69a1b930694cc7b076ea14a6',251,91,4.7,'Testarossa is better known for Pinot Noir, but their Syrahs, and particularly those from Garys\' Vineyard, are some of the best around. This 2009 is delectable now for its sheer drinkability. It\'s rich and luscious in blackberry, blueberry, smoked meat, pepper and earthy tobacco flavors, wrapped into smooth, complex tannins.'),
('19e5e6b4ba89422e3ea1dbf5b15194ca',81,92,4.7,'This is certainly one of Testarossa\'s best 2011 Pinot Noirs. The winery purchases most of its fruit, but in this case, the vineyard is co-owned by Testarossa, and winemaker Bill Brosseau had complete control in the vineyard. The wine is gorgeous, complex and ageable. Beyond the exquisite raspberry and blueberry fruit is a mineral-derived savoriness that makes it firm in the mouth. Gorgeous now, this single-vineyard wine should age well for at least 12 years.'),
('1628db17335d2b58b11e96bdcd91c885',257,93,4.7,'This single-vineyard wine feels light and silky in the mouth, like the passing of a cloud. Yet incredibly ripe cherry, raspberry, strawberry and cola flavors give it weight and importance, making it sweetly delicious. Brilliant acidity provides balance, suggesting pairing it with barbecued steak. But there\'s also as guarantee foraging as you can get in a California Pinot Noir. Should still be gathering steam in 2023.'),
('4571e240549da9763ca28f14dd3290e3',62,94,4.65,'One of Testarossa\'s best 2011 Pinot Noirs, of 14 released, this wine is, in a word, gorgeous. First off is the silky texture, as airy as a cloud. Then there are the flavors, complex and lush in raspberries, cherries, brown sugar, cinnamon and oak. The wine is so delightful to drink now, you might miss out on cellaring it until 2018 to see where it goes.'),
('6655c27bb1192cefa0ccc8ae3060abf0',22,95,4.6,'Here\'s one of Testarossa\'s more forward Pinots from the 2011 vintage, but that appeal is deceptive. It\'s rich and ripe in raspberry, strawberry and cola flavors, with an apparent sweetness that belies the dry finish. The acidity is adequate, giving it a tart softness. Yet the parts have not come together. Give it until 2017 and see what happens.'),
('9e085eb2eb10ee1fcfe69d9b16c7f972',302,96,4.55,'The rich aromas of blackberry, rosemary oil, dried sage, exotic spice and chocolate are impressive and complex. The mouthfeel is soft, enduring, velvety and long-lasting.'),
('e6598289bcc706fd65b914975720c78b',747,97,4.6,'This classy young Pinot is the second release from the winery\'s only Petaluma Gap vineyard. It\'s bone dry, mouthwateringly tart in acidity and delicate in structure, with complex cherry, cranberry, persimmon and cola flavors, nicely augmented by smoky oak. You can drink it now, after decanting for an hour or two, and it will soften a bit, or hold until 2020.'),
('caa8f949d5066c47b9cb01a4c91292a5',331,98,4.4,'Bovale is a little-known indigenous grape from Sardinia. This opens with savory aromas of cured meat, chocolate, ripe fruit and prune. The close is bold, bitter and bright.'),
('b9ab5f7f0817a467624b7ad70a7e595e',377,99,4.7,'Dazzling with silky richness, this wine is so delicious, you can\'t help but to fall in love with it. Tantalizing with waves of raspberry and cherry pie, ripe persimmon, mocha, red licorice and smoky oak flavors that finish long and satisfying. The balance of acids and tannins is just about perfect. Calling all steaks for the perfect pairing.'),
('e948558e989aa95a7bb64a9d7447e67e',193,100,4.35,'Sometimes you need a solid wine to pair with spaghetti and meat sauce or simple meat dishes like pork or breaded veal. This Sicilian Nero d\'Avola fits the bill and offers a bright bouquet of berry, almond and cola.'),
('a37794a2517a2c538d2255f9a493c829',221,101,4.6,'Serpico is a beautiful but also modern expression of Aglianico (the grapes come from ancient vines in the Taurasi area) that opens with dark notes of blackberry, crushed stone, chocolate, rum cake, licorice and cola. The mouthfeel is smooth, firm and very rich.'),
('73e32578134dcffe2fe484b9a3b743d7',196,102,4.35,'Leone d\'Almerita is a blend of Catarratto, Chardonnay, Sauvignon and Traminer that opens with a fragrant floral bouquet and pretty notes of honey, peach blossom and marzipan.'),
('a4a1a1c95d31b97828fc2abc26caf506',1606,103,4.45,'A very good wine while somehow failing to rise to expectations. Is it the vintage? All the elements are there, including ripe fruit flavors enriched with herbal and spicy complexities, generous acids and silky smooth tannins. Yet the wine is curiously New World flashy without offering nuance or depth.'),
('c61d0b6537cc825c7f9ce9477e2d1627',1107,104,4.45,'Pala\'s Entemari is higher in intensity and sophistication compared to the rest of the white wine portfolio and seems intentionally crafted for an elaborate seafood meal. Dried flowers, passion fruit, sweet nut, natural rubber and nutmeg spice add dimension and personality.'),
('6501afe09f8a95abccf8a33054c051ef',1144,105,4.25,'Notes of pear, peach and honey open the bouquet of this fresh wine. There\'s a touch of butterscotch at the back that gives it a medium-rich mouthfeel.'),
('ed3b0a65a87fbc1a3139b8f25f481587',554,106,4.45,'This pure expression of Nerello Mascalese opens with bright berry intensity and drying mineral nuances of brimstone and lead pencil. The mouthfeel is fresh, lean and etched.'),
('02162c73413fa07726275ac9d9ee69bd',472,107,4.5,'Made with a blend of diverse aromatic grapes from Sicily and beyond, this golden Passito is redolent of candied orange, dried apricot, honey, almond marzipan and loads of sweet, raw honey. The wine is dense and creamy and extremely sweet tasting on the finish.'),
('a1e1e27be1c5fb55331a9f3e97022437',367,108,4.6,'A flamboyant, crisp Chardonnay made in the popular style of elaborately toasty oak and very ripe fruit, which combine to offer an almost pastry-like dessert taste. Floods the mouth with pineapple tart, Meyer lemondrop and vanilla flavors, with suggestions of kiwis, limes and green apples. Delicious and appealing.'),
('e20670331f552de4e89f4c124a163d62',242,109,4.45,'Lighter in body and substance than the 2000 vintage, with cola, cherry and spice flavors wrapped in soft, easy tannins and crisp acids. Drinks very dry, with oaky influences. Nice in the mouth, and versatile at the table, but basically simple.'),
('ec9c09c7152267999a0caaab3b25b048',82,110,4.75,'Soft and ripe enough to drink now, after a decent decanting, it shows pure raspberry, blueberry and cherry fruit flavors, subtlely accented with cola and baking spices, and all of it wrapped into thick but smooth tannins. Good as it is, it will gain traction over the next 15 years.'),
('4811d3abe8da2c54864fe95548052b17',331,111,4.45,'Bovale is a little-known red grape from Sardinia that offers smooth and rustic characteristics that recall dried tobacco, earth, black fruit and spice. The finish is long and polished, with nice concentration and intensity.'),
('abf8ee9f681b57f20589fc145e31ef01',394,112,4.35,'Previous bottlings from this vineyard have been much better. This vintage is intensely ripe, almost Port-like, with cherry pie, cola and red currant flavors, and a hit of sweet oak. The acidity is just fine, but the wine lacks subtlety.'),
('b16f3c15ffee5309b48ef5f965872e91',229,113,4.35,'Elegant and pristine, this bears bright notes of citrus, honey, candied lemon, pear and peach. The wine is silky and fresh on the finish.'),
('4ad70ad1b01b28a0d4ce20cb0ea540bf',1606,114,4.65,'Although this Pinot is captivatingly rich in raspberry and cherry pie filling, red currant and Dr. Pepper cola flavors, it also has fine acidity and smooth, complex tannins, and a lovely overlay of sweet, smoky oak. Good as it is, there\'s no reason why it shouldn\'t develop bottle complexity over the next six years.'),
('9d7c133bb7e9483f22206a8e19c00ef6',82,115,4.75,'One sip is all it takes to be blown away by this Pinot\'s beauty. It\'s exquisitely crafted, a testament to both the vineyard and the winery\'s oenological talent. The palate is bright and tangy with acidity, and incredibly complex flavors of wild berries, mushrooms, balsam, cola and Asian spices. It\'s dramatic now, but will continue to improve for at least 15 years.'),
('522459a83b6babf7cdd7c305e74c5f56',255,116,4.45,'This is a very pleasant and elegant blend of Nero d\'Avola, Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot that does a great job of presenting a united aromatic front. There are no loose edges here and the wine is compact and smooth in the mouth. Very nice.'),
('1e4f6d2107c802bc17383e95f9e6a9b6',341,117,4.35,'This is a gorgeous, crisp white wine with a slightly herbal dimension and drying mineral tones that frame a solid core of stone fruit, pear and melon. This is the first vintage of a fascinating wine that represents a piece of enological archeology: Once-abandoned Grillo vineyards on the tiny, but ruined-filled, island of Mozia (off the coast of Marsala, Sicily) have recently been revived. Only accessible by boat, this is a dreamy destination for wine tourists.'),
('71b0051aec88c69efbd7c003d216018e',377,118,4.5,'There are Russian River Pinot Noirs that are dark, heavy and dense, and then there are bottlings like this. It\'s a silky, light-hearted wine, easy and gentle in the mouth. At the same time, the flavors are complex, with waves of cherries, red currants, cola, pomegranates, mocha and an array of sweet Asian spices. Drink now.'),
('aad6a7dbe1da97afb17d270e3cb2b6c7',227,119,4.35,'Sicilian Pinot Nero shows much of the variety\'s natural aromas of blue flower and wild berry, only in a thicker, more concentrated context. The southern Italian sun has done its part to produce a round, broad mouthfeel.'),
('28d53e57a2be6e6e3375f8a24a7ef29a',853,120,4.3,'A good, sound red wine, dry and full-bodied, with green herb, blackberry, blueberry, spice and oak flavors. It\'s easy to drink with a nice steak or burger, and a good value for the price.'),
('a587ca380f7bf2ae89740471a83b2f0f',297,121,4.6,'This is a pretty Pinot that\'s light and silky on the palate, and comforting in its moderate alcohol and spicy, exotic flavors. It offers waves of wild forest berry pie, baking spice, sweet-and-sour persimmon and sandalwood flavors that are intriguingly complex. Absolutely delightful now.'),
('3053b67aaa94978d7b9fdf9893ddc508',62,122,4.75,'So delicious, so dazzlingly seductive, it\'s impossible not to fall in love with this wine. It detonates on the palate with an explosion of cherries and raspberries, and wonderfully smoky, buttery complexities from oak. Drily crisp and finely structured in smooth, dense tannins, it offers great pleasure now, and should develop over the next 6–8 years. Production was low, but it\'s worth a search.'),
('70e0b21a1404238e10c7affbc96d7a22',1784,123,4.6,'This shows the combo of a cool vintage and deft winemaking. It\'s impressively deep in citrus, fig and pepper flavors, with just a touch of oak that adds a nice, smoky edge. With high acidity, it really gets those tastebuds whistling. Best of all, the wine achieves the Holy Grail: low alcohol, only 13%, and bone dryness.'),
('784fb675eac5c18b758f55dc42bd2169',229,124,4.35,'Elegant and pristine, this bears bright notes of citrus, honey, candied lemon, pear and peach. The wine is silky and fresh on the finish.'),
('8d6fadf2d71161c0383731b6aa664e50',544,125,4.55,'This beautiful vintage of Duca Enrico shows riper fruit than the 2006, with its hint of green leaf. The fruit here is plush, rich and chewy, with long-lasting tones of blackberry pie, leather, spice and moist pipe tobacco.'),
('5c27a74c4f75a29f30f306306c5179e3',181,126,4.55,'An icon wine of Sicily, Rosso del Conte is the Sassicaia of southern Italy because it opened the road for a quality-based revolution. This gorgeous blend (55% Nero d\'Avola, 17% Perricone and 28% other mixed varieties) is soft, subtle and rich, with long-lasting tones of cherry and spice and well-extracted concentration.'),
('613f27875800eccf53ab7f5a76426a63',45,127,4.35,'Rather heavy in texture, a big, full-bodied and tannic Pinot that seems overly extracted and oaky. The vintage was very difficult due to early September heat waves, and everything depended on exquisite timing. It\'s very good, despite the rusticity. Drink now through 2012.'),
('235221bac429a5a0417b8ba6753842d9',612,128,4.25,'Here\'s a luminous and vibrant rosato from Sicily with a saturated pink color and thick aromas of ripe raspberry and forest fruit. It has good acidity and enough heft and density in the mouth to pair with pasta or fish soup.'),
('f1994095222139b3ba521225d95a58de',359,129,4.8,'With the 2009 vintage, De Loach is at the top of its Pinot Noir game, and this one, from a chilly vineyard south of Sebastopol, is among its best ever. The crisp acidity, like a squirt of lime, that accompanies the raspberry, cherry and persimmon fruit is bracing. Meanwhile, a mushroomy earthiness gives complex layers that don\'t stop. It should age through the next decade.'),
('c4bd87606490be0af4d00f2e003fb01e',1107,130,4.4,'A beautiful blend of Vermentino, Malvasia and Chardonnay, this has sophisticated tones of exotic fruit, pineapple, peach and apricot. It offers a broad, creamy feel on the palate. These three grapes compliment each other nicely in terms of structure, aromas and texture.'),
('6abb7da11a1eeb7bea154a5d32257408',221,131,4.65,'Serpico is a bold, larger-than-life wine, with beautiful aromatic intensity and notes of black fruit, espresso and crushed granite. Some 18 months of oak aging adds elements of dark spice and smoke; and the wine shows firm tannins and a long, polished mouthfeel. It\'s very elegant and should withstand many more years of cellar aging.'),
('7d1688d7082d1ef0ebc3353c8ee80cb7',364,132,4.65,'If only more Zins were this good! De Loach hits this one out of the park, with its fabulous wealth of wild berry, mocha, anise, spice, grilled meat and mushroom flavors. The high alcohol adds a wonderful varietal heat to the peppery finish.'),
('283a31092847c14afbf34e830bea52d0',367,133,4.65,'You\'ll find plenty of fruit, in the way of ripe mangoes, peaches, green apples and limes, as well as a sweet coating of smoky oak. However, it\'s elevated by brisk acidity and a stony, tangy minerality that must come from the soil of this cool-climate vineyard.'),
('c91a6c19db368bbdb77effe9c81e80a6',366,134,4.65,'Lusty, powerful, ripe and concentrated, this Zin could also be described by the old Yiddish word, zaftig. The vineyard is in a warm part of the valley, and the grapes show the influence of sun and heat in the jammy, slightly baked quality of the cherries and blackberries. It\'s a really fine example of Russian River Zinfandel.'),
('e68d2a0e2a448c19aaf2df0963ae4aae',373,135,4.65,'Tastes of perfectly ripened pineapple, pear, lime and peach flavors. On the structural side is fine acidity and a tangy minerality, like a lick of cold steel. Oak is here, notable but perfectly integrated. Give this Chard a little time in the glass to breathe.'),
('ece663dc0ddc86739895e773643a1fd8',728,136,4.35,'You\'ll find lots to like in this dry, stylish Cabernet. It\'s full-bodied and tannic, but you can drink it now for the wealth of blackberry, black currant, cola, mineral and oak flavors.'),
('13f11db7849849aecafea1c162bb9215',550,137,4.5,'This is a dark and muscular expression of Syrah executed in a quasi-Australian style, with loads of concentration and spice, backed by smoked bacon, Teriyaki, candied berry and Indian spice.'),
('b464f01f5787e52d19fb2c30d1c001b2',547,138,4.5,'Sicily\'s Tasca family does a terrific job with this golden Chardonnay. The wine reflects the sunshine, warmth and generosity of the island. Aromas of stone fruit, vanilla, rose and almond blossom are followed by a beautifully creamy mouthfeel.'),
('e89ed7b8fbe2b3e573be6a46def6f566',124,139,4.5,'A founding father of Sicily\'s quality wine tradition, the 2006 Duca Enrico is a plush and rich red with bold berry flavors and a spicy vegetal touch of green curry leaf. An icon of southern Italian wine, the wine is well suited to roast beef or sophisticated meat dishes.'),
('8ea515acc229ddbe02cec055ddaa9347',719,140,4.35,'Here\'s a big, tannic Cabernet, stuffed with black currants, olives and cassis, with a lot of sweet oak. It\'s bone dry and elegant, and while it\'s not a cellar candidate, it does show fine character for drinking now.'),
('8af190e0f1fa43690e81b33e96f00244',308,141,4.5,'Great acidity and minerality in this elegant young wine. Doesn\'t show the rich concentration of De Loach\'s single-vineyard Chards, but then again, it costs far less. It\'s actually a good value for a dry, minerally and complex Russian River Chardonnay. Don\'t drink it too cold.'),
('2dedba27904032cd62c3ee9444a19ffd',1443,142,4.3,'This is a very distinctive, even eccentric, Cab that must reflect its single-vineyard terroir.  The usual black-currant and blackberry notes are there, but the aroma is sharply dominated by an herbal streak, somewhat stalky or green, as if some of the grapes didn\'t ripen.  Tastes a little sharp.  Purists might want to age it for 3-5 years to see if it softens up.'),
('d5015cbb71365a8b0036a6afc220deb4',96,143,4.6,'A leesy, young wine, with the slightly sour, creamy richness of sur lie aging. A peacock\'s tail of tropical and citrus fruits and pears is brightened by crisp acidity and sweetened by toasty oak. Rich and complex; drink now and over the next three years.'),
('cb97f3c270968b34cf538e151780f5a0',1356,144,4.55,'Give this young Cabernet a good decant before you serve, because it\'s a big, brooding wine that needs some air to open up. Right out of the bottle, it\'s tannic and dry, and the blackberry and black currant flavors are buried under a blanket of astringency. But it\'s quite a good, well-made wine.'),
('c94dc03be2e9c59058b0b43e17e9a535',82,145,4.65,'Rich in fine, pure tannins, this Pinot is delicious now, but has the structure to age. It shows ripe wild black cherry, currant, mocha, anise and spice flavors that finish with a smoky, oaky sweetness. Best now for its approachability, and over the next few years.'),
('240a3f37f37b966f4e5a3c304d6b58cd',394,146,4.65,'This is one of the winery\'s more elegant, sensual wines. What it does not possess in sheer power it more than makes up for in hedonistic delight. Racy and silky, it excites the palate with intricate layers of black raspberry and cherry tart, cola, Asian spices and smoky oak. The finish goes on and on and on.'),
('37382b85b9d7b68f8fd62cd8527485db',377,147,4.6,'This polished wine offers an array of ripe cherry, pomegranate, persimmon and cola flavors, making it rich and sweet in the mouth. Yet the finish is entirely dry, and you\'ll find plenty of scoury acidity to rip through the greasy richness of lamb or duck.'),
('cdfe565bc694dd3a1f5adc7b550cdee0',221,148,4.55,'Give this gorgeous wine a few more years in the bottle so that the evident oak tones become tame and supple. You can count on the wine\'s aromas of cherry, blackberry and plum to carry it forward. At this young stage, however, those oak shadings are too evident and the wine is in its infancy. Drink after 2012.'),
('f38610f3358080ddd4aeab54c9260aad',81,149,4.35,'A difficult Pinot Noir to evaluate. It\'s very dry, acidic and tannic, with sharp flavors of blackberries that sweeten into jam on the finish. The question is one of ageability. Try cellaring for five years and see what happens.'),
('9bd32a63b85bd0f438493ecb685d9ff4',979,150,4.3,'There\'s a delicate and light quality to this Inzolia, a native grape of Sicily, that resembles white flower and stone fruit. The wine is generous and round in the mouth with peachy flavors of mature fruit but it also has enough acidity to keep the palate refreshed.'),
('e3dd7618e21e200cb51772c727910cf7',294,151,4.3,'The Sallier de la Tour line from Tasca d\'Almerita offers some of Sicily\'s best values. This easy expression of Nero d\'Avola shows mild tones of cherry, spice and almond. It\'s a perfect pasta or pizza wine.'),
('39e9cdfba49477a081bfd72416b6d1bb',396,152,4.4,'This Pinot Noir may become more rich and charming in coming years, but right now it\'s fresh, tart and jammy in raspberries and cherries. It\'s also a bit heavy, almost as if a bit of Grenache found its way into the blend.'),
('9b2becc41ab2993c54ce3037b15166c9',242,153,4.35,'Released at less than one year of age, this wine is immature, almost a barrel sample. It\'s vibrant in cherries, milk chocolate and new oak, but disjointed. Needs time. Give it until late 2009 to come together.'),
('2959f01a14a88d05a0722aaeb686fab5',344,154,4.2,'This Nero d\'Avola offers very ripe aromas of stewed prunes and hickory smoke. The wine tastes and feels like a hot climate version of Amarone and offers huge intensity and flavors of raisin, dried prune, oregano and rosemary. Overall, this is a strange, super-ripe wine.'),
('11f359e51dfd016c66f2338888a80a89',1344,155,4.2,'Tastes like there\'s too much oak on this Chard. Although the new wood is only 20%, the wine oozes sweet, caramelized vanilla, with only modest expressions of fruit. The underlying wine just isn\'t powerful enough to support that powerhouse overlay.'),
('3293217dafe22a67352c29bd11ea9bd0',512,156,4.25,'New oak accounts for only 30% of the barrel regimen, but it dominates this Chardonnay, with buttered toast, vanilla and caramel flavors. Fortunately there\'s also strong pineapple, Asian pear and apricot fruit, but the oak is too powerful.'),
('de2e51c0e0a7ca94ad4706afbb450c49',1424,157,4.2,'Earth and wood aromas open to a tart berry palate. The wine has a mildly creamy texture, but the fruit seems clipped with a slight green note. High acidity gives the wine an edgy feel and it closes a bit short, with more tart berry fruit.'),
('4411873cb68ccc93da92f17f9545cdb1',171,158,4.35,'Camastra is a 60-40 blend of Nero d\'Avola and Merlot from Tenuta Regaleali that delivers distinct aromas of blackberry fruit, leafy vegetable, green pepper, cherry and moist earth. The wine is firm and black in concentration with a high quality of tannin.'),
('51a50e398a4f3b3a3e709966ff8822f4',38,159,4.2,'This Riesling is slightly sweet, but it\'s balanced by crisp acidity. The tangerine, green apple and peach flavors have a honeyed finish.'),
('794decb419ced42800aa6d2e3ef15eb8',196,160,4.35,'From vineyards ranging from 700 to 900 meters above sea level, Tasca\'s blend of Catarratto and Chardonnay offers fluid aromas of white flower, brimstone and stone fruit. It\'s an easy and refreshing wine that would pair perfectly with fried calamari.'),
('1cb0272620f06ec80a483918b2d83d27',180,161,4.6,'Made of equal parts ultraripe pineapple and exotic lime fruit, coupled with sweet, smoky crème brûlée and buttered toast from oak and lees stirring, this is a super-rich Chardonnay. Don\'t drink it too cold; it matures and knits together as it breathes in the glass.'),
('e0919b588c97ae3ebff2f00fe187ddee',377,162,4.3,'The vineyard could qualify for a Sonoma Coast appellation, being in a very cool location. The vintage also was a chilly one. The resulting wine is not opulent. It has a peppery, minty dryness and acid-edged tannins, with only suggestions of cherry fruit. Clean and proper, but feels like an off-vintage Pinot.'),
('dd64f252803313e4f84a6c82a00498d4',632,163,4.3,'Here is a delicately fragrant blend of Sicilian grapes with pretty tones of white flower, acacia, kiwi and peach. This competitively priced wine is fresh and light and would make a perfect pairing with tuna salad or salmon carpaccio.'),
('be1e64a80cdc3870f3305b938ea1f51a',1518,164,4.45,'This shows dark concentration, with dense aromas of sweet cherry, tobacco, prune and blackberry. On the palate, it delivers a ripe impression of sweetness and a soft, plush texture.'),
('9ecab1071efc4fe65992f3fb1e8cb501',1519,165,4.45,'Ros\'Aura is one of the most delightful rosatos to come from southern Italy. It\'s a concentrated bright pink color, with fresh aromas of wild berry and pink grapefruit.'),
('d840688af1c99cdbccd2aee9519f4fa9',1107,166,4.4,'A beautiful blend of Vermentino, Malvasia and Chardonnay, this has sophisticated tones of exotic fruit, pineapple, peach and apricot. It offers a broad, creamy feel on the palate. These three grapes compliment each other nicely in terms of structure, aromas and texture.'),
('43879ecfa6d26a15ee4e2a2f783179ac',302,167,4.5,'This blend of Cannonau, Carignano and Bovale opens with bright, intense fruit, with notes of blackberry, crème de cassis and pomegranate juice. The mouthfeel is firm and structured.'),
('39a43256eaa907daa16a5a5d13aeb13a',171,168,4.4,'This is a blend of Nero d\'Avola and Merlot in almost equal measures. The first varietal offers aromas of red fruit, wild fennel and pistachio. The second grape lends softness and bright cherry flavor. There\'s a touch of tar and graphite on the close.'),
('4e89685b14d2ffec3b54df7769b6642c',1039,169,4.4,'Il Frappato delivers loads of zest and bright aromas of berry, chopped mint, cola and ginger. There\'s a note of black pepper on the palate, followed by some almond bitterness.'),
('ab87341799cd73958e1de4f3e1316ad0',255,170,4.35,'This blend of Nero d\'Avola and Merlot shows a black-cherry note backed by toasted nut and leather accents. It feels tight and fresh, with an easy, crisp finish.'),
('df45f9d7c7beef7418834413f5132196',227,171,4.35,'Bright garnet in color, this delicate wine has aromas of cassis, sour cherry and violet, plus a drying touch of mineral. The mouthfeel is lean, fresh and sharp.'),
('c26b2620ba1ec593cb34eea5ea530992',78,172,4.6,'A beautiful Pinot that shows its coastal influence in the balance of ripe, long hangtime fruit and crisp acidity. Floods the mouth with cherry, cola, mocha, cinnamon toast, black pepper and vanilla flavors that are delicious. With its edge of tannins, it will hold for a few years of aging.'),
('86da72441a13e54754a8c95aae1bdf99',747,173,4.8,'A new bottling from the winery. The vineyard is in the Petaluma Gap, a cool area south of the Russian River Valley, toward San Francisco. The vintage was cool, too, so the wine is brisk in acidity and low in alcohol, but it still tastes amazingly ripe and complex. The wine dazzles with waves of black raspberry jam, sweet olive tapenade, sautéed brown mushroom, root beer, moo-shu plum sauce and mocha. If those flavors sound like they don\'t go together, just try the wine. It\'s seamless and compelling. Drink now–2020.'),
('7ca1e75585218af86ab1ba11d867f60a',45,174,4.65,'This is one of the darkest of Williams Selyem\'s new Pinots and also one of the ripest. It\'s jammy in the intensity of raspberry and cherry fruit, with a savory, Dr. Pepper cola richness. The spiciness, which is one of winemaker Bob Cabral\'s specialties in capturing, is exotic. It\'s a big, fat, rich wine that needs decanting now, and should age for 4–6 years.'),
('8c48bc06e8a05176d817c39da3d0bd29',183,175,4.4,'A pure expression of Grillo, this offers clean fruit, with pristine aromas of citrus, honey and white peach. The finish is crisp and streamlined.'),
('88ac3fba7cda70c3062013fd41d0bc73',612,176,4.3,'This is a terrific value wine (a rosé made from the indigenous grapes of Sicily) that opens with a bright pink color and fragrant tones of raspberry, white almond and rose petal.'),
('f8ec72d27b76afc1db5145826bfc721c',277,177,4.3,'The blend is 60-40 Grillo and Viognier and the wine offers aromatic components of both varieties. The first imparts green notes of kiwi and cut grass and the second offers sweet floral fragrances.'),
('500a87d932be3d98429fbe600519d80c',278,178,4.3,'Tangy and bright, this wine delivers a mouth-puckering blast of citrusy acidity, with a hint of bitter almond. Raspberry and peach notes help soften the finish.'),
('78c9fac831ac7f9f8cc296577ec81128',344,179,4.3,'This is a simple and cheerful Nero d\'Avola that would pair well with white meats such as roast chicken or pork. Aromas here include blueberry, forest berry and there\'s a touch of bitter almond on the close.'),
('a99b2a95329429c711c4e9491160b016',550,180,4.5,'This is a dark and muscular expression of Syrah executed in a quasi-Australian style, with loads of concentration and spice, backed by smoked bacon, Teriyaki, candied berry and Indian spice.'),
('62dd40076b1063b91d7fcd6d1447652e',547,181,4.5,'Sicily\'s Tasca family does a terrific job with this golden Chardonnay. The wine reflects the sunshine, warmth and generosity of the island. Aromas of stone fruit, vanilla, rose and almond blossom are followed by a beautifully creamy mouthfeel.'),
('d6487eba8c1ef74cc4780afae412ba0c',1,182,4.4,'There\'s lots of acidity in this young wine, which gives it a slightly minty, prickly feeling that actually adds to its food-friendliness. With pineapple, green apple, spice and smoky oak flavors, it finishes thoroughly dry. Easy to find, with 30,000 case production.'),
('9f5398d09ae5d7e421b80b20ac6f564d',233,183,4.4,'This is a wine that packs a lot of substance, although it has deliciously upfront flavors of cherries and berries. There\'s a meatiness to the palate that adds depth and interest, while crisp acidity defines the flavors on the palate. Textbook Santa Lucia Highlands Pinot Noir, fruity, complex and silky.'),
('4c736c4e1fcdd5305c7d34c44d290e00',364,184,4.4,'Rich, tannic and full bodied, with black cherry jam, red currant, raisin and spice flavors that are penetrating and long. It\'s a heady wine that\'s high in alcohol—drink now with grilled beef or chicken slathered in barbecue sauce.'),
('fec9f0a991ac2dac7405431111953893',712,185,4.4,'Rubrato is a clean and polished expression of Aglianico (stored in stainless steel instead of oak in order to preserve the freshness of the fruit) that would work with meatloaf or juicy cheeseburgers. It shows a smooth but firm quality in the mouth.'),
('8b48fe8ff806d357fd19b2e53dfe99b9',368,186,4.65,'De Loach has been showing a fine appreciation of dryness, acidity and minerality in its recent Chardonnays, and this single-vineyard bottling is another example of what makes these wines so drinkably good. It\'s rich in pears, pineapples and green apples, but that zesty stoniness lifts it into true complexity.'),
('f1673ae7d89eb7bb683b3e80ff9f8bf3',52,187,4.55,'Lush in ripe raspberries, cherries and cola, this single-vineyard Pinot Noir is balanced with crisp acidity. It\'s flamboyant, with plenty of oak influence, yet somehow manages to finish dry and tight. Drink now–2019.'),
('0d16b86ee22727757c9ec0c03a65976a',242,188,4.6,'What a delicious Pinot Noir. The cool, long vintage has given it wonderful lightness and acidity, yet also an intensity of fruit that makes it irresistible. Marked by flavors of raspberries, cherries, cola and red currants, it\'s a wine to savor now, with Pinot-friendly foods such as lamb and steak.'),
('c347f69760224cd634f61fe5a8157b61',251,189,4.6,'The winery brings a Pinot Noir-esque touch to this Syrah, with its silky-heavy texture and cherry, cola and white pepper flavors. The tannins give it away, lending weight and substance, but still, it\'s amazingly supple for Syrah this powerful. Drink now–2016.'),
('4cb2541df78ab718f32ba1c1aac7c2e8',257,190,4.6,'Has to be one of the most forward, immediately drinkable Pisoni Pinots out there. It\'s enormously flattering in raspberries, cherries, currants and cola, with sweet toasty oak complexities. The acidity is gorgeous, the tannins soft. There\'s no reason to age this beautiful wine, so drink it now and through 2016.'),
('a6137c420072a9ad419c2b6c278851cc',264,191,4.3,'This blend of Insolia and Chardonnay opens with easy layers of citrus, pear, kiwi and cut grass. Balanced acidity gives it informal, easy-drinking appeal.'),
('6f7d6b12e7d10b4f64533af8b3326235',993,192,4.5,'Although this is ready to drink now, it offers considerable tannins that are wrapped around layers of blackberries, black currants and cedar. The structure is impressive, so let it breathe in a decanter for an hour or two before serving.'),
('237795534546e2210d1985695c7f77b9',251,193,4.6,'A splendid Syrah, black in color, dry, tannic, acidic and rich in blackberry, currant, grilled meat, black pepper and toasty oak flavors that are incredibly complex and satisfying. Testarossa has a great history with this bottling, and while the wine doesn\'t have the immediately dazzling luxuriousness of the 2007, it\'s more ageable. Drink after 2016.'),
('78cd4d7603534cda929aac5723068f9d',364,194,4.6,'Made from selected barrels of the winery\'s various vineyard sources, this bottling is one of the more powerful Zinfandels out there. It\'s concentrated in blackberries, cherries, currants and oak, with wonderfully complicating notes of grilled meat, black pepper, violets and mu shu plum sauce. The wine will undoubtedly age for many years, gradually shedding primary fruit and picking up sweeter notes.'),
('a0b8053434ba541c0a2c22996c52b59e',469,195,4.55,'This is an unbelievable price for a Napa Merlot of this quality. The wine is softly tannic, dry and rich, with crisp acidity balancing complex flavors of cherries, currants, herbs, violets and cedar. Taste this against Merlots costing five times as much, and it will acquit itself well.'),
('dc24382aada2601611bf009cb0908fdc',5,196,4.45,'This tasty Pinot is one of Testarossa\'s more forward wines from the 2011 vintage. It shows the delicacy of texture and mouthwatering acidity that characterize all the wines, with candied flavors of raspberry, blueberry, mint and cola, enriched, as always, by lucious, smoky oak. It may be that the vines need some more age, for the underlying terroir seems fine.'),
('50c643a6396d23cfb16537a463b826ba',939,197,4.45,'This delicious Chardonnay combines brisk acidity and ripe tropical fruit and oak flavors, resulting in a rich wine. What it lacks in complexity it makes up for in opulence.');
INSERT INTO `wines` VALUES
(250212,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This state-owned estate of forests and vineyards grows organic grapes. This wine, softly structured and ripe has light black fruits and plenty of acidity. An undercurrent of tannin keeps the wine in order and will allow it to age. Drink from 2018.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Herdade de Catapereiro Single Vineyard',196685),
(250216,217207,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Muted aromas of tart gooseberry and lime peel dance in the bouquet, while pithy flavors of plum skin, currant and citrus rind unfold on the lightweight, slightly astringent palate. Pleasant hints of fresh herbs and saline make a fleeting impression on the close.',20,NULL,0,'Circumstance',196689),
(250280,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/02a3zhl7y0afl_375x500.jpg','Juicy and soft in blackberry and black cherry, this wine is nicely resolved in terms of tannin and oak structure,. These provide weight on the back palate, with enough heightened acidity on the finish to stay on balance. Strawberry and dried herb close things out.',29,NULL,0,'Lot 525',196620),
(250322,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/nFLCd9AbRzGcq5W4YRdXow_pb_x960.png','Almost ready to drink, this wood-aged wine is packed with herbs, dark berry fruits and the first signs of secondary spice and leather flavors. The tannins are still powerful and need to soften further, so drink this complex, concentrated wine from 2016.',41,NULL,0,'Quinta dos Quatro Ventos Reserva',196677),
(250350,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/14PGU.png','Smells of rust, iron, tomato and untracked peppercorns rise to the nose. On the palate, the wine is quite light and racy, with a little boysenberry and more sanguine flavors. Hold onto this one until 2016 for maximum enjoyment, as more flavors will emerge.',61,NULL,0,'Guidotti Vineyard',196639),
(250391,217148,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/uz82IOqnRYGH_R1EPl_YTQ_pb_x960.png','De Loach continues to impress with this Lake County vineyard-designate, a well-balanced Zin with plenty of density amid its brick tar and brambly blackberry fruit. With leveled acidity along with plenty of power, it\'ll both age and be pleasing to drink now, with smoky meats.',32,NULL,0,'Nova Vineyard',196642),
(250395,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/t9NqClWJSd-HM-EtTEsVjQ_pb_x960.png','Winemaker Bill Brosseau hits a single vineyard home run with this bottling from one of the Central Coast\'s oldest sites. It shows exotic plum, tangy cranberry, pine needle, juniper and pencil shaving scents on the nose. The palate is steeped in mulberry, marjoram and curry-like Indian spices, proving dynamic and delicious in the most compelling ways.',65,NULL,0,'Sierra Madre Vineyard',196639),
(250434,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/kNsx8cWOSZ6URMVlrXt36A_375x500.jpg','Warm vanilla notes are laid across ripe nectarine, apple skin and a twist of lemon rind on this single-vineyard study by the Los Gatos-based winery. Pencil lead kicks off the palate, which then opens into poached apples and lemon oil, laid across a sizzling acidity that lasts long.',48,NULL,0,'Lone Oak Vineyard',196639),
(250459,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Bq8ONU5eQh2o1HMPlvc-LA_pb_x960.png','With some firm structure, this wine also has great fruitiness. It offers plenty of raspberry fruits, good acidity and a solid texture of tannins. The acidity keeps the wine perfumed and fresh. Drink the wine from 2019.',80,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Clos des Ursulines',196775),
(250547,217512,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a young, fruity wine made for early drinking. With bright acidity, soft tannins and forward red fruit, it\'s easy-drinking and ready now.',15,NULL,0,'Portal da Vinha',196663),
(250668,217203,'other','Portuguese White','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','With strong wood-aging flavors, this is a full, very ripe and concentrated wine. Coming from old vines, it has depth of flavor, both fruity and rich. Peach and pear flavors dominate, along with spice from wood aging. The wine needs some aging, so drink from 2015.',19,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Reserva',196685),
(250692,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CriRUDPLTdya4EThOK_SgQ_pb_x960.png','This complex, mature wine has plenty of red fruit flavors, but its main character displays concentrated, tannin and spice. Hints of leather and rich acidity add their notes to this dense, dusty wine. It is ready to drink although it will still mature until 2020.',16,NULL,0,'Cabriz Reserva',196794),
(250777,217702,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This wine opens softly, with faint aromas of lemon-lime citrus and lean green fruit. The medium-weight palate offers a bit more concentration in green plum and lime tones, finishing pithy and somewhat bitter.',35,NULL,0,'Schaapenberg Vineyard Reserve',196689),
(250780,217705,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This opens with scents of green melon rind, strawberry hull and lime that carry through to the palate alongside an additional note of peach. A pleasant grassy tone gives interest to the finish, while ample acidity keeps the palate fresh and clean. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Barrelman\'s Select',196839),
(250795,217504,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is soft and accessible now, with plush notes of baked apple, creamed pear and oaky spice on the attack. The medium-weight palate is broad in feel, begging for a bit more lift to the rich fruit and buttered toast flavors. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Crocodile\'s Lair Kaaimansgat',196793),
(250798,217719,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/w6sdvUoZT3SMaa7qEmQ-tQ_pb_x960.png','This is a fresh and lively white, with some green bean and herbaceous notes to support the core of gooseberry and lime rind aromas and flavors. It\'s light and straightforward, but clean and so easy to enjoy. Drink now.',16,NULL,0,'The Game Reserve',196845),
(250850,217265,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/vEAUWjcVQ5G0RiV8mitkJA_375x500.jpg','Tech sheets hint at Stagecoach Vineyard being involved somehow in this Syrah, a chewy expression of coconut, smoke and game around a dense, concentrated body and well-integrated tannins. The finish is all about mocha.',19,NULL,0,'Lot 423',196620),
(250871,217780,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-TN6DBeaTROX8CsNgDYduQ_pb_x960.png','Spicy, herbal plum and cassis aromas mix in notes of olive and wet dog fur. This is more spunky and fresh than dense. Leafy berry, plum and olive are the key flavors on this Carmenère-led blend that finishes herbal and spicy, with high-toned residual acidity.',24,NULL,0,'Amplus One',196857),
(250958,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/o6yMEkIIQh25LcRRsaycaA_pb_x960.png','A mix of tropical and citrus aromas is balanced by classic Leyda scents of bell pepper and jalapeño. This is crystal clear and zesty on the tongue, with cutting acidity. Lemon, tangerine and briny notes create a citrusy flavor profile, while the finish is juicy, crisp and cleansing.',22,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(250975,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','A blend of Touriga Nacional and Touriga Franca, this dark-colored, serious wine is concentrated and structured. It offers black fruits, giving a brooding character that\'s full of power. The aftertaste with its acidity and juicy fruit is elevated and leaves with a lift.',18,NULL,0,'Andreza',196685),
(251037,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This rich wine has a dense core of dark, dry tannins. The fruit, still taking its time to come through, is full of dark plum flavors and will soon show a fresher acidity. Wood aging, dark chocolate and a smoky character all bode well for the future. Drink from 2016.',35,NULL,0,'Companhia daz Lezirias Reserva Tinto',196685),
(251038,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This rich, sophisticated wood-aged wine has complex fruits, structure and tannins. Ripe, juicy black fruits are intertwined with a solidly dry texture, powerful but still elegant. It will repay aging. Drink from 2016.',17,NULL,0,'Monte da Baía Reserva',196685),
(251039,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','A rich wine that is made by the Abreu Callado charity foundation. It has dark black currant fruits, big tannins and an elegant feel. With its structure, minerality and ripe, juicy fruitiness, it is finely structured and ageworthy. Drink from 2017.',22,NULL,0,'Abreu Callado Reserva',196685),
(251179,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/21PSO_low-335x1024.png','From the vineyard planted by the Pisoni and Franscioni families, this wine delivers bright raspberry and strawberry aromas with sweet star anise spice. The medium-bodied palate is lively and boisterous, with ripe cranberry, tangy red plum skin and sour cherry flavors, accented with a helping of dried herbs.',65,NULL,0,'Soberanes Vineyard',196639),
(251214,217203,'other','Castelão','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This is a finely perfumed wine, full of ripe Castelão grapes. It has a smooth, polished feeling from the wood aging, yet still allows plenty of room for a dense black-fruit character. It will need to age and will be best after 2016.',17,NULL,0,'Pegos Claros Reserva',196685),
(251231,218035,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/ULWx6wSqSXq9hfqkgL7y_A_pb_x960.png','As per usual, Purple Angel is a full-force experience. Hailing from a warm year, this is dense and purple in color, as it should be. Aromas of graphite, oak, tobacco and black fruit set up a jammy, full palate with saturated flavors of spice-laden blueberry and boysenberry. Finishing notes of tobacco, herb and oak cement this big-boned wine\'s ripe, beefy status. Drink through 2018.',85,NULL,0,'Purple Angel',196713),
(251240,218043,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A very pale, watery straw color, this is soft and low in intensity, with faint aromas and flavors of citrus pith and fresh grass. The palate is thin and light, followed by a short, brisk finish. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Sincerely',196839),
(251243,218046,'other','Chenin Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/vqPeRIrpTVqWGM-Ue4Q3JA_pb_x960.png','Scents of green apple and plum lead the bouquet, with a strong lime-pith note that carries through to the palate. The texture is soft and somewhat flat on the midpalate, but ample acidity and a pleasant astringency help to lift the close. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Classic Collection',196839),
(251266,217512,'other','Siria','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8x-J8AFlT1yvwBeAfDw5rg_pb_x960.png','According to legend, the Baron of Figuiera got his foot stuck in the stirrup while riding one day. He promised that where his horse stopped, he would build a chapel, and that\'s where this 2,100 foot high, cool-climate vineyard is today. The wine is crisp and fresh, with attractive citrus notes and plenty of refreshing acidity. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Barão de Figueira Branco',196663),
(251323,217625,'other','Arinto','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HtMAkZZcRwWCuQHa-NzIgg_pb_x960.png','Initially this wine is smooth and creamy textured. As it opens up it shows a cool, crisp character, with white apple fruits and layers of spice from wood aging. It\'s an elegant wine, very balanced already, but likely to age for several years. Drink now and until 2020.',40,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Encontro I Branco',196794),
(251334,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/dEYtzj3zSSqQf-6nBTn-WA_pb_x960.png','Tannins give a dark, mineral structure. The black fruits, slowly coming through, are still part of this serious purpose, with wood flavors and dry fruits prominent. It still needs aging, so don\'t drink before 2016.',22,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Reserva',196794),
(251344,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/pFMHgS7sQg2uJpH8Xken_g_pb_x960.png','With a licorice, chemise and cherry-laden nose reminiscent of a hillside hike through the chaparral in the morning dew, this wine is rather tannic on entry, tending toward chamomile tea with cranberry fruit. With a strong tannic backbone, it could drink well for awhile.',63,NULL,0,'Doctors Vineyard',196639),
(251484,217203,'other','Portuguese White','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','This blend of Arinto and Fernão Pires is soft and bland. Its light fruit and acidity feel open and ripe.',12,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal',196685),
(251493,217207,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Soft notes of straw and honeycomb grace the orange and red apple fruit tones. The mouthfeel is round and a touch flat on the midpalate, finishing with a bitter almond flavor. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Seriously Cool',196689),
(251495,217705,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A lightweight and easygoing white, this offers soft aromas and flavors of green apple, melon rind and citrus, all framed by bright acidity. The finish is short, but mouthwatering. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Bob\'s',196839),
(251512,218228,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CuY3irNpSwmSWKpi38YX7g_pb_x960.png','Berry aromas are a touch dusty and floral on the nose, with hints of earth and cedar. On the palate, this wine is bright and balanced, with fresh acidity. Rich berry, cassis and spice flavors finish agile and long. Drink through 2016.',20,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(251524,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/GcPX6-CWTyiaqm-uz-QdZA_pb_x960.png','From the eastern vineyards of the Douro, in Douro Superior, this estate wine is heavily structured while showing rich fruit and impressive tannins. The texture is strongly mineral, complex and hinting at the concentration from fruit grown in this hot, dry climate. Drink from 2016.',22,NULL,0,'Quinta dos Quatro Ventos',196677),
(251571,217203,'other','Portuguese White','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','This is a powerfully wood-aged wine, rich and smoothly textured. Full of ripe yellow fruits with a hint of lemon and full-bodied, it is still developing. A touch of minerality and a steely edge add interest and further complexity. It needs to age, so wait until 2016.',18,NULL,0,'Aguia Moura em Vinhas Velhas Reserva',196685),
(251790,217780,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/p4vZudrZTWCDnT18uGdn1w_375x500.jpg','Herbal and earthy up front, this blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Syrah, Carmenère and Malbec brings notes of green tobacco and black olive to the front along with toasty oak. The palate is tight and crisp, with choppy tannins. Flavors of toasty oak and berry fruit compote finish resiny, with juicy, zesty acidity. Drink through 2021.',85,NULL,0,'Rivalta Limited Selection',196857),
(251802,218426,'other','Riesling','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/bRmWfzAcTqeW23P-MCdGsg_pb_x960.png','Scents of lemon-cake icing meet the pretty yet not treacly tropical aromatics of white flowers on this barely off-dry wine. The sweetness is noticeable on the palate but far from overdone, with clean flavors of lemon custard, tangerine juice and a Key-lime finish.',13,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(251819,218426,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EU1VV2D-RUClV16A780QoA_pb_x960.png','This Merlot is dry, full-bodied and delicious in fruit and oak. Black cherries, currants, mocha, plums, vanilla and fragrant sandalwood all come together to provide a complex drink that\'s firm in tannins and fancy in the finish. Drink now.',28,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(251832,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/ddgOyx-nSEy9RYXt-OelCQ_375x500.jpg','Dense and structured, this is a firm wine from the Santar estate. It is powered by its tannins and partnered with ripe black plum fruits. There is a feeling of tough rocks, a dry core that need some time. Drink from 2015.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar',196794),
(251833,217625,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4B_4XW04RlOdcnZX8BsTbg_pb_x960.png','This complex, ripe wine reflects the steely character of Dão whites along with perfumed acidity and rich white fruit flavors. Lime, apples and pears are smoothed by wood aging and given a final burst of freshness. It\'s ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Reserva Branco',196794),
(251915,218512,'other','Frappato','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/u-UnBWlXQTuEcmZLCFu3iQ_pb_x960.png','Bright and savory, this opens with enticing aromas of wild berry, fragrant blue flower, rose and a whiff of exotic spice. The silky, easy-drinking palate offers succulent Marasca cherry, black raspberry, white pepper and a hint of clove alongside lithe tannins and fresh acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Il Frappato',196773),
(251922,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/20CBR_low-335x1024.png','Winemaker Bill Brosseau tapped into his family\'s vineyard to produce this light and delicate wine. Its aromas suggest white flowers, key lime and chalk, while its flavors are high-toned and tight, recalling chilled pear, lime and pomelo pith. A graphite-like minerality adds complexity.',49,NULL,0,'Brosseau Vineyard',196639),
(252003,217203,'other','Castelão','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','This is a rustic, barnyard-scented wine, with tannins and acidity but lacking fruit. Think of it as one to quaff without too much thought.',11,NULL,0,'Dona Helena Colheita',196685),
(252017,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/oM4u8RweSuWtEosCCcy04Q_pb_x960.png','Pretty as all get-out, this wine is a floral masterpiece—a study in coastal rose and forest scents with a counterpunch of white pepper that leaves one wanting more. Juicy raspberry, strawberry and tangerine flavors are seasoned in allspice and tobacco, the palate so beautifully delicate yet fully realized in savory complexity and length.',75,NULL,0,'Coastlands Vineyard',196626),
(252085,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/BbRE_m9RT0GZLUAl--CmdQ_375x500.jpg','This wine shows some of the natural tannic structure of the Douro while really bringing out plenty of fruit. It is rich, full of black fruits, ripe berries and elegant acidity. Firm and fruity at the end, it could age until 2016, but is good to drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Palestra',196794),
(252115,217335,'other','Chardonnay','	https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/x1000,sq/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h1e/hd1/8815561932830.png','Wet slate minerality leads the brisk, tightly wound nose. On the palate, the wine is a bit perfumed, at least for how tight the nose is, with elements of crisp apple, pear and a touch of nectarine.',45,NULL,0,'Dos Rubios Vineyard',196639),
(252265,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zMPComlfSn2E6BrZTOC2Bw_pb_x960.png','This wine shows a high degree of spiciness with a rose petal-like flourish—a stellar first effort from a new estate vineyard along Eastside Road. Brambly raspberry and dark cherry flavors seem brushed by a subtle waft of campfire smoke and molten chocolate, all swirling together in the glass as a lengthy, lively palate framed by acidity.',85,NULL,0,'Lewis MacGregor Estate Vineyard',196626),
(252338,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/rjX_PMSvRvGd0RvaQDt9CQ_375x500.jpg','This is a fine wine, with great structure and ripe fruit. Dark tannins, a tense mineral texture and blackberry tones are all there, giving a wine that\'s rich and full bodied. Drink from 2017.',10,NULL,0,'Aliança Reserva',196677),
(252363,217203,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','Dusty tannins dominate this opulent, full-bodied wine that isn\'t going to be shy as it develops. With its superripe black fruits and juicy acidity, it is fruity, but the power that is the most obvious element. Drink this bombshell from 2016.',30,NULL,0,'Andreza Grande Reserva',196685),
(252384,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/19PFO_low-335x1024.png','One of four monopole Central Coast bottlings from the Los Gatos winery, this bottling offers rich red cherry, vanilla, rose petal and watermelon scents on the nose. The palate is dry and structured, showing tart Montmorency cherry and hints of licorice and eucalyptus.',65,NULL,0,'Fogstone Vineyard',196639),
(252401,218426,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/BO6HgrN1TH6Zke2tEG6Tyg_pb_x960.png','Fresh, lively and brimming over with fruit flavor, from lemon to lime to peach. The appearance is light gold, the aromas are very immediate and effusive, the texture tangy and the finish light with a hint of sweetness.',13,NULL,0,'Avant',196751),
(252503,218569,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Another longtime standout for Williams Selyem, Allen Vineyard fruit imparts textural subtleties and a wealth of minerality and freshness. Citrus-driven in its cranberry and orange flavors, it shows depth and complexity, accented by lively thyme and clove notes.',82,NULL,0,'Allen Vineyard',196626),
(252504,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/490x/media/sys_master/twmmedia/hf8/hf0/11170707767326.png','Smoky clove and rose petal aromas underlie a delicately complex fruitiness in this wine, its cranberry and pomegranate flavors complemented by cardamon, dried herb and savory black tea. Light-bodied and fresh, it offers an indelible silkiness on the palate.',58,NULL,0,'Foss Vineyard',196626),
(252568,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/20ykzlp3ToqV0sgtOzH3-A_pb_x960.png','A big but mild-mannered wine, this has subtle oak and butter aromas plus ripe pear, butterscotch and white-peach flavors. A nicely thick texture carries all the complexity through the finish.',17,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(252710,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/b_Nf3y12TS2FrLrugLSppQ_pb_x960.png','Punchy citrus and minerally aromas open this fresh SB. A juicy, citric palate points in the right direction, while this tastes like tangerine and orange peel mixed with lime and green herbs. A crisp, persistent finish closes it out.',17,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva',196852),
(252721,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/QTtKv84RQvCAzR44unyOwg_pb_x960.png','Dense, earthy, herbal aromas of berry fruits and black plum feed into a racy, structured palate with high acidity. Spicy, herbal berry and plum flavors taste a bit salty, while this is plenty woody on an herbal, dry, fresh finish.',20,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(252722,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/2_MpOxMFT7iyG3FNQb8pLA_pb_x960.png','Straw yellow in color, this widely available wine offers vanilla, lemon curd, honeysuckle and a touch of browned butter on the nose. Once sipped, seared lemon and yellow apple show first, settling into a vanilla cream groove and finishing on a touch of marshmallow.',22,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(252736,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/RCwxrGIUQrCPhK-DP7gEyQ_pb_x960.png','From an organic, dry farmed vineyard, this wine is as feral as the forest—a study in wild boar, wildflowers and dried herbs. Bright acidity buoys that meaty quality in the form of tart rhubarb and strawberry tea flavors. Floral on the nose and palate, it\'s spicy too, with bold seasonings of clove and pepper.',95,NULL,0,'Precious Mountain Vineyard',196626),
(252753,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2022/08/ws-rochioli-Bottleshot/7e5b48bf7e0629bbe21b9811be7d8d35.png','Full and plush on the palate, this wine shines in spicy red and black cherry, offering both a juicy core and sculpted texture. Finishing long, it retains a freshness of acidity, fine tannin and seamless oak. A dark, earthy expression of the grape with a twist of spice.',82,NULL,0,'Rochioli Riverblock Vineyard',196626),
(252779,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/pFMHgS7sQg2uJpH8Xken_g_pb_x960.png','Mulberry, wet rock and sagebrush show on the nose of this single vineyard bottling from a site owned by the Hahn family. The palate is tangy at first, revealing dark red fruit with a smoky kick as it opens, backed by hints of juniper and dust.',67,NULL,0,'Doctor\'s Vineyard',196639),
(252977,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2022/08/2020_Williams_Selyem_Pinot_Noir_Estate_Vineyard_Russian_River_Valley_Bottleshot_1/89d5c7515172d2adab085dffdc5c671d.png','This is a soft, complex and floral wine, sourced from an estate vineyard on Westside Road. Black cherry, tangerine and oak reduction make for a bright, brooding combination of medium-bodied lushness and subtle power.',105,NULL,0,'Williams Selyem Estate Vineyard',196626),
(252989,218569,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This full-bodied, well-oaked wine offers vanilla, coconut, cinnamon and red cherry aromas that meet tart cranberry, strawberry, nutmeg and cream flavors. It\'s expansive, well balanced, spicy and delicious and will taste best after 2020.',58,NULL,0,'Weir Vineyard',196626),
(253175,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/YcebRDweR22QK01v4pqkiQ_pb_x960.png','Vines from high up in the vineyard produce this cool, fresh wine. It has bright acidity along with intense grapefruit and lemon fruits. The wine is tangy with a strong texture. Drink from 2018.',90,NULL,0,'Château Gris Les Terrasses',196775),
(253191,218228,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/OFlWCfdCScqHwM6UHkghiQ_pb_x960.png','Warm, furry aromas of olive, prune and animal hide are challenging. In the mouth, this cool-year Carmenère feels tartaric and narrow, with grating tannins. Fiery flavors of black fruits, raisin and oak are mildly salty and herbal, while the finish feels hot and tastes of minty oak and black fruits.',235,NULL,0,'Kai',196886),
(253192,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KklvJ7CfRdqc7AmoBBCGlA_pb_x960.png','This coastal-influenced Chardonnay smells of green olive, iodine and sea brine more than fruit. A citric, high-intensity palate is chalky and minerally, as intended. Flavors of dried, briny stone fruits and apple are outright salty like the ocean, while the finish on this new wine from chalk-based soils is woody and briny, with juicy acidity.',95,NULL,0,'Las Pizarras',196886),
(253279,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KKIN_yCHSXecoVaIAU0ohw_375x500.jpg','Densely brambly in red and black berry ripeness, this wine from a superb, high-elevation vineyard site is soft through the midpalate, before revealing megawatts of power and oak on the back of the tongue. Earthy, it finishes awash in vanilla-tinged oak.',32,NULL,0,'Lot 515 Monte Rosso Vineyard',196620),
(253332,217780,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/u7pEyNELT6S5RsxeqRknbA_pb_600x600.png','Saline, lime, grass, bell pepper and green bean aromas swirl around the bouquet on this fresh, coastal SB. This feels round yet crisp, with modest acidic cut and flavors or orange, passion fruit and minerals. Finishing flavors are similar, with a hint of green herb.',22,NULL,0,'Amplus',196857),
(253357,217999,'other','Fiano','https://cdn.vinissimus.com/img/unsafe/p385x/plain/local:///prfmtgrande/vi/ffrae16_anv800.png','Aromas of hazelnut nut, smoke and dried chamomile flower slowly come together. On the racy palate, a mineral vein underscores yellow apple, lime and dried sage while a bitter almond note wraps up the finish.',60,NULL,0,'Studi Fraedane',196908),
(253379,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/lJEDr20rRh6TP21v0RpjoA_pb_x960.png','A year in the barrel has given this powerful wine structured, yet polished tannins. While still young, it is powered by ripe red berry notes and driving juicy acidity. It\'s a wine for further aging, so drink from 2016.',10,NULL,0,'Quinta da Garrida',196677),
(253397,217335,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Rather reserved in aromas for a dessert wine, this allows blackberry, black pepper and mineral notes to emerge with time. The palate is lightly sweet, with ripe blackberry and blueberry-jam flavors, made interesting with a pencil-lead minerality throughout.',27,NULL,0,'Novitiate Late Harvest',196639),
(253582,217625,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Y66GQudGQRSsGp7OMrHC_w_375x500.jpg','A strongly wood-aged wine, it is packed with toast and vanilla, but has a hard time remembering the fruit. At the moment, the wine has weight, the lightest hints of ripe tropical flavors and acidity. It needs more aging to broaden out and allow the fruit to sing. Drink from 2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Condessa de Santar',196794),
(253599,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4emaI6j9RjqEHEIWjO_hJw_pb_x960.png','This soft, rounded wine has attractive ripe white-stone-fruit flavor. It also has a rich, spicy side, with light hints of wood that give it a mellow character. The wine is developing well and will be ready from 2017.',36,NULL,0,'Domaine Adélie Les Champs-Michaux',196775),
(253622,217780,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/NW470j1pTfO2gOoyq0HI9w_pb_x960.png','With tight, crisp aromas of berry fruit, toast, mineral and mint, this Cabernet Sauvignon blend is high toned—coming across racy and snappy. Jumpy, lively plum and raspberry flavors are backed by leafy, herbal notes and resiny oak. A spicy mint finish concludes this energetic yet oaky blend. Drink through 2021.',50,NULL,0,'Catalina',196857),
(253732,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/19PBR_low-1-335x1024.png','From the vineyard owned by winemaker Bill Brosseau\'s family, this bottling shows black raspberry, strawberry, wet slate and rose petal scents on the nose. The palate is loaded with earthy black plum and other dark fruits, lifted by a star anise spiciness.',65,NULL,0,'Brosseau Vineyard',196639),
(253814,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/D8qSpX9TS1K55PWGdgI4cg_pb_x960.png','Max Reserva is the easiest, most fruity of the Errazuriz Chardonnay lineup for 2014. Aromas of vanilla wafer, barrel toast, smoke and white fruits announce a smooth but simple palate. Peach, melon and toasty oak are the key flavors, while this finishes a touch salty.',20,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(253848,217148,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/D8qSpX9TS1K55PWGdgI4cg_pb_x960.png','Garden herb and forest floor aromas make a case for this wine to be considered the producer\'s “Finest Selection” (the “FS” in “OFS”). On the palate, wild strawberry, black cherry and berry are the story, while powerful spice adds intrigue to the velvety texture, roundness and full-bodied concentration.',40,NULL,0,'OFS',196642),
(254010,219700,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-IPR_MpuS7SB_RVYvodcGw_pb_x960.png','Beeswax and acacia aromas lift out of the glass while the bright palate offers ripe pear, nectarine and grilled herb. Mineral and almond notes add interest.',NULL,NULL,0,'Mozia',196776),
(254071,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/dEYtzj3zSSqQf-6nBTn-WA_pb_x960.png','Dão Sul\'s venture in the Alentejo has produced a wine that is soft, rich, all ripe berry fruits and gentle tannins. It\'s a warm, fruit-driven wine that has a rounded feel, with the acidity at the end giving some freshness. Drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Monte de Cal Reserva',196794),
(254223,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://bestbuyliquors.com/media/catalog/product/cache/d7df2e2181317fa7bc2566aa0a291dfe/t/e/testarossa-dos-rubios-vineyard-pinot-noir-2013_2.jpg','From one of the four Pinot Noir vineyards that this producer controls as monopoles, this dark-hued bottling shows blackberry, black plum, clove and star anise aromas. Tart cranberry, sour cherry and strawberry fruit marks the palate, rounded with rose petal and sage elements.',65,NULL,0,'Dos Rubios Vineyard',196639),
(254244,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Em-o-FQnTqiMFfZtZfJzBw_pb_x960.png','Forest, mint and campfire scents are complemented by brambly black cherry in this explosively complex wine. Soft and subtle, it has juicy layers of cranberry, orange and maraschino, with a roundness and firmness to the strong tannin. The finish is all about coffee, cardamom and five spice.',82,NULL,0,'Hirsch Vineyard',196626),
(254354,217310,'other','Baga','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KY_bjoP_S8KEjzBvJuxB1w_pb_x960.png','Baga, a grape unique to the Bairrada region, has a reputation for producing tough wines when young. This wine, however, shows the potential of aging the variety. Ripe and rich in character, this wine marries powerful blackberry tones with brooding, structured tannins. It could still age further, but the wine is very drinkable now.',41,NULL,0,'Aliança',196677),
(254360,219884,'other','Alicante Bouschet','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-ZGj8g1JTyGPi4f8TIUDIg_pb_x960.png','An unusual bottling of 100% Alicante Bouschet, this big, bold wine shows primary red and blackberry tones supported by soft tannins. Drink now through 2019.',15,NULL,0,'Aluado',196807),
(254490,217625,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/i83CMmpuTaWNgLwH8Mwrww_pb_x960.png','A solid, ripe and tannic wine that is full of firm fruits, ripe berries and a strongly mineral character. It has some concentration and certainly dense tannins while also showing a fresher, licorice and black currant side. Drink now, but best wait until 2015.',NULL,NULL,0,'Grilos',196794),
(254491,217625,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'All ripe fruit and cushioned tannins, this is a dense, very fruity wine. It is a powerhouse of richness and solid structure. Concentrated, with a touch of bitterness, it could age until 2016, but is drinkable with its fruitiness now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar',196794),
(254565,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/vkSBoEDWRBSn8dJ3dfUzsA_pb_x960.png','A dark and richly dense wine, this is packed with black fruit notes and concentrated tannins. Aged in French and American oak, it has a strongly spicy character, with bright acid and a solid tannic structure. Drink after 2015.',22,NULL,0,'Alabastro Reserva',196677),
(254662,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Zk0uchRVS6Czz0T5dD_f5g_pb_x960.png','This ripe wine offers swathes of red fruits and soft tannins. The structure is well embedded in the juicy red-cherry flavors that are further lifted by acidity. It\'s an attractive, smooth wine that will be ready from 2017.',48,NULL,0,'Domaine Adélie Le Champs-Martin Premier Cru',196775),
(254720,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/wcysjic6QHGH0K24GT94EQ_pb_x960.png','Broad aromas of seared lemons, white peach and nectarine are given nuance with a bit of quinine on this entry-level bottling. Stewed lemons and apple-custard flavors show on the plush and pillowy palate, cut with an acidic sizzle.',23,NULL,0,'Cuvee Los Gatos',196639),
(254722,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This blend of Jaén, Alfrocheiro, Touriga Nacional and Tinta Roriz is ripe and juicy, with black fruit tones. It does have a structure that will allow the wine to age for a few years, so drink from late 2016.',12,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal',196685),
(254723,217203,'other','Códega do Larinho',NULL,'An ancient variety now seen rarely, this Códega do Larinho has produced a wine that has a steely texture and tangy citrus flavors. It is bright with acidity, lime and grapefruit fruits and so crisp. It is ready to drink.',18,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Andreza Reserva',196685),
(254746,217780,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CS5CAKTqTDaPTVREgKt8EQ_pb_x600.png','Like any good Leyda Valley SB, this opens with oceanic aromas of citrus fruits, sea foam and minerality. In the mouth, it is juicy and stony, with washing acidity. Flavors of honeydew, lime and jalapeño finish firm, with good backbone. Drink this with salads, shellfish and ceviche.',15,NULL,0,'Reserve',196857),
(254754,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Not quite dry, this is is a warm, creamy wine. It has fresh lemon juice, pineapple, bright acidity and a dense texture that bestows an intensely fruity character. It\'s ready to drink, but will be better at the end of 2014.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta de Lourosa',196794),
(254820,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQaBSdFz-3rXfB95YNJ2L6ftq8seApUH-tchJrQR-WmSsvVDxmQvrGN5_PaXH8kdSB9_g&usqp=CAU','Jammy raspberry and plum aromas are primary and fresh on the nose. This ripe, round wine is sure to be a party-pleaser. Solid cassis, berry and spice flavors finish pure, with ripeness and proper balance.',18,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva Ribera del Tinguiririca',196852),
(254828,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2019/11/cha-biobio-2018-ed-limitada-esp.png','This opens with a blast of resiny oak, but airing calms things down, and ultimately the bouquet is round and full, with a mix of wood, vanilla and tropical fruit aromas. This is chalky, minerally and full in feel, accented by apple, pear, melon and spice flavors. Leftover oak and savory spice flavors dominate the finish.',23,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(254893,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/20CFO_low.png','The nose of this bottling delivers all of the standard aromas associated with the grape: Meyer lemon, white flowers and the lightest touch of sour cream. That creamy element extends to the palate and is rounded out with stone fruit flavors, oak smoke and sea salt.',49,NULL,0,'Fogstone Vineyard',196639),
(254908,218569,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is beautifully lilting in preciously defined aromas of rose petal and wild strawberry. From there, it\'s all subtlety and ethereal elegance. The wine is restrained, nurtured in a basket of nutmeg and graham cracker, as well as freshly packed mushroomy earth. This wine is a stunner right out of the glass, but is sure to continue its fine course through 2022–2025.',59,NULL,0,'Bucher Vineyard',196626),
(254912,218569,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Those who think they prefer anything but Chardonnay may be convinced otherwise with this wine. It is so powerfully evocative in crisply rendered Meyer lemon and tangerine notes, with aromas of fresh white flowers teasing provocatively on the nose. Seamless and seductively bright in acidity, it glides down the palate, hinting at a richness that never becomes overdone.',65,NULL,0,'Drake Estate Vineyard',196626),
(254917,218569,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5AEWrLrYRb2-haG0agXclg_pb_x960.png','This classic Chardonnay brims in lemon chiffon, stony minerality and luscious pear. The complex, soft, supple layers continue to surprise in the glass, teasing the palate with unexpected notes of nutmeg and Tahitian vanilla.',55,NULL,0,'Allen Vineyard',196626),
(254982,218228,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/PBKvarweTFmFBLK5iPSpAQ_pb_x600.png','Translucent red in color, this coastal Pinot is light and peppery on the nose, with saline and celery stalk scents along with baked plum and raspberry notes. Oak aging has left a buttery texture that\'s cut by acidity, while flavors of cherry and plum are supported by barrel notes and acid-based juiciness.',20,NULL,0,'Aconcagua Costa Single Vineyard',196886),
(254998,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This big, ripe and spicy blend is dominated by juicy Alicante Bouschet. Full black fruits flavors and a dry core of solid tannins come with the lightest hint of wood aging. Mainly, the rich fruit shows strongly. Drink from 2015.',19,NULL,0,'Companhia daz Lezirias Tinto',196685),
(255017,219884,'other','Rosé',NULL,'This blend of Shiraz and Castelão is in a soft and ripe rosé style. There is just a touch of tannin from the Shiraz to give weight. The aftertaste is lightly sweet.',8,NULL,0,'Storks Landing',196807),
(255083,218035,'other','Malbec','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/jnxG7HztRiitVQLfhgNoxg_pb_600x600.png','Broad, ripe berry aromas are dark and full on the nose. The palate is lively, with a shot of bracing acidity. Flavors of dark fruit, grilled meat, herb and salt finish briny, with a final wave of hard tannins. Drink through 2016.',25,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(255153,218569,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-teBbnwpQieX-b46kRZNig_pb_x300.png','This is an exceptional Zinfandel from a renowned site, as famous for Pinot Noir and Chardonnay as it has now become for Zin. Heady aromas of raspberry, blackberry and boysenberry tease before coming to life on the palate, accented by a delightful complement of allspice and juicy acidity. Medium bodied, it\'s incredibly easy to enjoy and rich in all the right ways.',55,NULL,0,'Bacigalupi Vineyard',196626),
(255241,219884,'other','Arinto',NULL,'Green plums and ripe apples bring out the best in Arinto\'s range of flavors. This is a soft wine, with light acidity that\'s well integrated into the rich fruitiness. Drink now.',8,NULL,0,'Paxis Branco',196807),
(255257,218512,'other','Grillo','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AnL31B8gRP6W_ID21F8pwA_pb_x960.png','Fragrant lemon blossom, citrus, beeswax and almond aromas carry over to the bright palate along with juicy lime, nectarine zest and dried herb. It finishes on a tangy saline note.',NULL,NULL,0,'Zagra',196773),
(255320,217719,'other','Chardonnay','https://grahambeck.com/images/uploads/products/Blanc-de-Blancs.png','This bright and well-balanced sparkler leads with attractive aromas of fresh lemon and orange slices, lightly toasted brioche and subtle fynbos herbs. The palate is creamy and smooth, with crisp acidity and medium carbonation that lifts and refreshes the finish. Delicious now, or hold through 2017 for a more mature character and additional depth.',26,NULL,0,'Premier Cuvée Blanc de Blancs Brut Méthode Cap Classique',196845),
(255347,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/aMGk93WAQFqrp4pdeoPhbg_pb_x960.png','Popcorn, mustard, pickle brine and a heavy blast of oak create a barrel-driven bouquet. This is acidic and juicy on the palate, but also resiny. Flavors of briny citrus, nectarine and raw oak finish long and woody, with a cidery aftertaste.',50,NULL,0,'Amelia Limited Release',196852),
(255412,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/jMrFjcTfR1-Lpxr4TYv4UQ_pb_x960.png','The winery sources this fruit from a vineyard near Hollister. It delivers aromas of bramble berry, espresso-dipped cherry and allspice. Cherry and chocolate power the palate, which also benefits from lifting mint, sagebrush and eucalyptus, finishing with chopped herbs.',58,NULL,0,'Vista Verde Vineyard',196626),
(255425,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/rQfTlWMMRWCJzq17iGvmLg_pb_x960.png','From vineyards close to Meursault, this brisk white wine is nicely touched by acidity and lemon flavors. A light layer of wood gives it a broader character. The crispness of this wine brings a bright, lively aftertaste.',23,NULL,0,'Sécret de la Famille',196775),
(255461,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HbBMtS3HSoeW1vQ9AHCTmA_pb_600x600.png','This wine from the personal vineyard of the winery\'s co-founder has assertive woodsmoke, toasted oak and forest aromas, its bright black cherry and pomegranate flavors accented by tamarind and black pepper. While strongly oaky and firmly tannic in texture, it has a sleek and nervy aspect that\'s very appealing.',82,NULL,0,'Burt Williams\' Morning Dew Ranch',196626),
(255462,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/490x/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h43/hc4/10675589677086.png','This is one of the producer\'s more full-bodied wines, a blend from several sites along Eastside Road, including Calegari, Foss and a new source—Lewis MacGregor Estate. Rich, round and plush, it\'s as strong as black coffee in its marriage of earthy allspice, baked cherry, blueberry and smoke. Moderate acidity allows for an underlying minerality.',55,NULL,0,'Eastside Road Neighbors',196626),
(255498,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/20PLM_low-335x1024.png','Rustic, hearty aromas of tar, cola, herbs and burnt rhubarb make for an intriguing nose on this entry-level bottling from Testarossa. The sips feature cola and cherry flavors, with a very quick finish.',27,NULL,0,'Cuvee Los Gatos',196639),
(255540,217625,'other','Portuguese Sparkling',NULL,'A delicious apple flavored wine, fruity-crisp and packed with lively acidity. It has a fine, light mousse, smoothly textured and with lively, perfumed final acidity. Drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Condessa de Santar Extra Brut',196794),
(255541,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Very fresh, this is also a ripe, smooth-textured wine. Lemon flavors go with melon, pear and a touch of apricot. The wine has some weight, stylish and rounded. It should age another few months.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Branco',196794),
(255544,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a dark and dense wine that has solid perfumed fruits. The tannins, still dry, are partnered with blackberry fruits, spice and just a touch of wood. The wine needs to age, so wait until 2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal Colheita',196685),
(255545,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A smooth and rich wine that is already delicious. It has ripe berry fruits, soft tannins and a full, juicy feel. A streak of acidity cuts through this generous wine. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Catapereiro Tinto',196685),
(255561,217839,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/U3380E2QRiaGTFy0BAm4mw_pb_600x600.png','Charred and heavily oaked from the opening gun to the closing tape. Amid all the barrel influence and toast, you\'ll find black plum and wild berry aromas and flavors. On the finish, oak reasserts its control over this wine.',18,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva Ribera del Maule',196852),
(255574,217780,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/xmyIhm9hR--az7PgDKG4BA_pb_600x600.png','Leesy, toasty opening aromas accent melon, flower blossom and stone fruit scents. This is woody but healthy in feel, with acidic lift. Flavors of resiny, briny melon and peach finish with a wave of barrel-driven vanilla, but overall this shows coastal freshness and proper balance.',24,NULL,0,'Amplus',196857),
(255604,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/b_Nf3y12TS2FrLrugLSppQ_pb_x600.png','Powdery, wayward aromas pick up more raciness and green character with time in the glass. A linear palate flat-lines at lime and green apple in terms of flavors, while the finish brings a slightly vegetal tone.',17,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva Ribera del Rapel',196852),
(255608,220442,'other','Nero d\'Avola',NULL,'Credited as the first wine made solely with noble native grape Nero d\'Avola, this iconic bottling opens with aromas that recall ripe berry, lightly toasted oak, leather and cooking spice. The firm, structured palate delivers ripe blackberry, juicy wild cherry, licorice, tobacco and savory herb alongside velvety tannins. It\'s already tempting but will continue to develop complexity. Drink 2015–2024.',70,NULL,0,'Duca Enrico',196776),
(255671,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2022/08/we-ferrington_Bottleshot_/73ffcc8f4c266eb2fce4c679c9721885.png','Notable oaky aromas like cedar and clove join bold fruit and spice flavors in this medium-bodied, stylized wine from a classic producer. This bottling seems less overtly ripe and more spicy in style than recent vintages. On the palate, it oozes clove, tamarind, cardamom and black-cherry flavors. Best after 2019.',65,NULL,0,'Ferrington Vineyard',196626),
(255681,218426,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/dCh-kVTyTWuZvUeWezAP3w_pb_x960.png','Sticky tar, dense blackberry, leather, soy and lilacs combine for a thick nose on this well-priced, widely available bottling. Beef char, dense purple flowers, blackberry jam and tar consume the palate, which is chewy with a strong tannic structure.',17,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(255802,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/21PLR_low-335x1024.png','Buttery vanilla and baked cherry aromas make for a pretty and plump entry to this bottling from a vineyard in the heart of the appellation. Approachable plum and cherry flavors meet baking spice on the palate, the texture soft and acidity ample.',65,NULL,0,'La Rinconada Vineyard',196639),
(255936,217203,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Still with its firm tannins in place and with layers of wood aging flavors, this is obviously a young wine. It has a background of ripe berry fruits and acidity that will develop over the next two years. It is potentially rich and full. Drink from 2017.',15,NULL,0,'Pegos Claros Colheita',196685),
(255950,217839,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Hailing from a cool vintage, this Chardonnay smells oaky and resiny to an extreme. In the mouth, it\'s lifted by a beam of acid but still comes across woody. Flavors of sawdust, barrel resin, stone fruits and citrus finish with a good feel.',35,NULL,0,'Amelia Limited Release Las Petras Vineyard',196852),
(255978,219884,'other','Rosé',NULL,'This wine is so soft, gently fruity and easy to drink, but without much character or freshness. It\'s a gentle ramble that takes no effort.',7,NULL,0,'Portada',196807),
(256077,218035,'other','Syrah','https://www.vinello.de/media/image/4a/a6/g0/montes-cherub-syrah.png','Hot pink in color, the palate is open and mild, but unstructured. Simple raspberry and plum flavors finish alert but with a basic finish of red and citrus fruits.',16,NULL,0,'Cherub Rosé of',196713),
(256088,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Saitone is a supremely historic vineyard, planted originally in 1895 in the thick of the Russian River Valley\'s Olivet Bench, a coveted spot these days for Pinot Noir. The wine offers supple, soft tannins around a juicy intensity of grenadine and berry crumble. The structured backbone of minerality is remarkable.',45,NULL,0,'Saitone Vineyard Olivet Bench',196642),
(256233,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is powerful and rich, allowing just a note of freshness to creep into the firm structure. Dark tannins, black fruits and smoky wood flavors combine harmoniously, lending a sense of great power and long-term aging potential. Drink from 2019.',115,NULL,0,'Le Corton',197241),
(256252,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This wine shows the characteristic granitic texture of the region. Berry fruits smother the firm tannins to give a rich, juicy wine that\'s bold, ripe, and ready to drink.',8,NULL,0,'Aliança',196677),
(256253,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This blend of Syrah, Petit Verdot, Aragonez and Alicante Bouschet shows power, with dense tannins shouldered by ripe black fruit flavors and a solid structure. From the Estremoz region of the Alentejo, it\'s a powerhouse of flavors and juicy acidity. Drink after 2016.',23,NULL,0,'Album Reserva',196685),
(256284,220442,'other','Grillo',NULL,'Extremely subtle aromas of toasted oak, yellow flower and a whiff of dill waft out of the glass. The firm palate offers yellow apple and nectarine peels and a hint of oak.',NULL,NULL,0,'Kados',196776),
(256359,219700,'other','Grillo','https://italianwineselection.com/images/detailed/14/MOZIA_GRILLO_2021-Sorrento.png','Pear and honeydew melon aromas lift out of the glass. On the fresh, tangy palate, a saline vein of minerality underscores white peach, yellow apple and juicy citrus flavors.',22,NULL,0,'Mozia Fondazione Whitaker',196776),
(256373,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'The wine has a fat fruity texture along with acidity and plenty of tannins. It is austere in character, very dry and dense and with a serious intent. There is a juicy aftertaste that is more attractive and has promise for the future.',18,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Andreza Reserva',196685),
(256433,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is its usual opulent, generous self, although in 2011 the fruit dominates. Ripe strawberry fruits are packed around sweet tannins and balanced with acidity. The wine is rich but is also powered with a firm structure. At the end, the wood aging shows. Drink from 2018.',85,NULL,0,'Caillerets Ancienne Cuvée Carnot Premier Cru',197241),
(256438,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'At this stage, this wine is closed, tight and mineral in character. As befits a great Perrières, it will be a serious, structured wine, textured and full of nervy, steely feeling, softening later into mature spice and toast. Drink from 2016.',95,NULL,0,'Perrières Premier Cru',197241),
(256480,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Mr6GWnJ1SUu5gzgGjmvSMw_pb_x960.png','This wine is ripe, juicy and packed with fresh red fruits. It has the softest tannins, the whole point being that this wine can be drunk young. The aftertaste brings out acidity. Drink from 2017.',23,NULL,0,'Sécret de la Famille',196775),
(256598,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A classic Douro blend of Touriga Nacional, Touriga Franca and Tinta Roriz makes a harmonious wine that has ripe berry fruits and a soft structure. It is a stylish wine with a fresh fruity aftertaste. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Colleja',196685),
(256613,220884,'other','Champagne Blend',NULL,'This is an easy and clean sparkling wine, with attractive aromas of red apple, orange and dried hay. Bright, brisk carbonation results in a lively and refreshing palate. A citrus-rind flavor lingers on the softly toasty finish. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Méthode Cap Classique Pinot Noir-Chardonnay',196839),
(256619,217780,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CS5CAKTqTDaPTVREgKt8EQ_pb_x960.png','Simple but friendly aromas of green fruits and spring vegetables set up a lemony feeling palate, with flavors of lime, green apple and herbs. This shows pyrazines on a juicy finish, but not so much that the wine comes across green, vegetal or bitter.',10,NULL,0,'Select Terroir',196857),
(256635,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A familiar brand on Portuguese wine shelves, this is a ripe wine, soft and smooth. Light tannins are finely integrated with the red berry fruits and juicy acidity. It\'s an easy wine that has good structure. Drink now.',8,NULL,0,'Cabriz Colheita Seleccionada',196794),
(256680,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This iconic wine is rich and perfumed. It\'s powerful and concentrated, with layers of wood contrasted by explosive, ripe fruits. Ripe red-fruit flavors are brightened by ample acidity, resulting in a sumptuous wine that also has enough tannins to age. Drink from 2018.',100,NULL,0,'Vigne de l\'Enfant Jésus Grèves Premier Cru',197241),
(256718,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/eF-rJX83QqiL3kYd0F7Ljw_pb_x600.png','Prune, tobacco and wild berry aromas are jumbled together. This is big, grabby and a touch clumsy, with heavily oaked flavors of hickory and burnt corn running alongside mint and berry. A resiny, oaky finish tastes smothering.',17,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva',196852),
(256847,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/1FY3Y6_3S1GAvqIxms9X9w_pb_x600.png','Scratchy, spicy aromas and a touch of juniper accent red-berry scents on this everyday Cabernet. The mouthfeel is dry, fresh and shows tangy acidity, while racy, edgy flavors of plum, spice and green herbs finish zesty.',10,NULL,0,'Select Terroir',196857),
(256849,217780,'other','Merlot','https://www.santaema.cl/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Detalle_G_R_Mer.png','Berry and currant aromas are jumpy and fruity in nature, while in the mouth, creamy oak creates a sticky feel. Candied, barrel-driven flavors of vanilla and clove outlast the wine\'s fruit content on the finish.',15,NULL,0,'Reserve',196857),
(256897,220442,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This offers subdued aromas suggesting orchard fruit and pressed yellow flower. The straightforward, rather lean palate offers citrus, saline and a hint of green pear alongside fresh acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Colomba Palatino',196776),
(256901,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/07/cdd-cs-1.png','Aromas of herbal red fruits, tobacco and vanilla are basic and modest. This has a wiry, acidic mouthfeel and flavors of mixed herbs, tomato, pie cherry, red plum and olive. A fresh, racy finish is tangy and tomatoey.',11,NULL,0,'Reserva Casillero del Diablo',196852),
(256928,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From the village of Blagny, considered part of Meursault, this full, rounded wine has a generous character, full of ripe fruit. It is given a crisper side by good acidity, and shows both freshness and weight at the end.',70,NULL,0,'Château de Blagny Premier Cru',197254),
(256930,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'In this generous and opulent wine, weight and richness accompany acidity and power. Ripe yellow and white fruits are given a touch of spice and new wood. It\'s gorgeous, but will be better after aging. Drink from 2018.',380,NULL,0,'Les Demoiselles',197254),
(256935,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/20CDI_low-1-335x1024.png','There\'s a touch of Riesling-like petrol to the nose of this best-barrels Chardonnay from Testarossa, as well as dried citrus, fresh roasted cashews and Chinese almond cookie. The palate is very soft, with ripe fruit such as baked oranges. A nicely buttered touch bolsters the refreshing, mouthwatering acidity.',61,NULL,0,'Diana\'s',196639),
(256943,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Rich and sweetly fruity, this wine wields intense power. Red fruits are initially opulent and pleasurable, but then the wine begins to show solid structure and concentration. The final texture, with its tannins and fruit in harmony, is impressive. Drink from 2018.',280,NULL,0,'Cuvée Héritiers Latour',197254),
(256944,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Solid and tannic, it perhaps lacks huge weight but shows elegant structure and rounded tannins. The wine is already deliciously fruity, and will charm as it ages. Black fruits are right up front, the tannins a fine supporting act. Drink from 2017.',740,NULL,0,'Les Quatre Journaux',197254),
(256945,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The name comes from the fact that this vineyard was once a truffle bed, high up the slope of Puligny-Montrachet. The wine shows wood, attractive fruitiness and layers of spice and almonds. It is rounded, the soft texture balanced by acidity. Drink from 2016.',85,NULL,0,'Les Truffières Premier Cru',197254),
(256955,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'While showing some smoky wood, this wine is more about pure fruitiness with yellow fruit flavors given a crisper shot with acidity. Full-bodied and rich, the wine keeps a refreshing brightness. The aftertaste is crisp and fruity.',95,NULL,0,'Genevrières Premier Cru',197241),
(257191,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/21CLR_low.png','The single-vineyard experts at Testarossa hit a homerun with this wine from a famed property. Aromas of 7-Up, recent rains and minerality kick off a refreshing experience, which is powered by a strong flavor combination of very ripe fruit (à la traditional California Chardonnay), barrel-related vanilla and brisk, lingering acidity (à la Old World).',45,NULL,0,'La Rinconada Vineyard',196639),
(257196,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Perfume partners with great acidity in this wine. The two work in harmony, resulting in a wine that has a soft texture, rich, jammy berry fruits and a backbone of tannins that will allow for aging. Drink from 2017.',60,NULL,0,'Clos de la Mousse Premier Cru',197241),
(257197,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A wine with great sweet fruits along with smoky, firm tannins. It is certainly structured, and the black jelly fruits are already delicious. Weight partners with acidity, creating a combination of freshness and richness at the end. Drink from 2018.',100,NULL,0,'Les Cailles Premier Cru',197241),
(257379,217265,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'While this wine is dry and crisp with acidity, it straddles the border of ripeness. On the plus side are vibrant lemon, lime and honey flavors. On the downside is a green, feline streak.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 393',196620),
(257415,219700,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4VnMQLX2Q1GzlRKOS5zigg_pb_x600.png','This is a blend of Nero d\'Avola and Merlot in almost equal measures. The first varietal offers aromas of red fruit, wild fennel and pistachio. The second grape lends softness and bright cherry flavor. There\'s a touch of tar and graphite on the close.',29,NULL,0,'Camastra',196776),
(257431,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Easy and gentle in structure, this has lots of Napa Valley polish and flair. It shows delicious notes of blackberry, green olive, sweet oak and spice, wrapped into firm, refined tannins and brightened by crisp acidity.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 338',196620),
(257437,217839,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/JxGcBXUPQiuyDIfYoKKJXg_pb_x960.png','Green aromas of grass and mint lead the way on this unspecified blend of red grapes. The palate is full and solid in feel, while sweet, almost candied flavors of blackberry finish creamy but with a sweetness that seems artificial.',11,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserva Winemaker\'s Blend',196852),
(257463,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Fruity and aromatic, this blend of Fernão Pires, Arinto and Sauvignon Blanc is fresh with attractive acidity and also riper tropical fruit and pear flavors. It has a mineral texture that gives the a fine structure. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Herdade de Catapereiro',196685),
(257500,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjav_nv_chard_update_outshinery.png?itok=p9SJrUzT','This unoaked Chardonnay is powered by tangy lemon and pineapple flavors. It\'s medium-bodied and has nice concentration without seeming overly ripe. Butter and vanilla touches weave through its lively fresh fruit notes.',17,NULL,0,'Avant',196751),
(257525,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/YsvMCqEcSTeS2y3FhkzuYA_pb_x600.png','Barnyard aromas with coffee grinds and lemony blackberry are less than inviting. This feels raw, scratchy and abrasive; flavors of herbal cherry and plum turn green and weedy on the finish.',10,NULL,0,'Select Terroir',196857),
(257529,218035,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/N6glXhwkREec6HM9wdvBhg_pb_x960.png','Blue-fruit aromas and flavors are indistinct on the nose. Massive tannins, lemony oak, plastic and graphite notes drive the palate. The finish is a forced marriage of licorice, oak, and vanilla.',13,NULL,0,'Classic Series',196713),
(257539,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A blend of wines from different Premier Cru vineyards, this is firm, as befits a Pommard, but has such great ripe fruit that it feels almost opulent. Lovely rich raspberry fruits are touched wit red currants and supported by solid tannins  at the end. Drink from 2017.',80,NULL,0,'Premier Cru',197241),
(257545,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/E4-KnE1USAG8uy4DPSC7VA_pb_x960.png','A nose of baked apple and saline minerality introduce this wine from this single-vineyard superstar winery. The palate picks up with zing, offering apple candy, lemon lime soda and a bit of bitter tension as well. The wine evolves steadily while on the tongue and is never boring.',45,NULL,0,'Bien Nacido Vineyard',196639),
(257546,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21CRO_low-335x1024.png','Testarossa\'s single-vineyard expertise shines on this wine from Rosella\'s, which is fresh and alive on the nose with ripe nectarine and grapefruit peel. The acidity carries prominently on the palate, but the ruby-red grapefruit elements are not sharp, possessing both sweet and savory sides and finishing with some bitterness. Serve with honey-glazed seared scallops.',45,NULL,0,'Rosella\'s Vineyard',196639),
(257558,219700,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/o4u-qSowQQmoQY-T8cp21Q_pb_x600.png','Made from a blend of Nero d\'Avola, Cabernet Sauvignon and Cabernet Franc, the 35th anniversary edition of this iconic wine opens with aromas of earth, leather, black currant and bell pepper. Black cherry, chocolate, cocoa and black pepper all weave together seamlessly on the elegant palate, alongside silky tannins.',70,NULL,0,'Rosso del Conte',196776),
(257625,217780,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/bnsyktZkRIyPgSIWwAW0rA_pb_x600.png','This opens with a blast of bell pepper and leafy berry aromas. The palate is juicy but scratchy, while flavors of plum, raspberry and herbs finish tart, with no evolution.',10,NULL,0,'Select Terroir',196857),
(257687,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is a soft ripe wine that has yellow fruits alongside crisper red apples and touches of grapefruit. That makes for a balanced light wine that has a fine texture and a fresh aftertaste. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Monta da Baía Branco',196685),
(257746,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2023/02/2021_Williams_Selyem_Pinot_Noir_Westside_Road_Neighbors_Russian_River_Valley_Bottleshot/e841b686e803c8bd7435c5aae79e6a71.png','Seductively smooth and intriguingly aromatic, this blend of several knock-out vineyards along Westside Road—Allen, Bacigalupi, Bucher, Rochioli Riverblock and Williams Selyem Estate—is instantly delicious, sharing a concentration of cherry, strawberry and citrus that perfectly captures the essence of the fruit, accented by a tease of black tea. An earthy minerality wraps around dry, polished tannins, with a streak of just-right acidity, giving it a realm of juiciness and flavorful sophistication. Enjoy through 2023.',69,NULL,0,'Westside Road Neighbors',196626),
(257751,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4ifR8XWsRP-JVqWQkBPoiA_pb_x960.png','Silky, with pronounced tannins that should mellow in time, this is an earthy, stemmy and perfumed wine. Succulent and balanced, it\'s brightly exuberant in black cherry yet brooding and complex throughout, changing slightly from savory to floral and back again. It\'s an incredible wine out of the gate; cellar with confidence, through 2021.',75,NULL,0,'Olivet Lane Vineyard',196626),
(257764,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This powerful, spicy wine offers structure and a thrust of wood. Firm and dark, as befits a Vosne-Romanée, it is densely powerful, full of black fruits that are already shining above the structure. Drink from 2017.',145,NULL,0,'Les Petits Monts Premier Cru',197254),
(257774,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The light, stony soil of Les Lavières produces structured, tight and firm wines, unlike many of the softer wines from Savigny. With new wood and licorice flavors, it is darkly textured and firm. The red fruits are still developing, showing the rich potential of the wine. Drink from 2017.',60,NULL,0,'Les Lavières Premier Cru',197241),
(257778,217999,'other','Fiano','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/tdqCZIwXQCKZtNyOkyM4LA_pb_x600.png','This savory, fresh white opens with aromas of white spring flowers and white tree fruits. The creamy palate delivers a great depth of flavors, including white peach, Bartlett pear and nectarine layered with notes of Mediterranean herbs and energizing mineral. This will develop even more complexity over the next few years.',31,NULL,0,'Pietracalda',196908),
(257781,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Corton Grancey is the site of Louis Latour\'s winery and has a long tradition in the family\'s hands. This 2011 is powerful and solid while offering very ripe and jammy fruits. Attractive acidity cuts through the richness and contrasts with the finely modulated structure. It has good aging potential, drink from 2018.',140,NULL,0,'Château Corton Grancey',197254),
(257788,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A blend of Viosinho and Verdelho, this a soft and ripe wine that has attractive pear, melon and gentle acidity. A light perfume from the Verdelho adds to the attractiveness of this fruity wine. It is ready to drink.',13,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas',196685),
(257977,218569,'other','Zinfandel','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2023/02/2021_Williams_Selyem_Zinfandel_Papera_Vineyard_Russian_River_Valley_Bottleshot/fb1a860f11ac9784f3c23d2d35225400.png','Continuing to preserve this historic vineyard, a rare planting of the variety within the appellation, this is an elegant yet explosive bottling. Blackberry and stone fruit tones are framed by soft, gentle tannins, sprinkled liberally with cardamom. A floral aroma permeates gently refreshing acidity and a finish of dark chocolate.',55,NULL,0,'Papera Vineyard',196626),
(257989,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://www.uncorked.com/dw/image/v2/BCCB_PRD/on/demandware.static/-/Sites-masterCatalog_terlato/default/Terlato_com_Product_Images/Feudi_di_San_Gregorio/Terlato-Feudi-Piano-Bottle-Shot-3000x3000.png?sh=549&sm=fit','Aged in both barriques and large casks, this hearty Taurasi opens with aromas of toasted oak and ripe black fruit. The palate slowly opens up to reveal dense black cherry layered with chocolate, toast and Mediterranean spices, alongside drying tannins. Give this time to open up and fully develop. Drink after 2019.',68,NULL,0,'Piano di Montevergine Riserva',196908),
(258083,219700,'other','White Blend','https://www.saporidoc.it/3138-large_default/leone-igp-tasca-d-almerita.jpg','This white blend is the quintessential seafood wine. It offers citrus, stone fruit, crushed mineral and pretty flower nuances.',20,NULL,0,'Leone d\'Almerita',196776),
(258086,218512,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This Syrah offers plush cherry and blackberry notes, with cured meat, tobacco and black pepper touches. It feels smooth, rich and soft.',15,NULL,0,'Case Ibidini',196773),
(258131,218569,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is a Pinot Noir of considerable force. Your first impression is of irrepressible power, with masses of fruit punching through an overlay of tannin and oak. Then the flavors fantail out, suggesting cherries, cola, currants and spices that are rich and complex through the long finish. For all its richness, the wine retains an agreeable delicacy of texture. Comprised of lots selected by winemaker Bob Cabral for this anniversary bottling, it\'s right up there with Williams Selyem\'s best 2010 Pinots, and just as ageable. Drink now–2022. The wine is only available as part of a two-pack from the winery for $250; the other bottle is the 2010 Morning Dew Ranch Pinot Noir, from Anderson Valley.',125,NULL,0,'30th Anniversary Cuvée Estate Vineyard',196626),
(258133,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/21CRI_low-335x1024.png','A gorgeous Chardonnay, flamboyant in tropical fruit, honey, cream and buttered toast, but so balanced in acids and minerals, so clean and pure, that it ventures into truly classic territory. The vineyard long has been a special one for Talley. Now, Testarossa gets to dip in, with fantastic results. One of the best Chardonnays Testarossa has ever produced.',39,NULL,0,'Rincon Vineyard',196639),
(258170,221599,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'One of the finest selections from South Africa today, Sadie\'s 2011 Columella is structured, complex and masterfully balanced, ready for a beautiful, long life ahead. The bouquet leads with lovely scents of rooibos tea, minty fynbos and African violets that frame the ripe boysenberry, blackberry and plum fruit spine. Layers of lush black fruit and earthy spice dance on the velvety palate, with peppery tannins that hang on to the lingering finish alongside hints of cocoa powder, licorice root and star anise. Drink now–2024.',130,NULL,0,'Columella',197368),
(258185,217203,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This wine shows the tropical fruit side of Sauvignon Blanc with pineapple and mango flavors. The acidity is there, floral and ripe. The wine is ready to drink now.',23,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Tyto Alba Vinhas Protegidas',196685),
(258198,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A fruity, young and crisp wine that is all about raspberry and red currant fruits. It is fresh with just a hint of caramel and with bright acidity at the end.',12,NULL,0,'Monta da Baía',196685),
(258234,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Very structured and dense, this powerful wine succeeds with its black fruits, touches of wood and integrated tannins. The wine is both ripe and fruity, suggesting serious aging. Drink from 2017.',110,NULL,0,'Les Cazetiers Premier Cru',197254),
(258284,221639,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'For most people this oak-aged SB is a love-it-or-leave-it type of wine, but in this case it falls somewhere in the middle. A largely neutral bouquet comes with resiny aromas of melon. This is round, smooth and soft in the mouth, with toasty, resiny apple, melon and bitter flavors. It\'s showing oxidation and age on the finish, meaning it\'s got one foot in the grave.',34,NULL,0,'Alfa Centauri',196852),
(258427,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'With some earthy, rustic flavors the wine seems to have missed out on some of its fruit. It is more about structure and firm tannins with only hints of juicy fruit behind.',12,NULL,0,'Monta da Baía',196685),
(258466,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Ripe and structured, it has the weight and broad feel of a Chassagne-Montrachet. Firmly textured and concentrated, it also shows soft fruitiness. The power will keep it aging well, so drink from 2017.',75,NULL,0,'Morgeot Premier Cru',197254),
(258471,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The wine shows the rich wood flavors with the same intensity as the red fruits. It is firm and somewhat extracted with licorice and dark chocolate coming through the cherry fruits. At the end, the solid wood is dominant, meaning the wine needs time. Drink from 2017.',60,NULL,0,'Les Duresses Premier Cru',197241),
(258544,219700,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CEwLO3tfRK6hZMgzIw1vvw_pb_x960.png','Lamùri shows a food friendly side of Nero d\'Avola that would pair with veal, pork or roasted turkey. The bouquet is redolent of cherry cola, forest fruit, ginger and toasted nut. Subtle notes of smoke and spice appear on the finish.',20,NULL,0,'Lamùri',196776),
(258569,221639,'other','Malbec',NULL,'Ripe aromas of blackberry, raisin and cassis blend nicely with graphite and vanilla notes. There\'s a mild, brooding power to this wine but mostly it\'s lush and generous, with warm blackberry, prune and licorice flavors. A smooth finish hums along with no tannic bite or hardness. Drink through 2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'Alfa Crux',196852),
(258571,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5pDrW1R_Sf64dAaM0cKdBg_pb_x960.png','Awesomely rich in black cherries, plums, licorice, mocha, cola and sweet oak flavors. Made from selected barrels of the winery\'s various vineyards around the state, its richness is balanced by brisk acidity and a soft scour of tannins. Drink over the next six years.',79,NULL,0,'Niclaire',196639),
(258664,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A strange orange-pink color for a wine that is somewhere between fruity and sweet and acid and bitter. This one hasn\'t found a balance.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Herdade de Catapereiro',196685),
(258686,218569,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The fruit is sourced from multiple vineyards across the appellation, including Eastside Estate, a vineyard formerly known as 3 Starrs recently purchased by the producer. Aromas of exotic plumeria provide an inviting entry, followed by a subtle, yet lightly rich expression of yellow apple and ample minerality. Everything combines for a balanced wine that\'s not overly heavy or overripe.',39,NULL,0,'Unoaked',196626),
(258698,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://www.feudi.it/public/gallery/items/22/bottle-serpico.png','Underbrush, leather, dense black plum, black cherry, clove and black pepper all meld seamlessly together in the glass. This is still young, with aggressive tannins and nervous acidity that need time to tame, but going forward, it should develop layers of complexity. This will be even better after 2019.',85,NULL,0,'Serpico',196908),
(258699,217999,'other','Greco','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/V4xRb7dGRRGJ-jRUuBZBqg_pb_x960.png','Here\'s a poised and structured wine that offers fragrances of jasmine, acacia, Spanish broom and flint. Creamy peach, citrus and honeydew carry the palate, along with energizing mineral notes. It\'s fresh and well-balanced, with crisp acidity.',31,NULL,0,'Cutizzi',196908),
(258768,218569,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4FZn1Lj-SWSbrNPosa0zlg_pb_x960.png','This beautiful wine could be from Chablis. It\'s so dry and flinty, with complex layers of lemons, limes, toast and honey, along with mouthwateringly brisk acidity. As delicious as the wine is now, you might want to cellar it for a few years.',52,NULL,0,'Hawk Hill Vineyard',196626),
(258788,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/c1cvqaDoQk2-biKdr8yNJg_pb_x960.png','This is waxy smelling, with a coastal vegetal note that conveys cool-climate grapes. The palate is short and clipped in feel, with a waxy, mealy note to the wine\'s core melon and peach flavors. It\'s chunky on the finish and is a touch mealy in taste.',17,NULL,0,'Gran Reserva Serie Riberas Ribera del Rapel',196852),
(258802,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a smooth, impressively rich wine powered by silky tannins and ripe black fruits. The palate is intensely concentrated with a big, bold structure and a solid feel. It does need some aging, so drink from 2016.',18,NULL,0,'Aguia Moura em Vinhas Velhas Reserva',196685),
(258806,219884,'other','Portuguese Red','https://res.cloudinary.com/evino/image/upload/t_bottle_large,f_auto/v1/products/1649400-standing-front.jpg','A blend of northern and southern Portuguese grapes, this is a seriously firm wine that\'s structured and dense. Spiced black plums are layered with big, drying tannins and acidity, which promise long aging for this impressive wine. Drink from 2017.',20,NULL,0,'Francos Reserva',196807),
(258815,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/21PRO_low-335x1024.png','This Pinot\'s immediate lusciousness belies its complexity. Your first impression is of ripe raspberries and cherries that taste like they were baked into a pie. Then layers of minerals, mushrooms, cola and earthier fruits like persimmons and rhubarbs appear, all made brisk by amazing acidity and finishing bone dry. Lovely now and over the next six years, after an hour or two in the decanter.',59,NULL,0,'Rosella\'s Vineyard',196639),
(258881,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This wine is impressive in its full-bodied approach to the variety, allowing it ample expression of garrigue and gamy bacon scents. Layered acidity keeps it from feeling overly dense and ripe, ending on a smoky oak note.',19,NULL,0,'Lot 508',196620),
(258943,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjje_nv_camelot_chard_outshinery.png?itok=TGgRLxk9','Lemon butter, apple pie crust and hazelnut are first to the aroma party on this carefully crafted Jackson family offering from a vineyard about 400 feet up in limestone-dotted soils. On the palate, strong but integrated acidity carries the myriad citrus, apple and spice flavors to completion.',30,NULL,0,'Jackson Estate Camelot Highlands',196751),
(258944,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'While this wine demonstrates the telltale cool element of the appellation, it also offers ripe fruit, pear and peach flavors lightly layered with wood. The wine is crisp at the end, with a mineral aftertaste. Drink from 2016.',45,NULL,0,'Caradeux Premier Cru',197254),
(258945,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Fruity and ripe, it also presents a fresh feel that cuts through the jammy red fruits and gives an edge to the weight and velvet texture. It\'s almost ready to drink but will be better from 2015.',75,NULL,0,'Vignes Franches Premier Cru',197254),
(258952,219700,'other','Grillo','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0273/7505/products/Tascad_AlmeritaGrilloCavalloDelleFate.png?v=1643340752','Here\'s a crisp, delicious white that opens with aromas of tropical fruit, pear and stone fruit. The savory palate offers juicy white peach, pineapple and nectarine flavors that are accented by intense mineral notes and supported by a backbone of zesty acidity.',20,NULL,0,'Cavallo delle Fate',196776),
(258954,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This was the first vineyard bought by the Bouchard family, purchased in 1791. More than 220 years later, this 2011 has a delicate touch of wood nestled in the heart of creamy fruit flavors. Crisp lemon and tight acidity give a bright, fresh aftertaste. Drink from 2016.',60,NULL,0,'Clos Saint-Landry Premier Cru',197241),
(259020,218512,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/UAYxgm6yRoavmGLp8gKDFQ_pb_600x600.png','Easy, fresh and true to the variety, this expression offers blue flower and forest berry notes, backed by almond and pistachio accents. The finish is crisp, tight and lean.',15,NULL,0,'Case Ibidini',196773),
(259027,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Made in a ripe, appealing style, this has rich flavors of pineapple jam, tropical fruit, vanilla and buttered toast, brightened by crisp acidity.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 350',196620),
(259054,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/mqNH9WALRhi_Fidoy69NdQ_pb_x960.png','What a delicious Pinot Noir. The cool, long vintage has given it wonderful lightness and acidity, yet also an intensity of fruit that makes it irresistible. Marked by flavors of raspberries, cherries, cola and red currants, it\'s a wine to savor now, with Pinot-friendly foods such as lamb and steak.',59,NULL,0,'Garys\' Vineyard',196639),
(259077,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/21PRI_low-335x1024.png','From an appellation that thrived in this vintage comes a wine with aromas of cinnamon, nutmeg and licorice shavings atop fresh hibiscus and pomegranate flavors. There\'s bountiful energy on the palate, with flavors of dried-cherry and a densely packed array of chopped dill, roasted fennel and dried mint.',64,NULL,0,'Rincon Vineyard',196639),
(259181,217999,'other','Falanghina','https://static.xtrawine.com/Global/Images/XW/products/wines/35807_FeudiSanGregorioSannioFalanghinaSerrocielo_2021_3.png?h=720','Here\'s a bold and delicious wine that\'s loaded with succulent white fruit sensations including mature Bartlett pear, tart green apple and citrus. The round, juicy palate is brightened by crisp acidity and energized with mineral  notes that add depth.',31,NULL,0,'Serrocielo',196908),
(259189,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From a parcel of vines in the Meursault village appellation, this attractive, soft wine has ripe grapefruit and pear flavors to go with the crisp acidity and the lightest touch of wood. Drink from 2015.',55,NULL,0,'Les Clous',197241),
(259199,218512,'other','Nero d\'Avola',NULL,'Big and ripe, this Nero d\'Avola weaves together blue flower, leather, fleshy blackberry, black cherry, clove, sage, vanilla and subtle oak sensations. The juicy fruit is framed by round, velvety tannins. You\'ll also notice a warmth on the finish before it closes on a licorice note.',52,NULL,0,'Tané',196773),
(259245,219700,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/v8y51cXtQ0Sw-uRREayyFw_pb_x960.png','Syrah finds a perfect home in Sicily. The sea breezes and sunny weather help give ripe aromas of blackberry, cherry, tobacco and smoked bacon. It exudes a spicy touch of barbecue sauce, with gritty tannins that give the wine texture, richness and power.',13,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour',196776),
(259325,217335,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6PxVA4MXT8OQboBkr5RtaQ_pb_x960.png','The winery brings a Pinot Noir-esque touch to this Syrah, with its silky-heavy texture and cherry, cola and white pepper flavors. The tannins give it away, lending weight and substance, but still, it\'s amazingly supple for Syrah this powerful. Drink now–2016.',54,NULL,0,'Garys\' Vineyard',196639),
(259378,218569,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/291cKtTVRiOI1GCoMQTb0g_pb_x960.png','Textured vanilla-cream and green apple appear initially in this wine, which offers plenty of weight and structure around a core of balanced acidity and fresh lemon zest. Cardamom and vanilla play at the edges alongside elements of savory brine and white flowers. The oak presence is subtle.',58,NULL,0,'Olivet Lane Vineyard',196626),
(259495,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/19PPI_low-335x1024.png','Has to be one of the most forward, immediately drinkable Pisoni Pinots out there. It\'s enormously flattering in raspberries, cherries, currants and cola, with sweet toasty oak complexities. The acidity is gorgeous, the tannins soft. There\'s no reason to age this beautiful wine, so drink it now and through 2016.',67,NULL,0,'Pisoni Vineyard',196639),
(259568,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'From the Latour domaine, this dense wine is full of plum and sweet strawberry. At the same time, it is solid with an undertow of tannins and a dark texture. The acidity is already well integrated into this ripe and full-bodied wine. At the end, the signs of wood aging emerge and need to integrate. Drink from 2020.',140,NULL,0,'Clos du Roi',197254),
(259619,222090,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This classic, iconic Pinotage opens with dense aromas of pressed purple violets, forest berries, raspberry sauce and fudge brownie. The lush and decadent palate offers more of the same, with a crushed velvet texture and final notes of licorice and toasted spice that linger long. It\'s delicious now, but should hold well through 2022.',40,NULL,0,'Estate Wine',197420),
(259620,222091,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a young, fresh and very attractive Chardonnay, brimming with aromas and flavors of wood-grilled apple, honeydew, Honeycomb cereal, buttered popcorn and toasted oak. The palate is round and full, yet with ample acidity, citrus flavor and a mineral streak that all provides lift and character to the close. Drink 2016–2020.',24,NULL,0,'Lesca',196845),
(259647,218228,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/LhGgbU7JRS2sLsR3QrRwog_pb_600x600.png','There\'s no denying this wine\'s stalky, oily aromas. In the mouth, this blend of Roussanne, Marsanne and Viognier is chunky, with flavors that follow suit: the palate is bitter, slightly oxidized and melony. For $40, not much is clicking here.',40,NULL,0,'The Blend Collection',196886),
(259664,217335,'other','Chardonnay','http://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/17CSM_low.png','Vanilla-soaked French toast and caramelized apples promise a butter bomb in this Testarossa take on the historic Sierra Madre Vineyard in the Santa Maria Valley. Once sipped, there is a surprising level of soda-like acidity, and a steadily emerging flavor profile that ranges from cream soda to squeezed lime.',45,NULL,0,'Sierra Madre Vineyard',196639),
(259678,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Firm in its tannins and with a sense of power, this full-bodied wine has great fruit, along with wood and licorice flavors. This complex and fruity, wine is generous and ready to age. Drink from 2017.',85,NULL,0,'Les Damodes Premier Cru',197254),
(259733,219884,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_959i6B8TzyEfTkv7R4law_pb_x600.png','This 50-50 blend of Pinot Noir and Touriga Nacional works surprisingly well. It has weight, but also a smooth texture and juicy swathes of black plum and red berry fruits. Juicy fruit flavors are encased in a firm, tannic shell that\'s solid and dark. The wine is drinkable now after decanting, but could benefit from aging until 2016.',18,NULL,0,'Consensus Pinot Noir-Touriga Nacional',196807),
(259815,222151,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This opens with initially assertive oaky tones of cocoa powder, vanilla sauce and sweet spice that marry seamlessly with raspberry jam and boysenberry fruit. The palate is velvety and plush, with decadent fruit flavors and earthy soil and spice notes that hang around through the long finish. Drink now–2020.',26,NULL,0,'The Prospector',196689),
(259909,217265,'other','Merlot',NULL,'This is a little sharp, with some prickly heat, but dry, with rich tannins and deep black-cherry, plum, red currant, pepper and cedar flavors. Ready to drink.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 344',196620),
(259930,219700,'other','Inzolia','https://static.xtrawine.com/Global/Images/XW/products/wines/40813_SallierDeLaTourInzolia_2022_3.png','Spicy, fresh and clean, this would pair with fried seafood or spaghetti con vongole. It offers pretty citrus tones followed by a drying mineral nuance.',13,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour',196776),
(259943,221639,'other','Tinto del Pais',NULL,'Earthy, damp aromas suggest compost but there\'s enough fresh black-fruit character to keep the bouquet balanced. This feels dense, saturated and heavy, with a syrupy leaning and full tannins. Flavors of baked blackberry and vanilla end a little stewy and soft. Drink through 2017.',30,NULL,0,'Spiga',196852),
(259953,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From a small parcel at the base of the hill of Beaune, this is a delicious wine with a touch of vanilla. It is rounded, smooth and rich, bringing out both fruit and toasty wood flavors that are integrated well. Drink from 2016.',40,NULL,0,'Clos Saint-Désiré',197254),
(259954,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'In this powerful, full-bodied wine, soft fruit accompanies the firm tannins. The wine is already well integrated, showing dense red fruits as well as structure. A touch of wood will soften soon. Drink from 2016.',60,NULL,0,'Morgeot Premier Cru',197254),
(260083,222244,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This is a well-balanced, well-structured white wine that\'s sure to evolve through 2020, at least. It\'s certainly attractive now, with subtle toasty notes of sweet spice and wood-grilled apple alongside hints of kiwi, sweet grass, green plum and lime. The medium-weight palate offers ample acidity and a streak of minerality that keeps things fresh and lifted through the softly spiced finish.',50,NULL,0,'Reserve',196689),
(260243,217504,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This wine is on the richer side of the Pinot Noir spectrum, and folks looking for a little more lushness out of the grape will be pleased. Ripe raspberry and wild strawberry flavors are laced with a forest floor earthiness, while glimmers of mocha and soft menthol unfold on the finish. Medium weight with a lifting acidic cut to the close.',40,NULL,0,'Galpin Peak',196793),
(260244,222151,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A Bordeaux-style blend made from 50% Cab Sauv, 30% Merlot and 20% Cab Franc and aged in new French oak for 24 months, this ripe and lush wine is ready for drinking now with easygoing black cherry and blackberry fruit aromas and flavors laced with notes of pepper, licorice root, tobacco leaf and soft leather. The creamy mouthfeel is given structure with medium tannins and balanced acidity.',40,NULL,0,'Cobblers Hill',196689),
(260251,222330,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'If big, ripe, oaky Chards are your thing, then this is one that\'s certainly worth searching out. Rich and full with a round, creamy mouth, the wine offers full-blown flavors of pineapple, guava, orange creamsicle and banana cream pie all abound, followed by a nutty, sweet spice-flavored finish. Thankfully, there\'s enough acid to keep things balanced and prevent the wine from being too heavy or flabby.',45,NULL,0,'Quartz Stone Single Vineyard',197445),
(260255,222331,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A solid Cab at an attractive price. There\'s a lot going on in this structured and well-balanced wine. Aromas of black currant and licorice dominate the nose alongside secondary glimmers of black pepper and crushed violets, all framed with a sweet oak streak. Flavors of juicy black raspberry linger well into the finish, which gradually fades into gorgeous white pepper spice.',27,NULL,0,'Unfined and Unfiltered',196689),
(260256,222333,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A super-interesting blend of 37% Syrah, 21% Mourvèdre, 18% Carignan, 10% Petite Sirah, 10% Grenache and 8% Tannat, the bouquet is loaded with assertive aromas of black currant, licorice, black olive, whole tobacco leaf, cigar box spice and leather. Creamy but firmly textured, like crushed velvet, with a rich boysenberry and plum juiciness to the palate.',20,NULL,0,'Chakalaka',197368),
(260271,222336,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A light and easygoing Chard with bright aromas of lemon citrus, green apple and watermelon rind. Riper apple and tropical fruit notes appear on the palate, followed by a refreshingly clean finish. 3,000 cases imported; drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Unoaked',196839),
(260354,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Soft and rounded, this has an open, fragrant character. It has ripe flavors of strawberries and red plums, with a touch of wood and delicious, fresh acidity. Only on the finish does the structured side show through.',35,NULL,0,'Ile de Vergelesses Premier Cru',197254),
(260412,222244,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'There\'s a natural essence to this wine, exhibiting the best qualities of the grape as well as a sense of terroir. Soft herbal and mineral accent the clean, fruity core. Green pear, melon rind and a hint of peach pit unfold on the palate and follow through to the long, slightly spiced finish. Perfectly drinkable now, but will cellar nicely for another 3-5 years.',30,NULL,0,'Organic Grapes',196689),
(260434,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Ripe, soft tannins layer with juicy, forward berry fruits and acidity. Here is a wine that is attractive, deliciously fruity, its flavors just ready to cut through a steak.',8,NULL,0,'Segada Tinto',196807),
(260443,221639,'other','Malbec-Tempranillo',NULL,'A bit warm and baked on the nose, with aromas of fruit cake and pastry. The palate is full-bodied and chewy, with ripe, sweet black fruit flavors that finish with vanilla and chocolate.',14,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(260458,222421,'other','Syrah-Viognier',NULL,'A good value, this is an easy-pleasing Syrah with vibrant notes of red plum, cherry and blueberry. Fine, dusty tannins reminiscent of cocoa powder and dried crushed berries stay after swallow alongside a hint of sweet smoke flavor.',20,NULL,0,'Goat-Roti',197456),
(260468,221639,'other','Tempranillo',NULL,'A huge success given the price. Impeccably smooth on the bouquet, with clean yet generous berry aromas. Ripe and balanced, with bright berry and chocolaty oak flavors. Solid on the finish, with lasting plum and berry flavors. Satisfying in every way.',11,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(260473,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Juicy fruit aromas and flavors of raspberry and wild strawberry abound on the nose and mouth, framed by notes of vanilla crème, purple flowers and light foliage. Balanced and surprisingly quite approachable now with an overall soft profile and easy finish.',35,NULL,0,'Three Pines Unfined and Unfiltered',196689),
(260475,222428,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This red, made from 61% Cab Sauv, 30% Shiraz and 9% Merlot, offers attractive floral aromas of lavender, baby powder and light menthol (like a Thin Mint) to the soft but ripe dark fruit notes. The mouth offers more spice and weight than the aromas would suggest, with a firm but approachable structure and cigar box spice on the medium-length finish.',42,NULL,0,'Estate',196689),
(260478,217719,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This approachable Cabernet-based blend, which also has 18% Pinotage, 11% Cab Franc and 2% Shiraz, is a spicy and balanced red with notes of menthol, purple florals, black cherry and berry. With a mouthfeel like crushed velvet, a black pepper finish and an attractive price tag, it\'s a shame only 100 cases were produced.',18,NULL,0,'The William',196845),
(260494,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Rzvg7SXFTsaUMPUDXKyf9g_pb_600x600.png','The spectrum of varietal aromas is here: saline, olive, forest floor, tea and red and black fruits. Weighty and round in the mouth, with good feel and full blackberry flavors supported by creamy oak and vanilla. Juicy and red enough on the finish, where a pop of acidity registers.',12,NULL,0,'Reserve Barrel Select',196857),
(260577,218569,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Pf8tvyjIQlug9gDx4pdmYA_pb_x960.png','This is a bold and sultry white from a great vineyard, displaying coconut macaroon and exotic pineapple and papaya on the nose. Rich and seductive, it reaches its biggest presence of crème brûlée-inflected oak and fleshiness at the midpoint, before finishing lean in spice.',58,NULL,0,'Heintz Vineyard',196626),
(260595,222477,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This is a blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Shiraz, Petit Verdot and Grenache, with a spine that\'s all ripe dark berries and cherries. But there\'s enough savory herbs and peppery spices to keep it complex and layered. The texture is slightly creamy, with a lush, fruity palate, and a tobacco- and toasted-spice-infused finish.',15,NULL,0,'Mountain Red',196839),
(260598,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Rich, round and concentrated, this is developing fast. The acidity is already comfortably embedded in the ripe red-berry fruit..',65,NULL,0,'En Chevret Premier Cru',197254),
(260655,222507,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Made with grapes sourced from 40-year-old bush vines, this Chenin boasts savory herb notes alongside the creamy peach, fig and sweet lime fruit. The medium-weight palate shows well-integrated oak notes that complement the earthy, herbal character. The texture is somewhat nervy now, but this should really start to shine from 2014 on.',50,NULL,0,'The Bernard Series Limited Release Old Vine',197456),
(260705,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/1mbdVkqmQU2F2ETStzXVgg_pb_x960.png','Berry and cola aromas are offset by a grassy/minty scent. In the mouth, the acidity is high so the feel is forward and scouring. Tastes earthy, herbal and meaty, with tobacco, black fruit, spice and mint. Full-forced and staunch; contains 15% Syrah.',14,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserva Privada',196852),
(260723,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Leather, berry, earth, raisin and roasted qualities define the nose on this Tempranillo-led blend of four grapes. Feels good in the mouth, with active raspberry, plum and coffee flavors that comes with a roasted accent. Mildly leafy, baked and woody on the thorough finish.',19,NULL,0,'B Crux',196852),
(260724,218042,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Balancing foliage notes of sous bois, eucalyptus and purple florals mingle perfectly with the ripe blackberry and cherry flavors. Full and creamy with medium acidity and fine tannins. A touch of black pepper and roasted espresso graces the long finish.',19,NULL,0,'Wolfkloof',196845),
(260739,218512,'other','Insolia','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/m-Qc6SATQ6qVhUtS_w8bcg_pb_x600.png','A simple citrus aroma provides for a fresh and inviting bouquet. Peach, pear and green apple touches give the wine added brightness and buoyancy.',15,NULL,0,'Case Ibidini',196773),
(260744,219700,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6-Ssb2acSNeiKqDm4sQLZQ_pb_x960.png','This shows a bright quality of fruit, with fine nuances of berry, tart cherry and plum. The acidity would pair with oven-roasted lasagna with a cheesy crust.',13,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour',196776),
(260758,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This has surprisingly structured fruits and firm tannins for a Nouveau, and it still maintains a juicy cherry flavor and ripe acidity. The finish has a tangy, textured character.',11,NULL,0,'Nouveau',197404),
(260779,217512,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/df-X1OYWTV6PoT8DBYsRnw_pb_x960.png','A delicious citric-dominated wine, very fresh, with a great apple skin texture, bright aciidty and crisp white fruits. It dances easily, lightly, ready to drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo',196663),
(260831,222420,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Light nuances of baking spice and forest floor grace the notes of lively black cherry and raspberry. The velvety mouthfeel is juicy and fruit forward, with a jammy richness that transitions onto the long finish, alongside a touch of black pepper.',15,NULL,0,'The Berry Box',196689),
(260893,222607,'other','Merlot-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This medium-weight blend of 70% Merlot and 30% Cabernet Sauvignon is flavorful and juicy with notes of black plum and berry accented by savory herbs. The finish is clean and lively and the palate soft. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Oak Lane',196689),
(260950,218043,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 37% Cabernet Sauvignon, 37% Shiraz and 26% Merlot boasts assertive aromas of cassis, black plum and licorice root. The medium-weight palate offers similarly concentrated fruit flavors, with a slightly chewy texture and a long, spicy finish.',15,NULL,0,'The Left Bank',196839),
(260970,217719,'other','Chenin Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/2R2VQ-wBSyCEbqXW_n4CUQ_pb_300x300.png','This exemplary Chenin starts with aromas of peach, pineapple and vanilla, rolling into juicy flavors of melon, honey and rich fruit. Balanced and with a slightly creamy mouthfeel, the wine is elegant but approachable enough for every day. Pair with salad, seafood. Imported by GBW, LLC.',16,NULL,0,'Gamekeeper\'s Reserve',196845),
(260982,222654,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This wine has a delicate nose of citrus and spicy nuts, with robust, round flavors of apple, citrus and spice. Balanced acid and fruit means the wine has complexity, but is still refreshing. Mouthwatering and food friendly, the Chardonnay has added class.',17,NULL,0,'Limestone Hill',196845),
(260996,217265,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Here\'s a dry, fruity Merlot brimming with cherry, chocolate, anise and smoky oak flavors. The tannins have a bit of an edge, which gives it a nice structure. Will work well against a grilled steak. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 122',196620),
(260999,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'In the flower label series, this deliciously bright soft wine has a great lift of berries, cranberry texture and a bubble gum exuberance. Always one of the most popular cru Beaujolais, this wine, from a light vintage, shows the delicious, immediate fruity side.',16,NULL,0,'Flower Label',197404),
(261020,222367,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of Cannonau, Carignano and Bovale opens with bright, intense fruit, with notes of blackberry, crème de cassis and pomegranate juice. The mouthfeel is firm and structured.',46,NULL,0,'S\'arai',197281),
(261021,222679,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'There\'s great richness to the nose, with a seriously decadent and robust apple-pie aroma. The palate shows a bit more balance and restraint, with ripe flavors of fig and melon fleshing out the creamy texture but staying bright thanks to lifting acidity. The evolving finish transitions from fruit to spice and finally ends on a citrus pith flavor.',30,NULL,0,'Platinum',197462),
(261034,222686,'other','Chenin Blanc-Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Fresh grass, vibrant citrus and tart gooseberry fill the nose and mouth, making this an approachable and clean white perfect for pairing with lighter chicken and fish dishes. 70% Chenin Blanc and 30% Sauvignon Blanc; drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Polkadraai',197491),
(261039,222690,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Hints of savory herbs spice up this approachable Chard, adding character to the grilled red apple and sweet citrus oil core. The medium-length finish offers a touch of sweet smoke flavor to keep things interesting. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Sarah',196878),
(261043,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'The name Quartetto refers to the blend of four grapes that produce an openly soft wine with good acidity and a gentle structure. For drinking now.',10,NULL,0,'Monte da Cal Quartetto',196794),
(261044,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Crisp and lively wine, with delicate lemon and more forward melon and apricot flavors. Ready for an apéritif this summer.',8,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano Branco',196807),
(261049,222693,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Berry preserves, black plum flesh and tobacco abound on the nose, while the medium-weight mouth provides more dried berry flavors laced with cocoa powder. Soft on the palate with an off-dry finish. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Kosher',197445),
(261113,221639,'other','Tinto del Pais',NULL,'Fresh berry aromas carry some spice notes, while the palate is rugged and a little hot. Juicy berry flavors are forward but not overly evolved or complex, and the the finish is tight and aggressive. Spunky and clean, with honest flavors.',14,NULL,0,'Urban Ribera',196852),
(261123,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Very oaky and very ripe, offering a flood of pineapple jam, pear, vanilla and toasty oak flavors. Crisp acidity provides needed balance and a clean, brisk mouthfeel.',18,NULL,0,'Cool Coastal Vineyards',196642),
(261191,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Opulent and ripe, full bodied and rich, this has notes of toast and spice as well as apricot and pear flavors. With its balanced character, it can be consumed now, but it will also age for another year.',25,NULL,0,'Domaine Beranger',197404),
(261206,222758,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Alluring aromas of tropical fruit and crisp citrus lead this complex Sauvignon Blanc. Balanced flavors of passionfruit, pineapple, lemon and spice are delivered in a creamy but clean package. Good for myriad dishes, from grilled seafood to more sophisticated fare.',10,NULL,0,'Winemaker\'s Choice',196839),
(261315,221639,'other','Tinto del Pais',NULL,'Intense and deep, with plenty of licorice, leather and pepper encasing serious dark-berry aromas. The wine runs round and full in the mouth, with chewy berry flavors, meaty tannins and a generous finish that\'s long and just a touch lemony from the wine\'s 20 months in barrel. A wine that speaks to you.',49,NULL,0,'AlfaSpiga',196852),
(261362,222823,'other','Chenin Blanc-Viognier',NULL,'This blend of 57% Chenin Blanc and 43% Viognier is opulent and forward. Rich scents of baked apple, clove-spiked orange, honeysuckle and hazelnut crisp dance on the nose and mouth, but the palate remains lifted with fresh acidity and a saline note. Accents of spice and toast remain through the long close. A gorgeous wine now, but it should age beautifully through 2015.',35,NULL,0,'White',197511),
(261367,222679,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This wine starts off with an enticing honeycomb and baked apple aroma, followed by secondary accents of baking spice and orange zest. The fully textured mouth is loaded with dried peach and apricot flavors, followed by a nice citrus zip that adds spring to the long finish.',27,NULL,0,'Noble Late Harvest',197462),
(261368,222826,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A full-flavored and ripe selection, with decadent scents of sweet spice, whole vanilla bean and peanut skin that give depth to the ripe pear and melon fruit. There\'s a tangy lift to the palate, as flavors of white cranberry and lemon zest keep the mouthfeel fresh. A honeyed almond accent unfolds on the close.',33,NULL,0,'Kama',196839),
(261400,222833,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A beautifully balanced and nuanced wine. The aromas are heady and thick but still vibrant, displaying juicy notes of black cherry, black raspberry sauce and semidried fig laced with accents of bittersweet chocolate, tobacco and white pepper. The texture is like crushed satin, with well-integrated tannins and a creamy mouthfeel. Touches of licorice root and smoky cedar spice augment the dark fruit on the lengthy finish. Drink now–2014.',50,NULL,0,'Series C',197445),
(261440,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://stilebrands.com/stilebrands/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Taurasi-Selve-di-Luoti-Aglianico-web.png','Year after year, Feudi\'s Taurasi delivers amazing intensity and volcanic soil aromas that are so distinctive they immediately give its Campania roots away. This boasts bold cherry, with deep tones of sweet-smelling blue flower, licorice, pinecone, tobacco, campfire and charcoal. The wine is plush and velvety on the palate and those fantastic mineral notes emerge on the finale.',44,NULL,0,'Selve di Luoti',196908),
(261555,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/36s74xLyTliu6xVFUGlDfA_pb_x960.png','Named after the monastery of Farizoa in Alentejo, this is in a fresh, fruity style, packed with sweet damsons, some fresh acidity, but more in open, welcoming richness. For drinking over the next year.',14,NULL,0,'Farizoa',196663),
(261600,222933,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'It\'s really a shame that only 25 cases of this wine were imported, as it\'s a fantastic Cab that\'s sure to compare favorably to some of your favorites. Black currant leaf, fennel, crushed violet and dried tobacco are intricately woven into the dark fruit aromas. The medium-weight mouth has a texture like crushed velvet, with firm tannins and assertive flavors of cassis, cigar and espresso that linger endlessly. Strong and a bit tight; try holding another 2–5 years.',50,NULL,0,'Lady May',197420),
(261726,223005,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Full-bodied and intense for a rosé wine, the Lekkerwijn offers complexity in a dry, concentrated delivery. Savory and spicy with an herbal spin, the wine finishes long. Pair with spicy food, duck, game fish.',23,NULL,0,'Solms Wijn de Caab Lekkerwijn',196839),
(261730,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Pleasant flavors of cherries, raspberries and licorice, and a spicy finish. Feels too sharp in the mouth, though, with a cut of green acidity. But for the price, it\'s a pretty good Pinot.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 165',196620),
(261750,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is structured, with tannins and dark fruits that are balanced by bright acids. The firm, dry tannins give the wine shape; it will ultimately develop into a round, rich Pinot Noir.',90,NULL,0,'Epenots Premier Cru',197254),
(261834,222833,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Although this might be second to the Series C, it\'s still up there in terms of high quality and class. Red plum, fresh fig and subtle blueberry are augmented by glimmers of licorice and earthy spice. The mouth is full and as forward as the nose, loaded with thick juicy fruit flavors that lead gracefully into the raspberry mash and tobacco infused finish. Drink now–2013.',35,NULL,0,'Series M',197445),
(261882,217148,'other','Gewürztraminer',NULL,'One of the first wines from De Loach after the Boisset takeover, this dry Gewürz is a good portent for the future. It\'s ultraclean and crisp, with very deep and satisfying flavors of Asian spices, peaches, litchi and citrus.',14,NULL,0,'Early Harvest',196642),
(261958,223107,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'The oak is pronounced on the nose and mouth of this wine, but it\'s supported by ripe fruit aromas and flavors of red apple flesh, guava and quince. It\'s lush and mouthfilling, but there\'s enough acidity to keep it from feeling overdone or flabby. Finishes clean with spiced tropical-fruit notes.',35,NULL,0,'Barrel Selection',197545),
(261962,223111,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Flavorful and harmonious, seductive notes of soft toast and walnut shell add dimension to the honeydew, red apple and orange zest notes. Medium weight, with good acidity and a lasting finish, this is balanced and approachable now, with all of the elements working together.',24,NULL,0,'Reserve',196689),
(262007,222654,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a stellar example of how to do South African Chard right. Delicate white florals and a firm minerality mingle with fruit notes of Gala apple and Anjou pear. The mouth is weighty but not flabby and a soft sweet woody spice lingers on the long finish.',50,NULL,0,'Bateleur',196845),
(262057,218426,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/a1OWZHOoTJCE72VWnWpw3Q_pb_x600.png','Smells forward and ripe, with wild berry, bramble, and blueberry aromas and an array of crushed, dust oriental Spices.  On the palate, it\'s awkward, somewhat hot, with 15% alcohol and some overripe, raisiny flavors that are Port-like.  Some, however, will go nuts over this style.',28,NULL,0,'Great Estates',196751),
(262121,223183,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This is a gorgeous Bordeaux-style blend that grabs you right from the start with a decadent nose of black currant liqueur, toasted coconut, black cherry, cedar and a hint of purple African violet florals. The mouth is round but not fat, with a firm but not unyielding structure followed by a toffee-kissed finish that lingers endlessly. Drink now–2015.',30,NULL,0,'Estate Reserve (Trilogy)',196689),
(262139,223185,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A gorgeous and elegant compositionally undisclosed red blend from winemaker Kevin Grant, this has all the finesse and complexity of a great wine. Bright and inviting with juicy red plum, blueberry, and wild raspberry aromas and flavors laced with hints of smoky, woody spice and minerality. Silky in the mouth with fine tannins and a long, nuanced finish. Drink now.',30,NULL,0,'Serenity',196839),
(262292,218426,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6EFZppNNR82r37NduYRBAQ_pb_x960.png','An easy drinking dinner wine, dry and balanced, with smooth tannins and plum, blackberry and coffee flavors. Has a rich, blueberry-muffin taste on the finish.',16,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(262310,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a blend of several vineyards, instead of the winery\'s usual single-vineyard Chards. It\'s been tastefully assembled, and displays good Central Coast acidity framing tropical fruit and oak flavors with a stony, minerally edge.',30,NULL,0,'Castello',196639),
(262327,223247,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Vibrant, attractive notes of black cherry, plum, raspberry sauce and licorice root draw you in immediately, and continue on to the palate alongside complementary accents of sweet spice and black pepper. Medium weight in the mouth with grippy tannins and a strong finish. Elegant yet intense.',35,NULL,0,'Ansela Van de Caab',197420),
(262334,223250,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A limited production wine (only 3,440 bottles produced) that has the depth and concentration one would expect for a wine with this price tag. Dark and floral with aromas of crushed African violets, black plum, cherry and clover. The mouth is lush and velvety, loaded with flavors of cassis, black berry, pepper and leathery spice that continue through the finish. Drink now through 2015.',65,NULL,0,'Minotaur',197557),
(262339,222330,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a top-end Chard from a very reputable producer. Sweet custardy notes of mango, pear and melon transition from the nose to mouth seamlessly, with accents of hazelnut and orange oil adding complexity to the long finish. Full and lusty with an overall decadent feel; drink now.',45,NULL,0,'Quartz Stone',197445),
(262365,223265,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This wine shows character and layers of flavor in its straightforward yet elegant approach. A mineral thread stitches together the ripe fruit notes of white melon, yellow apple, pear and Key lime. Medium weight, with a bit of a nervy feel right now, give this another year to really shine.',15,NULL,0,'Original Unwooded',197456),
(262436,223284,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Dark and wild, aromas of black berry and raspberry are intertwined with notes of whole tobacco leaf, sweet spice and a hint of licorice on the nose. The palate is lush and concentrated, loaded with more dark fruit flavors that are lifted by accents of white pepper, smoked meat and a mocha-infused finish. Balanced and decadent with an overall creaminess.',20,NULL,0,'Private Collection',196689),
(262451,219700,'other','Red Blend','https://www.winedirect.co.uk/image/cache/data/Segal/Cygnus_2016-1-215x768-600x800.png','Cygnus is a very distinct blend of Nero d\'Avola and Cabernet Sauvignon with intense aromas of barbecue sauce, liquid smoke, smoked ham and cola-like tones. The overall effect is thick, brooding and dense and this is the kind of wine you\'ll want to pair with succulent steak drenched in A-1 sauce.',30,NULL,0,'Cygnus',196776),
(262478,223300,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A blend of mostly Chenin Blanc, with 9% Chardonnay and 5% Viognier, this is a charming white with alluring notes of orange blossom and peony that mingle with the white peach and mango fruit. There\'s a nice vibrancy on the palate, with fresh tropical-fruit flavors that hang on to the finish.',17,NULL,0,'Chenin Blanc-Chardonnay-Viognier',197557),
(262551,223326,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This limited release is big and flavorful upfront, with assertive aromas of sweet spice, clementine, tropical fruit and blanched almonds. A fleshy pear flavor leads the round, mouth-filling palate, followed by a lengthy finish laced with notes of hazelnut toast and sweet spice. Ready to drink now.',31,NULL,0,'Spellbinding',196689),
(262555,222540,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Open and seductive, this has upfront notes of oak backed by moderate red apple, pear and faint herb accents. Medium weight, with a flinty streak, the palate is bright and mouthwatering, closing on a toasty, orange rind flavor.',35,NULL,0,'Renaissance',196689),
(262566,223328,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Honey and minor toast notes mingle with the red apple, mango and peach aromas and flavors. Easy-drinking and fruit-forward, the palate is bright and lively, with pineapple-core acidity that lingers on the finish. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Le Cotte Mill',196839),
(262568,222151,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This barrel-fermented Chenin shows well-integrated oak, with hints of soft baking spice to the melon and green-fig fruit core. A slightly creamy texture fills the mouth, with a seductive toasty accent staying through the medium-length finish.',16,NULL,0,'Barrel Fermented',196689),
(262576,223334,'other','Grenache-Syrah',NULL,'Silky and seductive with notes of raspberry, red cherry, blueberry and earthy forrest aromas. The finish shows a sweet mocha accent through the dominant fruit flavors. Balanced and approachable with well-integrated tannins and a strong finish.',65,NULL,0,'The Gypsy',196839),
(262591,222933,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The aromas are promisingly thick and chewy, with assertive notes of black cherry, cigar tobacco and bittersweet chocolate. The creamy mouth delivers more of the same alongside additional elements of cassis, pepper and leathery spice. The mocha-infused finish leaves little else to be desired; drink now.',18,NULL,0,'The Glass Collection',197420),
(262765,222367,'other','Bovale',NULL,'Bovale is a little-known indigenous grape from Sardinia. This opens with savory aromas of cured meat, chocolate, ripe fruit and prune. The close is bold, bitter and bright.',30,NULL,0,'Essentija',197281),
(262781,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This is a very pleasant and elegant blend of Nero d\'Avola, Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot that does a great job of presenting a united aromatic front. There are no loose edges here and the wine is compact and smooth in the mouth. Very nice.',29,NULL,0,'Triskelè',196776),
(262794,223405,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Strong aromas of cassis, cocoa nibs, fresh mint sprigs, black currant leaf and licorice are the first things you experience with this wine. After that, the creamy mouth provides loads of black berry, plum and anise flavors that stay through the finish. A firmly structured and well-balanced Bordeaux-style blend.',30,NULL,0,'John X Merriman',196689),
(262797,222693,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'With 16 months in French and American oak, it should not be a surprise that this wine is as rich and wonderfully wood-spiced as it is. Earthy spice by way of clove, cinnamon sticks, anise root and cigar box bring the typical dark fruit flavors to another level. Balanced and drinkable now with a finish reminiscent of a tanned hide.',22,NULL,0,'Pumphouse',197445),
(262809,222367,'other','Cannonau',NULL,'Thick in concentration and color, this ripe-and-ready wine delivers notes of sweet cherry cola, smoked ham, toast and red rose. It\'s big, jammy and chewy in the mouth with nice succulence and medium structure.',18,NULL,0,'Triente',197281),
(262863,223334,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A fresh and fruity wine that\'s ready to drink now. This has attractive aromas and flavors of green apple and lime followed by a clean, mouthwatering finish. There\'s a soft herbal streak that adds depth to the nose and mouth.',12,NULL,0,'Petit',196839),
(262864,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/y35eEPuaQJuA0Ly5A3OMrw_pb_x960.png','A solid Cabernet, offering plenty of savory blackberry, cola and spice flavors that finish dry and wholesome.',28,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(262870,222367,'other','Vermentino',NULL,'This refreshing wine is redolent of stone fruit, citrus and tangerine skin. It\'s an easy, food-friendly effort.',30,NULL,0,'Stellato',197281),
(262892,223438,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'This is an attractive but focused wine with loads of juicy red plum guts, mashed raspberry and blackberry preserve flavors framing licorice and sweet spice backnotes. Robust and spicy with a strong cocoa flavored finish.',40,NULL,0,'Roulette',197368),
(262901,223443,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz',NULL,'The \'08 Oro is Cab dominant while the \'07 favored Shiraz, a difference that seems to be an improvement. Rich and concentrated with lovely dark plum, cassis and black raspberry components coupled with accents of tree bark, sweet spice and soft cigar tobacco. Fresh and lush all at once; easy to drink now or can hold for a year or two.',18,NULL,0,'Oro',197445),
(262906,222429,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'There\'s a real richness to this wine, as aromas of butter and cream flood the nose alongside notes of ripe peach and apple. The mouthfeel is as full and lush as one would anticipate from the bouquet, and the finish is long but clean. Drink now.',53,NULL,0,'The Eleanor',196689),
(263032,222091,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Danie De Wets has steadily demonstrated both what he and the Robertson region--for many still an unknown--can deliver. He does it again in this convincing white, built (of course) on a solid Chardonnay fruit core. Rich but not sappy, it offers abundant flavor, a solid mouthfeel, elegant style and a spicy, long finish. An impressive white with balance and finesse well beyond its price and rustic origins.',24,NULL,0,'D\'Honneur',196845),
(263089,222933,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Black berry, raspberry and cassis abound on the bouquet of this wine, lifted by superattractive aromas of fudgy brownie. The fruit transitions completely to the full palate, with a touch of peppery spice staying through the close. Drink now.',25,NULL,0,'Grand Vin de Glenelly',197420),
(263100,222477,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Remarkably well balanced and easy to drink with soft toast, grilled peach and Red Delicious apple throughout. The finish has a distinct nuttiness to it, seeming almost sweet and spicy all at once. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Sutherland',196839),
(263178,222524,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Cuvée V, MAN\'s homage to the wines of Vouvray, is an attractive and semisweet-style Chenin Blanc that offers rich aromas of peach, lightly baked apple and tropical fruit. A slight prickle from the bright acidity dances on the palate and keeps the wine from feeling too sweet or heavy. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Cuvée V',197456),
(263191,222367,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Fresh and easy, this shows bright berry aromas, with subtle touches of forest floor and bramble. This should pair well with barbecued pork or grilled hamburgers.',NULL,NULL,0,'Silenzi',197281),
(263192,222367,'other','Vermentino',NULL,'This is crisp and refreshing, with pretty endnotes of lime, wild flower and honeydew melon. It\'s an easy-drinking Vermentino that should pair well with sushi rolls or tuna tartare.',15,NULL,0,'I Fiori',197281),
(263199,217504,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'There\'s a distinct flinty, mineral sharpness to the nose, adding complexity to the melon, green apple and Anjou pear aromas. Medium weight but textured, the apple skin and toast flavors linger endlessly on the finish. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Crocodile\'s Lair',196793),
(263223,223539,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'There\'s a nice herbal earthiness here, giving a rustic and intriguing feel to this otherwise ripe, dark-fruit-dominant wine. Black plum, cherry and berry fill the midpalate, while tobacco and pepper spice take center stage on the finish. Approachable and lively now with good balance and soft tannins.',15,NULL,0,'Silkbush Mountain Vineyards',197596),
(263249,223506,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Everything\'s in place as the complex grapefruit, pineapple and tangy-spice nose opens to a full, similarly flavored palate. The feel is ripe and full yet alive with vibrant acidity, the finish long and clean with zesty pepper notes.',14,NULL,0,'Grand Cuvee',197456),
(263313,218512,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/9zEJO4gGSgyuSWLyN61BtQ_pb_x960.png','Rusciano is a new wine from Valle dell\'Acate (a blend of native Sicilian varieties and Syrah) that shows very ripe characteristics of cherry, raspberry and spice. You can taste the mature black fruit here thanks to the wine\'s chewy, succulent density.',30,NULL,0,'Rusciano',196773),
(263362,223582,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Apple skin, orange rind and clove spice lead on the bouquet, while opulent flavors of popcorn and baked apple fill the medium-weight palate. Despite the rich notes throughout, there\'s a nice freshness, with a clean, softly spiced finish. Drink now.',13,NULL,0,'The Pirate of Cocoa Hill',196689),
(263388,223593,'other','Chardonnay-Viognier',NULL,'With 25% Viognier added to this Chard, there are a lot of floral characteristics adding complexity to the nose and mouth. Roasted apple, orange blossom and almond skin round out the mouth, while a touch of Earl Grey tea pleasantly unfolds on the finish. Drink now.',16,NULL,0,'Art House',197456),
(263468,223624,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A refreshing and approachable wine, with forward notes of green plum, plantain, Granny Smith apple and lime on the nose and palate. There\'s a slight roundness to the midpalate, but a vibrant twang lifts the finish.',11,NULL,0,'Chenin No. 5',196845),
(263480,223231,'other','White Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of 80% Chenin Blanc and 20% Pinotage, this white is fresh and fruity, with an enticing mixture of citrusy flowers and small red berries. There\'s a touch of earthiness on the palate, with a nice smoothness its medium weight. So crisp and alive now; drink up.',11,NULL,0,'Chenin Blanc-Pinotage',196689),
(263502,219700,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://www.vinello.eu/media/image/38/82/9e/Regaleali-Nero-DAvola.png','This is the kind of light and informal wine you can pair with pasta with fresh tomato sauce and basil. Made with Nero d\'Avola grapes, it offers aromas of cherry, raspberry, almond and roasted pistachio nut.',15,NULL,0,'Regaleali',196776),
(263503,223639,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'With the Owl Post being a reference to their preferred method of pest management, this is a welcome new release from Neethlingshof. Notes of purple flowers, black cherry, fudgy brownie and soft lanolin appear in the bouquet and medium-weight mouth. Balanced acidity and soft tannins linger through to the solid finish. Drink now.',25,NULL,0,'The Short Story Collection - The Owl Post',196689),
(263506,223284,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Beautiful aromas of lightly toasted red apple skins, peach pit and pineapple core draw you in immediately, while the ripe fruit flavors in the medium weight mouth keep you invested. Moderately intense and balanced, this would be a lovely match for roasted chicken.',20,NULL,0,'Private Collection',196689),
(263511,223641,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'Foliage and black pepper adds complexity to the strong raspberry, red plum and strawberry characteristics of this wine. It\'s straightforward but enjoyable with gentle tannins and a smoky, bacon-nuanced finish. Drink now.',18,NULL,0,'Vintage Selection Shiraz-Mourvèdre-Viognier',197456),
(263543,223258,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'An off-dry Chenin, with lush notes of peach, red apple and sweet lime. There are soft hints of sweet grass and spice that unfold on the bouquet and on the finish. Vibrant acidity keeps the flavors fresh and leaves a lingering tingling sensation. An easy choice for drinking now.',11,NULL,0,'Bush Camp The Sundowner',197445),
(263546,222367,'other','Nuragus',NULL,'I Fiori is a simple and fragrant white wine that reflects the aromas of coastal Italy and it\'s beautiful sea breezes. Wild sage, citrus and sea salt all converge on the bright bouquet.',NULL,NULL,0,'I Fiori',197281),
(263547,223655,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This wine shows good balance between the lively acidity and ripe notes of red apple flesh, pear and orange oil. The round mouthfeel of ripe fruit flavors are lifted on the finish by a tangy, green plum and lime zest accent. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Bush Vine',196689),
(263566,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This 60-40 blend of Nero d\'Avola and Merlot offers excellent value for this low price. Aromas include ripe cherry, blackberry and spice and the wine is smooth on the close with a crisp touch of cleansing acidity at the end.',12,NULL,0,'Calanìca Nero d\'Avola and Merlot',196776),
(263567,220442,'other','Insolia',NULL,'This elegantly packaged Insolia has a pretty, luminous appearance and pristine notes of stone fruit, citrus and mineral. This is your quintessential seafood wine: grilled sea bass, poached salmon or steamed mussels would all taste great in this wine\'s company.',13,NULL,0,'Colomba Platino',196776),
(263613,223676,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Although only 10% of this wine was aged in oak, you can definitely pick up on some of the woody accents—like vanilla and faint toast—that spice up core of green apple flesh and melon rind. Medium bodied and balanced, a sweet spice accent lingers nicely through the finish.',10,NULL,0,'Bergkelder Selection',196839),
(263644,223606,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A terrific value red blend of 32% Shiraz, 32% Pinotage, 18% Merlot and 18% Cab Sauv, loaded with fleshy fruit flavors of black plum, cherry and berry laced with hints of coffee grinds and earthy spice. The fine tannins and overall soft structure make this an easy drinker perfect for company.',11,NULL,0,'Blueish Black',196689),
(263661,223624,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Good intensity of fruit aromas and flavors are matched with a light, easy mouthfeel and clean finish. Aromas of guava, mango, yellow peach and sweet pineapple flood the nose and palate. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Five\'s Reserve',196845),
(263676,223707,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'There\'s a very cool minerality on the nose of this wine, followed by notes of green fruit, white currant and fresh hay on the nose and mouth. Medium weight in the mouth with bracing acidity and a clean, lingering finish.',25,NULL,0,'Pincushion Vineyard',197619),
(263688,223443,'other','Shiraz-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Forward and easy to drink with notes of cherry, cassis, purple florals and a touch of fresh coffee grinds in the bouquet. The mouthfeel is plump and rich with flavors of currant and licorice staying through the finish. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Oro',197445),
(263707,223718,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A nice selection for poolside entertaining, this bright and accessible Chenin Blanc offers attractive aromas and flavors of guava, melon and orange marmalade that are balanced by vibrant acidity. Ripe and flavorful without being overdone.',10,NULL,0,'Sultry',196839),
(263740,221639,'other','Malbec',NULL,'Warm and generous on the nose, with hints of brick dust and herbal strawberry fruit. Seems healthy and ready in the mouth, with good berry fruit, moderate spice notes and just a minor touch of herbal character. Works well, although it worked better when it was an under-$10 wine.',14,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(263765,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The acidity and minerality of this wine are instantly apparent, lending grip and bite. But its flavors of orange and apricot jam seem a bit sweet.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 320',196620),
(263774,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a simple wine, with orange, lime and vanilla flavors. Despite brisk acidity, it quickly turns cloying.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 314',196620),
(263788,223750,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Orange citrus dominates the medium-intense bouquet, but secondary aromas of green apple, melon rind, hard nectarine and a touch of honeysuckle appear upon deeper inhalation. Solidly structured with a vibrant mouth and an apple core flavored finish.',11,NULL,0,'Young Vines',196689),
(263796,223231,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An intersting and fruit-forward Cape blend composed of 57% Pinotage, 23% Shiraz, 14% Cab Sauv and 6% Merlot. Kirsch and red plum along with subtle accents of rubber and tar fill the profile. Soft and quite easygoing with low tannins and a short finish.',18,NULL,0,'Synergy Cape Blend',196689),
(263800,217504,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Here\'s a clean, racy white with aromas of green gooseberry, wet grass and lemon rind. Balanced in the mouth with a juicy finish.',15,NULL,0,'Edgebaston',196793),
(263812,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Rustic and sweet, a simple Syrah with flavors of candied berry, black pepper and sassafras.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 292',196620),
(263816,217265,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Tough and gritty, this Zinfandel-based blend has brusque tannins and sweet berry, black pepper and cola flavors. Drink this lusty wine with everyday fare.',11,NULL,0,'Lot 313 Field Blend',196620),
(263865,223287,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Red berries, bramble, sweet spice and a touch of caramel are the core of this wine. Medium weight in the mouth with soft tannins and a short, clean finish.',18,NULL,0,'Adama',197557),
(263867,218046,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/ETDEfhWJSLKjKb8IMK5BgA_pb_x600.png','This is an easy pleaser with typical Chard flavors of ripe red apple and pear accented by toast. There\'s a hint of beeswax in the bouquet, while the nutty oak notes linger through the solid finish.',17,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar',196839),
(263876,223791,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This Chard might be unwooded, but it\'s not short on character. Medium weight with solid ripe apple and pear flavors partnered with interesting accents of honeysuckle and pineapple. Straightforward and simple but very easy to enjoy.',12,NULL,0,'Fantail Unwooded',196839),
(263893,223590,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This wine smells immediately fresh and tart, with scents of green plum, gooseberry, hard nectarine and straw filling the nose. The leanness continues in the mouth with citrus flavors leading thorough to the clean but lingering finish.',14,NULL,0,'Sunbird',196689),
(263913,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'With the 2009 vintage, De Loach is at the top of its Pinot Noir game, and this one, from a chilly vineyard south of Sebastopol, is among its best ever. The crisp acidity, like a squirt of lime, that accompanies the raspberry, cherry and persimmon fruit is bracing. Meanwhile, a mushroomy earthiness gives complex layers that don\'t stop. It should age through the next decade.',45,NULL,0,'Pennacchio Vineyard',196642),
(263933,223582,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Donatus, Latin for Gift from God, is a blend of 77% Chenin Blanc and 23% Semillon. Soft tropical fruit, orange, melon rind and a hint of oak unfold on the nose, while the lively light-weight mouth offers more fresh topical fruit and pineapple acidity. Balanced and easy to drink.',22,NULL,0,'Donatus White',196689),
(263959,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Pinot Noir just doesn\'t get richer than this. It floods the mouth with ripe flavors of raspberries and cherries, with fascinatingly earthy things, like truffles and pine cones. Vibrant acidity and a hint of furry tannins give it a fine structure. This upscale Pinot Noir is drinkable now and should evolve over the next six years.',44,NULL,0,'Durell Vineyard',196642),
(263965,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Two-plus years in the cellar have softened and mellowed this wine, taking off the edges and giving it a nice roundness. It\'s quite impressive, filled with classically varietal cherry, cola and sweet persimmon fruit, while that famous Russian River acidity gives it a boost of tartness. Drink this delicious, rich wine now–2016.',44,NULL,0,'Le Roi',196642),
(263966,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'If only more Zins were this good! De Loach hits this one out of the park, with its fabulous wealth of wild berry, mocha, anise, spice, grilled meat and mushroom flavors. The high alcohol adds a wonderful varietal heat to the peppery finish.',30,NULL,0,'OFS',196642),
(263980,223750,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Tasty and satisfying, especially for the price, with notes of plum flesh, strawberry and blueberry in the nose and mouth. Lean but so drinkable with soft mocha and pepper spice unfolding on the solid finish. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Young Vines',196689),
(263984,218512,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This blend of Grillo and Insolia (30%) offers fresh floral tones of lemon and almond blossoms. There\'s some pulpy, peach-like notes in the mouth and the wine also delivers a playful touch of acidity on the close.',20,NULL,0,'Zagra',196773),
(263987,223835,'other','Shiraz-Pinotage',NULL,'With 58% Shiraz and 42% Pinotage, this is an accessible and enjoyable Cape blend with vibrant notes of black berry, all-fruit preserves, root beer and a soft touch of caramel sauce. Cherry and fleshy plum fill the mouth, and a kiss of vanilla lingers on the close.',8,NULL,0,'Cape Blend',196839),
(263998,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Lusty, powerful, ripe and concentrated, this Zin could also be described by the old Yiddish word, zaftig. The vineyard is in a warm part of the valley, and the grapes show the influence of sun and heat in the jammy, slightly baked quality of the cherries and blackberries. It\'s a really fine example of Russian River Zinfandel.',36,NULL,0,'Butler Vineyard',196642),
(263999,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'You\'ll find plenty of fruit, in the way of ripe mangoes, peaches, green apples and limes, as well as a sweet coating of smoky oak. However, it\'s elevated by brisk acidity and a stony, tangy minerality that must come from the soil of this cool-climate vineyard.',44,NULL,0,'Hawk Hill Vineyard',196642),
(264006,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'De Loach has been showing a fine appreciation of dryness, acidity and minerality in its recent Chardonnays, and this single-vineyard bottling is another example of what makes these wines so drinkably good. It\'s rich in pears, pineapples and green apples, but that zesty stoniness lifts it into true complexity.',44,NULL,0,'Ritchie Vineyard',196642),
(264007,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Opens with crusty, rock-solid aromas of mineral, shoe polish, herb and dense black fruit. This is a thick but smooth-bodied Cabernet with richness and sweet flavors of blackberry, cassis, fine herbes and brown sugar. Mild tannins, excellent structure and length define the finish. Drink now through 2016.',95,NULL,0,'Don Melchor',196852),
(264034,223848,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A soft vanilla bean accent shines through the moderate aromas of red cherry and strawberry. Hints of game and cola unfold on the palate, fighting their way through the medium finish.',17,NULL,0,'Biography',197636),
(264041,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Tastes of perfectly ripened pineapple, pear, lime and peach flavors. On the structural side is fine acidity and a tangy minerality, like a lick of cold steel. Oak is here, notable but perfectly integrated. Give this Chard a little time in the glass to breathe.',35,NULL,0,'Estate Collection',196642),
(264043,217839,'other','Syrah','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/07/gr-Sy-2019-min.png','Opaque in color, with a driving bouquet loaded with graphite, pastry and incredibly ripe black-fruit aromas. Feels rich, but with fine acidity creating superb balance. Tastes like a cascade of blackberry, cassis and chocolate, and then comes a finish of coconut, vanilla and texture. Drink now through 2014; contains 9% Cabernet Sauvignon.',150,NULL,0,'Gravas del Maipo',196852),
(264095,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Picture perfect Sonoma Zin, said to be made from old-vine vineyards. It\'s dry, softly tannic and sweetly ripe in black raspberry, cherry and blackberry fruit, with a rich earthiness and even an umami touch of grilled bacon. Delicious for drinking now.',34,NULL,0,'Forgotten Vines',196642),
(264101,223861,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of 55% Cabernet Sauvignon and 45% Tinta Barocca, this is a light and fruit-forward wine that\'s easy pleasing and very drinkable. Notes of red berries and plum unfold throughout, with a touch of smoke on the finish.',9,NULL,0,'John B. Cabernet Sauvignon-Tinta Barroca',196845),
(264110,220442,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Here\'s a well-priced blend of Insolia and Chardonnay from Sicily that performs perfectly as a light appetizer or finger food wine. There are zesty aromas here of citrus and lime and a dusty mineral note picks up the rear. It\'s light, lean and easy in the mouth.',12,NULL,0,'Calanìca Insolia and Chardonnay',196776),
(264120,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This polished wine offers an array of ripe cherry, pomegranate, persimmon and cola flavors, making it rich and sweet in the mouth. Yet the finish is entirely dry, and you\'ll find plenty of scoury acidity to rip through the greasy richness of lamb or duck.',44,NULL,0,'Maboroshi Vineyard',196642),
(264126,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Earthy and dark to start, with blackberry, cassis, mineral and leather on the nose. Feels rich and slightly syrupy, with herb, sweet berry and brown sugar flavors. Impressive for its power and density; finishes smooth, with mild tannins and caramel flavors. Drink now through 2015.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block Las Terrazas Unfiltered',196852),
(264196,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_x960.png','Dense in color, with earthy, crusty aromas of baked berry, moss, tobacco, cola and cassis. Feels lush, meaty and deep, with tobacco, balsamic flavors, baked blackberry and chocolate. Mellow, lightly herbal and smooth on the finish; hits all the high marks. Drink now.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block 27 Unfiltered',196852),
(264222,221639,'other','Torrontés',NULL,'Tropical and blowsy on the nose. The palate is now chunky and heavy, while the flavors are mustardy and oily, with fruit notes that fall into the melon, peach and orange field. Flat and short on the finish, which indicates that it\'s already fading. Better to wait for the 2010.',11,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(264257,221639,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A bit gaseous on the nose, with cidery apple aromas. The palate is waxy, oily and heavy, with chunky melon and papaya flavors. Meaty and full-bodied for a value-priced Chard, but also heavy and struggling for balance.',12,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(264291,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Rich, tannic and spicy, a classic Sonoma Zinfandel with enough elegance to pair with upscale food. It\'s a little hot in alcohol and overripe, but wears it proudly, celebrating its Zinny personality with a sweet flourish. That\'s characterisic of the vineyard, which is on a warm ridge within this cool appellation.',34,NULL,0,'Von Weidlich Vineyard',196642),
(264424,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/r4o_iL2cSeySKQ1cUXy5ng_pb_x960.png','This is the best of the winery\'s new releases, both for drinking now and for cellaring. Combines power and elegance, with upscale flavors of cherries, currants, cola, rhubarbs, dried herbs and oak, wrapped into devastatingly rich tannins and a perfect touch of acidity. Should age well for 10 years.',100,NULL,0,'Litton Estate Vineyard',196626),
(264458,218035,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.oenoforos.com.cy/template/main/GetImage.php?imgpath=/stk/image/37.png&width=160&height=200','Light, elegant and lithe on the nose, with a touch of stemminess to the core plum and cherry aromas. Feels just right, with a feminine touch and snap to the mouthfeel. Flavors of red plum, raspberry, herbs, tomato and dried spice lead to a fresh, focused finish. Top level for under $15.',14,NULL,0,'Limited Selection',196713),
(264484,218228,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/JJ3JvJUYTmiyIC4CnukYbQ_pb_x960.png','Rubbery and gassy at first, with a ton of barrel power that pushes charred aromas onto the nose. Feels correct and well-balanced, with honest Pinot flavors of red fruits, herbs and baked earth. Tastes and feels harmonious.',28,NULL,0,'Wild Ferment',196886),
(264524,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Even by De Loach\'s standards of enormously ripe Zinfandels, this one stands out. It\'s a hydrogen bomb of a wine, fantastically rich in berries and fruits that have a slightly dried quality to them. The tannins are thick, and the alcohol seems higher and hotter than the stated 14.5% by volume.',34,NULL,0,'Riebli Valley Vineyard',196642),
(264525,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Paxis is a warm, earthy wine, packed with ripe, soft and forward fruit. It does have a structure that could allow the wine to age, but there is no need as its fruitiness makes it ready to drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Paxis',196807),
(264578,218035,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/mL8dp4asRmeoczeYID6uBQ_pb_x960.png','Nice on the nose, with tropical aromas, ocean-based saline and mild green-fruit notes. Feels crisp and cleansing, with tangy flavors of lemon, green apple and underripe pineapple. Lime and green flavors of tarragon and grass drive the finish.',14,NULL,0,'Limited Selection',196713),
(264583,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8d6u8XTtQEC8ClBYm5J2nw_pb_x960.png','Shows the exotic power of the vineyard, with wild cherry, raspberry, cola and spice flavors, and the crisp acidity of the far Sonoma Coast. But not one you want to drink now. It\'s tight, dry, minerally, aloof. Needs time. Definitely a wine to cellar until at least 2014.',56,NULL,0,'Peay Vineyard',196626),
(264610,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This Pinot Noir may become more rich and charming in coming years, but right now it\'s fresh, tart and jammy in raspberries and cherries. It\'s also a bit heavy, almost as if a bit of Grenache found its way into the blend.',45,NULL,0,'Estate Collection',196642),
(264615,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/SGh8MxSiRqeeoxfk-pAKPw_pb_x600.png','Intense and black up front, with coconut, tobacco and blackberry aromas. Feels round and plump, with dark, toasty flavors of mildly herbal berry and cassis. Finishes warm, spicy, a little heavy and with tannic grip. A fun wine that\'s big boned and concentrated.',22,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(264619,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This wine heads the range of good value wines under the Monte Alentejano name. It has some weight and a tangy, structured character, and has not lost its black-plum flavors. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano Reserva',196807),
(264742,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_x960.png','Big, stout and solid, with a smoky, pure-fruit nose that\'s very attractive. Lush and full in the mouth, with pure, deep, intoxicating flavors of blackberrry, black currant and Mediterranean black olive. Solid throughout and holds its form across the finish. Ripe, smooth and delicious. Drink now thru 2012.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block 27',196852),
(264787,217839,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Muscled up and dark, with robust blackberry, tar, spice and mocha aromas. The palate is big and dense but raring to run, with smashing black cherry, berry and black plum lushness. Turns more oaky on the finish, with coconut and mocha. Impressive for New World Syrah. Drink now through 2013.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block 34',196852),
(264848,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Y0zjP7gOSJi9-Q25WGXXRw_pb_x960.png','Chunky black-fruit aromas come with strong notes of coconut, chocolate and cedar. Feels fresh, zesty and voluminous, with sweet oak, coconut, mocha and herbal flavors to go with standard berry and cassis. Long and mildly herbal tasting on the finish.',21,NULL,0,'Single Vineyard',196886),
(264906,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Smoky and smooth up front, with bacon, rubber and pure black-fruit aromas. The palate is equally pure and deep, with lush blackberry, cassis, tannins and proper balance. Spicy and tasting of licorice on the finish, with an overall appeal that justifies its price. Excellent Chilean Cabernet that can compete with Napa and elsewhere. Drink now through 2015.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block: Las Terrazas',196852),
(264939,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A powerful wine that shows berry fruits, with dark tannins and layers of acidity. It is structured while being fruity and juicy; a great pasta wine that is ready to drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Vega',196807),
(264970,218426,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5OmkO9TiRX2mhWO1EYVjGg_pb_x600.png','You\'ll be hard pressed to find a better wine at this price. A blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Zinfandel, sourced only from coastal counties, it\'s totally dry, full bodied, firm in tannins and drinkable now for its wealth of blackberry, currant, black cherry and oak flavors. Production was 52,000 cases.',14,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve Summation',196751),
(264980,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/eNo4J9lWTh-Fjrp2BnVLhg_pb_x960.png','Pungent but green up front, with a mix of citric and vegetal aromas that includes lime, peas and canned beans. Feels good and bright, with zesty acidity propelling passion fruit, grapefruit and bell pepper flavors. Finishes both green and crisp, with a blend of tropical and cool-climate character.',12,NULL,0,'Estate Reserva',196886),
(264981,219884,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/B9sFzb2iT5ePxEZT_K5OTw_pb_600x600.png','Solid and chunky, a wine that fills the mouth with its attractive red fruits, structured tannins and a general juicy feel. A fine barbecue wine.',8,NULL,0,'Bigode',196807),
(265105,217999,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/lHkdxpcYS9iq53xMwKUEhQ_pb_x960.png','Made from Aglianico grapes, this fresh rosé is a garnet-pink color, with savory aromas of forest floor, bramble, wild berry and white almond. A touch of sassy spice defines the finish.',15,NULL,0,'Ros\'Aura',196908),
(265137,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HVXcz1tWSUWWx-aikOMgaw_pb_x960.png','Gets going with tropical aromas and notes of fresh apple. Feels smooth but not that substantial, with pithy flavors of white fruits and sweet citrus. Similar on the finish.',12,NULL,0,'Estate Reserva',196886),
(265154,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/nL_US-ZVTl-txZ5J1tJQpw_pb_x960.png','Stands out for its fruit quality, balance and structure. The nose is strong and piercing, with charred notes, black-fruit aromas and depth. Ripe and clean in the mouth, with elevated blackberry flavors and a chewy, meaty mouthfeel. Toasty and tasting of black licorice on the finish. A serious, well-made Chilean Cab to drink now through 2012.',22,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(265192,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8Op8t5wYThy9LpTSnsMiyw_pb_x600.png','Leafy and herbal on the nose, with light berry aromas, tomato and basil. Shows pretty good body and balance despite some stickiness, with herb, red bell pepper, spice and berry flavors. A little oaky on the finish.',12,NULL,0,'Estate Reserva',196886),
(265203,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2022/08/ws-rochioli-Bottleshot/7e5b48bf7e0629bbe21b9811be7d8d35.png','Among the heavier, softer and more extracted of the winery\'s fall offerings. It shows the ripeness and full-bodied richness of the block, with powerful cherry, pomegranate, cola and spice flavors, and is very dry and classically proportioned. But it\'s not the greatest Riverblock ever. Drink now–2015.',78,NULL,0,'Rochioli Riverblock',196626),
(265223,221639,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Neutral up front except for sweet cherry and plum aromas. Feels full and grabby, with biting tannins pushing dark, baked flavors of earthy black fruits and chocolate. Grabby and resiny on the oaky but short finish. Feels hard but tastes good.',12,NULL,0,'Urban Maule',196852),
(265233,221639,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Reasonably accurate on the nose for Leyda Sauvignon Blanc, but also a little pickled smelling. Feels chunky and a little flat, with mild flavors of green apple and citrus. Finishes somewhat bitter, like walnut or almond skins, with a green-banana flavor.',18,NULL,0,'Centauri',196852),
(265279,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A big-hearted wine, despite its modest alcohol. This character comes from the bold fruitiness—blackberry and sweet plum flavors—underpinned with acidity and a light touch of tannins. Ready to drink.',8,NULL,0,'Paxis Tinto',196807),
(265314,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Storks have traditionally nested in the tall chimnies of DFJ\'s winery, and this wine celebrates that. Soft, ripe and easily fruity, it has a light tannic touch, followed by some bright acidity and red-berry flavors. Screwcap.',8,NULL,0,'Storks Landing Tinto',196807),
(265323,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A blend of Chardonnay and Fernão Pires, this is light, fruity and ready to drink. Its citrus and white-fruit flavors are soft, open and approachable. Screwcap.',8,NULL,0,'Storks Landing Branco',196807),
(265380,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/74-hTHC1Tf6L28erqJE-FQ_pb_600x600.png','This complicated, soft Pinot Noir is very rich in cherry, red currant, cola, licorice and spice flavors, but it\'s a little heavy. It shows the Williams-Selyem fingerprint of impeccable growing and winemaking technique, but it\'s hard to tell where it\'s going.',56,NULL,0,'Flax Vineyard',196626),
(265383,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MrWbDNNxQRmlAb20rtfBww_pb_x600.png','The bouquet blends tropical aromas with popcorn, and the palate is toasty as well, but not cloying or thick. Flavors of green banana, orange, melon and pineapple are spicy and zesty, and there\'s pineapple and woodspice to the finish. A natural-yeast Chard with balance and zest to go along with tropical sweetness.',21,NULL,0,'Wild Ferment',196886),
(265470,218035,'other','Rosé','https://www.vinello.de/media/image/4a/a6/g0/montes-cherub-syrah.png','This rating is probably as much a reflection of tasting the wine too late in its evolution as anything else. At this mature state, the wine is heavy and syrupy, with stalky, almost bitter red-fruit flavors. Finishes with matchstick and grassy flavors. Wait for the 2011.',20,NULL,0,'Cherub Rosé of Syrah',196713),
(265684,218569,'other','Port','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/nAG5HiUXQbmNo0Qduf66Zg_pb_x960.png','High alcohol of 20% makes this dessert wine hot in the mouth. That\'s the main impression, because the sweetness and fruit aren\'t quite strong enough to balance the heat. Nonetheless it\'s pretty sweet, with blackberry jam and chocolate flavors.',40,NULL,0,'Mistral Vineyard',196626),
(265831,218569,'other','Zinfandel','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/490x/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h79/h58/11163652947998.png','This is a very rich Zinfandel that veers toward the soft, high alcohol end of the spectrum. It\'s ripe in berry and cherry flavors that have an edge of currants and raisins, but the finish is dry. Drink now.',60,NULL,0,'Forchini Vineyard',196626),
(265977,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Rzvg7SXFTsaUMPUDXKyf9g_pb_600x600.png','Aromas of crusty blackberry are dark and herbal, while the palate is zesty and fresh, with tight acidity supporting flavors of cassis, black cherry, cola nut and pepper. Toasty, herbal and licorice-like on the finish. A good yet common wine.',12,NULL,0,'Reseve Barrel Select',196857),
(266048,217780,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/uNJ_o9_-SNGSJzjfYf4qnA_pb_x600.png','Saturated purple in color and grapy on the nose. The palate is mouthfilling but carries semisharp acidity, and the flavors run in the direction of standard black fruit. Notes of mocha and coconut soften the finish, and overall this is a good but rather generic wine.',12,NULL,0,'Reserve Barrel Select',196857),
(266063,221639,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A little soft and showing warmer-climate aromas of passionfruit and tropical citrus. The palate is starting to fade just a bit, but it\'s still pumping out grapefruit, lime and green apple. Perfectly fine to drink now or wait for the 2010 version.',11,NULL,0,'Urban Maule',196852),
(266092,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/NButV-5sS4ev2J5tUKjgWg_pb_x960.png','Quiet on the bouquet except for a dusting of oak and banana. The palate is heavy and wide, if a bit flabby, and the flavors of melon and mango run sweet, much like fruit punch. Soft and sweet on the finish as well, and overall it\'s good but generic. Not many Chards in the price range will fare better.',8,NULL,0,'Xplorador',196852),
(266187,224337,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'The 2007 vintage was generally a great one for Bordeaux-style reds in Stellenbosch, and the Els Signature definitely demonstrates it. Sure, it\'s ripe and sexy with a lot of sweet oak characteristics like cocoa powder and smoky wood, but it\'s got the ripe fruit core of black plum and dark forest berries to back it up. Spicy layers of leather, cigar box and black tea leaves add complexity to the palate, while chewy tannins provide a firm structure. A bit young now, so try after 2015.',95,NULL,0,'Signature',196689),
(266255,218426,'other','Zinfandel','https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQjgBuiM07F0LBZx3jAW05cwK4IDbXdEzwL9FAdjIdZt2fkWtkIjPlWu7K18ZKN2u3A-w&usqp=CAU','An okay wine that\'s light in color and aromatics, traceable in part to its cooler-climate heritage (95% of the grapes were grown in Mendocino, the rest in Sonoma, Monterey and Santa Barbara), which does give it some subtly pleasing red fruit and spice notes. But 2008 was also for much of Mendocino a vintage from hell and this wine may in truth be reflecting that year\'s challenges.',16,NULL,0,'Jackson Estates Grown Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(266269,224349,'other','Semillon-Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This beautiful Semillon-dominant blend that shows great finesse, depth and power. Rich and opulent in every way, notes of baked red apple, lemon verbena, honey-drizzled peach and sweet orange oil flood the nose and mouth, while additional flavors of hazelnut cream, fig bread and soft sweet spice carry into the long finish. Round, but with enough acidic lift to keep it from being flabby. Drink now–2015.',30,NULL,0,'Henrietta',196839),
(266273,224352,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'One of the best vintages of Rubicon to date, and for the price it\'s a fantastic value that\'s great for building up your cellar. Right now, the wine is still young and tight, with firm, gripping tannins that need some time to mellow. Fortunately, there\'s a great concentrated black-fruit core and enough acidity alongside the tannins to support long-term aging. Spicy and earthy, with accents of black tea, cedar and crushed violets. Try after 2016.',31,NULL,0,'Rubicon',196689),
(266290,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HVXcz1tWSUWWx-aikOMgaw_pb_x600.png','Smells clipped, tough and oily, with a hardness to the bouquet. The palate is fleshy and wet, with reasonably fresh melon and papaya flavors. Finishes pithy and slightly bitter, and overall it\'s barely a good wine on its best day.',12,NULL,0,'Estate',196886),
(266397,222668,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'A stunning Pinotage that shows great varietal character in its aromas and flavors of black cherry and currant infused with spicy notes of biltong, bark, clay, cinnamon and soft tar. The wine is firmly structured, with gripping tannins and medium acidity, striking a balance between the astringency of the tannins and freshness of the fruit. Nuances of baking spice and fudge linger on the close. Tight now; try after 2015.',30,NULL,0,'Primo',197456),
(266420,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','A superb wine, the tannins carrying along the dense structure with ease and grace. The purity of the ripe berry fruit is very marked, with acidity giving freshness to the sweet wine. The whole ensemble is developing well, but will need many years\' aging.',115,NULL,0,'Domaine du Clos Frantin Aux Malconsorts Premier Cru',196775),
(266431,224396,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This stunning Bordeaux-style blend opens with ripe aromas of black fruits like cherry, currant and plum, laced with a serious licorice and spice streak that shows staying power. The seductive mouthfeel boasts a slightly creamy texture with mouthfilling tannins. The palate is loaded with mulled boysenberry. Hints of tobacco, mocha and sweet spice all linger on the long close.',38,NULL,0,'Five',197609),
(266433,217719,'other','Chenin Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/47OJFOm5R6C6youjKGWZGw_pb_x960.png','A ripe and forward style with upfront notes of pineapple, softly-grilled peach, juicy melon and a touch of spice. The mouthfeel is round and rich, but with enough acidic cut to keep the palate fresh and lively through the long finish. Flavors of sweet orange citrus and ripe green fig linger endlessly.',28,NULL,0,'Bowed Head',196845),
(266443,223405,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Named after five stone pine trees that stand over the vineyards, this small-production Chard is lush and toasty, offering great weight and richness followed by a long, nutty finish. Notes of red apple skin and peach are accented by hints of white clover and honeysuckle that unfold with time in the glass. Brisk lime-flavored acidity lifts the mouth and provides freshness to the palate.',38,NULL,0,'Five Soldiers',196689),
(266473,222826,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Named for the winemaker\'s youngest daughter, this ripe and sweet selection boasts intense oak-driven aromas of butter and creamy vanilla that mingle well with the honeydew, pear and peach notes. Thankfully, there\'s good cut to the round mouthfeel, as zesty orange-flavored acidity keeps the finish fresh and long. Drink now–2014.',33,NULL,0,'Cuvée Anaïs',196839),
(266525,224396,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A great value, this Merlot-dominant blend, with splashes of Cab Sauv and Cab Franc exudes ripe aromas and flavors of rich dark fruit and berries jazzed up with layers of cigar tobacco, leather, savory herbs and tree bark. Concentrated and mouthfilling, with a velvety texture, it\'s a well-balanced wine with fine, but persistent tannins and a lengthy finish.',24,NULL,0,'Three',197609),
(266535,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/sj8IPIZnQV-hGwkfXQAIag_pb_x960.png','As so often results from this vineyard, this is a lovely wine, the fruit ripe and showing considerable sweetness as well as richness. The structure is soft, open and elegant, surrounding the core of sweet tannins. Not for long-term aging, but worth waiting 4–5 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Amoureuses Premier Cru',196775),
(266548,219700,'other','Malvasia','https://italianwineselection.com/images/detailed/14/Capofaro_2019-IWS-Sorrento.png','Tenuta Capofaro\'s beauty is captured in this precious wine, in its golden color and bright aromas of peach, honey and white almond. The creamy finish is sweet and delicious.',31,NULL,0,'Tenuta Capofaro',196776),
(266553,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Firm and solid, this is a wine marked by blackberries, solid and dense tannins. The concentration will bring all the elements together to give an important wine, while never losing the 2008 acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Porrets St.-Georges Premier Cru',197241),
(266556,221768,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A complex blend of 75% Shiraz, 10% Cinsault, 8% Cab Sauv, 6% Gren and 1% each of Carignan and Mourvèdre, this is a concentrated and flavorful selection that\'s brimming with raspberry sauce and dark berry fruit aromas and flavors. Framed by black tea, sweet spice and vanilla bean accents, the mouth is firmly structured with medium tannins and acidity, ending on a soft, roasty note.',17,NULL,0,'Secateurs',197368),
(266564,223391,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Brims with dark fruit notes of mulled boysenberry, cassis and black cherry, all streaked with spicy accents of menthol and black tea leaves. The mouthfeel is slightly creamy, but framed by medium tannins. Notes of licorice stick, espresso and roasted cocoa nibs linger through the long close. Drink now–2014.',22,NULL,0,'Faithful Hound',196839),
(266599,222679,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Attractively ripe aromas of melon and softly baked apples lead the nose, with a touch of sweet smokiness, almost like cured bacon, following close behind. Medium weight with balanced, lifting acidity and a spice-infused clementine rind finish.',21,NULL,0,'Robusto',197462),
(266620,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'From the most famous slope in Morgon, this is a powerful wine, its tannins still working their way into the fruit. Black cherries, and sweet plums are dominated by a firm, concentrated structure. Give this wine another year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Côte de Py',197404),
(266621,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Structured and concentrated, it has a silky richness that is very Volnay, while at the same time giving the bright fruits of the year. The final tastes are smoke and crisp acidity.',85,NULL,0,'Ancienne Cuvée Carnot Caillerets Premier Cru',197241),
(266637,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Shows softness, perhaps missing a big structure. To compensate there is a great red fruit element that dominates the tannins. Juicy and fruity, layered acidity to finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Rugiens Premier Cru',197241),
(266668,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'As rich as it is tannic, this is powerful and concentrated. It shows the rich 2009 fruit at its best, full of sweet berries, deliciously ripe. Enjoyable, while it is also serious.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de la Chaponne',197404),
(266675,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'For sheer hedonism, this is one of the best Cabs on the market. This classic Napa Cab is dry, complex and a joy to drink now, framed by elegant tannins. A spectacular bargain. Production was 4,000 cases.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 157',196620),
(266704,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'One of Duboeuf\'s 2009 successes, this is powerful, excellently balanced between solid tannins and fresh fruit. The black cherry flavors revolve around a dry core, concentrated and complex, with a full and ageworthy aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Prestige',197404),
(266711,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/oLcpKPK1T_SVEiDc01h62Q_pb_x960.png','Opulence and a definite streak of sold tannins combine to give a wine that has intensity, rich fruit and sweetness plus a licorice layer. The wine offers bright acidity as well over pure strawberry fruit flavors.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Chabiots Premier Cru',196775),
(266714,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Another of Cameron Hughes\' terrific Cabernets at a good price. This wine will easily stand beside Cabs far more expensive, with its dry, crisply complex flavors of blackberries, cherries, currants, anise, mocha and oak.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 172',196620),
(266715,218228,'other','Syrah','https://prikeshop.ee/app/uploads/imported-images/errazuriz-syrah-la-cumbre-2018-637d7e86626b9.png','A smooth, modern and rich version of Chilean Syrah that\'s bringing it. The nose is full of mineral, graphite, coconut and heavenly black fruit, while the palate is bright, pure and delicious as it leans toward black-currant liqueur, blackberry and boysenberry. Fruity to the max, with a meaty finish and plenty of body. Drink now through 2013.',120,NULL,0,'La Cumbre',196886),
(266727,222420,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of equal parts Syrah and Mourvèdre wiith 8% Tannat, The Pepper Pot offers concentrated aromas and flavors of dark forest berries and fleshy black plums. A hint of leather and game unfolds on the finish, while medium acidity keeps the flavors fresh on the palate.',15,NULL,0,'The Pepper Pot',196689),
(266733,222679,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This Chenin seems to have an older soul than its peers, with mature notes of honeyed almond and sweet spice that infiltrate the Anjou pear and hard peach flavors. Citrus pith adds a touch of bitterness to the otherwise toasty, sweet spice-infused finish.',19,NULL,0,'De Tradisie',197462),
(266742,222367,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Made with overripe, concentrated grapes, Assoluto is a crisp and luminous dessert wine. It releases very feminine aromas of honey, yellow rose, vanilla cream and loads of stone fruit. There\'s glycerine, but also acidity to maintain that ideal balance between thickness and freshness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Assoluto',197281),
(266752,219700,'other','Malvasia','https://italianwineselection.com/images/detailed/14/Capofaro_2019-IWS-Sorrento.png','This beautiful Malvasia-based wine shows the beauty and good cheer of the island of Salina off the northern coast of Sicily. The wine is luminous and light but it also shows enormous purity of its honey, peach and apricot aromas. Pair it with foie gras or aged cheese.',NULL,NULL,0,'Tenuta Capofaro 500ml',196776),
(266755,222331,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'With 4,300 bottles produced and only 110 cases imported, this is a gorgeous small production Cab that should be grabbed up when you find it. It\'s all dark fruit and sweet spice with notes of black currant, fig, plum, leather and cigar box. With firm tannins and a medium-full weight, this is a big but balanced wine that\'s easy to enjoy now or can be cellared for a couple of years.',42,NULL,0,'Three Pines',196689),
(266801,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Rich as well as tannic, this is concentrated, with dense fruits and sweet acidity. Its structure offers good aging as well as pleasurable fruit now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château du Grand Pré',197404),
(266802,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A big, bold and fruity wine that is full of ripe berry fruits, rich and generous. This is Beaujolais at its most exuberant, a celebration of delicious fruit. It could age, but is ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine des Rosiers',197404),
(266824,224337,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A kitchen-sink blend of 60% Shiraz, 20% Cab Sauv, 7% Grenache, 6% Mourvèdre, 4% Cinsault and 3% Viognier. Aromas of crushed violet petals are pitted against the intense mulled-raspberry and black-fruit core. Drinkable now, with approachable tannins and a dusty, cocoa-sprinkled finish, but could age until 2014.',20,NULL,0,'Big Easy',196689),
(266828,217265,'other','Merlot',NULL,'This is an unbelievable price for a Napa Merlot of this quality. The wine is softly tannic, dry and rich, with crisp acidity balancing complex flavors of cherries, currants, herbs, violets and cedar. Taste this against Merlots costing five times as much, and it will acquit itself well.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 175',196620),
(266838,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A solidly tannic wine that powers with bitter chocolate, plum skin and black berry flavors. Very concentrated, it has the structure and acidity to offer aging potential for 2–3 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Carquelins',197404),
(266841,224486,'other','Merlot',NULL,'This is a stellar and immensely attractive Merlot that\'s sure to impress any true wine lover. Fig, black plum flesh, sweet cola glaze and black raspberry sauce dominate, with accents of leathery spice and cigar tobacco adding depth and complexity. It\'s round and full in the mouth with dainty fine grain tannins and a long finish. This can easily be drunk now or cellared for another 2–5 years.',75,NULL,0,'Mount Bullet',197462),
(266849,219700,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A bit less obvious and more elegant than the 2007 vintage, this edition of Diamante (a Passito dessert wine from one of Sicily\'s best producers) shows piquant aromas of lemon zest, candied fruit, dried apricot, honey and butterscotch. The wine slides over the palate with crisp, clean determination a thick creaminess.',30,NULL,0,'Diamante 500ml',196776),
(266857,224491,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Tart and fresh, with lovely aromas of grass, green plum and asparagus. Glimmers of stony minerality flash on the palate, with lime pith and plum skin flavors driving through to the mouthwatering finish. Brisk and slightly pricky texture.',16,NULL,0,'Private Cellar Series',197456),
(266878,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Dominated by its dry tannins, this is a tight black currant and dark plum skin-flavored wine, surrounded by a firm core of tannins, a firm and dark-hued wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos des Garands',197404),
(266879,217999,'other','Aglianico',NULL,'DUBL is probably the first metodo classico sparkling wine available in the U.S. that is made in Campania. That\'s just one reason to find this wine so exciting. Other reasons include its clean bouquet of peach, sweet berry, white cherry and almond paste.',55,NULL,0,'DUBL Brut Rosato Metodo Classico',196908),
(266885,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'The wine is dry, soft, elegant and lovely, with full-bodied black cherry, currant, red licorice and cola flavors. It certainly is one of the best Syrahs you can buy at this price.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 177',196620),
(266887,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'There is great structure here, with dusty tannins percolating through the rich wine. It has power, concentration and density, with cocoa and cherry flavors well integrated. Think about aging for 1–2 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sélection',197404),
(266907,224505,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot-Shiraz',NULL,'This wine needs a little bit of time to fully integrate, but it has an attractive crushed-velvet texture with medium tannins, and a flavorful palate. Forward fruit flavors of berry preserves and black plum abound, and a black pepper accent remains on the medium-length finish.',12,NULL,0,'Made With Organically Grown Grapes',196839),
(266910,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A solid, dense wine, packed with tannins and with a dry core. The soft fruit has flavors of strawberry, hinting at richness to come. At this early stage, tannins and acidity are still forming. Hold for five years.',140,NULL,0,'Les Beaumonts Premier Cru',197254),
(266926,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A textured, structured wine, solid and packed with tannins. It is full of concentrated black currant and prune flavors, layered with dark coffee. It is worth aging for at least 1–2 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Montchavy',197404),
(266927,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'An elegant wine, its berry fruits fitting well into a structure that balances tannins and soft acidity. It has style, the fruit full of sweet black berry juice and a lift of acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Paradis',197404),
(266964,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','The tannins here are fine, dusty almost, giving the wine a softer core than is normal for this vineyard. Around the tannins, the jammy blackberry fruits give a sweet side to the flavors. Rich and soft.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Porrets Saint-Georges Premier Cru',196775),
(266965,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Tannic and mineral, this is intensely structured. With its firm tannins and dark plum flavors, it is on the dry side, needing 2–3 years to show its best. This is Beaujolais for aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Belles Grives',197404),
(266966,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Firm and structured, this is serious Beaujolais. The ripe cherry and plum flavors are surrounded by dry, dark tannins that promise some aging. Hints of smoky minerality go well with the final juicy acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de la Seigneurie',197404),
(266967,222477,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'You should know what you\'re getting yourself into here, as the name definitely doesn\'t lie. So minty and herbaceous it\'s almost hard to believe, and it all mingles with notes of crushed violets and black currant leaf as well as a solid fruit core of cassis and black plum skins. It\'s firm and tight in the mouth but approachable after a little breathing time.',45,NULL,0,'The Mint',196839),
(267003,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Full and rich, this is a ripe, generous wine that offers great swathes of black berry fruit. It is well structured, the tannins folding into the ripe fruits, although never losing sight of delicious jelly acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château de Prieuré',197404),
(267004,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A complex and intense single-vineyard wine, it has ripe berry fruits with dark tannins. Only at the end is the juicy character of the wine on show.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine des Versauds',197404),
(267006,223676,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The nose of this Cab is very inviting with heady aromas of black cherry, cassis and blueberry infused with leather and woody spice. More of the same unfolds on the palate with cedar notes supporting the dark fruit. The mouthfeel is round and full but structured with tightly woven tannins carrying through the long finish.',22,NULL,0,'Unfiltered',196839),
(267015,223334,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'It takes some time for this wine to open up in the glass, but when it does you\'re greeted with black cherry and cassis aromas laced with hints of cigar box. Structured with mouth-coating tannins and medium acidity, a leathery texture carries through the close.',12,NULL,0,'Petit',196839),
(267017,222635,'other','Aligoté',NULL,'From one of the Leflaive family vineyards close to Puligny-Montrachet, this is as rich as Aligoté can get. Even so, the texture is crisp, with fresh kiwi and herbs, finishing with intense acidity.',17,NULL,0,'Aligoté du Domaine',197408),
(267054,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The tannins do have some firm character, but the fruit is more dominant, fresh and up-front. There is an attractive red-berry character, offering ripe fruits over a soft texture.',75,NULL,0,'Les Epenots Premier Cru',197254),
(267076,218035,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/mL8dp4asRmeoczeYID6uBQ_pb_x960.png','Year after year this ranks as one of Chile\'s most complex and satisfying SBs. The nose is like an ocean breeze mixed with saline, citrus and fresh greens. The palate blends zestiness with fleshy weight, and the flavors suggest lime, green apple and grapefruit. Clean and long on the finish; drink now before it fades.',15,NULL,0,'Limited Selection Leyda Vineyard',196713),
(267084,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Lean and tannic, this is a tough wine, its tannins dominating the underlying juicy fruit. It has power, with a firm and dry texture. Give it 2–3 years to develop.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Jean Descombes',197404),
(267115,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This is dry Beaujolais, boasting as much structure as fruit. The tannins are prominent, underpinning the spicy black berry fruits. The effect is rich, a wine that will age well over 2–3 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château des Capitans',197404),
(267116,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Ripe and juicy, this is an immediately appealing wine, full of forward fruit that is rich and sweet. Dark cherry lies over cranberry sharpness. The wine flows easily from the glass, an example of the sunny side of Beaujolais.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Moulin-à-Vent',197404),
(267121,223641,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This is a rich and concentrated wine with welcoming aromas of black fruits, bacon, African violets and soft black pepper. The mouth is as intense as one would anticipate with more concentrated dark plum and currant flavors and accents of coconut on the long finish. The tannins are gripping and the structure firm; try with hearty red meat dishes for a superb pairing.',20,NULL,0,'Private Collection',197456),
(267132,222330,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Named after the gravel soils in which the vines are planted (and the old quarry site), this Cab is well balanced and surprisingly approachable now with flavors of blackberry, black currant leaf, cola, sandalwood and a kiss of menthol on the finish. It\'s soft, silky tannins linger through the long finish.',45,NULL,0,'Gravel Quarry',197445),
(267145,222933,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Jammy black fruit and berry notes fill the nose and mouth, while a hint of bramble and milk chocolate add depth and interest. Medium weight, with dusty but structured tannins, and a fudgy finish.',20,NULL,0,'The Glass Collection',197420),
(267163,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Rich, fruity wine that is full of black plum juice and soft tannins. Milk chocolate sweetness adds to the generous nature of this juicy wine. Drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Michelons',197404),
(267164,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'The year 2009 seems to have been a tannic one in Fleurie, producing wines that will benefit from some aging. This fits that bill well, a mineral and austere black fruit flavored wine, with a smoky aftertaste to go with tight acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'La Madone',197404),
(267185,224555,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Mocha notes are upfront on the nose, with supporting fruit elements of raspberry and cherry flesh. Medium weight with a touch of bitter fruit-skin flavors in the mouth, and a short but clean finish. Easy and straightforward; drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Frontier',196839),
(267207,217839,'other','Merlot','https://www.goodygoody.com/ccstore/v1/images/?source=/file/v5162279927065589054/products/21224.Concha-Y-Toro-Xplorador-Merlot_750ML.png&height=475&width=475','Dark and full-fruited, with coffee, cumin and big berry fruit aromas. This is a pleasant surprise and a great value; the palate is bright and clean, with black-fruit flavors and cola galore. Creamy, mildly toasty and rich on the finish; overall it excels at its price point.',8,NULL,0,'Xplorador',196852),
(267223,224517,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This blend of 67% Viognier, 19% Chenin Blanc and 14% Grenache Blanc is crisp and tasty, with forward aromas of pear, hard peach, yellow florals and a touch of oak-driven spice. Roundly structured, with a lush texture and a nice, clean herbal characteristic to the close. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'The Wolftrap Viognier-Chenin Blanc-Grenache Blanc',197456),
(267227,224569,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A funky edge frames this wine, both on the nose and in the mouth, and adds character to the otherwise straightforward blackberry, boysenberry and fig-preserve core. Cured meat and sweet spice grace the palate and persist through the medium-length close. The blend is 52% Pinotage and 48% Shiraz.',14,NULL,0,'Pinotage-Shiraz',196839),
(267228,223791,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Solid and straightforward, this refreshing and vibrant Sauv Blanc is light and approachable, with aromas and flavors of lemon, sweet grass and pineapple core throughout. A crowd-pleasing selection for entertaining.',19,NULL,0,'Fantail',196839),
(267245,218426,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjvr-sauv-blanc-nv.png?itok=qDq2eNCx','This is a good Sauvignon Blanc whose touch of oak adds smoky cream and vanilla. The underlying wine shows Lake County balance, with citrus, lemongrass, peach and green apple flavors accented by crisp acidity, and finished with honey.',11,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(267246,223593,'other','Shiraz-Mourvèdre',NULL,'Herbaceous aromas are balanced against a strong core of black fruit and berries. A touch of anise and roasted espresso beans add intrigue to the bouquet, while accents of licorice sticks, clove and whole black peppercorns carry the finish. A very well balanced wine with solid weight and appropriate medium grain tannins.',16,NULL,0,'Art House',197456),
(267265,224517,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'Bright red mixed berries are infused with a mocha streak, filling the medium weight, but juicy palate. Straightforward and enjoyable with clean fruit flavors and a short but softly spiced finish.',11,NULL,0,'The Wolftrap Syrah-Mourvèdre-Viognier',197456),
(267295,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'It\'s a fine wine, full-bodied and dry, with spicy flavors of currants, teriyaki beef, black pepper and cola, with a bracing minerality that grounds the richness. Could be more concentrated, but it\'s a great value.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 156',196620),
(267297,217504,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Here\'s a fresh and attractive unoaked Chardonnay with vibrant flavors of pear, sweet clementine, yellow florals and crunchy peach. There\'s an impression of effervescence from the forward acidity, and the finish is long but remarkably crisp.',21,NULL,0,'Sans Barrique',196793),
(267311,218042,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Skin-driven red fruit characteristics abound on the nose, alongside soft vanilla and purple floral accents. Cherry and mulberry flavors dominate in the lightly-structured mouth, and the wine closes with a mouthwatering freshness.',10,NULL,0,'Shiraz-Mourvèdre-Viognier',196845),
(267334,224597,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Pop the cork and let it breathe for an hour before drinking, as this wine needs some time to open up and show it\'s true colors. Cassis, black pepper, mocha, balsamic reduction and a hint of tar unfold in the bouquet. The medium acidity and tight tannins take firm hold of your palate and linger through the finish.',15,NULL,0,'Organic',197368),
(267335,217780,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/bnsyktZkRIyPgSIWwAW0rA_pb_x600.png','Stocky, meaty and full on the nose, and despite a hint of leafy, herbal green it\'s a more than solid offering. Black cherry and herbal flavors are generous, while the finish is full and competent. Shows good overall quality and solidity compared to prior vintages.',10,NULL,0,'Selected Terroir',196857),
(267344,222911,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'With 12 months spent in French oak, this wine offers rounded notes of boysenberry and cassis framed by hints of purple florals and sweet spice. There\'s a lively lift to the fruit in the mouth, driving the palate to a clean and juicy finish. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Roodewyn',196845),
(267353,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Some producer in Carneros didn\'t want the wine that went into this negociant\'s ‘07 Syrah, to judge by its quality. Lucky for Cameron Hughes. It\'s a fine wine, full-bodied and dry, with spicy flavors of currants, teriaki beef, black pepper and cola, with a bracing minerality that grounds the richness. Could be more concentrated, but it\'s a very great value.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 178',196620),
(267360,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3OMisWgFQzOohbmCKM8k8g_pb_x960.png','A good Sauvignon Blanc but not up to the standards set by previous vintages of Terrunyo. The nose is less exciting and pungent than it has been, with grassy, generic citrus aromas. The flavors are slightly green and vegetal, with asparagus mixing with green apple and melon. And it\'s more soft-sided than memory suggests it should be. Drink now.',25,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Vineyard Selection Block 28',196852),
(267384,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'New oak accounts for only 30% of the barrel regimen, but it dominates this Chardonnay, with buttered toast, vanilla and caramel flavors. Fortunately there\'s also strong pineapple, Asian pear and apricot fruit, but the oak is too powerful.',30,NULL,0,'OFS',196642),
(267393,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Syrah',NULL,'This soft, elegant wine is slightly herbaceous, with green olive and sage flavors alongside the riper blackberries. It\'s totally dry, and the tannins are very finely ground, giving it a pliant, gentle mouthfeel. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 179',196620),
(267399,224623,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Here\'s a solid and accessible Shiraz with medium- intense notes of red cherry, raspberry and cola on the nose and mouth. The mouth is medium weight with delicate tannins and black pepper spice, while the finish offers a glimmer of mocha.',10,NULL,0,'Vineyard Creations',196839),
(267409,218046,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/E6Cat38lTrKaCZYqORHyVA_pb_x960.png','With 22 to 24 months in new French oak, there\'s a lot of richness to this wine in the form of raspberry sauce, milk chocolate and balsamic reduction. There\'s plenty of fruit to support those heavy flavors, though, with vibrant cherry and plum flavors in the medium weight mouth. Cola and spice add interest to the close.',17,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar',196839),
(267410,223593,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'With 6,000 cases imported and an attractive price tag, this is an easy choice for dinner with friends around a hearty stew or braised meat. Bright and intense with strong berry preserve flavors backed by notes of graham cracker, bramble and sweet spice. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens',197456),
(267413,222477,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A bit muted and shy on the nose, with faint accents of fresh grass, sweet citrus and just-ripe gooseberry. The palate offers a pithy-citrus flavor, adding a touch of bitterness to the clean close.',15,NULL,0,'Sutherland',196839),
(267417,223800,'other','Moscato',NULL,'A spritzy and effervescent selection, the carbonation helps to lift the inherent sweet fruit aromas and flavors of guava, peach and mushy pear. An ideal choice for a warm summer day by the pool, served very cold.',7,NULL,0,'Sustainable Agriculture Perlè',196839),
(267432,223676,'other','Merlot',NULL,'This is classic Merlot at a great price, with notes of black plum, cherry, blackberry and licorice on the nose and mouth. Balanced and softly textured with medium tannins and a solid, clean finish. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Bergkelder Selection',196839),
(267476,222911,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A touch sharp with prominent acidity and soft tannins in the mouth. Tart dried cherry, raspberry and plum fill palate, with a clean, medium-length finish sealing the experience. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Reserve',196845),
(267477,224641,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Herbal and green with notes of pepper, black plum skins, menthol and damp forrest floor. It\'s easy to drink with light tannins and a medium weight followed by a short finish.',51,NULL,0,'Liber III',197484),
(267478,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8Op8t5wYThy9LpTSnsMiyw_pb_600x600.png','Dark, earthy and rubbery aromas go along with a reasonably fruity bouquet, and as a whole the entry is good. The palate is full, a bit rough and rugged, with ripe, sweet black-cherry and cassis flavors. Concentrated and a touch syrupy, but good for what amounts to basic Cabernet.',12,NULL,0,'Estate',196886),
(267484,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Fresh fruit shows the acidity of the year, while the black currant flavors give great freshness. The aftertaste is soft, flavored with strawberry juice.',40,NULL,0,'Beaune du Château Premier Cru',197241),
(267520,223750,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This is a fresh and easy to drink white that\'s perfect for pairing with salads or citrus-based grilled fish. Medium weight with prominent tart flavors of lemony citrus and green berries, and the finish offers a hint of fresh hay.',11,NULL,0,'Young Vines',196689),
(267555,217504,'other','White Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of 39% Rhine Riesling, 28% Viognier, 13% Chardonnay, 9% Chenin Blanc, 8% Sauvignon Blanc and 3% Sémillon. Tropical fruit, tangerine citrus, lychee and yellow florals fill the light mouth, followed by a lively and somewhat brisk finish.',18,NULL,0,'Blanc de Mer',196793),
(267562,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Opens with briar, raspberry and a spot of char. The palate is basic, simple in feel, maybe a touch curt, but overall the wine is fresh and tastes of plum and herbal berry fruit. It\'s slightly dry and leafy, but it\'s bright and fresh in the mouth, with good balance.',8,NULL,0,'Xplorador',196852),
(267617,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'An intense, mineral-driven wine, tasting of the limestone soil as well as very ripe fruit. Great acidity keeps the richness in line, toast offering sweetness. The wine is full-bodied, the flavors going right through to the apple-skin-textured core.',75,NULL,0,'Clos Saint Marc Premier Cru',197408),
(267650,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The vintage as well as the vineyard gave this hugely rich wine. It has weight, concentrated fruit and toast flavors, the acidity on line right through the center. Peach, pineapple and grapefruit combine to give an impressive, textured fruitiness. Age for 2–3 years.',105,NULL,0,'Charmes Premier Cru',197408),
(267656,219700,'other','Malvasia','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/dXefcAcgTw2ifoFKo-DZow_pb_x960.png','From the tiny island of Salina off the north coast of Sicily (where the Tasca family runs a beautiful boutique hotel called Capofaro), comes this excellent expression of Malvasia. This dessert wine shows exactly what this versatile white grape variety is built to do best: The bouquet is redolent of honey, golden vanilla cream, candied apricot and sweet almond marzipan.',66,NULL,0,'Capofaro',196776),
(267671,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'An interesting Pinot Noir, showing a bit of heat, but whose flavors are taut and complex. The usual cherries and cola you find in almost all California Pinot Noirs are grounded with meaty notes, like grilled hamburger, finished with a splash of tamari. Such are the tannins and acids that the wine should age gracefully for a good eight years, but you can drink it now.',45,NULL,0,'van der Kamp Vineyard',196642),
(267685,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A big, ripe earthy wine, layered with tannins and dark black fruits. It has density and concentration, while keeping a sense of freshness and balance. A powerful and impressive wine that will age well.',30,NULL,0,'Quinta das Tecedeiras Reserva',196794),
(267807,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Powerful, concentrated Chablis. It is rich, with ripe apricot and nectarine fruit, laced with Seville orange acidity. With a touch of toast, a well-integrated structure, this is a wine for medium-term aging.',80,NULL,0,'Vaudésir Grand Cru',197408),
(267818,219700,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/OkaPRn_rRzC2KEpC3GQXbw_pb_x600.png','Diamante is a passito dessert wine from the producer\'s historic Tenuta Regaleali property outside Palermo. The wine boasts a beautiful golden color along with aromas of candied fruit, honey and marzipan.',60,NULL,0,'Diamante',196776),
(267867,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This fruit-forward Pinot offers a blast of cherries and raspberries. It\'s almost as sweet as jam, but it finishes dry, as the acidity and tannins that constitute its structure rush in. A lovely wine to drink now, right out of the bottle, and over the next few years.',45,NULL,0,'Thornton Vineyard',196642),
(267900,218512,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/eqTnuX7gT4SGGDnYhyXgYg_pb_x600.png','Tané is a beautiful barrique-aged blend of Nero d\'Avola and Syrah from southeast Sicily that shows rich intensity and a velvety feel in the mouth. The fruit is dense and smooth, and the wine\'s bright flavors last a long time on the palate.',52,NULL,0,'Tané',196773),
(267905,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This beautiful vintage of Duca Enrico shows riper fruit than the 2006, with its hint of green leaf. The fruit here is plush, rich and chewy, with long-lasting tones of blackberry pie, leather, spice and moist pipe tobacco.',67,NULL,0,'Duca Enrico',196776),
(267949,219700,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MYIj5KisQQi--zUBaAQzxw_pb_x300.png','The Tasca family shows a deft hand with Cabernet Sauvignon, and has worked hard to match this international variety to the unique Sicilian territory. This beautiful vintage opens with nicely ripened dark fruit, cola, root beer, cured meat and Teriyaki sauce. The wine\'s texture is polished, smooth and firm.',50,NULL,0,'Tenuta Regaleali',196776),
(267982,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'An impressive and elegant wine. It has a delicious line of juicy red and black berry fruits, powered with a fine balance of acidity and firm, chunky tannins. With good potential, give the wine 3–4 years.',15,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte Special Selection',196807),
(267999,219700,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/pqfIbKRAQKqpXeReEcedOA_pb_x960.png','Sicily\'s Tasca family does a terrific job with this golden Chardonnay. The wine reflects the sunshine, warmth and generosity of the island. Aromas of stone fruit, vanilla, rose and almond blossom are followed by a beautifully creamy mouthfeel.',60,NULL,0,'Tenuta Regaleali',196776),
(268028,219700,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HVLzeE0ETi2Ol_VPG7om7Q_pb_x600.png','This is a dark and muscular expression of Syrah executed in a quasi-Australian style, with loads of concentration and spice, backed by smoked bacon, Teriyaki, candied berry and Indian spice.',30,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour La Monaca',196776),
(268039,220442,'other','Insolia',NULL,'Careful winemaking and low vineyard yields make this a classy and sophisticated Sicilian white with a rich, creamy mouthfeel. The wine\'s compelling aromas include apricot, almond, yellow candy, pineapple and exotic fruit.',50,NULL,0,'Bianca di Valguarnera',196776),
(268109,220442,'other','Nerello Mascalese',NULL,'Làvico is a tight, bright wine that shows an elegant and austere side of sunny Sicily. The wine is redolent of wild berries, cola, dried ginger and light spice.',NULL,NULL,0,'Vajasindi Làvico',196776),
(268117,219700,'other','Nerello Mascalese','https://www.arvi.ch/images/thumbs/0004870_Nerello-Mascalese-Il-Tascante_6232_32476_510.png','Tascante combines “Tasca” and “Etna” spelled backwards. This wine represents the estate\'s first vintage of Nerello Mascalese from the fiery Sicilian volcano. It\'s a tight, tonic expression with small berry fruit and a long finish highlighted by crushed clove and nutmeg.',40,NULL,0,'Tascante',196776),
(268162,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional','https://res.cloudinary.com/evino/image/upload/t_bottle_large,f_auto/v1/products/1649390-standing-front.jpg','An elegant red, with power, acidity and black berry flavors curling around a structured core of dark tannins. This is cool Touriga, very poised, worth aging for two years, with a delicious spicy aftertaste.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(268192,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A juicy, fruity wine with just a line of tannins at its core. Its red berry fruits are delicious and easy to drink, the wine with its richness needs no aging. It\'s pure fruit bomb pleasure.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Q do E',196794),
(268243,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A butter-smooth and rounded wine. Its pear and ripe apple fruits are contrasted with a layer of wood and crisp acidity. It opens up to give richness, weight and delicious final yellow fruit flavors on the finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Rabource Premier Cru',197408),
(268304,219884,'other','Alicante Bouschet',NULL,'Almost black in color, this is a concentrated powerhouse of black plum, damsons and dark berry fruits. It is explosively rich and densely structured, with intense juicy fruit.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(268325,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A fresh wine, with red berry fruit and fine acidity. It has a firm core of tannins balanced with the fruit. The wine, made from 20-year-old vines, is likely to be ready to drink in the next two years.',15,NULL,0,'Quinta das Tecedeiras Flor de Tecedeiras',196794),
(268335,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'From the far north of the Vinho Verde region, the rich and creamy wine balances acidity, green plum and crisp minerality. Aromatic, elegant, fresh.',17,NULL,0,'Touquinheiras',196685),
(268343,219884,'other','Alfrocheiro',NULL,'Powerful, concentrated wine, whose tannins fold well around the berry fruits, acidity and sweet plum juice flavors. It is solid and chunky, full of ripe flavors and bold acidity. Worth aging for 1–2 years.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(268402,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Intensely wood-aged wine, with plenty of toast. That doesn\'t make the wine any less attractive with its yellow fruit flavors giving weight in the background. In a year\'s time, the wood and fruit balance should even out.',NULL,NULL,0,'En Remilly Premier Cru',197408),
(268453,219700,'other','White Blend','https://static.xtrawine.com/Global/Images/XW/products/wines/40813_SallierDeLaTourInzolia_2022_3.png','An unusual wine for Sicily, Sallier de la Tour Le Bianche represents an innovative blend of Viognier, Semillon and Sauvignon. The aromatic intensity—with almond blossom and honey—is definitely there, and the wine is smooth, silky and soft on the finish.',30,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour Le Bianche',196776),
(268454,218512,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/IafYXgVQS56xMs4kuEgbbQ_pb_x600.png','Bidis is a smooth blend of Chardonnay and Insolia from the southern side of Sicily. The 60% Chardonnay component adds depth, balance and stone fruit aromas. The Grillo element grounds the wine in local tradition with fresh notes of wild herbs and fragrant white flowers.',32,NULL,0,'Bidis',196773),
(268470,219884,'other','Shiraz','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fSQKgHmlTkeahORJ1YBazQ_pb_x960.png','A big textured, smooth wine, sweet fruits with firm tannins finished with dark perfumes. It is a blockbuster, thankfully without high alcohol, balanced in its richness. A barbecue wine, ready to drink now.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(268480,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Winemaker José Neiva delights in unusual blends such as this particular combination which should be tried more often. It is a big rich wine, packed with ripe flavors, plums, dark chocolate, rich sweet berries and firm tannins.',13,NULL,0,'DFJ Caladoc/Alicante Bouschet',196807),
(268500,219700,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/0vV0DHfeSUmg6ynTxiWjpw_pb_x960.png','Only a handful of metodo classico sparkling wines are produced in Sicily, and this Chardonnay-based bubbly from the Tasca family is among the best. Perfect for appetizers on a warm spring afternoon, the wine delivers tonic effervescence and aromas of white flower and citrus.',60,NULL,0,'Almerita Brut',196776),
(268523,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This wine is certainly a powerful statement: smooth, super-rich, tarry black berry fruits, spice and a sizable serving of wood vanilla. A wine to admire, not to enjoy.',27,NULL,0,'Grou Grey',196685),
(268552,218512,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/V3BbKai7RI-c_zK53ETCcQ_pb_x600.png','Il Moro offers intense aromas of blackberry, cherry, plum and rum cake. It\'s a tight, compact wine with great fruit intensity that would pair well with vegetable risotto or smoked cheeses.',25,NULL,0,'Il Moro',196773),
(268554,219700,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/vdhvBJhwTfe1cl0EflUXrA_pb_x600.png','Created to celebrate a 50th wedding anniversary, Nozze d\'Oro is a blend of Inzolia and Sauvignon that offers bright floral intensity and a wonderfully pristine and crisp mouthfeel. Pair this wine with lobster risotto.',30,NULL,0,'Nozze d\'Oro',196776),
(268572,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional Blend',NULL,'An attractive, fresh wine, the tannins and bright acidity giving a firm support to the lively berry fruits and dry tannin core. The aftertaste continues freshness.',13,NULL,0,'DFJ Touriga Nacional-Touriga Franca',196807),
(268633,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Here in the maritime climate north of Lisbon, Alfrocheiro works well to produce a rich, smooth and velvet textured wine, with a beautiful layer of acidity over the wood.',13,NULL,0,'DFJ Pinot Noir-Alfrocheiro',196807),
(268644,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Fragrant and fresh, this is a great bright, crisp Vinho Verde. The acidity is intense, balanced with an elegant softer texture. It just cries out for seafood.',12,NULL,0,'Clemen Reserva',196685),
(268765,220442,'other','Grillo',NULL,'Grillo is the base for many famous Sicilian white wines including fortified Marsala. However in this case, the grape produces a crisp, fresh, easy-drinking wine that pairs with seafood or Thai mango salad.',15,NULL,0,'Kados Risignolo',196776),
(268772,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Ripe and juicy, maybe a little rustic round the edges, certainly fruity. Red berry flavors dominate along with an edgy center of tannin, while juicy acidity completes this attractive wine.',11,NULL,0,'Samora',196685),
(268794,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A blend from Puligny-Montrachet and Meursault, this is a soft rounded wine with white fruit acidity, almond flavors and a gentle lemon zest texture. Drink in the next two years.',19,NULL,0,'Les Sétilles',197408),
(268848,220442,'other','Nero d\'Avola',NULL,'Duca di Salaparuta sources fruit from vineyard sites spanning the island of Sicily. From the Passo delle Mule location, this bright Nero d\'Avola is generous in terms of its fruit-forward aromatic profile. The mouthfeel is firm, polished and crisp.',18,NULL,0,'Passo delle Mule Suar Marchesa',196776),
(268865,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This rich, delicious blend of Castelão and Alicante Bouschet is soft and juicy, with black and blue berry flavors, dusty tannins and a fine, jammy aftertaste.',11,NULL,0,'Catapereiro',196685),
(268949,217203,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Soft, fruity wine from the Castelão grape grown in sandy vineyards, this is smooth and ripe, with a good edge of acidity. The wine has great berry fruits, just a touch of tannin, ready to drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal',196685),
(268964,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Nero d\'Avola and Merlot are combined to produce an easy-going red that would pair with grilled meat or breaded veal. The wine is lean and crisp with light berry tones and a touch of charred toast on the close.',13,NULL,0,'Calanìca Nero d\'Avola-Merlot',196776),
(268991,219884,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon and Tinta Roriz',NULL,'An elegant wine, the tannins a core element in the firm structure. Acidity and black currant flavors go together with spice. It is a young wine, ready to drink, but will develop.',8,NULL,0,'Pedras do Monte',196807),
(269047,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Light, fresh and crisp, typical of bright cool whites of the Lisbon region. It has lively, fresh acidity, picked out with lemon and grapefruit flavors.',9,NULL,0,'Portada Branco',196807),
(269064,219700,'other','Rosé','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0620/5145/1073/products/Tenuta-Regaleali-Regaleali-Le-Rose.png?v=1679307626','This is a terrific value wine (a rosé made from the indigenous grapes of Sicily) that opens with a bright pink color and fragrant tones of raspberry, white almond and rose petal.',13,NULL,0,'Regaleali Le Rose',196776),
(269083,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A rounded wine, keeping the white fruit character of pears, given vibrancy by a citric grapefruit flavor. Full in the mouth, it has a smooth texture, finishing softly.',11,NULL,0,'Samora Branco',196685),
(269094,219884,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Attractive spicy wine from Setúbal region\'s signature grape. Ginger, berries and light wood work well together to give richness without weight.',8,NULL,0,'Pedras do Monte',196807),
(269137,220442,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This value wine opens with a fresh, citrusy bouquet and features a compact, streamlined mouthfeel.',13,NULL,0,'Calanìca Insolia-Chardonnay',196776),
(269167,217310,'other','Portuguese White','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','A medium-dry Vinho Verde, this is light and fresh without being quite crisp enough. Well chilled, though, it makes a lively and fresh apéritif.',7,NULL,0,'Aliança',196677),
(269183,220442,'other','White Blend',NULL,'The blend is 60-40 Grillo and Viognier and the wine offers aromatic components of both varieties. The first imparts green notes of kiwi and cut grass and the second offers sweet floral fragrances.',13,NULL,0,'Calanìca Grillo-Viognier',196776),
(269194,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Soft and fresh, a wine with delicious acidity, almonds and pink grapefruit flavors. A mineral edge comes through to give a vibrant aftertaste.',11,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal Escolha',196685),
(269196,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Fresh, herbal and stalky, a light-bodied red wine that has some well-balanced residual sugar to go with the red berry fruits. The soft texture masks the acidity. Screw cap.',7,NULL,0,'Portada Tinto',196807),
(269197,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A bizarre blend of the hybrid Negra Mole and Trincadeira. The is soft, rather heavy in texture, rich plum flavors, lacking acidity.',11,NULL,0,'Esplanada',196807),
(269246,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This version of Calanìca (made from 60% Frappato and 40% Syrah) offers a low impact bouquet of earthy forest fruit and bramble. It\'s a light, lean wine with a touch of soft spice on the close.',20,NULL,0,'Calanìca Frappato-Syrah',196776),
(269284,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Curious stalky fruit aromas don\'t translate well in this rather lean wine. It has black currant fruits, light tannins, prominent acidity, but lacks balanced density.',13,NULL,0,'DFJ Tinta Roriz-Merlot',196807),
(269314,219700,'other','Grillo','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/9xtHntMhRd2CiuGn3jOmwQ_pb_x960.png','This is a fresh, tonic and light Grillo that would pair with endive salad and sliced oranges or red beets in vinaigrette. The wine offers citrus, green herb and fresh kiwi aromas.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour',196776),
(269326,219700,'other','White Blend','https://www.saq.com/media/catalog/product/7/1/715086-1_1626063926.png?quality=80&fit=bounds&height=&width=','This fresh and easy Sicilian white is a blend of Insolia, Grecanico and Catarratto with easy citrus and stone fruit aromas. Pair it with Chinese chicken salad.',10,NULL,0,'Regaleali',196776),
(269610,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A rare, maybe unique, blend of Arinto and Sauvignon Blanc, which imparts a curiously mineral character. The fresh character of both grape varieties seem lost in the rounded character of the wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Terras do Dão',196794),
(269714,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Chile\'s most expensive wine is excellent, and with only 50 cases being imported it\'s definitely a collector\'s edition. The nose is deep, dense and black as night, with olive, tobacco, coconut and bold black fruit aromas. The palate is racy and tannic, and the flavors of plum, cassis, blackberry, chocolate, prune and fig are elevated. A tough and ribald wine that will be at its best from 2012–2015.',260,NULL,0,'Viñedo Chadwick',196886),
(269816,223247,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A worthy tribute, this dark and concentrated Shiraz oozes rich fruit notes of mulled boysenberry, blackberry and cherry all dusted with cocoa powder, whole baking spice and tree bark. Big and gripping with assertive tannins and a firm structure, this is one that should age nicely; try after 2014.',60,NULL,0,'Ronnie Melck A Tribute',197420),
(269817,225110,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of Cab Sauv, Merlot, Malbec and Tempranillo, this red boasts a beautiful array of aromas and flavors: cassis, eucalyptus, blackberry, fig, tobacco and cinnamon. With a velvety texture and medium tannins, there\'s a good grip to the long finish laced with accents of leather and black tea leaves.',28,NULL,0,'Scaramanga',197557),
(269820,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Although it took a little while to open up, the wine eventually expresses itself beautifully with deep notes of crushed purple florals, black cherry and blueberry along with a hint of game. Lush and full with a satiny texture, the mouth is heady and satisfying with a concentrated fruit core supported by cedar and mocha on the close.',27,NULL,0,'Unfined and Unfiltered',196689),
(269823,222826,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A seductive and easy-pleasing wine, this ripe and lush beauty, named after the winemaker\'s daughter, will draw you in with its sultry notes of ripe brambly berries, forest floor, cured meat, sweet smoke and spice. The mouthfeel is like velvet and the finish long, with a gorgeous mocha- and licorice root-flavored finish.',39,NULL,0,'Cuvée Ameena',196839),
(269824,223183,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This gorgeous Cape blend, made from 30% Pinotage, 31% Syrah, 30% Cab Sauv and 3% Mourvèdre, is ripe and immediately enticing on the nose with aromas of crushed Thin Mint cookies and iris petals mingling perfectly with the blackberry, blueberry and fig fruit core. Well balanced and firmly structured with a spicy, lingering finish.',25,NULL,0,'Three Cape Ladies',196689),
(269830,217719,'other','Red Blend','https://images.wine.co.za/GetWineImage.ashx?ImageSize=large&IMAGEID=249607','There\'s great spice and depth to this tribute wine in honour of Graham Joseph Beck. Intense notes of cigar box spice, black pepper, cedar bark and cocoa powder all abound in the bouquet and follow through all the way to the long close. Black fruit flavors are present, but the spice takes center stage. Firm, gripping tannins flood the mouth and linger endlessly; try from 2014 on.',65,NULL,0,'Ad Honorem',196845),
(269865,224349,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Only 30 cases of this gorgeous wine are imported, so snag what you can when you find it. It\'s a deep and complex Syrah, exuding attractive aromas and flavors of juicy red cherry and fresh raspberry spiced up with accents of vanilla crème, sweet wood, soft Earl Gray tea and whole baking spice on the close. Creamy and lush with a silky texture; drink now–2014.',30,NULL,0,'Estalét',196839),
(269868,223405,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Earthy notes of fresh whole tobacco leaf, licorice and vanilla bean spice up the blackberry and cassis fruit on the nose and palate. The velvety mouthfeel is loaded with dusty, fine-grain tannins, with a lifting acidity that keeps the long, cedary finish fresh and vibrant. Ready to drink now, but should also keep nicely for another 2–4 years.',49,NULL,0,'Peter Barlow',196689),
(269877,217719,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/b966gsAbRaiQlKksiEzagw_pb_x960.png','Ripe, rich and overall yummy, this Syrah offers bright notes of red plum and cherry laced with a touch of gaminess and soft foliage. The medium-weight mouthfeel boasts fine tannins and prominent acidity that provides a nice lift to the long, spicy finish.',23,NULL,0,'The Ridge',196845),
(269912,217999,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/X0tNqLXNSgq4-o0HFLIy5Q_pb_x600.png','Campanaro is a unique blend of Fiano and Greco grapes that opens with a beautiful bouquet of stone fruit, honey, white almond and Golden Delicious apple. It a dry, crisp wine with a focused, fine feel in the mouth.',33,NULL,0,'Campanaro',196908),
(269919,222090,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Bright black berry and purple floral notes immediately waft from the glass, followed shortly after by glimmers of sweet smoke, tea leaf and soft leather. Fruit-forward and balanced, the round mouth is framed by medium-fine tannins and lifting acidity. A hint of milk chocolate sexes up the close.',40,NULL,0,'Estate Wine',197420),
(269962,223791,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The name of this wine doesn\'t lie; if you like mint, then this one\'s definitely for you! Gorgeous notes of fresh eucalyptus take center stage to the blackberry and boysenberry fruit backbone. The menthol continues on in the mouth, with a gripping and structured finish that tastes like Thin Mint crumbles.',24,NULL,0,'Mint Haven',196839),
(269966,222821,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Cedar plank-grilled meat and herbal accents jazz up the heady black fruit core of this wine. Rich and dark, flavors of black berry, plum flesh, cigar box, licorice and pepper dance in the mouth and stay through the solid finish. Fine but firm tannins provide structure and texture, and the wine, though delicious now, should age nicely through 2014.',33,NULL,0,'Reserve',196689),
(270021,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Produced from old vines, this is a serious and concentrated wine. It has a strong mineral texture that adds to the dark tannins to make a forceful structure. Powered by the structure and the black fruits it will age well. Start drinking in 2018.',40,NULL,0,'Aguia Moura em Vinhas Velhas Garrafeira',196685),
(270095,222151,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Opulent, lush and round in style, this leads with ripe aromas of apricot, yellow apple and mange, laced with hints of clementine oil, marzipan and toasted baking spice. The palate is full and creamy, but balanced by ample acidity, lifting the texture from an overly flabby impression. Flavors of woody spice and peach pit dance on the lingering finish. Drink now–2017.',50,NULL,0,'Nine Yards',196689),
(270169,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This wine has structure and freshness although the fruit is on the lean side, offering black cherries and swathes of crisp acidity. The aftertaste is juicy, fresh and mineral.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine dit Baron',197404),
(270170,218426,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/yXAeiKQgReOW-R0TLDL1dg_pb_x600.png','Root beer and slate show on the very restrained nose of this wine that combines fruit from Monterey County (66%) and Santa Barbara Counry (34%). The palate is light and slightly metallic, with iron as well as eucalyptus and shreds of cranberry and raspberry fruit.',26,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(270194,217625,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8stWDx-9TZmfPeZ5_q9cbQ_pb_x960.png','This partner of the red Grilos is intense and fruity. It shows fresh acidity while also having ripe apricot, tangerine fruit and a lightly mineral texture. It is still young, so will be better drunk at the end of 2014.',NULL,NULL,0,'Grilos Branco',196794),
(270232,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Ripe red berries and a touch of red plum give this wine a full, fruity character. Light tannins add a suggestion of structure. It\'s juicy and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de la Madone des Loges',197404),
(270237,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Tight acidity, cherry flavors and a hint of banana give this wine a light and fruity character. It has probably too much acidity for its own good, making it too crisp, missing out on richness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château de la Perrière',197404),
(270258,224337,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A blend of 55% Cabernet Sauvignon, 25% Shiraz and 5% each of Merlot, Cabernet Franc, Malbec and Petit Verdot, this rich and approachable wine boasts lush aromas and flavors of brambly black berry, cherry and currant alongside notes of violet and chocolate fudge. The mouthfeel is like crushed velvet, with a creamy texture and a decadent finish reminiscent of chocolate-covered espresso beans.',39,NULL,0,'Proprietor\'s Blend',196689),
(270276,217780,'other','Carignan','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/1ZpKaLYXQZqxx7PUzZvZbg_pb_600x600.png','Rich, chocolaty, toasty aromas of lactic oak and vanilla match red-fruit scents of raspberry and strawberry. This is lively on the palate, with an acidic pulse. Flavors of raw oak, creamy vanilla, plum and boysenberry finish overtly woody, with a lasting flavor of oak grain. Drink through 2018.',24,NULL,0,'Amplus Old Vine',196857),
(270369,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a big wine with dark tannins and rich black fruits that are powerful and dense. The strong mineral texture comes from the rocky soils of Catapereiro. Wood aging adds to the complexity. Drink from 2017.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Herdade de Catapereiro',196685),
(270399,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'With intense banana aromas, this is a tight wine with high acidity. It has crisp red-currant fruits that are not quite ripe. Tangy and shot through with banana flavors, the wine will be better from 2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine des Darroux',197404),
(270604,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This has some of the concentration you would expect from old vines, along with a lighter, fresher character that gives the wine a lift. It\'s as much young and fruity as structured, a well-balanced wine that will be ready to drink from 2016.',14,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas',196685),
(270717,217265,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The color is deeper than usual. Aromas are thick with blackberry and boysenberry, and similarly generous flavors seem to spread out and coat the mouth. Accents of chocolate and vanilla add welcome complexity to this rich-tasting wine that\'s based on Tempranillo grapes.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 466',196620),
(270738,223506,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Aromas of melon, red apple and Bosc pear immediately waft from the bouquet of this wine, while beguiling hints of toasted oak, heather, yellow flower and lemon custard dance in the background. It\'s quite round and lush on the palate, with bold, ripe stone-fruit flavors that transition into notes of caramel corn and buttercream on the finish.',50,NULL,0,'Appellation Series',197456),
(270773,218569,'other','Gewürztraminer','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/JIOK1aZzT06okCwn7uCESA_pb_600x600.png','Beautiful lychee and rose-petal aromas open the bouquet of this lithe late-harvest wine, made in small amounts. Apple and melon highlight the fruitier overtones atop a base of balanced minerality, which softens the sweetness. The finish is tangy and rich in nutmeg.',40,NULL,0,'Vista Verde Vineyard Late Harvest',196626),
(270912,220442,'other','Nero d\'Avola',NULL,'Mature plum, blackberry and raspberry sensations take center stage on this young Nero d\'Avola. The ripe fruit is accented by notes of subtle oak, espresso, black pepper and mint, alongside drying tannins.',25,NULL,0,'Passo delle Mule',196776),
(270982,221639,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Sassy passion-fruit and feline aromas set up a crisp, clean-feeling palate with tangy, green, zesty flavors of scallion, lime and sour apple. A minerally, chalky finish is zingy and clean. This is nice for value-priced Sauvignon Blanc.',9,NULL,0,'Urban Uco',196852),
(271002,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This wine is just starting out, which explains the toast factor that currently dominates the nose and palate. As it opens, the opulent, ripe fruit from this great vineyard shows through in the form of powerful, and intense pineapple and apricot flavors that mingle in the tight texture. It will age for many years—start with at least six.',500,NULL,0,'Chevalier-Montrachet Grand Cru',197408),
(271005,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Corton-Charlemagne expresses the power of Chardonnay, rather than the subtlety. Given that, Olivier Leflaive\'s version is finely nuanced, and its weight comes as much from the rich white- and yellow-fruit flavors as the tight structure. Like most grand crus, this needs to age, so give it 5–6 years.',170,NULL,0,'Corton-Charlemagne Grand Cru',197408),
(271011,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'With his family based in Puligny-Montrachet, Olivier Leflaive knows a thing or two about the grand crus of his village. This Bâtard-Montrachet is intensely textured, concentrated and ripe, and it exudes equal amounts of acids. Powerful yet elegant, the toast note is a subtle expression in this rich wine. This for long-term aging.',375,NULL,0,'Bâtard-Montrachet Grand Cru',197408),
(271038,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This single vineyard wine is powerful with its concentrated tannins and dark cherry fruits. Good acidity goes with the fruit and the dry core. A shame that a hint of banana spoils the aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine des Quatre Vents',197404),
(271040,217335,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Luscious golden in color, this dessert wine shows aromas of honeyed and seared lemons, with hints of marigold and toasted sunflower seeds. The palate is rich and sweet, but balanced expertly with a great tartness.',25,NULL,0,'Novitiate Late Harvest',196639),
(271057,218035,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/7s6VQ-C9SgWRYfYfwNE1lQ_pb_x600.png','Blackberry and spice aromas are earthy, leathery and stalky. This is youthful and tannic at this point, while oaky flavors of clove and wood spice ride heavily atop blackberry and dark plum fruit. Oak notes and firm tannins indicate that this will be best from late 2015 through 2018.',22,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(271098,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A fresh, fruity wine that also has some richness. With flavors of peach, canned pineapple, and a touch of greener herbaceousness, it\'s balanced and rounded. Wait until late 2014 before drinking.',12,NULL,0,'Herdade de Catapereiro',196685),
(271162,218426,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjvr_nv_pnoir_screwcap_outshinery.png?itok=AnN1dssz','On this Pinot\'s plus side is a clean savoriness, with bright acidity highlighting raspberry, cocoa and spice flavors. On the debit side is its soft, fleshy ripeness. Drink up.',22,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(271178,217310,'other','Bical','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','Bical produces delicious pear and apple flavored wines. This bright, fruity wine is a fine example of this creamy freshness. It is a wine for drinking now, while fresh and crisp at the end.',9,NULL,0,'Galeria',196677),
(271209,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is an oaky Chardonnay with buttered toast and butterscotch flavors that overlay rich apricot, tangerine and tropical fruits. The opulence is balanced with crisp acidity. It\'s all a bit forward and obvious, but in a good way.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 364',196620),
(271213,218426,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/a1OWZHOoTJCE72VWnWpw3Q_pb_x600.png','Fresh in zingy, ripe blackberry flavor, this well-made Zin has firm tannins and a dollop of peppery spice on the finish.',17,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(271230,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The opulence of this Chard comes at least as much from the buttered toast and caramel notes of oak, as it does from the underlying pineapple and tropical fruit flavors. It\'s a crowd pleaser. Drink now.',40,NULL,0,'Estate Vineyard Olivet Bench',196642),
(271370,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'One of the best-known Puligny premier crus, Folatières has produced a rich, opulent wine as it often does. In 2010, it feels more structured and more minerally than previous vintages. It is ripe and full bodied, and it is well suited to age for 4–5 years or more.',130,NULL,0,'Les Folatières Premier Cru',197408),
(271444,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is a light, fruity, fresh and clean wine. With lemon and crisp apple flavors, it is bright, simple, attractive and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cabriz Colheita Seleccionada Branco',196794),
(271489,220442,'other','Nerello Mascalese',NULL,'Made from the native grape Nerello Mascalese, this elegant wine opens with aromas of red berry, vanilla and a whiff of leather. The palate offers polished tannins and a creamy red-cherry flavor that\'s lightly accented by subtle oak and baking spice.',25,NULL,0,'Làvico',196776),
(271503,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A well-structured wine, it offers ripe, creamy fruits and attractive acidity. With mouth-watering citrus flavors, yellow fruits and smooth aftertaste, it represents great value from a lesser-known appellation.',27,NULL,0,'La Grande Roche Premier Cru',197254),
(271548,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Made from fruit sourced from vines close to Puligny\'s grand crus, this has some of the same structure and dense minerality as many of the village\'s best wines. It\'s vivid, upfront and rich with boisterous fruitiness. The structure will take many years to round out.',130,NULL,0,'Les Pucelles Premier Cru',197408),
(271556,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Originally better known for its red wines, this vineyard to the south of Chassagne-Montrachet now produces mainly white wines. This bottling is structured, firm and tight, and it promises a future that will always be serious and austere. Keep it for 4–5 years.',95,NULL,0,'Abbaye de Morgeot Premier Cru',197408),
(271595,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Full and round, this is a ripe blackberry-flavored wine. It has a touch of licorice, followed by juicy fruitiness and some acidity. The aftertaste, with its flavors of wood aging, suggests it could mature through 2015.',12,NULL,0,'Samora Tinto',196685),
(271597,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Ripe red berries, a light structure and plenty of fresh acidity make for a wine that best drunk young.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cortello Tinto',196794),
(271606,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is a typically light, fruity and off dry Vinho Verde. It has an attractive, refreshing prickle on the tongue followed by crisp apples and citrus flavors. Clean, fresh and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Xadrez',196794),
(271612,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Soft, smooth and fruity, this polished wine is full of red berry fruits and a touch of licorice. The juicy, ripe, immediately attractive aftertaste comes from the local Castelão grapes in the blend. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Monte da Baía',196685),
(271613,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is a fine, simple wine for this summer. With acidity, fresh apple and pear flavors, it\'s attractive and aromatic.',11,NULL,0,'Dona Helena Colheita',196685),
(271676,219700,'other','White Blend','https://www.vinello.eu/media/image/bf/38/43/tasca_dalmerita_regaleali_bianco.png','Made from a blend of Inzolia, Grecanico, Catarratto and Chardonnay, this bright, refreshing wine is great for summer sipping. It offers juicy white peach, tart green apple, lemon zest and grapefruit sensations that slide easily across the palate.',15,NULL,0,'Regaleali Bianco',196776),
(271677,218512,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Fermented and aged in barriques, this structured Chardonnay opens with aromas of subtle oak, citrus and lemon drop. The palate delivers fresh acidity and flavors of toast, apple, butterscotch and nut.',30,NULL,0,'Bidis',196773),
(271712,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Champ Gain is on the upper slope of Puligny-Montrachet. This is a rich, toasty and ripe-fruited selection, full of yellow fruit, mango and clementine flavors. It also reveals the minerality found in most wines from this village.',95,NULL,0,'Champ Gain Premier Cru',197408),
(271736,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Here\'s a rich, smooth wine for drinking now. It\'s softly luscious, packed with blackberry, cherry, anise and cedar flavors that finish with quite a bit of complexity.',18,NULL,0,'Lot 357',196620),
(271744,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A wine with some structure, firm tannins and attractive black cherry and spice flavors. The wine has good weight and a dense texture that promises medium-term aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Lafayette',197404),
(271788,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/IUemBDrLTfGEvXA2OJshQA_pb_600x600.png','This smells typical of coastal Chilean SB, meaning it\'s citrusy and green, but the nose seems a touch flat. Not so the palate, which is snappy and juicy. Flavors of grapefruit and passion fruit lead the way, with a backing of green bean and mild bell pepper controlling a crisp, fresh finish.',20,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(271799,220442,'other','Pinot Nero',NULL,'Oak, crushed berry and vanilla aromas take center stage on this Sicilian Pinot Nero. The palate offers ripe red cherry, prune, toasted oak, sweet baking spice and chocolate alongside drying tannins.',40,NULL,0,'Nawari',196776),
(271818,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/m1WtQJfVQKujCVZgYCJYPg_pb_x960.png','This easy-drinking Aglianico offers succulent black cherry, plum and raspberry flavors accented by notes of cinnamon and clove. It\'s round, fresh and friendly. Drink soon to capture the juicy fruit.',25,NULL,0,'Dal Re',196908),
(271923,225668,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This opens with tropical fruit aromas of pineapple, mango and melon that are framed by hints of honeysuckle and sweet spice. The medium-weight palate boasts similar tropical fruit tones, but with an assertive mineral and lime-zest lift on the close, ending fresh and lively. Drink up.',20,NULL,0,'Wild Yeast',196845),
(271959,217625,'other','Portuguese Sparkling',NULL,'The wine tastes full of ripe fruits as well as acidity. A touch of bitter almond gives a hard edge to the otherwise fruity, apple and pear flavored wine. Drink from 2015 to give the wine some bottle age.',45,NULL,0,'Encontro Special Cuvée Brut',196794),
(271960,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MQYOHyAITg6NlZpZjWiKGA_pb_x960.png','This young, fresh Aglianico opens with aromas of ripe black fruit, forest floor and cooking spices. The linear palate offers ripe black cherry layered with notes of earth, licorice and cooking spice, all balanced by firm tannins.',19,NULL,0,'Rubrato',196908),
(272065,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Dry and earthy, with tobacco, mushroom and raspberry flavors, accented with smoky oak. Feels a bit hollow in the middle palate and short on the finish, but is an elegant, silky wine. Drink now.',58,NULL,0,'Estate Vineyard Olivet Bench',196642),
(272069,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A fruity, forward wine with a touch of smokiness to go with the red cherry fruits and clear acidity. It\'s a full wine, structured with its background of tannins. The aftertaste brings out bright fruits.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Javernière',197404),
(272247,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Here\'s a big, tannic Cabernet, stuffed with black currants, olives and cassis, with a lot of sweet oak. It\'s bone dry and elegant, and while it\'s not a cellar candidate, it does show fine character for drinking now.',28,NULL,0,'Lot 399',196620),
(272284,217839,'other','Pinot Noir','https://marquesdecasaconcha.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/pn-3.png','Warm, earthy, dusty aromas of red plum and smoky oak turn toastier the longer this sits. A fresh but balanced palate offers equal amounts of snappy acidity and creamy weight, while tart plum and spice flavors finish toasty and charred, with crisp acidity generating length.',26,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(272333,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Although this rosé smells of wild strawberries, the aroma is better than the palate, which tastes chemical with a bitter almond aftertaste. Serve very cold.',NULL,NULL,0,'Dona Helena Colheita',196685),
(272362,218512,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/C1LyhKqPT7ecscLv-EBJuQ_pb_600x600.png','Here\'s a delightful red that offers fruity aromas of strawberry, wild red cherry and raspberry that carry through to the palate alongside notes of white pepper and mineral. It\'s easy drinking, with bright acidity and a smooth texture.',15,NULL,0,'Tenuta Ibidini',196773),
(272380,217310,'other','Tinta Roriz','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hTzqkrQsTHSenXY62-lt1g_pb_x960.png','Young and fruity, this a crisp, lightly acid wine. Its raspberry fruits are already delicious.',9,NULL,0,'Vista Rosé',196677),
(272437,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'You\'ll find lots to like in this dry, stylish Cabernet. It\'s full-bodied and tannic, but you can drink it now for the wealth of blackberry, black currant, cola, mineral and oak flavors.',28,NULL,0,'Lot 400',196620),
(272479,223258,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Ripe, fruity and forward, this opens with attractive, jammy scents of blackberry, cherry and boysenberry preserves, with touches of cocoa nib and licorice root character. The palate is vibrant and juicy, while an earthy spice note adds depth to the medium-length finish. Drink now.',19,NULL,0,'Paul de Villiers',197445),
(272544,220442,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A blend of Insolia and Chardonnay, this wine opens with subdued aromas of yellow spring flowers and pear. The round, straightforward palate offers golden apple, white peach and lemon zest alongside fresh acidity.',15,NULL,0,'Calanica',196776),
(272599,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'The earthy aromas of Castelão show strongly. Complex, rich and juicy, this wine\'s tannins and black fruits vie amicably for dominance, and they promise good aging. It has a spice note and a firm structure, with a fleshy character.',15,NULL,0,'Catapereiro Escolha',196685),
(272600,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'While this wine has the crispness of Chablis, it also has weight and concentration. The bright green-apple flavor is underpinned by a sense of minerality. Nervy, tense yet fruity, this can age for 2–3 years.',45,NULL,0,'Fourchaume Premier Cru',197408),
(272645,223506,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The bouquet of this wine starts off subtle and dainty, needing time to become more expressive and reveal scents of cured meat, sweet smoke, violet and small red berries. Gamy notes are at the forefront of the medium-weight palate, with underlying flavors of red cherry and currant. A smoky, savory and spicy selection; drink now–2017.',75,NULL,0,'Appellation Series',197456),
(272719,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Toasty aromas go through to the palate, highlighting the wood aging. It is tense, mineral, packed with apple and lemon acidity. The aftertaste is equally crisp and bright.',23,NULL,0,'Les Deux Moulins',197254),
(272760,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Fruity and rounded, this has attractive, citrus-like acidity that cuts through the caramel and apricot flavors. There is a delicious, forward orange-juice flavor that adds to the fresh feel of the wine. It\'s ready to drink, although it will also age.',55,NULL,0,'Sentier du Clou Premier Cru',197408),
(272766,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'An elegant yet ripe wine, this comes laced with citrus acidity, and the yellow fruit and melon flavors give it a sense of richness. It\'s lively and crisp, and it has a toasty base. Age it for 3–4 years.',90,NULL,0,'Clos Saint-Marc Premier Cru',197408),
(273053,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This fruity blend of Frappato and Syrah opens with pretty aromas of blue flower and rose. The round, fresh palate offers juicy black cherry and strawberry accented by black pepper.',16,NULL,0,'Calanica Frappato & Syrah',196776),
(273106,221768,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A creamy hint of white chocolate adds fullness to the soft currant, cranberry and strawberry hull flavors. The palate is mouthfilling and round with a good citrus lift to the fresh close.',16,NULL,0,'Secateurs Cinsault-Shiraz-Grenache',197368),
(273111,222421,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A classic go-to, this blend offers great freshness and ripe fruit flavors at a terrific price. Green melon, red apple, ripe citrus and a touch of floral character all unfold in the nose and mouth, ending with a crisp and mouthwatering finish.',10,NULL,0,'White',197456),
(273118,219884,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hAa4DZV-ShSC4jfbYiF5ww_pb_x600.png','Smooth and rounded, this is a food-friendly rosé. It has a ripe strawberry flavor, with a touch of lime juice and a soft, full finish. Just a touch of tannin gives extra character.',8,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago',196807),
(273119,219884,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Soft and ripe, a flavor of crushed strawberries leads this wine in a fruity direction. It has notes of vanilla and spice, with attractive balancing acidity. This is a food-friendly rosé.',7,NULL,0,'Portada Winemaker\'s Selection',196807),
(273120,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This has soft, ripe fruit, with notes of lime and orange zest fitting easily with the ripe peach and melon flavors. This is warm, rounded and ready to drink.',7,NULL,0,'Portada Winemaker\'s Selection',196807),
(273208,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/490x/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h3b/h27/11170676506654.png','A new bottling from the winery. The vineyard is in the Petaluma Gap, a cool area south of the Russian River Valley, toward San Francisco. The vintage was cool, too, so the wine is brisk in acidity and low in alcohol, but it still tastes amazingly ripe and complex. The wine dazzles with waves of black raspberry jam, sweet olive tapenade, sautéed brown mushroom, root beer, moo-shu plum sauce and mocha. If those flavors sound like they don\'t go together, just try the wine. It\'s seamless and compelling. Drink now–2020.',55,NULL,0,'Terra de Promissio Vineyard',196626),
(273243,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Big and black-colored, this is a blockbuster in both looks and mouthfeel. It\'s dense, concentrated and packed with juicy fruit that\'s touched by a note of pepper due to the alcohol. It needs a few years to age, although it will always be an in-your-face wine.',15,NULL,0,'Andrez Reserva',196685),
(273262,225996,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A bit muted and easy-drinking with soft notes of tart green apple and lemon peel throughout. It\'s brisk and prickly on the tongue with a fleeting finish; drink up.',10,NULL,0,'The Ruins',196845),
(273267,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Despite its light touch, this is fruity and full, with its blackberry fruit dominating the warm spice note and acidity. Soft tannins keep the wine together. Drink now. Screwcap.',6,NULL,0,'Coreto',196807),
(273370,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 60% Nero d\'Avola and 40% Merlot has a pretty fragrance of blue flower, black berry and baking spice. The simple palate is less expressive, offering fleeting wild cherry flavors.',16,NULL,0,'Calanican Nero d\'Avola & Merlot',196776),
(273384,223791,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A pale salmon color, this rosé shows ripe notes of cocoa-dusted cherry and strawberry alongside sweet citrus oil. Creamy and full in the mouth, it\'s a richer rosé that can stand up to heartier fare.',14,NULL,0,'Fantail Pinotage',196839),
(273548,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Plenty of crisp acidity balances the citrus, tropical fruit and pear flavors in this ripe Chardonnay. There\'s also a strong jacket of smoky oak with its buttered toast and vanilla richness. The result will please Chard lovers at a good price.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 361',196620),
(273581,219884,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/gvbWLI6NSXeQLxxau5869w_pb_x960.png','This is an attractively balanced apple- and pear-flavored wine. It is crisp, fruity and nicely creamy, with some bright acidity on the finish Drink now or age for a year.',6,NULL,0,'Coreto Branco',196807),
(273659,218228,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The price on this wine is laughable, but the quality is excellent. Earthy aromas of lead pencil, baked plum, cassis and black cherry include chocolate and minerality. The palate is rich, jammy and a touch stewy, with herbal blackberry, cassis, chocoalte and coffee flavors. Even more chocolate and licorice rise up on the long finish. Put this away until 2015, then drink through 2024.',400,NULL,0,'Viñedo Chadwick',196886),
(273716,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Smooth and round, this wine has bright acidity, tempered by the toast and sweet apricot flavors. It has a structured core, and it finishes with the acidity. Age this for 2–3 years.',45,NULL,0,'Charmois Premier Cru',197408),
(273738,219884,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/HTGrVuF3QzS5GghKUMIK1Q_pb_x600.png','This is rich and smooth, with rounded and ripe fruit. Red apple, banana and lime flavors work together to yield a wine that\'s ready to drink.',8,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Branco',196807),
(273751,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is fruity, with pear and baked apple flavors that lend a rich, spicy character. It has some weight along with an attractive touch of acidity.',8,NULL,0,'Segada Branco',196807),
(273851,226118,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz',NULL,'A hot and dark wine with raisiny notes of plum, date and kirsch. The tannins are firm and the finish gripping.',32,NULL,0,'Passioné',197445),
(273863,217265,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A robust, rustic red wine for drinking now with stews, burgers, vegetarian rice and bean dishes in red sauce. The winery doesn\'t tell us the varietal blend, but it\'s ripened to the limits of raisins, and high in alcohol, with a resulting glyceriny sweetness.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 348 Field Blend',196620),
(273888,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Full, rich and round, this is packed with ripe yellow-fruit flavors, layered with toast. It bears a spice note, delicious acidity and a concentrated, open finish. Let it age for 2–3 years, but it is also enjoyable now.',105,NULL,0,'Bouchères Premier Cru',197408),
(274113,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Rich and textured, the wine is spicy with a burnt, smoky character. The fruit is quiet, just hinting at citrus.',20,NULL,0,'Les Genevrières',197254),
(274143,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EjICDuKfTk-SaBEOpdlJXA_pb_x960.png','Floral aromas of cassis and plum are open, spicy and complex, with a balsamic accent. This feels solid as a rock, with firm tannins and a lively flavor profile that includes blackberry, baked notes, spice and cocoa powder. On the finish, oak is reflected through flavors of vanilla and mocha. Drink from 2014–2022.',90,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Founder\'s Reserva',196886),
(274184,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a lightweight, fruity and softly tannic wine. The red berry flavor is bright and breezy, and the acidity is a dominant feature. Screwcap.',10,NULL,0,'Brigando',196807),
(274185,219884,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Fruity and off-dry, this has light touches of sweet strawberry and vanilla to go with the orange zest acidity. Screwcap.',8,NULL,0,'Pink Elephant',196807),
(274190,219884,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Smooth, rounded and dry, this has plum and strawberry flavors. Full in the mouth and touched by spice, this is a rosé for food.',8,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano',196807),
(274191,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A rounded wine, this gives pleasure with its pear and ripe apple flavors. Lightly touched with acidity, this has a soft finish.',9,NULL,0,'Point West',196807),
(274310,218569,'other','Pinot Noir','https://static.wineaccess.com/optimized/images/products/2022/08/2020_Williams_Selyem_Pinot_Noir_Estate_Vineyard_Russian_River_Valley_Bottleshot_1/89d5c7515172d2adab085dffdc5c671d.png','From the winery\'s own Westside Road vineyard, formerly called Litton, comes this grandiose, if immature, Pinot Noir. In its youth it\'s all about primary, jammy raspberry and cherry fruit. On the edges are fine acidity, smooth tannins and a perfect appliqué of oak. Shows the hallmarks of this great, emerging vineyard, but needs serious time to come around. Try after 2015.',100,NULL,0,'Estate Vineyard',196626),
(274353,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Big in every sense, this powerful, almost black-colored wine is solid, packed with dry tannins and ripe fruit. Made from Alicante Bouschet, it is a rich, opulent wine, with a strong spice, pepper and fruit character. This blockbuster needs aging, so drink from 2018.',77,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezirias 1836 Grande Reserva',196685),
(274358,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.alhamracellar.com/wp-content/uploads/7231614.png','As per usual, Don Melchor is singing a pretty tune. Deep, dense aromas of floral berry fruits and tarry darkness are solid and complete. Pure, elegant and confident across the palate, this delivers firm cassis, plum and cherry flavors backed by a toasty finish accented by licorice. This is rich and brawny but not heavy; drink through 2023.',125,NULL,0,'Don Melchor Puente Alto Vineyard',196852),
(274377,219884,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/0A36CzPeQpGfaYcrD_6ysw_pb_x960.png','This is a rounded, full-bodied rosé that also has a herbal element. It has a wild strawberry flavor, with light acidity and sweetness. Screwcap.',6,NULL,0,'Coreto',196807),
(274398,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A typical local blend of Arinto, Fernão Pires and Chardonnay, this is smooth, ripe and creamy. It has touches of herb, honey and pineapple, which are laced together by citrusy acidity. The finish is soft.',15,NULL,0,'Catapereiro Escolha',196685),
(274512,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This Brouilly is light and smooth in character. The wine has hints of tannins under the bright cherry fruits, fresh acidity and open texture. It\'s not a wine for aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château du Prieuré',197404),
(274544,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Very soft and easy going, this has rounded peach and apple flavors. The acidity is light, hinting at citrus. Screwcap.',8,NULL,0,'Storks Landing',196807),
(274589,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/05/cdp-2018-min.png','Price aside, this is a fine, ready to drink, full-bodied Carmenère with earth, cola, tree bark, cherry and cassis aromas. It\'s full and a touch soft in the mouth, with easy tannins and bold flavors of blackberry, herbs, bitter chocolate and leather. On the finish, it\'s peppery tasting and mildly herbal. Drink now through 2016.',200,NULL,0,'Carmín de Peumo',196852),
(274601,217839,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/R23mx_22STKFW2-stzsEmQ_pb_x960.png','Pure, alluring aromas of minerally black fruits, lavender, cola, fir tree and pepper combine to form a highly inviting bouquet. This doesn\'t fall off in the mouth, where it\'s more fresh and bouncy than heavy. Flavors of dark berry fruits, herbs and chocolate end in a rich, grabby, textured finish. Drink this lusty but elegant Syrah now through 2016.',22,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(274763,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Very soft and dull, it offers white fruits and some acidity. Drink now.',24,NULL,0,'En Paradis',197254),
(274921,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/cTmtDbjiTyWf4MQM1Tki0g_pb_x960.png','There is a touch of minerality in this wine as well as a dry edge and ripe red-fruit flavors that are already attractive. It should be aged at least three years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos de l\'Ermitage',196775),
(274971,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'The top-of-the-range red from Casa de Santar estate in homage to the first count of Santar in the 18th century. It is a powerfully velvet wine, very elegant, packed with ripe tannins, dark fruits and a structure that demands aging. Keep for at least six years.',60,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Conde de Santar',196794),
(274983,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','In a soft and jammy style, packed with red berries and given a plummy juiciness. The structure is here, the fruit hanging on to it, giving the wine a gentle, final feel.',NULL,NULL,0,'Aux Clous Premier Cru',196775),
(274988,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A well-balanced rich wine, showing the ripe fruit of 2009, giving sweet plums, ripe acidity and some firm, structured tannins. It is even worth aging for a few months.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Riaz',197404),
(275031,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/E_4ALVmmTj2vU23PRMwoLw_pb_x960.png','One of the strengths of cool Beira Interior is that it produces powerful wines without the attendant alcohol of warmer climates. That\'s apparent with this intense, dark wine. Blending Touriga Nacional and Tinta Roriz, the dense and brooding wine with its rich blackberry fruitiness alongside dry, mineral tannins is a study in concentration and needs to age. Drink from 2018.',55,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo Grande Escolha',196663),
(275047,218228,'other','Red Blend','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/x1000,sq/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h06/h78/9681594253342.png','Smooth, deep aromas of berry, spice, earth and minerals are rolled into a pure, harmonious whole. This Cabernet Sauvignon-led blend is racy, clean and layered on the tongue, while oaky flavors of vanilla and cream are backed by ribald blackberry and cassis. The elegant finish is potent and deep. Drink through 2020.',90,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Founder\'s Reserva',196886),
(275117,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Amazingly ripe and deep wine from 2004, so it\'s all that it\'s going to be. Thick and figgy aromas bring bacon, mint and cool, cushiony cola notes. The palate is megasaturated with chocolaty oak and dark berry power galore. Remains oaky on the finish; a massive wine to drink now through 2017.',42,NULL,0,'Alfa Crux Red Wine',196852),
(275144,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Zk0uchRVS6Czz0T5dD_f5g_pb_x960.png','Ripe and soft wine, flavored with prune and black plums and a sweet jelly flavor. The wine has open, soft tannins and some good ripeness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Adélie Champs Martin Premier Cru',196775),
(275145,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A finely structured wine that has firm tannins to go with the ripe juicy red fruits. Bitter cherry and crisp acidity fit easily together, while the dry core comes out strongly in the aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château de Nervers',197404),
(275191,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Hur7CFP1QeW3mmT02QcDTA_pb_x960.png','Big, black and juicy, it manages to be both dense and structured and freshly fruity at the same time. With this combination promising great things, the wine is ripe and fragrant. The dark color from the Petit Verdot in the blend follows through to the firm texture while allowing room for refreshing juiciness. Drink from 2017.',55,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas Grande Escolha',196663),
(275198,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Almost black in color, this is a powerful and concentrated wine. Named after the barn owl that is found in the woods around the vines, it is packed with dense and dry tannins. Acidity comes from the black currant fruit while perfumes come from the Touriga Nacional in the blend. Drink this complex wine from 2017.',23,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezirias Tyto Alba',196685),
(275220,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Montagny produces wines that have a warm, southern feel. This full-bodied wine is packed with flavors of yellow fruits, and it offers ripe acidity and a touch of toast. The finish shows a limestone-like minerality.',NULL,NULL,0,'Premier Cru',197408),
(275266,217625,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'The Dão region has some superb expressions of Touriga Nacional and this is one of them. With its richly perfumed fruit, dusty tannins, spiced damson and blueberry flavors, this is a great wine, ready for drinking in another 4–5 years.',20,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Touriga Nacional',196794),
(275267,226362,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A stunning wine loaded with nuance and complexity, Fusion V is a blend of 56% Cabernet Sauvignon, 20% Cabernet Franc, 12% Malbec, 7% Merlot and 5% Petit Verdot. Spicy accents of leather, tobacco and cured meat add intrigue to the dark fruit core, while pepper and sweet licorice spice infuse the long finish. It\'s textured like crushed velvet with a firm structure of dusty tannins that linger. Drink now–2014.',50,NULL,0,'Fusion V',196689),
(275277,217512,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'From vineyards in the Douro Superior, this is a powerful wine showing its rugged terroir, with dark fruit and tannin, hints of wood aging and packed, concentrated flavors. From a great Douro vintage, this is worth cellaring over 3–4 years.',16,NULL,0,'Fronteira Selecção de Enólogo',196663),
(275278,217512,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'In recorded existence since 1498, Quinta de Pancas produces wonderfully balanced wine. This winemaker\'s selection is for aging, very dark and dense, powered with berry fruits and tight tannins. Who says it\'s impossible to find ageworthy wines at reasonable prices?',15,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas Selecção do Enólogo',196663),
(275303,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'There is no question about the wood here. It dominates the aroma and the palate, burying the fruit in a smooth, vanilla character. It is a pleasure to drink, but seems to have removed itself from Beaujolais.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cuvée Elevé en Fût de Chêne',197404),
(275313,217512,'other','Touriga Nacional','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Fc8onnygT5K9EnvRrr9YyA_pb_x960.png','A beautifully ripe and complex wine, this 100% Touriga Nacional from the mountainous interior shows great elegance and fragrance along with power and richness. It brings out the granite terroir with its strongly mineral, steely texture, still giving room for the black currant fruit. Drink this ageworthy wine from 2017.',30,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo Reserva',196663),
(275410,226362,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Cocoa-dusted black cherry and berry aromas hit you first in the bouquet, followed by soft notes of black tea, violets and licorice shortly after. Full and rich in the mouth, the fruit is intense and juicy, framed by a lush but firm structure and balanced acidity hinting at the life that this wine still has to come. Long finish with a peppery back note.',35,NULL,0,'Z',196689),
(275413,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Myh4L41rS2GnV3i90ube1Q_pb_x960.png','Like other wines in the Fronteira range, this is certainly powerful. It is also ripely smooth, its dark tannins wrapped in a velvet, dusty texture and ripe plum juice fruits. Important, complex wine.',45,NULL,0,'Quinta da Fronteira Grande Escolha',196663),
(275420,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Want dense tannins? Then this your wine. Of course, it has much more than that. It has mineral-driven stone fruit flavors, a sense of terroir, of restrained power. It also has a serious side, and definite aging potential.',18,NULL,0,'Escada',196807),
(275507,218035,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/qDdzS6RwRDqapnrUHxh0GQ_pb_x600.png','Loamy, dark, rich aromas of pastry, blackberry, blueberry and turned earth scream “ripe.” In the mouth, this is bulky but focused. Flavors of black fruits, chocolate, fig, herbs and spice finish with notes of tobacco, raw oak, mint and bright acidity. Drink now through 2019.',90,NULL,0,'Folly',196713),
(275597,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Mining a rich vein of sweet black plum fruits, this is big and powerful while held together with firm tannins, very ripe fruit, a smoky wood character and a ripe, juicy finish. Age for 4–5 years.',80,NULL,0,'Quinta de Cabriz Four C',196794),
(275622,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/h0T8o1sXTnuaEJIJRVPuKQ_pb_x960.png','The classic Douro blend of Touriga Nacional, Touriga Franca and Tinta Roriz has created a solid, dense and very structured wine. Black plums dominate on the fruit spectrum, supported by dry tannins. Fragrant and fresh, it\'s a wine to age. Drink from 2017.',40,NULL,0,'Quinta da Fronteira Reserva',196663),
(275623,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Deep, alluring aromas of blackberry and cassis are youthful and thus a bit animal and wild. In the mouth, this young CS is chunky, rubbery and dense. Flavors of blackberry, cassis and black coffee are on the dark side, while the finish offers a meaty, substantive feel, tons of lasting fruit flavor, and a touch of heat and burn that will fade away with more time in bottle. Best from 2016–2022.',50,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Andes Pirque Vineyard Block Las Terrazas',196852),
(275631,217839,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Cola, spice, wild berry, herb and graphite aromas are powerful and raring to go. This feels racy, juicy and tangy, with a mix of oak, herb, tomato, leather and savory berry flavors. A long, herbal, chocolaty finish is pure in feel and offers a fine conclusion to this cool-climate wine. Drink through 2018.',50,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Costa Los Boldes Vineyard Block 3',196852),
(275632,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3OMisWgFQzOohbmCKM8k8g_pb_x960.png','Minerally citrus aromas are the greeting on this high-end, pure SB. Stony minerality and citric acidity make for a fresh, polished mouthfeel, while flavors of lime, passion fruit and grapefruit are focused and smooth, and not at all soft. When people talk about fine cool-climate Chilean SB, this is what they should be referencing.',30,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Costa Los Boldos Vineyard Block 5',196852),
(275639,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A perfumed wine, it has a rich, rounded character packed with yellow fruit. Layers of wood add complexity and density. The wine is named for the white owl found in the nature reserve close to the vineyards.',16,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Tyto Alba',196685),
(275699,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is made using a selection of fruit that\'s sourced from both banks of the Serein River. It\'s a properly crisp Chardonnay, and it offers a white fruit flavor and a bright, lively finish.',35,NULL,0,'Les Deux Rives',197408),
(275711,218228,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4UcZNQ6lSqaDgZCRe_UmVw_pb_x600.png','Stewed red berries and an herbal streak define the nose, which also offers carob and spice notes. The palate feels mostly deep and padded, with layering and flavors of herbs, pepper, spice and plum. A meaty, herbal finish with a tomato paste quality is the final act.',20,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(275760,218035,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/jmKZlGApSlSVDlSbUbe5JA_pb_x960.png','This Cabernet-led blend is Montes\' new icon wine from Marchigue in the Colchagua Valley. It is ripe, warm, leathery and earthy, with aromas of aged cheese, tobacco, raisin and cedar. The mouth is hefty and bold, with a mix of coffee and herbal flavors as well as cassis and blackberry. The finish is heavy and a bit raisiny, with depth and density. Drink now through 2015.',300,NULL,0,'Taita Wisdom in Wine Marchigue Vineyard',196713),
(275763,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/SvE3x-cEQ6KB_2zAsB1NYw_pb_x960.png','As with other wines from Quinta do Cardo, this is packed with minerals and a dark, stony texture. It is concentrated, full of intense acidity and powerful tannins. Rich, it conveys a genuine sense of aging potential. Don\'t drink before 2018.',16,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo Selecção do Enólogo',196663),
(275776,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A ripe, smoky wine, full of sweet jelly berry fruit. It is rounded and rich, a delicious wine that rolls easily around the mouth.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos des Quatre Vents',197404),
(275790,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'White and black is the name, but that hardly does justice to this richly ripe wine that fills the glass with its heady perfumes. Tannic, yes, but also fruity, with concentrated plum fruits and a tight structure. Age for 3–4 years.',15,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Preto Branco Reserva',196794),
(275792,222330,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 52% Cabernet Sauvignon, 16% Malbec, 14% Merlot, 13% Petit Verdot and 5% Cabernet Franc offers a minty character that prevails among the intense black plum and berry aromas and flavors. Well-integrated, with a decadent crushed velvet texture and a long oak-kissed finish reminiscent of dark chocolate-covered cherries.',20,NULL,0,'Grand Classique',197445),
(275824,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Syrah',NULL,'A good, sound red wine, dry and full-bodied, with green herb, blackberry, blueberry, spice and oak flavors. It\'s easy to drink with a nice steak or burger, and a good value for the price.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 208',196620),
(275829,217839,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/khexoeEARCOt3lDqm5doIw_pb_x960.png','Crisp plum and berry aromas are a little sharp while the oak element on the nose is drying. The palate is tight and fairly high in acidity, yielding herbal, minty flavors of raspberry and red plum. Short and solid on the finish, but clean and good overall.',12,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserva',196852),
(275830,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'For simple SB, this is a good value with legitimate aromas of lime, green apple and mineral. The palate has a round feel along with good acids, so the flavors of lemon, tangerine and melon are lifted and fresh. About as honest as you\'ll get in under-$10 Sauvignon Blanc.',8,NULL,0,'Xplorador',196852),
(275917,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Certainly rich, but also finely structured, it keeps its exuberant fruit firmly in check with dry tannins, dense texture and a fresh edge of acidity. With this structure, this is a great, rich, meat-friendly wine.',80,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Encontro I',196794),
(275934,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Ripe and also tannic, this is structured wine, its berry fruits pushing through a dry plum skin texture. It is solid and chunky while remaining fresh and fruity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château des Vierres',197404),
(275935,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A surprisingly dumb wine, not giving much beyond very dry tannins. The result is a wine that has bitterness, with dark chocolate and bitter cherry fruits. Will it open up? Maybe, but the jury is still out.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de la Tour du Bief',197404),
(275943,217203,'other','Alvarinho',NULL,'Still young, this wine brings out the ripe and creamy side of Alvarinho. Its citrus character is prominent along with a strong mineral texture. Weight from the skin contact during fermentation has produced a dense structure. Keep this wine until 2015.',22,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Nostalgia',196685),
(275968,218569,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is a rare premier release from the winery\'s new vineyard. It\'s a blend of different clones, and only 47 cases were produced. The wine is very exotic. It shows tiers of raspberries and cherries, but also more feral notes, of dried meats or leather, mushrooms, tart balsam, tangy minerals and scads of dusty, sweet Indian spices. Tannic and dry, it should unfold slowly over the next 10 years.',68,NULL,0,'Block 10 Mass Selection Estate Vineyard',196626),
(276004,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/wTUIE5yaTs-UL6LccSN3nQ_pb_x960.png','A fruity wine, this has exuberant red-berry flavors that suggest this wine can be consumed now. Gentle tannins balance the fine acidity and rich, warm texture.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Charmes',196775),
(276065,217625,'other','Encruzado',NULL,'Encruzado is the Dão\'s star white grape, able to produce, as here, a wine that combines a great sense of style, some weight, along with the freshest of lemon tints. There is some fullness as well, while the final taste is crisp.',15,NULL,0,'Cabriz Encruzado',196794),
(276066,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A new brand from an old estate for DFJ Vinhos, Rocio is powerfully dark colored, complex and concentrated. Tannins are contained within a structure that is initially severe and then round out into juicy black currant flavors, always tempered with firm tannins.',18,NULL,0,'Quinta do Rocio',196807),
(276108,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_600x600.png','Electric purple in color, it conveys wiry aromas of wet dog, green herbs and berry fruits. The palate is loud and clacky, with a jumpy overall feel and an overriding sense of youth. Boysenberry, blueberry and blackberry flavors come with undertones of green herbs and licorice, while the finish is aggressive and moderately complex. Drink through 2019.',50,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Entre Cordilleras Peumo Vineyard Block 27',196852),
(276180,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.santaema.cl/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Detalle_G_R_CS.png\r\n\r\nReserve','A touch green and herbal/spicy on the nose, with lively red berry and plum aromas. Snappy and zesty on the palate, with red berry, citrus and herbal olive at the base. Finishes solid, with some heat. Juicy, healthy and herbal.',14,NULL,0,'Reserve',196857),
(276193,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/eF-rJX83QqiL3kYd0F7Ljw_pb_x960.png','This bold wine opens with a blast of black fruit and cassis, and then dry spice and herbal aromas settle in. This is racy in the mouth, with a good body and flavors of red plum, raspberry, spice and herbs. It\'s acid-driven and fairly elegant on the way out.',NULL,NULL,0,'Gran Reserva Serie Riberas Ribera del Cachapoal',196852),
(276214,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Made from old vines (Vinhas Velhas), this is a seriously concentrated wine, showing structure and acidity as well as red berry fruits. The wine is juicy, firm-textured and ageworthy. Keep for 3–4 years.',15,NULL,0,'Lua Nova em Vinhas Velhas',196685),
(276241,226517,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Herbal notes mingle with aromas of kirsch, violet, tobacco and tanned hide. Sweet spice and pepper unfold on the palate, integrating seamlessly with the black fruit flavors. The structure is firm but not too tough or unapproachable now, with medium acidity and a long, lingering finish.',24,NULL,0,'Philosophers\' Stone',196689),
(276257,217512,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'Pure Touriga Nacional, firm while also fruity, this is an intense, aromatic and finely perfumed, smokey wine. The wood aging has softened the tannins while keeping the structure.',21,NULL,0,'Quinta da Pancas Reserva',196663),
(276266,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Packed with strawberry aromas and red berry fruits, this is a ripe, fruit-forward wine only lightly disturbed by tannins. There is a great juicy quality here.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château des Bachelards',197404),
(276297,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/IRF_lbU0SLyMyVsl91epGg_pb_x960.png','Gears up with basic aromas of apple and tropical fruit. The palate is round and a little syrupy in feel, with candied, sweet flavors of melon and banana. Has the weight and sweetness to offer mass appeal.',12,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserva',196852),
(276350,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fKLM_albTgimoq25S_qYNA_pb_x960.png','This is fresh and juicy while also having structure; a mineral edge to the texture gives power. Acidity and juiciness both contribute to the ripe, full-bodied mix. The wood-aging is too dominant at this stage, so give the wine several years. Drink from 2017.',20,NULL,0,'Quinta da Fronteira Selecção do Enólogo',196663),
(276351,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/e-IyNuNBSoKslsknS7RiMQ_pb_x960.png','Big, bold and ripe, it has concentrated fruit flavors that give black plum juice and acidity, while the tannins still show strength and power. The blend of Syrah, Alicante Bouschet and Aragonez is coming together richly and with density. It needs to age, so don\'t drink before 2016.',17,NULL,0,'Portas da Herdade Reserva',196663),
(276374,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Black-colored wine, showing the rich minerality of the Douro and its impressively structured fruit. Cranberry acidity mixes with black berry and a firm tannic core. Age for 2–3 years or more.',9,NULL,0,'Vega Reserva',196807),
(276376,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Almost Port-like in its rich aromas, this is a concentrated and sweet wine, filled with dark chocolate, bitter licorice and chewy berry fruits. Age for at least four years.',25,NULL,0,'Grande Encontro',196794),
(276377,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Dão Sul\'s showpiece quinta in Santar has produced this mellifluous, rich wine, with wood flavors that are married to yellow fruits, cantaloupe melon and a hint of acidity.',35,NULL,0,'Paça dos Cunhas de Santar Vinha do Contador',196794),
(276385,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'An equal blend of wine fermented in stainless steel and fermented in wood (hence Consensus), this is finely balanced. Its apple and apricot fruits have great acidity, while also rich, fruity and structured. The finish is lingering, fresh.',13,NULL,0,'Consensus',196807),
(276427,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'The wine shows bitter fruits, a layer of dry tannins as well as attractive acidity. It has a touch of spice over the juicy, fruity aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Château du Grand Vernay',197404),
(276487,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is heavily wood dominated. Toast and juice come from wood as much as fruit at this stage. Behind this, generous yellow fruits and a ripe, full-bodied character will lead to a ripe and complex wine. It needs aging, so don\'t drink before 2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Secretum',196685),
(276627,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EzEry-KjRimH3QmiLKaiLQ_pb_x960.png','Grapey aromas suggest boysenberry, and soon comes a wave of forced, minty oak. The palate is aggressive at first, with heavy, bullish flavors of minty wild berry and coconut. Falls off on the finish, leaving tannic bite and warmth.',12,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(276643,219884,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This is a powerful, solid wine from selected fruit that brings out ripe black currant flavors and a dense structure. The ripe Cabernet Sauvignon has plenty of acidity to give a juicy edge to the dry tannins and rich texture. Spice comes from wood aging. It needs to age, so drink from 2016.',10,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Grande Reserva',196807),
(276653,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Intense and crisp, it shows bright fruits and some weight as well. A touch of yellow fruits give the grapefruit a warmer character and good depth of flavor. It\'s a Vinho Verde for cooler days, ripe and ready for food.',18,NULL,0,'Maria Papoila Escolha',196685),
(276666,217839,'other','Riesling','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/xoJWvRR1TqK6QykkXPsPFw_pb_x960.png','This first-time Riesling from CyT delivers petrol/diesel aromas along with mild apple and peach scents on what amounts to a true, varietal nose. The palate has a punch-like, juicy feel that\'s fresh but light, while tropical flavors of lychee and mango end juicy but with weight.',NULL,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Costa Los Boldos Vineyard Block 6',196852),
(276678,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A brute of a wine, both in its immense flavors and its excessively weighty bottle. It has richness, full of concentrated sweet plum juice and dense tannins—very rich, very in your face.',45,NULL,0,'Monte da Cal Vinha de Saturno',196794),
(276689,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-tQxWTN6Qo26fnE0VZR8AA_pb_x960.png','Perfumed wine, from both wood and Touriga Nacional in the blend. This is serious stuff, offering firm, dry tannins as well as balanced black currant fruit and a dusty texture.',20,NULL,0,'Herdade de Farizoa Reserva',196663),
(276702,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Black on the bouquet, with charred aromas vying with pepper and blackberry. Feels good but choppy, with firm acidity and solid flavors of wild berry, plum, vanilla and chocolate. Fades on the finish with class; a pure and appealing blend of Cabernet, Merlot and Carignan.',25,NULL,0,'Centauri',196852),
(276738,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A smooth, fruity wine, with fine red-cherry flavors and very soft tannins. It is spoiled by a banana flavor that intrudes into the fresh fruit.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Buyats',197404),
(276772,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/rQfTlWMMRWCJzq17iGvmLg_pb_x960.png','This is full of citrus flavors, with toast and pineapple touches. It\'s attractive, crisp and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Secret de Famille',196775),
(277003,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'The name astrolabe is a reference to the instrument\'s importance to the Portuguese navigators as they rounded the world in the 15th century. The wine is more earthbound, tied firmly to the Dão grapes and a finely structured character.',8,NULL,0,'Astrolábium Reserva',196794),
(277098,222420,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Herbs, pepper, cedar and smoked sausage on the nose and palate give this Cabernet a rustic, inviting character. Flavors are delivered in a mouthfilling, layered way on the tongue, with lots of spice and cedar in the finish. Good minerality and balance mean it\'s not overpowering for food.',23,NULL,0,'Finlayson Family Vineyards',196689),
(277103,222690,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This bright, mouthwatering red starts with cherry, cocoa and cedar on the nose, followed by ripe berries, spice and pepper on the palate. Supple and expressive, the wine will pair well with stews, burgers and lamb.',35,NULL,0,'Boet Erasmus',196878),
(277114,222429,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Savory and rich aromas of balsamic, crushed herbs, cherries and plums are followed by spice, violets and plum flavors. Round and hearty with medium tannins, the wine has a friendly but elegant character.',82,NULL,0,'The Stork',196689),
(277119,226635,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The Proprietor\'s Blend starts with an intriguing nose of sweet cedar, black currant and violet, followed by classic flavors of black fruit, leather and spice. Good tannins and minerality keep it elegant but ageable. An impressive balance of New and Old World styles.',37,NULL,0,'Proprietor\'s Blend',196689),
(277130,222333,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A luscious nose of rich red berry, pepper and black currant is followed by velvety, mouthfilling flavors of tobacco, anise and red berries. Fruity but balanced by good acidity. Pair with lasagna, pizza or ribs. Ready to drink now.',38,NULL,0,'Flagship',197368),
(277136,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Zk0uchRVS6Czz0T5dD_f5g_pb_x960.png','Soft and ripe, this has light tannins, red berry fruit and a round texture. It has a touch of firmness, acidity and good density. Drink now, or age it for 2–3 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Adélie',196775),
(277192,217625,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'A wine that brings out the mineral character of Touriga Nacional in the Dão. It has a dark quality to it, with some austerity, although the weight of fruit acts as a fine counterbalance.',25,NULL,0,'Cabriz',196794),
(277193,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Gently ripe red fruits envelop the firmer tannins with this velvet-textured wine. There is generosity, an open feel to it, emphasized by the ripe berry fruits and delicious final acidity.',15,NULL,0,'Paça dos Cunhas de Santar Nature',196794),
(277238,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Three barrels were made of this structured, tannic wine that offers a juicy balance between acidity and dark tannins. It is perfumed with acidity that cuts through the red berry and dry concentration. It is a dense wine, full of fruit. Drink from 2019.',160,NULL,0,'Les Beaux Monts Premier Cru',197254),
(277261,218569,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'The vineyard is known for its Pinot Noirs, but winemaker Bob Cabral says this is a singular block. The wine is one of the finer California Chenin Blancs, bone dry, moderate in alcohol, and clean in mineral-inspired citrus fruits. It\'s a complex and unusual alternative to Sauvignon Blanc or Pinot Grigio.',25,NULL,0,'Limestone Ridge at Vista Verde Vineyard',196626),
(277281,224517,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An eternal crowd pleaser, the Chocolate Block starts with alluring aromas of violet, anise, black currant and mocha, leading into bold layers of smoke, cherry, chocolate and spice. Elegant but with backbone, this wine will age nicely.',39,NULL,0,'The Chocolate Block',197456),
(277310,222635,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Made from fruit sourced in the Côte de Beaune, this is a soft, fruity wine, with approachable red berry fruit. It is ripe, full bodied and just lightly tannic. The acidity gives the finish a clean cut.',28,NULL,0,'Cuvée Margot',197408),
(277321,223438,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This Swartland red offers aromas of spice and red cherry/berry aromas, followed by vanilla, cherry and pepper flavors. Soft and smooth, the wine is a good everyday red sip that will pair well with myriad meat and game dishes.',35,NULL,0,'Zinfandel - Syrah',197368),
(277351,223250,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Black currant leaf and juicy plum guts abound on the nose of this Bordeaux-style blend, and those aromas transition into the dominating flavors of the palate alongside suggestions of pepper and sweet smoked meat. Balanced, with fine tannins and a clean but lingering finish.',19,NULL,0,'Lady in Red',197557),
(277353,222420,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This blend of 38% Sauvignon Blanc, 44% Sémillon and 13% Viognier is ripe but balanced with brisk acidity and lively citrus flavors against the tropical fruit and melon backbone. Prickly grapefruit flavors dominate the mouthwatering finish. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'The Honey Pot',196689),
(277508,222652,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Luscious aromas of plum, cedar, blueberry and cloves give this wine a sultry start. Integrated spice and dark fruit flavors are structured but rich and mouthfilling. A spin of cocoa powder on the finish adds character.',30,NULL,0,'L\'Amour Toujours',196839),
(277512,222151,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A savory, masculine nose of black currant, cloves and spice lead into flavors of black fruit, spiced sausage and toast in this sexy Cabernet. Flavors are meaty, spicy but soft. Balanced but has a plucky, spicy backbone. Pair with lamb, steak, savory dishes.',38,NULL,0,'Cobblers Hill',196689),
(277635,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Tight and racy, with prickly herbal and bright berry aromas. This is a fun but serious wine; it\'s rugged and choppy in the mouth but full of life and spunk. Flavors of herbal berry, bramble, tea and spice are a tad  rustic, but it\'s still high-end and polished, with short-term aging potential. Drink now–2013.',28,NULL,0,'Centauri Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot-Carignan',196852),
(277645,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Mr6GWnJ1SUu5gzgGjmvSMw_pb_x960.png','This is a firm wine, but it has ripe red fruit. It shows an attractive touch of smoke, and there is fine balance between the firm tannins and fragrant fruit. Drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Secret de Famille',196775),
(277685,217265,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Solid, big and fruity, which is basically what a Campo de Borja Garnacha should be. Sweet red fruits and robust kick define the palate, which is tannic but not obtrusively so. Zesty and a bit of a one-noter, but a nice one. Garnacha with 30% Syrah and 10% Mourvèdre.',10,NULL,0,'Lot 98',196620),
(277846,226517,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Red berry, anise and spice on the nose and palate give this Cabernet, Cabernet Franc and Merlot blend an easy drinking but distinctive character. A touch of smoke and a lingering, spicy finish add to its appeal. Pair with smoked ribs, sharp cheeses.',19,NULL,0,'Philosophers\' Stone',196689),
(277851,223582,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Dark and delicious, with aromas of cherry, blackberry and vanilla and an elegant array of cigarbox, cedar, spice and smoke on the palate. Lively and structured, with a lingering finish of tobacco and berries. Pair with barbecue and ripe, soft cheeses.',11,NULL,0,'Cocoa Hill',196689),
(277855,222421,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The ever-creative Charles Back scores again with this blend of Shiraz, Cabernet, Merlot, Barbera and Primitivo. The nose offers red currant, cinnamon, cherry and vanilla, and on the palate, friendly fruit flavors are finished with a blast of fiery spice. The wine can age but is good today with spicy ribs, beef and assertive flavors.',13,NULL,0,'The Goatfather',197456),
(277856,222429,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Beautiful, brooding and with a bit of an edge, the Gravel Hill starts with aromas of smoke, cloves, black currant and pepper, leading into a layered, savory array of rich spice and black fruit. Elegant but assertive, the wine has a distinctive South African character, with a touch of Old World minerality and restraint.',139,NULL,0,'Gravel Hill',196689),
(277872,222540,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Alex Dale\'s Burgundian sensibilities keep the Radford Dale line poised and pretty, and this blend of Cabernet, Merlot, Shiraz and Viognier is no exception. On the nose, smoked sausage, fennel, rich red berries and spice; on the palate, the wine offers ample fruit but is backed by a clean minerality that weaves it all together in a neat package.',50,NULL,0,'Gravity',196689),
(277915,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'One heck of a value, this elegant, spicy Cabernet comes alive with tobacco and blackberry flavors that broaden in scope and flavor as you sip. Ample tannins and acidity round out the smooth texture. The wine is deeply colored, aromatically inviting and completely satisfying on the finish.',15,NULL,0,'Collection',196620),
(277922,218569,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Quite a good Zinfandel, although it does show some of the weaknesses that strike this vineyard in a cool year. You\'ll find a smooth, full-bodied wine, with ample tannins and fine berry-cherry fruit and spices. Yet it\'s curiously ambiguous in the mouth, and the concentration falls apart midpalate.',50,NULL,0,'Forchini Vineyard North Flats',196626),
(277934,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From a single vineyard now designated as a monopole, this wine by winemaker Bill Brousseau, who designed the vineyard, and vintners Rob Jensen and Kirk Williams shows minty herbs and tangerine oil on the nose. There is great restraint on the palate that walks a razor\'s edge of balance, with flavors of tart Key lime pith and riper orange blossom.',48,NULL,0,'Dos Rubios Vineyard Monopole',196639),
(277941,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This dense wine has a strong sense of dry tannins as well as red-berry acidity. It is balanced, in keeping with the cherry and strawberry fruits. The acidity, cutting through, keeps the wine bright and fruity. The end is strawberry jam with attractive acidity. Drink from 2018.',90,NULL,0,'Les Chaillots Premier Cru',197254),
(278000,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This wine has earthy aromas, and it\'s densely packed with dark chocolate and black plum flavors. The dense tannins still dominate, so give it a few months.',10,NULL,0,'Colleja',196685),
(278019,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjvr-cab-sauv-nv_1.png?itok=wZZFpV5e','A solid Cabernet, dry and full bodied, that shows the structure and flavors of more expensive bottlings. Rich in blackberries, currants and cedar, with hints of coffee and toffee and a touch of new oak.',20,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(278038,226801,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This bright, fruity blend starts with aromas of toasted vanilla and black cherry, followed by a rich, dark chocolate-covered cherry and spice palate. Anise and spice add to the appeal. A wine with aging potential that could also be drunk now with the right dish.',48,NULL,0,'De Wet',196954),
(278064,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Made from Caladoc and Tinta Roriz, this is a polished, while still fresh, wine. It\'s acidity points up the juicy berry fruits, the tannins almost an afterthought in this balanced, structured wine.',9,NULL,0,'Alta Corte',196807),
(278071,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Firm and structured, it has acidity allied to ripe black currant and berry fruits. With solid tannins in the background it needs time to soften. Drink from 2016.',8,NULL,0,'Portada Winemaker\'s Selection',196807),
(278165,218228,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AFyce1ZwRNmb6aVg7X-e8w_pb_600x600.png','A deep, dark Syrah with cola, spice, pepper, cedar and olive notes to go with more familiar blackberry and mocha. The palate is deep and pure, with juicy acidity pushing herbal berry and layered spice flavors. Has good flow and feel, and overall it strikes the right chords.',21,NULL,0,'Single Vineyard',196886),
(278221,222693,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend features aromas of vanilla, sweet tobacco and cherry followed by big, masculine flavors of cassis, raspberry, tobacco and cedar. Deep spice undertones add to the dimension of the wine. Ageable and intense and best paired with more robust meat dishes.',17,NULL,0,'Babylons Toren',197445),
(278236,222429,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Smooth, silky and inviting, the Ecurie offers aromas of pepper, tobacco, cedar and berry on the nose and pretty, approachable berry and spice flavors. Vibrant but elegant, the wine offers good structure and friendly fruit.',22,NULL,0,'Ecurie',196689),
(278237,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Deep, rich aromas of cloves, cedar and red berry start this elegant but exotic red blend from Cameron Hughes. On the palate, spicy fruit, smoke and a minerally backbone give it a poised character. Friendly but demands attention.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 104',196620),
(278258,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A wine that combines extreme fruitiness with more complex layers of wood, licorice, ripe spice, blackberries and a firm core of tannins.',10,NULL,0,'Monte da Cal',196794),
(278296,217512,'other','Siria',NULL,'Lightly straw-colored, this is a crisp and fruity wine. Apples, citrus and a touch of ripe melon dominate at this stage, giving a young, fresh character. It\'s still bouncy and tangy and will broaden out over the next few months to give more complexity. Drink from 2015',13,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo Branco',196663),
(278355,226846,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Sumptuous blackberry, cassis and mocha aromas and flavors are delivered in a smooth, lush wave in this sexy Cabernet. Balanced, approachable and ending with a lively, spicy finish, the wine is versatile and will pair well with game, roast lamb.',20,NULL,0,'Manor House',196839),
(278421,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/21CSO_low-335x1024.png','Warm butter and white peach aromas are cut by sea salt and brisk lemon-peel sharpness on this single-vineyard study by winemaker Bill Brousseau. Ripe apple, juicy lime, more salt and a crisp minerality mark the palate.',48,NULL,0,'Soberanes Vineyard',196639),
(278439,226862,'other','Rosé',NULL,'An interesting wine composed of 70% Chardonnay and 30% Pinot Noir. The bouquet offers notes of ripe red apple and soft toast alongside nuances of small red berries. Medium-weight with good balance and a dry but nutty finish. Drink now.',17,NULL,0,'Chardonnay-Pinot Noir',197599),
(278443,226863,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Red plum and strawberry are the main attraction in this fruit-forward wine, with secondary notes of crushed violets and soft black pepper. The mouth is velvety with fine tannins and medium acidity, followed by a clean, medium-length finish. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'DMZ',196839),
(278444,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'Soft, rich wine, with flavors of ripe plums, a touch of bell pepper, spice and tense acidity. Great drink-me-now wine.',9,NULL,0,'Point West',196807),
(278485,217780,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Loamy, soft aromas of plum and berry don\'t show much punch. In the mouth, this is mostly fresh, with a solid feel. Flavors of plum, raspberry, red currant and herbal notes skew toward red, while a punchy, bright finish is upbeat. This is 75% Cabernet Sauvignon, 18% Carmenère and 7% Cabernet Franc.',50,NULL,0,'Catalina',196857),
(278493,219884,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This full-bodied wine is rich with tropical fruit as well as a more citrus character. It\'s ripe, packed with apples, apricots and then cut with acidity. There is a cool, fresh aftertaste.',11,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(278494,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/GjX6YLfBROyllxs9K_czAg_pb_x960.png','Stony citrus and passion fruit aromas are a touch gritty. Overall, this is focused, minerally and green in nature. Flavors of lime and green mango finish with snap pea and a hint of jalapeño. Acidity and juiciness define the wine.',20,NULL,0,'Aconcagua Costa Single Vineyard',196886),
(278555,226879,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Aromas of red berry, wild cherry, clove and cinnamon give this Shiraz a stylish start. Flavors of red fruit, spice and anise are integrated and smooth. Well structured but drinkable now. The lingering finish offers pepper, anise and spice.',15,NULL,0,'Que Sera',196845),
(278652,217335,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/20CSB_low-1-335x1024.png','Made in a leaner, acidic, minerally style, this bone-dry wine feels ultra-clean and distinguished in the mouth. It\'s austere, but you\'ll find a core of pineapples, apples and limes. Great with a shellfish-inspired risotto. Elegant and food-friendly, it should develop over the next 4–5 years.',39,NULL,0,'Sanford & Benedict Vineyard',196639),
(278731,224396,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This robust red starts with aromas of coffee, smoke, leather and pepper followed by flavors of coffee, smoke, cedar and spicebox. A stylish wine with a taut edge.',45,NULL,0,'Saddle',197609),
(278735,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'A very nice Bordeaux-style blend ready to drink now. It\'s soft, dry and complex, offering waves of blackberries, black currants, blueberries, cedar and herbs, wrapped into fine, rich tannins.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 119',196620),
(278832,218426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/qicuK1S1QcS0vH-h78lrqg_pb_x600.png','A Meritage-style blend based mainly on Cabernet and Merlot, grown in Mendocino, Sonoma and Napa counties. Slightly rustic in tannic structure, it has sleek flavors of berries, currants, charred oak and spices. A pretty good value for this sweetly charming wine.',17,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve Alisium',196751),
(278888,218569,'other','Port','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/nAG5HiUXQbmNo0Qduf66Zg_pb_x960.png','Made using classic Port grape varieties, this is rich and sweet, with chocolate, coffee, orange, plum and spice flavors. Crisp acidity provides needed balance. It shows a complexity that lifts it above the ordinary. Drink now–2015.',40,NULL,0,'Mistral',196626),
(278895,226933,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Cabernet Franc',NULL,'This wine has rich flavors and aromas but an overall refined style. In the nose, savory pepper, coffee and a touch of cedar. On the palate, luscious flavors of cedar, coffee and pepper. An elegant wine with depth.',26,NULL,0,'Vernon Basson',197887),
(278983,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Rich and bold, it\'s a blend of Cabernet Sauvignon and Tinta Roriz, both giving a floral character as well as some concentrated tannins. The dry structure and the intense acidity at the end suggest some aging. Drink from 2015.',9,NULL,0,'Pedras do Monte',196807),
(279028,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'A Bordeaux-style blend made primarily from Merlot, plus Cabernet Sauvignon, Cabernet Franc and Malbec, this is layered with waves of blackberries, blueberries, currants, dark chocolate and oak flavors. The tannins are pure and refined. Production is 2,000 cases.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 335',196620),
(279143,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This structured, dense and smoky wine features dry tannins and a mineral texture. It has blackberry fruitiness to go with this scaffolding, so it will develop well to give a ripe, full, rich wine. Wait until 2015.',10,NULL,0,'Patamar Reserva',196807),
(279198,218035,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zvXeOTMVTqiVWi5YUZA-EQ_pb_x960.png','A bit rugged to start with, with solid berry and crusty dark aromatics. The palate has good size and cushion, with a creamy feel housing soft baked plum, herb, cough drop and vanilla flavors. A little woody on the finish, which fades with a modicum of grace. Neither edgy nor aggressive.',12,NULL,0,'Classic Series',196713),
(279307,218228,'other','Red Blend','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/x1000,sq/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h06/h78/9681594253342.png','Although this blend smells a bit loamy and earthy, there\'s plum, cherry and cinnamon aromas that are frontal in their attack. The palate is serious and tight, with medium-strength tannins and flavors of baked berry, spice and coffee. On the finish, pepper and olive notes enter the frame. Drink now–2017.',95,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Founder\'s Reserve',196886),
(279347,222668,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Intriguing aromas of sweet cedar, plum and spice start this approachable but poised Shiraz from Fairview. On the palate, the berry, spice and smoke flavors are rounded and soft, with a crisp minerality underneath. Food-friendly and a great everyday red.',36,NULL,0,'Jakkalsfontein',197456),
(279372,222607,'other','Chenin Blanc-Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'With 2,000 cases imported, here\'s a value white composed of 80% Chenin Blanc and 20% Sauvignon Blanc. Green apple flesh and orange rind are lifted by notes of crushed yellow flowers, while green plum flavors flesh out the medium-weight mouth. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Oak Lane',196689),
(279379,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fiDjIQwbRNO0vMV0NSNe6w_pb_x960.png','Dominated by acidity, this is a wine that offers red and black currant fruits, very juicy, just smoothed by wood.',10,NULL,0,'Pancas',196663),
(279383,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Bright red-fruited wine, its acidity well blended into the soft, full fruit. The wine has spice, toast, wild herbs.',9,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago',196807),
(279506,217265,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A one-dimensional, pungent style of SB that\'s fresh, zesty and tangy in the mouth courtesy of zippy acidity and flavors of tangerine, grapefruit and passion fruit. Finishes more in the pink grapefruit zone, but with snap. Chiseled and linear, but definitely still kicking.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 225',196620),
(279517,227043,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz',NULL,'A nose of mocha and savory spice starts this organic blend from Waverly. On the palate, interesting sweet cedar, violet and nutmeg flavors give it a pretty but warming character. Not overly complicated, but definitely versatile.',15,NULL,0,'Organic Viticulture',197456),
(279591,219884,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Soft, ripe, juicy wine, full of bright red berry fruits, soft tannins and a light structure. The wine is ready to drink, the final flavor lifted by acidity.',8,NULL,0,'Fonte do Beco',196807),
(279642,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This is an impressive young Cabernet: It\'s bone dry, tannic and intense, with flavors of mountain blackberries and black currants. It may even age for a few years.',26,NULL,0,'Lot 360',196620),
(279724,217512,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Red berry, toast, vanilla and soft tannins. A wine that is fruity, ready to drink.',10,NULL,0,'Pegos Claros',196663),
(279733,222693,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Faint suggestions of sweet smoke and beeswax mingle with the red apple and melon flavors, adding interest to this otherwise straightforward and easy drinking wine. Drink now.',13,NULL,0,'Kosher',197445),
(279748,227092,'other','Syrah',NULL,'With the R62 standing for the famous Route 62 in South Africa, this is a beautiful unfiltered Syrah that\'s naturally fermented and matured 16 months in Burgundian oak. Sweet spice, cocoa nibs, raspberry and balsamic-drizzled strawberries abound, with fine-grained tannins leading masterfully into the cocoa-dusted finish. Complex, balanced and delicious now, but can be cellared for two to three years.',40,NULL,0,'R62',197896),
(279787,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/UkWNaKcZQZit02JID3XCbQ_pb_x960.png','With its dark color and firm tannins, this dense wine from 2,000-foot-high vineyards belies its light alcohol to give rich structure. It is fresh as well, with black currant juiciness coming through the spice and structure. It\'s still young, juicy and needs to age. Drink from 2015.',13,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo',196663),
(279882,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'An attractively light wine, showing its cool climate origin, with red currant fruit and juicy acidity. It\'s a great summer red, maybe even slightly chilled.',6,NULL,0,'Coreto Tinto',196807),
(279901,218228,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/XLqEsy0HSFmywIVZj4kG6w_pb_300x300.png','Solid up front, with minty, herbal aromas that include olive, carob and black plum. Feels lifted and high in acidity, with a sharpness to the mouthfeel along with herbal flavors of olive and green-leaning plum. Fresh but short on the finish.',12,NULL,0,'Estate Reserva',196886),
(279982,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'DFJ\'s venture into the Alentejo has produced a full-bodied wine packed with ripe plums and berry fruits. Tannins are rich, integrated into the fruits. A touch of earthiness needs to blow off before the wine is ready to drink in 2015.',9,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano',196807),
(280048,223641,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This Pinotage-Shiraz blend offers aromas of heavy spice, smoke and cherry, and on the palate, a smooth, velvety blend of red berry fruit, smoke and warming spice. The wine has a touch of the Pinotage snap, which gives it added character. Overall elegant and approachable while still maintaining its South African style.',9,NULL,0,'Savanha Pinotage-Shiraz',197456),
(280054,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_6NbTxQYQTCFUQeF0ICxOA_pb_600x600.png','This wine\'s quality ranges from year to year. This vintage smells foxy, jumpy and not all that convincing, with spunky cherry and berry notes. It\'s clamp city in the mouth, with hard tannins and herbal, foxy flavors of wild berry that finish choppy and grinding.',12,NULL,0,'60/40 Reserve Barrel Select',196857),
(280078,224517,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Soft peach and wild berries lead the way on the nose, while the medium weight mouth offers a bit more fleshy stone fruit and watermelon flavors. The finish is dry and accented by hints of peppery spice.',11,NULL,0,'The Wolftrap',197456),
(280127,217203,'other','Códega do Larinho',NULL,'An old and rarely planted vine in the Douro, Códega do Larinho has produced a rich, lightly perfumed wine. With plenty of acidity and citrus, it is both ripe and refreshing. It could benefit from a few months in bottle; drink after 2015.',18,NULL,0,'Andreza',196685),
(280141,217512,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CLiddc3dQsGP84CzKrTApw_pb_x960.png','A pale yellow-colored wine, it\'s full of ripe white peach, melon and plums. It\'s rich but also shows bright acidity and a touch of citrus. It\'s an easy wine to drink now–2016.',12,NULL,0,'Pancas Branco',196663),
(280196,218035,'other','Gewürztraminer','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3t36GVQxTpKNaA1MrJAQmw_pb_600x600.png','While the nose on this sweetie isn\'t deep, it\'s lush, inviting and peachy as they come. The palate feels fresh and straightforward, and the flavor profile blends tropical fruit flavors with spice and honey accents. Overall this seems natural, easygoing and expressive.',27,NULL,0,'Late Harvest',196713),
(280207,217265,'other','Viognier',NULL,'A little sweet and sour in lemonade, pineapple juice and orange soda flavors, but clean and refreshing. Shows an exotic edge of honeysuckle, vanilla flower and jasmine tea.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 117 Grenache Blanc-',196620),
(280342,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'This is an attractive, fruity, fresh rosé. It is dry but balances acidity and fruitiness with its sweet strawberry fruit and light touch of vanilla pod. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezirias Catapereiro',196685),
(280362,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Soft and luxurious, this is made from Merlot and Cabernet, and it offers rich, complex flavors of blackberries, cherries, currants, dark chocolate, herbs, spices and cedar.',18,NULL,0,'Lot 337',196620),
(280407,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Good price for a Cab from this small, prestigious appellation. The wine is bone dry and dense in mountain tannins, with rich flavors of black cherries, blackberries, currants and wild herbs, like rosemary. Shows real elegance and style. Now–2012.',18,NULL,0,'Lot 121',196620),
(280497,219884,'other','Alvarinho-Chardonnay',NULL,'The Chardonnay and Alvarinho complement each other well, the one bringing a rounded texture, the other adding a fresh and mineral character. Together, they produce a refreshing, ripe wine that has attractive citrus and yellow fruits. Drink from 2015.',11,NULL,0,'DFJ',196807),
(280524,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Although this is ready to drink now, it offers considerable tannins that are wrapped around layers of blackberries, black currants and cedar. The structure is impressive, so let it breathe in a decanter for an hour or two before serving.',20,NULL,0,'Lot 316',196620),
(280525,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4Vssqva6SL2XMriXLJW-sw_pb_300x300.png','For South American dessert wine, this is at the top of the class. The nose is light and offers nectarine, tangerine and peach aromas, while the mouthfeel is honeyed and plump, with orange marmalade, cinnamon and nutmeg flavors. The finish is long and complex, and a touch soft in feel.',18,NULL,0,'Late Harvest',196886),
(280537,227240,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Affordable and exuberant, this Pinotage/Merlot blend starts with cherry, vanilla and cedar aromas followed by bright flavors of fruit and spicy pepper. The finish is spicy and assertive. A great wine for grilled meats and more robust cuisine, and a fun introduction to Pinotage.',15,NULL,0,'Merlot-Pinotage',196839),
(280538,218426,'other','Pinot Gris','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zgx23SSeQ6OfWgeFvMoEpA_pb_x960.png','A good, solid Pinot Gris, with superripe flavors of pineapples, pears, peaches, honeysuckle flowers, vanilla and cinnamon spices. The acidity is nicely brisk. Would score higher if it were drier, as it has a sugary, jammy edge.',20,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(280568,223334,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Bright berry and crisp red plum aromas and flavors dominate this wine, with a touch of menthol on the nose. The alcohol stands out a bit in the mouth and overwhelms the short finish.',12,NULL,0,'Petit',196839),
(280587,217839,'other','Malbec','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/gBdHwhFQSYOCDhziuTNd8Q_pb_x960.png','Edgy aromas of citrus peel, green bean and green tobacco fail to register. The palate feels both flabby and high in acidity, as if it were worked on to not much avail. Tastes herbal and green, with a minty finish.',12,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(280617,222507,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Here\'s a big, rich Chenin boasting developed notes of honeydew, tropical fruit, peach preserves and soft spice. Medium-full in the mouth with good balance and a lengthy finish. The palate shows a hint of petrol along with fresh red apple slices sprinkled with cinnamon and honey. With 2,500 cases imported, drink now and, at this price, often.',13,NULL,0,'Citrus Grove',197456),
(280701,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Soft, dry and satisfying, this is a gentle Cabernet for everyday drinking. It has pleasant flavors of blackberries, currants, cedar and spices.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 126',196620),
(280707,227278,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Cherry, cedar and vanilla aromas lead this red blend from Darling. Red fruit, candied spice, smoke and pepper on the palate is a touch angular, with a lively, tart spin. Pair with grilled, spiced meat or robust cheeses for added enjoyment.',24,NULL,0,'Darling Hills Ovation',197887),
(280711,217265,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'It is one of the mysteries of the universe how negociant Cameron Hughes produces wines like this at such a great price. It is a Zinfandel lover\'s Zinfandel, rich and peppery and briary. Really satisfies with wild forest red and black berry flavors tingled with tons of spice, and finishes dry and balanced.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 88 Ancient Vines',196620),
(280808,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A great, enjoyable Chardonnay, extremely rich and ripe, but perfectly balanced. Crisp coastal acidity provides a clean boost to the enormous tropical fruit and peach flavors. The oak is strong, but in keeping with the size of the fruit, providing crème brûlée, buttered toast and smoky meringue opulence.',39,NULL,0,'Sleepy Hollow Vineyard',196639),
(280846,217839,'other','Malbec','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4VXpj2m_Qziw6d0eEVh3wQ_pb_x600.png','This hard-drilling, bullish Malbec is bright purple in color, with grapy, heady aromas. The palate is rubbery and grabby, with a shock of zesty acidity. Oversized, roasted black-fruit flavors finish with size, power and a grating feel.',18,NULL,0,'Serie Riberas Gran Reserva Ribera del Tinguirica',196852),
(280859,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MUiYriQfRk-tf-hKiiE7EA_pb_x960.png','The 2010 vintage in Chile was quite cool, and that\'s reflected in this wine. Aromas of berry fruits are lean and underdeveloped. In the mouth, this shows astringency and rubbery tannins, while flavors of red fruits are slightly sharp and a touch green. Drying tannins make for a drawing finish.',22,NULL,0,'Amplus',196857),
(280895,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Shows real Stags Leap character in the dusty tannins, dryness and power, yet appeals with lush cherries, currants, spices and cedar. It\'s balanced and harmonious now, and should develop over the next six years.',25,NULL,0,'Lot 100',196620),
(280922,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Mineral, steel and toast set this impressive, well-structured wine on to the road for aging. Behind this initially severe, very young exterior is the richest yellow and white fruit, exuding power, concentration and density. Give it 6–8 years and many more.',350,NULL,0,'Bâtard-Montrachet',197408),
(280924,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'As always, Corton-Charlemagne offers an opulent Chardonnay. In this vintage, the wine has intense tropical fruits, very ripe although never losing sight of its acidity. There is terrific concentration here, giving a wine that is very rich.',182,NULL,0,'Corton-Charlemagne',197408),
(280965,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5b9lewwUSe-rvqL2UJa4wg_pb_600x600.png','Very pure, focused, intense, a Chardonnay whose minerality and fresh acidity provide grounding and structure to the elaborate, decadently good flavors. Exotic, with waves of tropical fruit pastry, lemondrop candy, golden mango, pineapple crème brûlée, buttered toast and dusty Asian spices.',38,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Camelot Highlands',196751),
(280966,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'An impressive Pinot. Shows massive fruity ripeness in a well-developed tannin structure, with good acidity, but it\'s really too young to drink now. Shows massive, primary flavors of black and red cherry pie filling, red plums and cola, with sweet, smoky, vanilla-infused oak influences. Hold until sometime in 2011.',56,NULL,0,'Bien Nacido Vineyard',196639),
(280974,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is the most citrusy of Testarossa\'s \'07 Chards, brimming with Meyer lemon, lime and pineapple flavors. Smooth, smoky oak and lees add complex layers of butter, cream and tart yeastiness. Brilliant but immature, the wine should come into its own after 2009.',39,NULL,0,'Bien Nacido',196639),
(281031,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This blend of Fernão Pires and Arinto is soft, fresh and fruity. Juicy green plums, citrus and bright acidity all give a lively character. A tangy texture needs several months aging. It will be best at the end of the 2014.',11,NULL,0,'Casa Ermelinda Freitas Monte de Baía Branco',196685),
(281090,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'An impressive wine, very much for aging. It has rich fruit, laced with the purest acidity, lemon vying with ripe white peaches. With great richness come weight and intensity, the toast giving an extra dimension. Age for 4–6 years.',137,NULL,0,'Les Pucelles',197408),
(281094,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Dominated by its toasty wood flavors, this is a wine still under development. It has weight, the fruit offering great potential richness. Spice, lime fruits and a firm, steely core all promise to come together into a fine wine in five years.',100,NULL,0,'Champ Gain',197408),
(281103,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A gorgeously ripe wine, its rounded yellow fruits tempered by wood aging. There is a mineral core, with a steely character to go with the pure pleasures of the rich fruit. The wine is fruity now, and does need to age to bring out the rest of its complex flavors.',137,NULL,0,'Les Folatières',197408),
(281136,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/aNpjwkKiRmGgKfzdqV2_Iw_pb_600x600.png','Combines rich, vibrant acidity with fruity intensity in a very clean, opulent wine. Offers waves of tropical fruits, honeysuckle, buttered toast and minerals, with a long, spicy finish. The extensive new oak is perfectly in keeping with the size of this crowd-pleaser. Now–2014.',30,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Seco Highlands',196751),
(281137,219700,'other','Nero d\'Avola','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/o4u-qSowQQmoQY-T8cp21Q_pb_x600.png','One of the greatest wines to be born on Sicilian soil, Rosso del Conte is a rich and complex wine with numerous aromatic accents to keep you entertained. You\'ll get blackberry, forest floor, cola, pipe tobacco and leather. It is soft and luscious and lasts a long time on the palate.',70,NULL,0,'Rosso del Conte',196776),
(281167,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'There are lots of juicy blackberry, cherry, currant, dark chocolate and cedar flavors in this Merlot-based Bordeaux-style blend. It\'s bone dry and refreshingly crisp in acidity, and it shows firm, hard tannins. It doesn\'t have the depth to age, so drink it soon with rich food, like beef stew.',16,NULL,0,'Lot 325',196620),
(281177,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_600x600.png','This has a dense bouquet, with aromas of beet, clove, mint, tomato and berry fruit. The mouthfeel is rich and saturated, with a rawness that didn\'t exist in prior years. Flavors of mixed herb, earth and savory berry end with a long finish.',38,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Entre Cordilleras Peumo Vineyard',196852),
(281185,217265,'other','Viognier',NULL,'Sweet and sour, like a pineapple throat lozenge. Crisp acidity gives it a clean finish, but it\'s a pretty simple wine.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 118',196620),
(281190,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Grapy and fruity, like it\'s fresh out of the fermenter. Also sweet and soft, with a melted jam consistency and taste. Drink this simple wine now.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 135',196620),
(281242,217999,'other','White Blend','https://static.xtrawine.com/Global/Images/XW/products/wines/36579_FeudiSanGregorioPrivilegio05L_2019_3.png','A luminous dessert blend of Fiano and Falanghina, Privilegio is an opulent and creamy wine with sweet tones of candied fruit, honey and white almond that last long on the palate. Pair this beauty with a platter of aged cheese and sweet marmalade.',60,NULL,0,'Privilegio',196908),
(281300,223593,'other','White Blend',NULL,'The bouquet of this wine is immediately attractive and remarkably vibrant, offering plenty of honeydew, Anjou pear and fresh pineapple accented by notes of pink peony. Well balanced and medium weight with bracing acidity and a clean, peach pit-infused finish. An easy-drinking white perfect for casual outdoor dining or sunny afternoons.',16,NULL,0,'Art House Viognier-Chenin Blanc-Sauvignon Blanc',197456),
(281313,218569,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'Sparkling wine from Williams Selyem? Yes, in tiny quantities, in this case only 100 cases. The wine is dry and rich in lime, raspberry, mineral and yeast flavors, but a little rough, lacking the finesse you want in a fine bubbly.',50,NULL,0,'Drake Estate Vineyard Blanc de Noir',196626),
(281359,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This blend of Sauvignon Blanc and Fernão Pires is aromatic and ripe. Its fruitiness is tropical, with pineapple as well as apricot flavors. It\'s softly textured  and ready to drink.',15,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Catapereiro Escolha Branco',196685),
(281431,226863,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The nose of this Chard is so lively and welcoming with accents of lilac, jasmine, white peach slices and clementine. Matured in barrel for 10 months, the wine\'s palate offers more intense, mature flavors of peaches and cream, ginger and supporting tropical acidity. Well structured with a defined and evolving finish, it takes you from citrus to fresh peach to vanilla wooded spice.',15,NULL,0,'DMZ',196839),
(281441,218035,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EqPruM3HSomafcCtzYWYwA_pb_x600.png','Starts with typical aromas of olive, herbs, spice and pepper, and there\'s berry fruit underneath. The palate is racier and more staunch than the 2007, with cherry, olive, plum and a hint of raisin. Tightly formed, with a lively DNA and a tangy finish touched up by cocoa.',24,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(281447,226863,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A bright, tasty Shiraz loaded with flavors of chocolate-covered cherry, raspberry compote and integrated sweet spice throughout. Balanced with a medium weight, structured tannins and a juicy plum-infused finish. Approachable now and great for shell steak or lighter game stews.',15,NULL,0,'DMZ',196839),
(281454,223391,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This delicate, elegant NLH wine starts with alluring aromas of lush honey, apricot and citrus and offers a vibrant, lively balance of fruit and acid. Pair with cheeses and fruit salads.',35,NULL,0,'Noble Late Harvest',196839),
(281476,218228,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/u-K4P6QlQe2Y8WuvE2Zrfg_pb_x600.png','Herbal on the nose, with basil and tomato leaf aromas. The palate feel is reasonably good if a bit hollow, while the flavors reflect the bouquet via dry, herbal, peppery red fruit. Spicy with green olive and standard red berry on the finish.',12,NULL,0,'Estate',196886),
(281544,218035,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Impressive as always, with dense, meaty aromas of baked black fruits, compost and dried cheese. The palate is thick to the max, with chocolate, coconut and baked plum and berry flavors. Ultrarich on the finish, with warmth and density. Once again \"M\" shows how deep and rewarding high-end Chilean reds can be. Drink now through 2015.',95,NULL,0,'Alpha M',196713),
(281559,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'This vintage was a good one for Cameron Hughes\' Bordeaux-style wines, and this Cabernet-based blend, which contains a splash of Carmenere, is as good as anything they\'ve released. It\'s juicy-rich in blackberries, currants, carob and cedar, wrapped into firm, fine tannins.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 103',196620),
(281588,223593,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A balanced, well-structured wine, and a superb value. Cassis, black plum guts and anise are supported by soft sweet spice and leather fleshing out the nose and mouth, with lingering dusty tannins leaving you begging for more. Ready to drink now; pair with flank steak fajitas.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz-Merlot',197456),
(281589,223593,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Beautiful mineral aromas unfold on the nose with accents of bay leaves and stone fruit shining through. The mouth is round but not overdone or flabby, with tangerine citrus keeping the rich flavors in check. A great bistro wine to pair well with lighter lunchtime fare such as salads and panini. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Café Juno',197456),
(281607,227426,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A grassy nose mingled with fresh citric fruits is followed by a unique combination of refreshing fruit, herbs and fresh green pepper in this elegant sip from Capaia. Earthy while at the same time appetizing, the wine has a crisp finish.',19,NULL,0,'Blue Grove Hill',197920),
(281612,226846,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Soft aromas of gooseberry and fresh fruit are followed by lush, like flavors in this glamorous white. Integrated flavors include peach and a spicy spin. Finishes lively and crisp.',18,NULL,0,'Manor House',196839),
(281613,218043,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'An alluring nose of mocha, dark fruit and tobacco spice starts this stylish Shiraz. Rich, integrated flavors of mint, cherry and a touch of smoke are appealing and serious. A lingering finish adds to the classy character. Pair with a savory stew.',14,NULL,0,'Sincerely',196839),
(281616,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'True to this negociant\'s style, this Chardonnay offers lots of bang for the buck. It delivers true varietal character, offering flavors of pineapples, pears and oak, wrapped into a creamy texture that finishes dry and spicy.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 108',196620),
(281617,222668,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Upfront aromas of ripe plum, tobacco and pepper lead this savory Shiraz from Fairview. On the palate, its dry plum, roasted meat and mint flavors are big and balanced. The long finish has a touch of menthol and pepper.',36,NULL,0,'The Beacon',197456),
(281644,218512,'other','Frappato','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0276/0110/9056/products/u-UnBWlXQTuEcmZLCFu3iQ_pb_x600_15424494-f816-49c6-b70e-225e31c87063.png?v=1621017866','Il Frappato delivers loads of zest and bright aromas of berry, chopped mint, cola and ginger. There\'s a note of black pepper on the palate, followed by some almond bitterness.',20,NULL,0,'Il',196773),
(281653,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Juicy, sweet and fat in glycerine, this has complex flavors of blackberry and cherry pie filling. The tannins and acids give it a fine, elegant structure. Drink now.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 332',196620),
(281676,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Rzvg7SXFTsaUMPUDXKyf9g_pb_x600.png','Electric purple in color, this powerful wine opens with jammy, loud aromas of boysenberry and herbal qualities. Likewise, spunky berry flavors are herbal in nature. Minty oak and medicinal notes dominate a rubbery, long finish.',12,NULL,0,'Barrel Select',196857),
(281685,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The relatively unknown Pezerolles Vineyard is at the far northern end of Pommard, touching Beaune above Les Epenots. It produces wine that seems softer than many Pommards, with rich fruit, the tannins firm but definitely playing second fiddle. It is the smoky plum fruit with just a dash of acidity that makes this immensely pleasing.',90,NULL,0,'Les Pezerolles Premier Cru',197241),
(281686,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A big, jammy wine with full ripe strawberries and sweet, juicy blackberries. The tannins are soft, and the acidity plays a balancing supporting role. Not for aging, but delicious to drink in the next few years.',55,NULL,0,'Teurons Premier Cru',197241),
(281703,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/M5ZfaQZaTKqPwnWQxKuqLg_pb_x960.png','Exhibiting all the ripeness and richness of an Aloxe-Corton, this wine revels in delicious raspberry fruits, topped with red currant acidity. The wine rolls around the mouth, with a velvet texture on top of some firm tannins. There is a complex sweet and sour aftertaste, as the ripe fruit combines with fresh acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Clos des Maréchaudes Premier Cru',196775),
(281763,217265,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Is there anywhere Cameron Hughes isn\'t selecting or blending wine? This NZ foray is clean and concentrated enough, with white grapefruit flavors and a touch of pineapple. Drink up.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 134',196620),
(281796,223715,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This wine starts with a combination of white flowers, spice, tropical fruit and green notes, with dry, crisp flavors of citrus and mineral on the palate. A good wine for fans of more angular whites, the wine will pair well with spicy Asian cuisine, grilled spicy fish or chicken.',12,NULL,0,'Beyond',197609),
(281804,218043,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A lovely nose of violet, clove and pepper begin this stylish wine from Neil Ellis. On the palate, blackberry and spice flavors are concentrated and balanced. Smooth tannins and a smoldering finish add to the package.',43,NULL,0,'Vineyard Selection',196839),
(281813,217512,'other','Portuguese White','https://www.gmdrinks.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Forgotten-Field-Blanco-Lisboa-600x800-1.jpg','A blend of Chardonnay with Arinto and Vital, this is a simple, fruity and fragrant wine. It has lively acidity, a crisp, mineral texture and a ripe, full feel at the end. Drink through 2015.',10,NULL,0,'Forgotten Field',196663),
(281817,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'The merest prickle on the tongue adds to the freshness of this crisp, clean, lightly sweet wine. Very fruity, it conveys apples and citrus, with a soft, fragrant aftertaste.',9,NULL,0,'Salsus',196685),
(281829,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is Bouchard\'s hallmark Beaune, a blend from different premier cru vineyards. The wine is dense, firm and dominated by dark tannins, which offer good aging potential. The sweet tomato acidity and black berry fruits merge with a noticeable flavor of wood—the combo still needs time to fully balance out. Wait at least four years.',40,NULL,0,'Premier Cru Beaune du Château',197241),
(281897,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Shows plenty of finesse in the dry, minerally profile, and the crisp acidity that makes the finish clean and savory. Could be a bit richer, but the pineapple and lemon candy flavors satisfy.',45,NULL,0,'Golden Coast',196642),
(281944,227479,'other','Muscat d\'Alexandrie',NULL,'This dessert wine starts with an opulent nose of honey, apricot and spice, and on the palate, it has a rich, honeyed character of citrus and apricot. A generous amount of spice gives it spirit. Pair with cheeses, fruit.',14,NULL,0,'Heaven On Earth Organic Sweet Wine',196839),
(281946,223861,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A rich, fragrant nose of citrus and apple starts this unwooded Chardonnay, and the quality continues on the palate, where fresh fruit and citrus flavors offer a clean but complex sip. A lingering finish is added appeal. This is your next everyday summer sip—stock up.',13,NULL,0,'Natural Unwooded',196845),
(281985,217839,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/7UENq4CYTSyl_xXcLL145Q_pb_x960.png','Once upon a time this Concha y Toro label was a Best Buy regular. At $21 it no longer qualifies, but it\'s every bit an excellent wine in 2006. Aromas of plum, cola, pepper and Christmas spice are alluring, while the palate is saturated yet balanced. Flavors of plum and berry are perfectly ripe, and the structure and texture are just right.',21,NULL,0,'Marques de Casa Concha',196852),
(281989,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A structured wine that pulls together dark tannins and firm fruit with a young, rough edge. It is a heavy wine, dominated by its structure, the red fruit skin and strawberry jelly flavors a welcome distraction from this dryness. Age for three to four years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Porrets Saint-Georges Premier Cru',197241),
(282005,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/BKi6i82zSqGMOvb66HzpQQ_pb_x960.png','A solid, dense wine, its rich tannins dominating dark black fruits. The wine is ponderous, brooding, with shafts of acidity giving it a lift. But it does need a couple of years to soften that core of serious tannins.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Clos Frantin Les Murots',196775),
(282076,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/1FY3Y6_3S1GAvqIxms9X9w_pb_x600.png','Rubber and earth aromas lead to a mix of berry fruit scents and a pinch of vinegar. It\'s firm in the mouth, with cranberry and herbal raspberry flavors. Gives about as much as it can but at the same time it shows a tart, basic, mildly herbal DNA.',10,NULL,0,'Selected Terroir',196857),
(282096,227457,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A fresh citrus and delicate tropical fruit nose gives this Durbanville white a stylish start. Steely and crisp on the palate, with flavors of gooseberry and grass, the wine is balanced and soft. Pair with grilled seafood or salads.',25,NULL,0,'Biesjes Craal',197484),
(282104,227505,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Intriguing aromas of plum, savory spice and smoke lead this rich Syrah. Balanced flavors of ripe plum, mint, pepper and spice paired with structured tannins and a lingering spicy finish give the wine an ageable character. Intense and assertive.',35,NULL,0,'Cape of Good Hope',197456),
(282126,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Soft and fruity, this is a ripe style of rosé. It\'s dry and peppery, with fresh acidity cutting through its rounded texture. It\'s a rosé for food, with a full aftertaste.',11,NULL,0,'Casa Ermelinda Freitas Monte de Baía',196685),
(282128,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional-Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/iJdy4V3kThCKRWCpcSpOHQ_pb_x960.png','With a strongly juicy character and high acidity, this wine brings out the tannic character of the two grapes in the blend rather than the fruit. There\'s a spicy character and red fruit acidity at the end.',9,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Tinto',196807),
(282157,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Light, crisp, lemon-scented, with fresh apricots, pear juice and toast flavors. This is a wine that gives immediate pleasure, but with just a tight steeliness at the core to promise some aging. Imported by Frederick Wildman & Sons, Ltd.',32,NULL,0,'Vauvry Premier Cru',197408),
(282170,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Awfully good for the price, with crisp, Carneros acidity and a creamy texture framing nice flavors of pineapples, peaches, green apples, cinnamon spice and minerals.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 127',196620),
(282179,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Lots of sweet raspberry and cherry fruit in this easy-to-drink Pinot Noir. It\'s nice and silky, with a spicy finish. Nice with grilled tuna, lamb or beef, and a good value for the price.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 271',196620),
(282213,223791,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'With only 1,500 cases produced, this beautiful estate Chenin Blanc has lots of character and complexity. The nose boasts stony minerality, white peach and baby\'s breath florals while the palate shows its sweeter side with honey, pressed peaches and tangerine oil. Balanced and full with a robust body and lingering finish.',19,NULL,0,'Estate',196839),
(282244,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://s2.wine.style/images_gen/618/61881/0_0_orig.jpg','The natural earthiness of Castelão shows through this soft and ripe blended wine. It\'s smoothly textured and juicy, although that barnyard feel doesn\'t quite go away. Drink now for its fresh acidity and easy fruit.',10,NULL,0,'Forgotten Field',196663),
(282245,217839,'other','Riesling','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/xoJWvRR1TqK6QykkXPsPFw_pb_x960.png','Like German or Alsace Rieslings, this Chilean version hints at petrol but falls short, thus the nose is wayward and perfumed. In the mouth, this is peachy in feel, with sweet but uncommitted flavors of nectarine and apricot. A chunky finish comes up short on acidity and structure.',30,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Costa Los Boldes Vineyard Block 6',196852),
(282246,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'An attractively fruity wine that\'s easy to drink and fresh. Lemon and apples give a crisp edge, followed by a zesty, fragrant character. Drink this light wine now.',8,NULL,0,'Portada Winemaker\'s Selection Branco',196807),
(282247,217780,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/qn916y2oSuSGG0Yu_1KMlQ_pb_600x600.png','Mild vanilla cookie and dusty, yeasty aromas get this unoaked Chardonnay going. An innocuous-feeling palate carries melony flavors of honey, sweet apple and banana, while a touch of brine rises up on the finish.',10,NULL,0,'Select Terroir Unoaked',196857),
(282277,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','A firm wine that has ripe but structured tannins. It is not a big wine, but rather shows a tighter style of Pinot Noir that balances sweet red fruits and a spice edge of wood. It would benefit from aging for 2–3 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Clos Frantin',196775),
(282322,223005,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'With a confectioned finish and sweet mocha notes on the nose, this might have seen a little too much wood in its 16 months in new French oak. Lovely notes of small red berries, sous bois and pepper appear in the bouquet, while sanguine notes overpower the soft mouth. Overall, it\'s easy to drink but a little disjointed.',40,NULL,0,'Solms Hegewisch',196839),
(282330,222421,'other','Viognier',NULL,'A vibrant, easy-to-drink and attractively priced Viognier. Melon, pear and delicate citrus oil flesh out the creamy mouth. The finish lingers slightly but is clean and refreshing. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Goats in Villages',197456),
(282360,223791,'other','Merlot',NULL,'The nose of this Merlot is intriguing, with its cinnamon spice and plum character. On the palate, straightforward fruit flavors with a spin of spice and lingering, perky finish. A good overall wine for everyday enjoyment.',20,NULL,0,'Fantail',196839),
(282404,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/e9eW4kq6RF2qTXyOVrVB1A_pb_x960.png','All about sweetness and softness. The fruit is rounded, with ripe plum and berry flavors and vibrant fresh acidity. With light and open texture, this wine gives immediate pleasure, but is not for aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Les Santenots Premier Cru',196775),
(282501,227576,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Ripe fruit aromas mingle with pepper, leather, mocha and spice on the nose of this elegant red. Dry and balanced, the palate offers ripe berry and spicy notes, and a lingering finish. Good textured tannins add to the ageable appeal.',40,NULL,0,'Kevin Arnold',196689),
(282551,218035,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CIsEW5FMToKKK18Kmg4-Zw_pb_x960.png','Touching up against syrupy, this ultra-rich style of Syrah from Apalta in Colchagua is pumped full of coconut, barrel char and deep berry fruit. It\'s a saturated Syrah with palate-coating berry, vanilla and spice flavors. It\'s also slightly candied and immensely ripe. Finishes with barrel notes, chocolate and thickness.',28,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(282558,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Firm, mineral, tight wine, given an extra dimension by pear skins and a touch of caramel. The wine is impressive for its appellation, offering a structured, terroir-driven character. Imported by Louis Latour Inc.',15,NULL,0,'Chameroy',197254),
(282602,223005,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'An interesting and fruit-forward alternative to more common dry sparklers, this red sparkler is sure to impress with its appearance alone. Aromas and flavors of black cherry, wild strawberry and soft earthy spice dominate the profile. Balanced and softly tannic with a lingering finish and an even longer lasting impression on the drinker.',20,NULL,0,'Solms Astor Cape Jazz',196839),
(282614,223247,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Medium-intense aromas of pear, red apple skin and delicate sweet spice appear on the nose, while accents of toast and limey citrus unfold in the mouth. Vibrant and easy to drink with a clean, softly wooded finish. Try with grilled steak fish like swordfish or mahi mahi.',24,NULL,0,'Isabella',197420),
(282649,220442,'other','Pinot Nero',NULL,'Bright garnet in color, this delicate wine has aromas of cassis, sour cherry and violet, plus a drying touch of mineral. The mouthfeel is lean, fresh and sharp.',NULL,NULL,0,'Vajasindi Nawàri',196776),
(282684,218035,'other','Gewürztraminer','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3t36GVQxTpKNaA1MrJAQmw_pb_600x600.png','This wine is flat and capped on the nose. On the palate, it\'s angular and narrow, with cidery flavors and little to no complexity.',23,NULL,0,'Late Harvest Botrytised Grapes',196713),
(282707,221639,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Given that Argentina is hardly SB country, this wine sticks out for its clarity, minerality and freshness. The nose offers lean lime and other citrus aromas. That\'s followed by a juicy palate with lime, passion fruit and tangerine flavors. Tropical but also citric, with cutting acidity.',19,NULL,0,'B Crux',196852),
(282717,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Full in the mouth, this is a rich, wood-lifted wine, the peach and apricot fruits given an edge by a light steeliness. The acidity fits well into the rich flavors here, creating a burst of apple juice over the yellow fruits. Imported by Louis Latour Inc.',15,NULL,0,'Les Genièvres',197254),
(282839,218228,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_bxoe6kpRVOBF0W2t9sYtg_pb_x960.png','Fiery, leafy and loaded with aromas of carob and herbs. This is rambunctious Carmenère with powerful herbal raspberry flavors and a stout, thick body. For varietal character, this really showcases the essence of the Carmenère grape. It\'s thick, plump and smooth, but wholly herbal.',25,NULL,0,'Single Vineyard Don Maximiano Estate',196886),
(282840,218035,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/mCPyL4MHTJa-WF9SsCfctA_pb_600x600.png','Maybe a little more ripe and heady than some of its Chilean buddies, but this SB from Montes offers freshness, zip and good citrus, tarragon and other green-herb flavors. The feel is good, the character fresh, and the finish long and clean. Offers maybe a little more green-leaf character than some might like, but overall this is another fine value SB from Chile. Drink immediately.',12,NULL,0,'Classic Series',196713),
(282868,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'An eccentric, although likeable, Cab. It shows the dryness and tannic astringency that Atlas Peak Cabs are famous for, along with upfront, accessibly New World flavors of cherry jam, black currants and cedar. Hard to know if it\'s an ager, but it\'s a pretty good wine.',20,NULL,0,'Lot 120',196620),
(282903,223593,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A fresh nose of mineral and citrus gives this white a spirited start. On the palate, minerally, slightly angular flavors unfold. The wine has an assertive quality but needs some complexity to round it out. Overall though, crisp and food-friendly.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens',197456),
(282946,227664,'other','Muscat',NULL,'A well-balanced, powerful dessert wine, this opens with an intense bouquet of fresh peach, orange blossom, jasmine, gardenia and honeysuckle. The mouthfilling, sweet palate is loaded with flavors of ripe stone fruit, mango, melon and orange marmelade, but is kept bright by refreshing acidity on the close. Secondary notes of ginger and white tea linger long on the evolving finish. A wine of class and strength, this is delicious now, but should also easily age through 2020.',90,NULL,0,'Vin de Constance',197609),
(282992,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EjICDuKfTk-SaBEOpdlJXA_pb_x960.png','Quite leafy smelling, with tobacco and a ton of barrel influence. Big, woody and resiny feeling, with rugged tannins pushing sweet, ripe berry and spice flavors. Toasty, chocolaty and herbal as it finishes, but always there\'s a strong oak presence.',95,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Founder\'s Reserve',196886),
(283030,218046,'other','Cabernet Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/wrLFc-xZTSCWGnVBLbqInQ_pb_x960.png','This Cabernet-based blend is loaded with intense aromas of black currant leaf, briary forest, black cherry and tobacco leaves. Solidly structured with moderate tannins and medium weight, the palate is juicy and satisfying with blackberries and plum skins leading through to the coffee-infused finish.',14,NULL,0,'Roodeberg',196839),
(283036,223861,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This Shiraz-dominated (70%) blend is a bit darker than one might anticipate, with black currant liqueur, pepper, anise and plum skins taking center stage in the profile. Well-balanced with medium dusty tannins and a lingering finish infused with toasty oak spice. Try pairing with braised short ribs or spiced lamb loin.',16,NULL,0,'Shiraz-Petit Verdot-Viognier',196845),
(283041,222420,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Smoky, savory berry and vanilla aromas lead this friendly Shiraz. On the palate, smoky meat and pepper spice meld with juicy, ripe fruit. The wine is smoky and full of complex spice. The lingering finish has a meaty spin. Pair with lamb stew, grilled meats.',20,NULL,0,'Finlayson Family Vineyards',196689),
(283091,222591,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'With just 30 cases imported, this is a tough find but worth the hunt, as it will certainly continue to evolve and flourish over the next 10 years, at least. Aromas and flavors of baked apple, peach preserves, honeycomb and orange oil abound, with herbal glimmers of white tea and honeysuckle in the background adding depth and interest. The palate is lush and round, yet pure in character, with ample acidity to keep the flavors from feeling overdone. Hints of honey-roasted nuts and sweet spice grace the long finish.',37,NULL,0,'Straw Wine',197368),
(283092,223334,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This is a rich, well-balanced and layered white, with lots of aging potential. Notes of red apple, peach, melon and orange blossom mingle with spicy accents of toasted brioche, clove and vanilla bean. It\'s medium weight and crisp in acidity, with a long, evolving finish that ends decadent yet elegant. Drink now–2020.',65,NULL,0,'The FMC',196839),
(283095,225095,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This is a dense and concentrated wine, still in its youth, with heady, fruity tones of black plum, berry, cassis and date that are layered with notes of licorice, cigar box and roasted cocoa nib. The mouthfeel is ripe and lush, with firm, gripping tannins providing balance and structure, lingering long on the finish. Drink now–2020.',125,NULL,0,'Vinified and Bottled on L\'Ormarins',197456),
(283111,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Zk0uchRVS6Czz0T5dD_f5g_pb_x960.png','Soft, jammy, forward wine, that exhibits sweet strawberries, a generous structure, and only light tannins. Drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Adélie Les Champs Martin Premier Cru',196775),
(283166,218426,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3zgBRy6aSXi-pawIfNmjeg_pb_x960.png','The winery tells us this is a blend of Loire and Rhône varieties. It\'s crisp in the attack and followup, then shows its ripe fruit wit jammy apricots and citrus fruits. The finish is rather sweet.',17,NULL,0,'Summation',196751),
(283167,218046,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/n3UU-b2DTAiXxlyzPaMHfA_pb_x960.png','Crisp and fruit-forward with notes of wood-grilled peaches, mango and tropical acidity. The aggressive acidity and tangy finish liven up the round and somewhat heavy mouthfeel. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'Roodeberg',196839),
(283208,222367,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Extremely floral on the nose and well structured in the mouth, this pretty white wine from Sardinia offers aromas of yellow rose, vanilla bean and almond paste. There\'s enough density here to pair with pistachio-encrusted sole or sea bream.',NULL,NULL,0,'Entemari',197281),
(283231,223231,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 37% Pinotage, 27% Cabernet Sauvignon, 27% Merlot and 9% Shiraz is dense and concentrated, with deep aromas and flavors of fleshy black plum, boysenberry, crème de cassis and fruit cake. The lush, creamy palate is decadent and satisfying, with enough balancing tannin to provide a crushed velvet texture. Notes of coffee and toasted oak unfold on the close. Drink now–2018.',100,NULL,0,'Faith',196689),
(283298,223250,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Rustic and earthy with smoke, bramble, rubber, wild berries and balsamic reduction in the forefront. The mouth offers more berry and ripe plum notes, leading to a sweeter mocha dominant finish. Drink now.',20,NULL,0,'Dark Lady of the Labyrinth',197557),
(283329,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_5XwsOsiTvayp0iYXKBOiQ_pb_x960.png','This monopole within the Chablis grand cru vineyards produces top Chablis. In 2006, the wine is powerful, but layered with intense minerality, a flinty character on top of the ripe white and yellow fruits. It has concentration, a depth of flavor that is impressive. It will age well.',90,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Moutonne Grand Cru',196775),
(283357,223334,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This is a ripe, sweet and immediately attractive dessert wine, with forward aromas and flavors of dried apricot, golden raisin, papaya, honeycomb and gingered orange. Hints of sweet spice and toasted nuts unfold on the long close. It\'s viscous and lush, but with ample acidity to lift the finish. Drink now–2018.',55,NULL,0,'T Noble Late Harvest',196839),
(283371,222090,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A blend of 69% Cabernet Sauvignon, 22% Cabernet Franc and 9% Merlot, this powerful and dense selection features fruit-forward notes of blackberry, boysenberry and cassis that are laced with accents of tobacco leaf, licorice, pressed violets and lavender. The structure is full and weighty, with gripping yet fine-grained tannins and a spicy, toasty finish. Drink now–2020.',50,NULL,0,'Paul Sauer',197420),
(283442,217719,'other','Champagne Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/47OJFOm5R6C6youjKGWZGw_pb_x960.png','The sweet edge to this sparkler makes it quite attractive and a pleasant alternative to the more common dry styles typically served today. The nose offers notes of toast, apple skins and pineapple core while the mouth shows riper flavors of peaches and cream and a hint of honey. Overall, a fun and well-balanced semi-sweet sparkler.',16,NULL,0,'Bliss Demi-Sec',196845),
(283447,225996,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'A lovely sparkler at a fantastic price made with organic grapes. The bouquet is fresh and lively with notes of sweet pea florals, pear and peach. Light and soft in the mouth with faint ripe stone fruit and bracing acidity leading through to the crisp and somewhat tart finish. Drink now and with plenty of friends.',10,NULL,0,'The Ruins Brut',196845),
(283450,217719,'other','Champagne Blend','https://www.lavernewines.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Graham_Beck_Brut_Rose_NV_NEW.png','A soft, dry sparkling rosé with modest aromas and flavors of strawberry hull, white cranberry and grapefruit peel. Medium bodied with assertive carbonation and a clean finish. So juicy and refreshing, this would be an excellent choice for brunch or lunch al fresco.',16,NULL,0,'Brut Rosé',196845),
(283473,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/0cvwhOu5TDaGHA1VlflbfQ_pb_x960.png','This sweet-fruited wine is laden with white fruits and touched with pineapple yet still remains deliciously fresh. It is a creamy wine, toast flavors rounding it out, the minerality only showing through on the firm finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Clos Grand Cru',196775),
(283479,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zkXw45mESWmSWDK6cjPEbw_pb_x960.png','Big, fruity ripe wine that also keeps the flinty, mineral nature of fine Chablis. The texture is creamy, with wood over peaches and apricots. But the acidity cuts through this rounded fruit like a sharp knife, giving shape and preserving the true freshness of the wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Vaudésirs Grand Cru',196775),
(283493,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Soft and melted in the mouth, sweet in oak, and as as sugary as a raspberry tart, this Pinot is delicious. But it lacks structure and complexity. Seems designed to dazzle, rather than offer substance.',45,NULL,0,'Swicegood Vineyard',196642),
(283563,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A soft, easy citrus- and pear-flavored wine, just fruit and caramel. This is almost apéritif Chardonnay, fresh and finishing crisply. From the village of Chardonnay in the Mâcon region. Imported by Louis Latour Inc.',17,NULL,0,'Le Chardonnay de Chardonnay',197254),
(283568,222367,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Tangy and bright, this wine delivers a mouth-puckering blast of citrusy acidity, with a hint of bitter almond. Raspberry and peach notes help soften the finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Chiaro di Stelle',197281),
(283616,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/YYKCGu19T-OJ32pDnWlaaw_pb_x960.png','As a Corton-Charlemagne should be, this is big and opulent. The minerality is quite present, a fresh addition to a wine that has more to do with ripe, racy tropical and yellow fruits that fill the mouth. It is not a wine for aging, maybe 2–3 years, but is certainly delicious now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon',196775),
(283662,223265,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Ripe and forward, this attractive and well-balanced wine is delicious now but also shows the stuffing to evolve over the next few years. Complex yet focused, notes of apple, yellow melon, citrus zest, toasted brioche and beeswax mix harmoniously, ending with a long and evolving finish that transitions from bright fruit to lush oak and finally subtle sweet spice.',25,NULL,0,'Old Vine',197456),
(283691,218228,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/u-K4P6QlQe2Y8WuvE2Zrfg_pb_x600.png','Generally ripe, clean and fresh. Smells pure and spicy, with blackberry aromas setting up a crisp palate. Tastes a little herbal as do almost all Chilean Merlots, but the berry fruit and spice elements are uncompromised and uncomplicated. A likable value Merlot.',12,NULL,0,'Estate Reserva',196886),
(283787,227775,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A blend of 78% Cabernet Sauvignon, 12% Petit Verdot, 5% Merlot and 5% Malbec, this is a tight, focused selection, with excellent precision to the black plum, blackberry, dried raspberry and cassis fruit core. Well-integrated accents of leather, cigar box and pine resin add depth and complexity. The medium-weight palate is structured yet elegant, with fine-grain, lingering tannins. Drink now through 2020.',44,NULL,0,'Director\'s Reserve',196689),
(283815,217780,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/SPQOyEN8Tb2q2KURgcEYfQ_pb_600x600.png','Slightly funky and pickled, but also dusty and endowed with raspberry and plum aromas. The palate rests on tangy rhubarb and nectarine, while the bouncy mouthfeel has spritz and kick. If not for the pickled rhubarb character, it would be more strongly recommended.',12,NULL,0,'Rosado Soul',196857),
(283883,227789,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'“The Affair” refers to the relationship between the French and Italian varieties in the blend. Sadly, this isn\'t the hottest affair, with the strong game, red currant, strawberry hull, milk chocolate and smoky dried salami notes all downplayed by the lean mouth and waxy finish.',28,NULL,0,'Temptation The Affair',196793),
(283887,223130,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A delicate, floral white, this offers immediate aromas of orange blossom and honeysuckle that accent the white melon and apple fruit tones. The linear palate is well cut with laser-like precision through the green plum and apple flavors, followed by a kiss of toast on finish.',30,NULL,0,'Five Generations',197547),
(283957,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Q04HvSnxQwKKoe0MMo-piQ_pb_x960.png','Lightly herbal on the nose, but overall there\'s more ripe berry and toasty chocolate aromas than green. Full, meaty and deep for a value-priced wine, with blackberry and black plum flavors along with a pinch of oregano and basil. Shows good weight and balance throughout. Impressive for a 50,000-case product.',8,NULL,0,'Xplorador',196852),
(284033,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/tmSQm9xpRoij3QZvYyezuA_pb_x960.png','The fruit here is attractive, pears and white currants on top of pink grapefruit and orange zest. It shows its structure and its tense minerality only slowly, allowing the acidity to give it a lift and vibrancy. This is a wine that is still young, still smoothing out its hard edges.',47,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Vaucopins Premier Cru',196775),
(284043,221639,'other','Tinto del Pais',NULL,'Ripe blackberry, graphite and tobacco aromas become oakier with airing, making resin, vanilla and mocha notes rise up. The wine is lush and weighty in the mouth, with loamy, baked flavors of black fruits, raisin, herbs and chocolate. A smooth, textured finish is home to licorice and sweet berry flavors. Drink now through 2017.',45,NULL,0,'Alfa Spiga',196852),
(284079,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A rich, somewhat heavy but delicious wine. High alcohol gives it plenty of body, housing blackberry, currant, cocoa, pepper and cedar flavors. A good buy for an upscale barbecue wine.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 194',196620),
(284080,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Bright, brisk acidity saves the day with this Chardonnay, giving it a zesty crunch and making the pineapple, orange and oak flavors, which are pretty sweet, taste drier than they really are. An easy-drinking Chard at a fair price.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 238',196620),
(284160,217780,'other','Cabernet Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/NW470j1pTfO2gOoyq0HI9w_pb_x600.png','Big and saturated is the best way to describe this mammoth blend of Cabernet, Carmenère and Cab Franc. It\'s full of ripe fruit, coconut and cassis on the nose. Next up is a pure, bulky palate of raspberry, plum and vanilla. There\'s some sweet, resiny oak notes if you dig deep, but overall it is a high-end, structured red blend. Drink now through 2012.',37,NULL,0,'Catalina',196857),
(284185,223676,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This starts off sweet and unctuous, with scents of superripe nectarine and apricot that flood the bouquet, followed by hints of baking spice, lightly toasted nuts and honey. The full, round texture is balanced by refreshing acidity that carries through to the long, bright finish. Drink now–2016.',19,NULL,0,'Noble Late Harvest Bergkelder Selection',196839),
(284186,227832,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A blend of Viognier, Roussanne, Chardonnay, Chenin Blanc and Sémillon, this leads with bright aromas of fresh red apple, peach, tangerine and beeswax. Round and lush, the palate feels opulent and attractive, but with ample acidity to balance. Notes of ripe quince, baking spice and toast linger on the finish.',35,NULL,0,'Cyclus',197445),
(284189,223590,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This Cabernet-basred blend, with 13% Merlot, 4% Petit Verdot, 3% Cabernet Franc and 2% Malbec, opens with intense aromas of tobacco, leather, sweet smoke, cured meat, dried fig and fruit cake. Flavors of black berry, cherry and cassis unfold on the medium-weight palate, alongside firm, muscular tannins that hold on through the lingering finish. Drink now–2016.',36,NULL,0,'Tiara',196689),
(284259,222367,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Notes of pear, peach and honey open the bouquet of this fresh wine. There\'s a touch of butterscotch at the back that gives it a medium-rich mouthfeel.',NULL,NULL,0,'Silenzi',197281),
(284342,222151,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'A blend of 58% Cabernet Sauvignon and 42% Merlot, this boasts bright aromas of rich red cherry, currant, tobacco and char. Medium weight and well-balanced, with structured tannins and ample acidity. Spicy, black pepper and toasted oak flavors fuel the finish.',50,NULL,0,'Cobblers Hill',196689),
(284420,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Light in body and tart in acids, this bone-dry Pinot Noir shows modest flavors of cherry skins, red apple peelings and cola.',16,NULL,0,'Lot 326',196620),
(284425,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Oaky but simple, with smoky, caramel flavors covering thin notes of pineapple sour candy.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 132',196620),
(284484,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Firm and tight, a wine that reveals more structure than fruit initially, leaving the citrus and grapefruit flavors to emerge later. Then it closes up again, keeping some of the mineral austerity. Keep this wine for a year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Montée de Tonnerre Premier Cru',197408),
(284490,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/2_rs4mOfTqCVeykqzF2qJQ_pb_x960.png','A full-bodied wine that is rich and generous. It has spice from new wood, honey and buttered toast, as well as a delicious soft acidity that is mouthwatering. The fat texture introduces an apple and pear finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Les Charmes Premier Cru',196775),
(284685,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A smooth, spicy Syrah to drink now. It has a leathery, gamy edge to the blackberries and black cherries, and finishes sweet in fruity essence.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 205',196620),
(284811,222450,'other','Riesling',NULL,'Rich and seductive, this brims with dense aromas and flavors of baked apple, dried stone fruit, tangerine peel and a touch of lanolin. There\'s great balance between the round, lush texture and clean, refreshing acidity, keeping the palate fresh and lively. Soft nuances of honey-roasted nut and toast unfold on the finish. Drink now–2016.',20,NULL,0,'Noble Late Harvest',197462),
(284820,223590,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Beautiful aromas lead the bouquet of this wine, a bright and fruity mix of tropical fruit, ripe pear, white melon, sweet orange and a touch of honeycomb. The well-balanced, medium-weight palate offers clean notes of melon, Anjou pear and clementine, followed by a clean, lightly spiced finish. Drink now–2016.',35,NULL,0,'Chenin Avec Chêne',196689),
(284828,218035,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/U1yuELyKRI6z-dQYrv12MQ_pb_x600.png','Rooty, sweet and heavily oaked for a $15 blend, with alfalfa, green notes and a blast of root beer float. The palate is tannic and also creamy due to wood resin, with earthy, foresty flavors of olive, leaves, tobacco and mocha. Good but overly oaked and herbal.',15,NULL,0,'Limited Selection',196713),
(284861,223590,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'This delicious rosé is a combination of sweet strawberry and a touch of lemon crispness on the nose and the palate. Its light, elegant character is supported by a dancing acidity and a balance of ripe berry flavors and minerality. A great food pairing choice or stellar solo sip.',30,NULL,0,'Kaapse Vonkel Brut Rosé',196689),
(284967,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/1YMtScv6TYKs5GK1bCF2yQ_pb_x960.png','Spice, especially nutmeg, is a distinctive character in this soft, ripe wine. It lacks some definition, but is attractively round. Fruit flavors tend toward white pears, edged with toast, while the texture is fat, full.',90,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Clos des Mouches Premier Cru',196775),
(285100,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Thick and rich, with hedonistic black-fruit aromas and all the accents of leather, tobacco and olive that come with a great Chilean Cabernet. In the mouth, everything comes together in a commendable knit, and it doesn\'t sacrifice anything, be it berry fruit, herbal accents, tannic grip or acidity. Drink now through 2013.',41,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Old Pirque Vineyard Block: Las Terrazas',196852),
(285187,227975,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This easydrinking red starts with aromas of white pepper, clove and cinnamon and leads into a supple combination of juicy berry and tobacco/clove spices. Medium-bodied and ageable, it\'s a great red for myriad meals.',16,NULL,0,'The Old Man\'s Blend',197456),
(285256,218035,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Most 2006 Chilean Chardonnays are past their prime, but Montes Alpha still shows vitality along with rich aromas and flavors of pear, banana and barrel-driven toast. The feel is smooth and pure, while the flavors run straight to ripe apple, banana nut bread and buttered toast. Firm and holding steady on the finish, although it\'s probably best to drink immediately while the wine is still kicking.',26,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(285277,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EO3hDSssQDy82J7u9kI_aQ_pb_x960.png','Fresh and soft initially, this wine takes a while to reveal some mineral structure. But then, deliciously friendly white fruits surround this taut structure. The acidity is crisp, fresh, leaving orange zest and green fruits for the finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Vaillons Premier Cru',196775),
(285300,217719,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.winecellar.co.za/media/catalog/product/cache/44c2fe89da8a1ebfb2cbda58692b0b0a/g/r/graham-beck-blanc-de-blancs.png','Ripe Chardonnay aromas and a touch of spice lead the nose of this delicate sparkler from Graham Beck. The flavors of rich fruit, minerals and spice are balanced and clean. The wine has complexity but a soft touch, and the finish is lingering but light. Imported by GBW, LLC.',22,NULL,0,'Premier Cuvée Blanc de Blancs Brut',196845),
(285317,217719,'other','Champagne Blend','https://images.wine.co.za/GetWineImage.ashx?ImageSize=large&IMAGEID=266002','Delicate, yeasty aromas of honey and citrus lead this semi-dry sparkler from Graham Beck. On the palate, sweet honey is balanced by citrus acidity. A feminine, fun wine that will pair well with ethnic, spicy dishes and fresh fruit and berries. Imported by GBW, LLC.',16,NULL,0,'Bliss Demi Sec',196845),
(285325,218426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AgB3zXrRTvWrdj9lIUWrjw_pb_600x600.png','Soft and dull, candied fruit, this Cab-based blend also has a white sugary finish.',12,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve Meritage',196751),
(285362,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Palazzio is Testarossa\'s blend of various vineyards. It showcases a regional Central Coast personality, and a fine one at that. The \'06 has elements of ripe cherries, raspberries and root beer, enriched with smoky oak, and appeals for its silky, crisp mouthfeel. Best now and for a year or two.',37,NULL,0,'Palazzio',196639),
(285471,217719,'other','Champagne Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/72vKwARWSWqUeXQSfQDYEQ_pb_x960.png','A very pretty nose of fresh flowers, citrus and creamy toast leads into a balanced, rich Chardonnay-like character on the palate. Minerally, clean, fresh but serious, this wine is food-friendly and elegant. Imported by GBW, LLC.',16,NULL,0,'Brut',196845),
(285475,227426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Starting with a nose of fruity blackberry and cherry, this Merlot-dominated wine has integrated tannins, balancing minerality and an overall friendly character. Flavors of blackberry, pepper and plum are backed by smooth tannins and a lingering finish.',20,NULL,0,'Blue Grove Hill',197920),
(285551,217780,'other','Carignan',NULL,'A rock-solid wine with bright currant, berry and rooty, cola-infused aromas. The mouthfeel is excellent and integrated, with earthy, savory, spicy flavors of blackberry, cherry and tea. Long and savory on the finish, with complexity. Wines like this are what make the Chilean Carignan category worth exploring. Drink now through 2012.',27,NULL,0,'Amplus Old Vines',196857),
(285582,217335,'other','Syrah','https://www.winebid.com/Photo/Medium/1575722','A very nice Syrah, dark and dry and full-bodied. Although it\'s a bit young and thick in jammy, primary fruit flavors, it\'s smooth and balanced. With rich blackberry pie, chocolate, violet, beef carpaccio, bacon and pepper flavors, it should develop through 2011.',34,NULL,0,'Subasio',196639),
(285640,225095,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This wine has a direct and approachable feel, with bright, fruity aromas and flavors of black berry, cherry, fig and currant alongside accents of toasty vanilla and cocoa. It\'s medium weight and well balanced, with a solid structure and an enduring finish.',35,NULL,0,'Optima',197456),
(285743,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_600x600.png','As in previous years, this wine delivers earthy, proprietary aromas and flavors on a structured frame. The palate has forward berry and plum flavors, while the feel is rich, only mildly tannic and 100% healthy. Never does it sag, and with adequate acidity it doesn\'t lack for purpose or a finish line. Drinkable now into 2011.',41,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Peumo Vineyard Block: 27',196852),
(285756,222090,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Full-bodied with juicy flavors of berry and plum underscored by smoke, spicebox and leather, this blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Pinotage, Merlot and Cabernet Franc has an ageable and elegant character whose slight rigidity will soften over time. Pair with grilled meats, robust cheeses.',13,NULL,0,'Kadette',197420),
(285795,222607,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'There\'s a lush, decadent edge to this wine, thanks to heady aromas of vanilla cream, chocolate-covered raspberry and boysenberry preserves. The palate shows more restraint, with textured, fruit-skin flavors of plum and cherry that finish slightly chewy. Enjoy this now.',25,NULL,0,'The Ambassador',196689),
(285814,223835,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'The nose of this friendly but soulful blend is packed with savory spice, dark berries and vanilla. Integrated pepper and spice and big berry flavors give it strength and finesse. An approachable, stylish red that will pair well with spicy dishes—think grilled kebabs and Moroccan cuisine.',10,NULL,0,'Cabernet-Pinotage',196839),
(285819,224534,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Soft, savory aromas of smoked meat and pepper typify this poised red from Stellenbosch. The elegant, integrated style marries spicy fruit and minerals in a gentle but ageable package. Food friendly because of its acid balance, the wine will be excellent with everything from duck breast to filet mignon.',10,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot-Shiraz',196689),
(285861,219884,'other','Trincadeira',NULL,'Fresh and fruity, this is a wine that\'s all about juicy textures, ripe fruit, touched by dry tannins. Flavors of tomatoes, red plums and a lively acidity.',14,NULL,0,'Grand\' Arte Trincadeira',196807),
(285983,227832,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This is a rich and attractive Chenin, with initial scents of honeycomb, yellow flowers, honey-drizzled apple and soft pear. Round and lush, the flavors are ripe and mouthfilling, with flavors of grilled apple, honeydew, orange oil, sweet spice and toast that  linger through the finish.',30,NULL,0,'Anima',197445),
(286000,224517,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An appealing blend of blackberry, anise and smoked meat aromas is followed by flavors of smoked meat and pepper in this savory Syrah blend. The slightly oily mouthfeel and rich flavors are cut by acid and tannins that give it balance.',11,NULL,0,'The Wolftrap Syrah Mourvèdre Viognier',197456),
(286062,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A beautiful Pinot Noir, lilting, refined and utterly delicious. Testarossa stumbled with the \'04, but otherwise their track record is great, and the \'06 is right up there with the marvelous \'05 and \'03. The wine\'s cherry, licorice and smoky oak flavors are captured in a rewarding texture of silk and satin.',54,NULL,0,'Fritschen Vineyard',196639),
(286071,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://www.testarossa.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/20PSB_low-1-335x1024.png','Despite the pale color, this is a powerful wine. It comes from this famous vineyard that pioneered the Santa Rita Hills. Erupts in the mouth with cherry, currant, licorice, cola and vanilla flavors that finish dry and spicy. The tannic edge suggests ageability, which Pinots from this vineyard are easily capable of. Best now–2012.',56,NULL,0,'Sanford & Benedict Vineyard',196639),
(286077,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A little rubbery and tough on first sniff, but this pedigreed Chilean Cab settles with airing and soon shows exciting, fully ripe raspberry, cassis and blackberry flavors. The mouthfeel is perfectly cushioned yet intense, and the finish is ripe, smooth and composed. Ready to go now but should hold steady for another three years.',37,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Block: Las Terrazas',196852),
(286093,218228,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/FE15-o5KRiOoT9IngxkVhQ_pb_x600.png','Solid and deep, with straight-ahead, monotone aromas of cassis and blackberry. The palate is solid, full and offers nice feel and composition, while the flavor profile bursts with black cherry and dark plum flavors. Toasty and heated on the finish, with lingering tastes of licorice and burnt toast. Syrah with smaller amounts of Cab Franc, Carmenère and white Roussanne.',35,NULL,0,'The Blend Limited Edition',196886),
(286171,223641,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Here\'s a clean and fresh selection, with bright citrus, grass, melon rind and pineapple core aromas. White peach and nectarine flavors flesh out the medium-weight palate, with ample acidity to keep the finish crisp and lively. Drink now.',18,NULL,0,'Vintage Selection',197456),
(286251,218569,'other','Gewürztraminer','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/JIOK1aZzT06okCwn7uCESA_pb_600x600.png','With residual sugar of 22.4%, this dessert wine has fantastically sweet flavors of apricot jam, tangerine marmalade, gingersnap cookie, vanilla and crème brûlée, balanced with crisp acidity. The alcohol is a refreshingly low 9.8%.',50,NULL,0,'Saralee\'s Vineyard Cluster Select Late Harvest',196626),
(286258,227576,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An alluring nose of violets, berries and a touch of spice begins this stylish wine from Waterford. On the palate, flowers, spice and minerals unfold and mingle with elegance. The tannins are pronounced but refined. The wine will age and offer more as time passes, but it\'s a gorgeous sip today.',100,NULL,0,'The Jem',196689),
(286294,224555,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Black currant, red berry, tobacco and spice give this robust wine a masculine edge. Luscious berry combined with savory spice and leather is backed by rich, sturdy tannins and a long, serious finish. Can age, but is excellent to drink now.',37,NULL,0,'Lapa',196839),
(286365,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Although the wine is labeled a Vineyard Designate, it\'s a blend of multiple vineyards. Dry, fairly full-bodied and tannic, it has complex cherry, currant, licorice and sandalwood flavors. Drinkable now, it will benefit by waiting until 2017 in the cellar.',45,NULL,0,'Vineyard Designate',196642),
(286414,221639,'other','Tinto del Pais',NULL,'Rock-solid Tempranillo that wows with its richness and depth, but also shows a touch of ripeness-based sweetness that critics could see as candied and simple. But that\'s splitting hairs, and we prefer to compliment the wine\'s dynamite intensity and its rangy finish. Maybe a touch bigger and less complex than Fournier\'s AlfaSpiga, but still excellent. Imported by Fine Wines from Spain.',85,NULL,0,'Ribera del Duero',196852),
(286474,218035,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/r2DVop4gRG2FdzVVrZP1Ig_pb_x600.png','Dense and structured, with aromas of smoked meat, ripe berry fruit and a certain marshmallow-vanilla sweetness that comes straight from the barrel. The feel is big and grabby, with strong tannins framing flavors of cassis, blackberry, vanilla and chocolate. And it\'s quite creamy and sweet on the finish.',24,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(286482,218426,'other','Zinfandel','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjvr-zin-nv.png?itok=ePaYJQSW','A bit heady in alcohol, but dry and softly balanced, with picture-perfect Zinfandel character. The intricate flavors are of ripe, crushed blackberries, briary mulberries, black pepper, cola, beef carpaccio, and all kinds of grilled wild forest mushrooms and bark. Drink now.',25,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(286534,225996,'other','Viognier',NULL,'A rich and smoky Viognier, this opens with aromas of grilled yellow peach, melon and orange oil. The palate offers flavors of toasted brioche and almond to complement the ripe fruit core. Drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Made with Organically Grown Grapes',196845),
(286545,218042,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Ripe blackberry aromas mingle with spice and smoke in this Shiraz. The palate offers supple waves of dark fruit, pepper and a touch of vanilla. Fine-grained tannins and a lingering finish complete the package.',30,NULL,0,'Number One Constitution Road',196845),
(286553,228227,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot blend offers aromas and flavors of tobacco and plum with a spin of cherry. Hearty but elegant, the wine will age nicely for several years. Pair with like-minded dishes with a smoky edge.',24,NULL,0,'Classique',197599),
(286641,222668,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'This single-vineyard Shiraz from Fairview has both pluck and poise. The nose offers red fruit, spice and a touch of flowers. On the palate, rich, upfront red berry flavors are balanced with minerality, acid and a nutty oak spin. Good, long finish.',36,NULL,0,'Eenzaamheid',197456),
(286691,217999,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Made from a blend of Coda di Volpe and Falanghina, this has aromas of lemon zest, pine forest and Mediterranean herbs. The fresh, linear palate offers lemon-lime, nectarine and mineral alongside crisp acidity.',16,NULL,0,'Bianco',196908),
(286764,222091,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a Chardonnay that showcases the best of what South Africa can offer: fresh fruit, elegant minerality, good value. The nose of citrus and flowers is both flirty and sophisticated, and the palate is friendly but complex, with mingling fruit and spice. Everything about the wine makes an impression  from start to finish.',18,NULL,0,'Bon Vallon',196845),
(286773,222428,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Muscular spice, deep red berry and blackberry and sturdy tannins give this strength and elegance. The fruit is assertive and delicious, the mouthfeel fresh and the finish lingering. Could use a few years of aging for extra character, but today, a robust and stylish choice.',27,NULL,0,'Estate',196689),
(286780,218042,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'A soft, elegant nose evokes darker berries and spice on this subtle Pinotage. On the palate, pronounced spice and smoke is softened by luscious fruit and smooth tannins. A very pretty wine and an accessible version of a tough variety.',18,NULL,0,'Phanto Ridge Limited Release',196845),
(286833,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fKLM_albTgimoq25S_qYNA_pb_x960.png','With plenty of weight, but weight that is concentrated around a tight, firm tannic core. The wine has great ripe plum and black cherry fruits, brimming from the glass. The acidity is a strong presence, and with the tannin promises several years\' aging.',16,NULL,0,'Fronteira',196663),
(286838,223848,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This evolving Bordeaux blend offers beautiful aromas of blackberry, anise and spice, followed by a full, complex mouth of tobacco, cedar, black fruit and spice. Lingering finish. Pair with grilled lamb, or a beef filet.',20,NULL,0,'Quinary',197636),
(286882,222540,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Sultry, smoky oak accents the ripe fruit core, full of apricot, peach and pear aromas and flavors. Notes of vanilla custard and orange oil add depth to the medium-weight palate, with brisk acidity that shines on the long, spicy finish. Drink now–2016.',NULL,NULL,0,'The Renaissance of',196689),
(286906,222507,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A vibrant nose of blackberry, spiced meat and a touch of flowers leads on this good, everyday Shiraz. Spice and fruit are balanced by firm tannins and fresh acidity. A solid red for everyday enjoyment.',15,NULL,0,'The Old Cellar',197456),
(286944,222507,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A layered nose with aromas of grapefruit, lemon and flowers is the start of this poised and pretty white. Crisp acidity, great balance and fresh, approachable fruit come together to offer an elegant, reliable sip. Pair with spicy foods, grilled fish or salads.',15,NULL,0,'The Steppe Buzzard',197456),
(286953,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/nFLCd9AbRzGcq5W4YRdXow_pb_x960.png','Fresh, jammy strawberry aromas, followed by a soft, balanced wine, with tannins and wood in fine harmony. It\'s ripe, packed with berry fruits, edged with dry tannins. The strawberry gives a fresh aftertaste.',29,NULL,0,'Quinta dos Quatros Ventos Colheita',196677),
(286956,218569,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/9fb5zUJ7QLmUkrW7MYaUEA_pb_x960.png','This unusual and distinctive Zin has a silky texture and rich, finely ground tannins. The flavors range from classic black and red currants, mulberries, cloves and pepper to pastry flavors of coconut macaroon and fig cookie. Could easily develop over a decade.',48,NULL,0,'Feeney Vineyard',196626),
(287010,228295,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This white Swartland blend of Grenache Blanc, Viognier, Rousanne and Chenin Blanc offers a rich combination of pear and flowers with a nutty spin. Lush but clean, it\'s a sophisticated food pairing wine or an indulgent sip on its own.',34,NULL,0,'7',197368),
(287159,222450,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'From the cool-climate region of Elgon, the Cluver Pinot offers sweet berries and violet on the nose and an unfolding palate of red berry, coffee and chocolate. Restrained and ageable, the wine\'s acidity gives it food-oriented character; pair with game or wild fish.',65,NULL,0,'Seven Flags',197462),
(287169,223861,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Fruity, floral and feminine, this cheerful white blends Sauvignon Blanc and Colombar. On the nose—lemon zest, minerals and tropical fruit—and on the palate, fruity but crisp citrus flavors are balanced by fresh acidity. Want a go-to summer white for everything from grilled seafood to Indian cuisine? Check this out.',8,NULL,0,'John B. Sauvignon Blanc-Colombar',196845),
(287226,226863,'other','Cabernet',NULL,'This is an easy and clean selection, with fruity notes of cherry, strawberry and a touch of carnation. Light weight and brisk in acidity, this ends bright and mouthwatering. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'DMZ Rosé',196839),
(287272,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/aMGk93WAQFqrp4pdeoPhbg_pb_x600.png','Toast, coconut and pineapple all work the bouquet. It\'s zesty and healthy on the palate, with pear, coconut and baked apple flavors. Much less oaky than in the past, yet still endowed with a lot of coconut and vanilla. A very nice wine that runs ripe and sweet, as evidenced by the 14.5% alcohol.',33,NULL,0,'Amelia',196852),
(287341,227749,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This lively blend of Shiraz, Pinotage, Merlot and Mourvèdre offers a vibrant nose of allspice, black currant and mocha, followed by poised black fruit, spice and pepper on the palate. Medium-bodied with a fresh, juicy finish.',15,NULL,0,'Cape Blend',197368),
(287357,222421,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Fresh, spicy and floral, this Rhône-style blend of Viognier, Crouchen Blanc, Chenin Blanc, Pinot Gris and Muscat offers a zing on the palate with complex waves of melon and tropical fruit. Fresh and expressive.',10,NULL,0,'Goats do Roam',197456),
(287366,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Very ripe and exuberant, with powerful blackberry, currant, cassis, mineral and cedar flavors. But it\'s also tough and hard in tannins, and not showing well now. Needs time. Best after 2010.',16,NULL,0,'Lot 74',196620),
(287382,223506,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A new addition to Boschendal\'s line-up, The Rose Garden Rosé pays tribute to the estate\'s iconic grounds and garden. Fresh aromas and flavors of raspberry, strawberry hull, white cherry and melon rind recall sunny days spent outside. Light sweet-spice accents carry through the refreshing finish, ending clean and mouthwatering.',13,NULL,0,'The Rose Garden',197456),
(287410,222607,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A strong black pepper element leads on the nose of this spicy Shiraz from Stellenbosch. On the palate, robust red fruit and pepper and good tannic structure offer ageability and a good, everyday red for grilled meat and spicy dishes.',9,NULL,0,'Oak Lane',196689),
(287488,222821,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Cinnamon, plum, blackberry and cedar aromas start this rich but poised red. Savory flavors of black fruit and spice are accompanied by fine, chalky tannins. Pair with lamb, richer fare.',34,NULL,0,'Bonne Nouvelle',196689),
(287502,223506,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This zippy, fresh sip starts with tropical fruit and citrus aromas, followed by balanced citrus and asparagus flavors. All of it dances on a racy acidity. An elegant, world-class white.',16,NULL,0,'1685',197456),
(287510,224555,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Cinnamon, pepper and black cherry aromas start this ageable blend of Shiraz, Merlot and Cabernet. Flavors of plum, clove, pepper and tobacco are intricate and need to time to soften in the bottle. Overall, assertive and offering a minerally lift that gives it food pairing appeal.',15,NULL,0,'Frontier Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz-Merlot',196839),
(287611,218035,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/U-AFy_beQIWjD92L75WdvA_pb_x600.png','A good and lively bargain-priced Chard. Light toast, honey and pear aromas draw you in, and the balanced white-fruit palate is convincing. Sophisticated and with good acidity.',12,NULL,0,'Classic Series',196713),
(287620,228408,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Round and upfront with flavors of grapefruit, mango and lemon, this will please fans of a denser style of SB. Because of its structure, it can stand up to heartier dishes and hold its own well against spicy cuisine.',15,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve Sur Lie',196793),
(287625,228411,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Earthy, leathery and peppery scents on this Swartland offering will appeal to fans of a more grounded Shiraz, and the flavors follow suit. Berry and tobacco layers are folded into smooth tannins, but the wine has structure. It\'s a little on the rustic side, though with a good barbecue the edge might be evened out.',15,NULL,0,'Indalo',197368),
(287656,228422,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'The tart berry flavors here wear some cinnamon, chocolate and earth accents. Still, they can\'t rise above stronger bitter notes and sharp tannins.',14,NULL,0,'Reserve',197445),
(287762,217512,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/v_0EpOgtSxWi8dOmR_zPVA_pb_x960.png','The 15th century Quinta de Pancas, north of Lisbon, produces this 100% Cabernet Sauvignon wine. It has initially lean tannins, but the fruit has spice, black currant fruits and a tight line in wood and final sweetness. For aging.',10,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas',196663),
(287770,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Quite an impressive wine, especially from this prestigious appellation at this price. Dry and full-bodied, it shows black cherry candy, currant, herb, anise and cedar flavors, wrapped into finely ground, dusty tannins. Fine now, and could even develop bottle complexity over the next 2-4 years.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 164',196620),
(287795,228459,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Soft and subtle tropical fruit aromas are anchored by some spice on the nose of this pleasing but straightforward wine from Matuba. There\'s pineapple, lemon and grapefruit on the palate, and the finish is clean and refreshing. Imported by American Wine Distributors, Inc.',15,NULL,0,'Premium Select',196839),
(287811,228466,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This has some delicious heft in the nose, with all of the tropical, citric notes desired in a Sauv Blanc, but on the palate it\'s clunky. The mouthfeel is overly viscous, weighing down the lively flavors beneath. Needs more complexity, but at the same time, a lighter touch.',8,NULL,0,'Idube',197368),
(287917,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A very good, immediately impressive Cabernet. We\'ve never seen Chalk Hill Cab of this quality at this price. It shows powerfully oaked, ripe flavors of blackberries, black currants and spices, wrapped into fine, dense tannins. Just what Cab lovers love. Easy to find, with 8,606 cases produced. Drink now.',16,NULL,0,'Lot 140',196620),
(287929,217839,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Starts with intense black-fruit aromas and dark, smoky accents as well as baked berries, licorice and meat. In the mouth, it\'s a bit clumsy and amped up, with big tannins, extract and a mouthfeel that grabs. Flavors of berry fruit and mint are good, while the finish bounces toward a loud finish. Not what you\'d call an elegant wine; it\'s more about ripeness, power and extract.',41,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Rocahue Vineyard Block: 34',196852),
(288098,223590,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The Frans Malan red blend offers plush aromas and flavors of blackberry, violet, plum and cigarbox. The character is approachable but complex, with a smoked, lingering finish. A delicious house wine.',30,NULL,0,'Frans Malan Cape Blend',196689),
(288104,222690,'other','Rosé',NULL,'With its juicy, citrus, melon and strawberry aromas and flavors, this dry rosé is mouthwatering and a food winner. Good minerality, fresh fruity character and a spicy finish give it added appeal. Crisp and refreshing, with layers of complexity to give it character.',15,NULL,0,'Jess',196878),
(288107,228532,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This blend of Chenin, Chardonnay and Viognier starts with an assertive nose of minerals and spice, leading into a balanced, smooth blend that is both fresh and elegant. Curvy apricot is laced with a bracing acidity and the finish, minerally and clean, lingers. Pair with fresh grilled seafood.',24,NULL,0,'White Blend',197368),
(288308,228532,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This intricate blend of Shiraz, Carignan, Grenache, Mourvèdre and Viognier offers aromas of cherry, herbs, spice and blueberry, followed by berry and spice flavors with a refreshing mineral backbone. A more restrained style with a complex finish.',24,NULL,0,'Red Blend',197368),
(288309,222421,'other','Shiraz-Pinotage',NULL,'Rich and ripe, this Shiraz/Pinotage blend start with savory spice and red berry aromas, followed by juicy, integrated black fruit, pepper and complex spice. Good minerality and structure with a friendly, easygoing appeal.',14,NULL,0,'Goats in Villages',197456),
(288316,222507,'other','White Blend',NULL,'With its mélange of Verdelho, Viognier, Grenache Blanc, Rousanne and Chenin Blanc, this layered white offers something for most palates. On the nose, citrus, flowers and tropical fruit lead, followed by flavors of soft but vibrant fruit balanced with a citric, minerally zing. Complex but refreshing.',15,NULL,0,'Fair Maiden',197456),
(288320,223593,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A dense nose of savory spices, molasses and dark chocolate give this affordable red blend added appeal. Cloves, pepper, leather and a touch of smoke on the palate give it a masculine edge. Tannins are firm but friendly. Pair with grilled ribs, sausage.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens Cabernet - Shiraz - Merlot',197456),
(288322,222420,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'As the name suggests, this wine is all about peppery spice. Aromas of white and black pepper and red berry are followed by intricate, lively flavors of spice, leather, smoke and red berry. Grippy but unfolding, with a clean, dry finish.',15,NULL,0,'The Pepper Pot Finlayson Family Vineyards',196689),
(288352,217148,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Dried cherry, cedar-toast and cumin notes mark the nose of this Sangiovese-Cabernet Sauvingon-Merlot blend. It has a decidedly Tuscan cast to its sour-cherry-and-leather profile, and finishes dry, even and long, with hints of chocolate and plenty of toasty oak.',80,NULL,0,'Splendo Blendo 1',196642),
(288354,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Reserved, but with lovely aromatics, this Zin has tart dark-berry fruit and a slight nuttiness. Quite structured, this will benefit from a couple of years of cellaring.',30,NULL,0,'Gambogi Ranch',196642),
(288361,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Aromas of red berries with thyme and anise accents also show a whiff of acetone that bothered some tasters. After that, this wine is on very comfortable ground. Smooth and evenly textured, it has a balanced, even graceful quality often lacking in Zinfandels. Good length and mild pepper and spice mark the finish.',21,NULL,0,'Estate Bottled',196642),
(288365,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Decidedly lighter in color and weight than the Barbieri Ranch wine, the Saitone shows a bouquet of tart cherries, strawberries and herbs. Anise-tarragon notes add interest on the textured palate. Closes with dry, talc-like tannins.',30,NULL,0,'Saitone Ranch',196642),
(288441,226846,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This robust SB starts with a nose of cut grass and gooseberry, followed by a complex, spicy array of tropical fruit and spice. Weighty but balanced, the wine will pair well with more complex seafood dishes: think halibut or tuna.',10,NULL,0,'The Winemaster\'s Reserve',196839),
(288453,217265,'other','Petite Sirah',NULL,'A little lopsided in the mouth, with strong, jagged tannins. But it\'s Petite Sirah, after all. Shows rich flavors of blackberries, black currants, anise, black pepper and sweet oak, with hints of chocolate here and there. Easy to like now with a good steak or chop.',20,NULL,0,'Lot 167',196620),
(288514,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Dark cherries, plums, olives and licorice, as well as an edgy, chemical note. Lean in style, the palate\'s mixed berry flavors have olive accents. Finishes long, with firm tannins and tart acidity.',30,NULL,0,'Papera Ranch',196642),
(288516,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A solid foundation of ripe dark-cherry fruit adds vanilla, toast and cinnamon accents that work to create a full bouquet and palate. This Pinot has character and complexity. Finishes long, with licorice and mineral elements playing off the dry cherry flavors. Editors\' Choice.',21,NULL,0,'Estate Bottled',196642),
(288617,228627,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The Marklew red blend exhibits a nose of vanilla, black fruit and spice, followed by a balanced, elegant array of black fruit, currants and warming spice. Good tannic structure and a lingering finish seal the deal.',40,NULL,0,'Capensis',197420),
(288641,222421,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Red fruit, cassis and spice abound in this medium-bodied blend, whose mouthfeel is full but spicy. Balanced and full of fruit but displaying a dry, clean style overall, the wine is fun and easygoing.',10,NULL,0,'Goats do Roam',197456),
(288645,226846,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A sultry nose of pepper, jammy berry and plum is touched with a little barnyard earthiness in this distinctive Shiraz. Leather, pepper and smoke, paired with firm tannins, unfold on the palate. Pair with grilled, spicy ribs.',20,NULL,0,'Manor House',196839),
(288650,224623,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This light-bodied white starts with a nose of tropical fruit and citrus, leading in to flavors of creamy pineapple and fruit lifted by a crisp acidity. The wine has a lively character with a peppery spin. Pair with grilled seafood, fresh oysters.',11,NULL,0,'Vineyard Creations',196839),
(288652,223593,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Balanced and fresh, with aromas and flavors of citrus, spice and honey, this flirty Chardonnay has some toasty weight that gives it a shot with heavier dishes.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens',197456),
(288742,223641,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Herbal citrus and asparagus aromas lead this plucky white from Spier. On the palate, fresh, clean citrus and slate mingles with grass and fresh fruit. An excellent warm weather sip: pair with seafood and poultry dishes.',20,NULL,0,'Private Collection',197456),
(288861,223791,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'An alluring nose of black cherry, cedar, cinnamon and anise leads this friendly, ageable Cabernet. Cedar, spice and tobacco unfurl on the tongue, offering a classic style red with food-friendly restraint. An elegant sip suitable for lamb, beef or aged cheeses.',22,NULL,0,'Fantail',196839),
(288950,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is the winery\'s top Pinot, Our Finest Stuff. It\'s nice and dry, with crisp acidity and firm tannins framing cherry cola flavors, but it\'s not particularly complex or ageworthy. Needs greater force, power and concentration for a reserve bottling.',38,NULL,0,'O.F.S.',196642),
(288973,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a big, delicious mèlange of pineapple, pears, buttered popcorn and coconut vying with mineral and toasty oak elements. Fat and friendly, it\'s got the goods to hold the taster\'s interest. The “California Cuvée” designation means that it\'s made of fruit from many places—more proof that good bottles are not all vineyard designates or single AVA wines. Enjoy now and over the next two years.',42,NULL,0,'Signature Reserve',196639),
(289055,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kj_gr_nv_chard_outshinery_.png?itok=OoQ8hnzn','Bright pear, peach, pineapple, ginger snap and floral notes grace a fresh, fragrant nose. The palate\'s exotic tropical fruit, ginger and lychee nut flavors mingle beautifully in a medium-full, though perhaps slightly sweet, package. Elegant and appealingly fresh.',35,NULL,0,'Great Estates',196751),
(289061,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/UJa4TsiKSq-c5R-Nz7-WYQ_pb_600x600.png','Taste this wine and you\'ll agree: It\'s big. Even fat. A fragrant, buttery apple-floral bouquet opens into a banana, orange and hay palate. The mouthfeel is creamy, round and lively—it\'s full-flavored without being too weighty. Pear and butterscotch linger on the finish.',60,NULL,0,'Stature',196751),
(289113,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot','https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-w7646mtz5d/images/stencil/1280x1280/products/358/655/kjvr-merlot-nv__86243.1637611921.png?c=1','Marked by exceedingly ripe fruit, this wine explodes with sweet blackberry, cherry and chocolate flavors. It has a smooth mouthfeel and a soft finish.',10,NULL,0,'Collage',196751),
(289204,218426,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/edhH-eATTu-PJKLoqLQRiw_pb_600x600.png','A little too strong in feline spray character, but nicely dry and crisp, with citrus, gooseberry and vanilla flavors.',20,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(289287,222652,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A nose of peppery, spiced meat and smoke leads into this savory, spicy red. A full, appealing mouthfeel gives the wine character, but the flavors are a touch rustic. Needs more balance and finesse, but overall, a good everyday sip.',13,NULL,0,'Starlette Rouge',196839),
(289438,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Doesn\'t show the polish and drama you expect from a Howell Mountain Cab, but it\'s a pretty good wine, and there aren\'t many Cabs at this price off the mountain. It\'s a little vegetal. If you can get past that, it has sturdy tannins and some good black currant and cedar flavors.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 143',196620),
(289449,217512,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Bright citrus crispness on this young, lively wine. It has a creamy texture, pierced with fresh acidity, with extra weight from some peach juice flavors.',10,NULL,0,'Pancas',196663),
(289517,217265,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Boasting typical passion fruit and herb aromas in a light- to medium-bodied format, this is a decent value in low-end Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc. Crisp and herbal on the finish.',11,NULL,0,'Lot 26',196620),
(289525,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This sleek, elegant wine opens with a crisp bouquet of limes, nuts and toast. Subtle orange and stony mineral flavors sit atop a taut structure, making this archetypal Puligny. Firm acidity and a long, complex mineral finish make this young thoroughbred a champion. Editors\' Choice.',50,NULL,0,'1 er Cru Les Champs Gains',197408),
(289568,217839,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zQFARgjIQyeDeSpa9lR8dQ_pb_600x600.png','Powdery fruit and air freshener aromas are probably the best part of this narrow, unfriendly rosé. Sour citrus flavors rest on lemon, while the palate is piercingly acidic. A lot of work needs to be done to make this a worthy summer rosé.',11,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve Shiraz',196852),
(289624,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Peach, orange and spice aromas and flavors, a buttery, full mouthfeel and nicely utilized oak all combine to create a harmonious impression. Ripe apple and butterscotch flavors show good weight. The long toasty finish maintains harmony and balance all the way.',50,NULL,0,'1 er Cru Charmes',197408),
(289958,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/7Uy3fDEOSkKcFqW5YBNDlw_pb_600x600.png','Made in a softly flamboyant style, with massive flavors of citrus and tropical fruits, buttered toast, cinnamon and crème brûlée, firmed with stony minerals. Tons of stuffing in this opulent Chardonnay, which was aged in 50% new oak.',35,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Piner Hills',196751),
(289975,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Only 20% new oak on this wine, but it sure does stand out, dominating the modest fruit with a smoky, charry taste. Hard to like this toothpicky Chard.',11,NULL,0,'Lot 20',196620),
(290015,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Admirably restrained, with cream, apple and toasted brioche on the nose, followed by a crisp, lemony palate. It\'s light in the mouth, with a short, one-note finish of custard apple. Drink now.',14,NULL,0,'The Flying Winemaker',196620),
(290092,218228,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.hatchmansfield.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/Image1-ECSVR20B-1-1216x1536-1-336x1024.png','Red and black wild berry aromas mingle with sharper notes of herbs and slightly green ones. The berry flavors are lean, framed by well-crafted tannins and scored by good acidity. Finishes dry and and tart.',10,NULL,0,'El Ceibo Estate - Estate',196886),
(290384,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/IzU1VtbXQZeO-7ez2BrYLg_pb_x960.png','A firmly dry wine, driven by the dark tannins, only opening slowly to give ripe berry fruits. The soft side of the wine does bring out the lighter nature of the Baga in the blend, which has been tamed by wood aging. There is a final flourish of fresh black plum juice.',26,NULL,0,'Quinta das Baceladas',196677),
(290465,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From a parcel within the Chevalier-Montrachet vineyard, this is beautifully balanced, but a wine with considerable potential. It is rich, but thrust through with a sword of steel, giving acidity that offers a succulent counterpoint to the yellow fruits. The wood is becoming well integrated, offering further richness. For long-term aging.',660,NULL,0,'La Cabotte',197241),
(290467,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'This is De Loach\'s finest Zinfandel of their five new releases. In fact, it\'s their best Zinfandel ever, and one that defines Sonoma County cool-climate Zinfandel. It\'s brilliant in balance and structure, with beautifully sculpted tannins and fine acidity, and just the right touch of oak. Within that package are savory flavors of wild blackberries, picked at their peak under the summer sun. So easy to drink, yet so complex.',30,NULL,0,'O.F.S.',196642),
(290474,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'With its blend of Touriga Nacional, Castelão and Cabernet Sauvignon, this wine successfully blends Portugal and France. There is already some maturity here, the wine soft, with red berries and a leather tannin character. Ready to drink now, with a final fresh acidity.',10,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Branco',196807),
(290515,217512,'other','Castelão','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/EJrc8ggtTfWf8qyyLqO9tg_pb_x960.png','Starts with pleasant notes of black cherries,  leather, and a hint of game, but also features a slightly drying, stalky note that shortens the finish. Tasted twice, with consistent notes. Imported by Signature Imports.',10,NULL,0,'Tradição Tinto',196663),
(290661,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','An elegant style, the ripe fruit restrained and kept in check by the dry tannins and acidity. The flavors start lightly, but then the wine gives a fine intensity and concentration as it opens up. The berry flavors are balanced by the dried fruits, with a new wood layer coming through to finish. Worth aging for 2–3 years.',11,NULL,0,'Casa d\'Aguilar Tinto',196677),
(290679,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Couldn\'t be riper or more powerful in flavor, a Chard that just detonates with explosive pineapple tart filling, honey, vanilla and crème brûlée. Could use a bit of subtlety, but fans of pure Chardonnay flavor will be delighted.',32,NULL,0,'Durell Vineyard',196642),
(290722,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'From Bouchard\'s own vineyards, this is a fine example of what is among the most renowned of Volnay\'s vineyards. It has much of the generosity of Volnay along with a solid core of structure, bringing plum skins, dry tannins and red berry fruits. Calls for medium-term aging as befits a lighter vintage.',69,NULL,0,'Clos des Chênes Premier Cru',197241),
(290732,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A lovely Cabernet, rich and pure and quite frankly delicious. Although it shows those famous mountain tannins, they\'re softly refined and entirely drinkable now, letting the blackberry, chocolate, violet and mineral flavors come through.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 146',196620),
(290752,217310,'other','Baga','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KY_bjoP_S8KEjzBvJuxB1w_pb_x960.png','Bairrada\'s difficult grape, the Baga, needs time for aging, which is what has happened here. The result is a wine that is fragrant, not heavy, poised and fresh. The red berry fruits are lifted by acidity, there is a tell-tale Baga dry tannic core, but well in balance. A great food wine.',11,NULL,0,'Quinta da Rigodeira Baga',196677),
(290755,219884,'other','Arinto',NULL,'Crisp, structured wine, showing the fruit skin and bite that makes Arinto such an interesting variety. There is an orange zest edge, emphasizing lightness, freshness, finishing a delicious wine.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte Arinto',196807),
(290799,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Solid, foursquare wine, full of structure and fruit, bringing light tannins into play with black plums and sweet acidity. But the wine also has a lightness of touch, offering approachability as well as concentration. Age for 3–4 years.',69,NULL,0,'Taillepieds Premier Cru',197241),
(290808,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Fine ripe fruit here, with soft, sweet berries and surprisingly smooth tannins. The wine is rich, not heavyweight, but glorying in the opulence of Pinot Noir. The finish brings on the tannins again.',149,NULL,0,'Les Suchots Premier Cru',197241),
(290812,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A solid wine, showing some generosity and richness, the fruits displaying a fine balance between sweetness, dry tannins and bright acidity. It has some of the sensuous character of good Volnay, opening into ripeness. Worth aging for several years, but already offering considerable pleasure.',89,NULL,0,'Caillerets Premier Cru Ancienne Cuvée Carnot',197241),
(290855,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6cUexm7qTSOk-7sGuC8I0g_pb_600x600.png','From mountain vineyards comes this deep, dark, impressively intense Cab. Opens with a blast of new oaky smoke, char and vanilla, but once in the mouth, huge waves of flamboyant blackberry and cassis, black cherry and vanilla oak flavors unfold, with a meaty note. The wine is totally dry and balanced, and while it\'s drinkable now, it should improve through 2015.',50,NULL,0,'Trace Ridge',196751),
(290858,218426,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/RnOFjviuToiv7RWB6cq97w_pb_x600.png','Opens with a pure, clean, high-toned aroma, powerful yet delicate, of cherries, cola, coffee, cinnamon and smoky oak. In the mouth, the wine has fantastic density and concentration, rich in fruits and spices, but with a brilliant Pinotesque silkiness. Simply a marvelous wine.',35,NULL,0,'Seco Highlands Estate',196751),
(290862,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz',NULL,'A brand new line from K-J. This very attractive wine has lush fruit and spice flavors, with maximum extract. Tannins and acids all are adequate. What K-J seems to be aiming for is a new flavor, neither Cabernet nor Syrah but in-between, and they\'ve succeeded. Yes, it\'s simple and uncomplicated, but there\'s plenty of pleasure for the money. Best Buy.',9,NULL,0,'Collage',196751),
(290879,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A tannins-dominated wine, firm and dry. The fruit is relatively subdued, with a juicy character of raspberries, red plum skins and crisp acidity. This is a wine that needs aging to soften those tannins: give it 4–5 years.',145,NULL,0,'Aux Malconsorts Premier Cru',197241),
(290884,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a very pure, fresh and clean Chardonnay. While it\'s rich in tropical fruit, pear, green apple and smoky oak flavors, it\'s also well balanced. Shows brisk, citrusy acidity and a firm stream of minerals.',32,NULL,0,'O.F.S.',196642),
(290939,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/K9jw-wZyRxCZAl_n152hTw_pb_x600.png','From one of the highest vineyards in the Sonoma Mayacamas comes this profoundly structured, deeply tannic Cab, which also is quite oaky. Bone dry and relatively closed and astringent, it\'s of very fine quality, |and desperately needs time. Twenty years isn\'t out of the question to allow the nuclear core of blackberries and cherries to unfurl.',50,NULL,0,'Hawkeye Mountain',196751),
(290943,218426,'other','Syrah','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/VQ-WcxGnSO2X0tc8ZDZsww_pb_600x600.png','Pours dramatically dark and brooding, with an enormous burst of white pepper, blackberry and coffee and an edge of smoked meat and leather. Huge in the mouth, with masses of blackberries, plums, espresso. Bone dry, thick in sweet tannins, and long on finish. Drink now— 2012.',30,NULL,0,'Highlands Estate Alisos Hills',196751),
(290949,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5b9lewwUSe-rvqL2UJa4wg_pb_600x600.png','Here\'s an intense, nervy wine, brilliantly acidic, layered and rich. It has enormous lemondrop, mango and pineapple flavors and lots of smoky, vanilla-accented new oaky notes, and is creamy in the mouth. The finish is long, lush and spicy. This is a real palate flatterer.',30,NULL,0,'Highland Estates Camelot Highlands',196751),
(290960,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3rbgYVc6RUyVjJBQmWs51w_pb_x600.png','From one of the best Chardonnay regions in the state, a cool-climate wine with pronounced peach, apple and tropical fruit flavors and a blast of zesty, spicy, smoky oak. Clean and crisp, with a creamy, rich texture. Finishes with a vanilla note. The package is marred by too much sugar; consumers love sweetness, but this one takes things a little too far.',17,NULL,0,'Camelot Vineyard',196751),
(290963,218426,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/qicuK1S1QcS0vH-h78lrqg_pb_x600.png','Rustic, fruity stuff here, with bold fruity-spicy flavors. A galumphing wine that\'s big and boisterous; nothing shy about it. A bit rough-edged, it needs meat and pasta and similarly uncomplicated foods to tame it.',9,NULL,0,'Collage',196751),
(290966,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'One of Bouchard\'s signature wines, this is beautifully textured, a series of bright fruits, strawberries and sweet acidity. There are tannins, but this is lighter than in some vintages, a wine for short-term aging.',118,NULL,0,'Beaune Grèves Premier Cru Vigne de l\'Enfant Jésus',197241),
(290974,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Very pure lemon and toast flavors dominate this wine. It has crispness, intense freshness and lively acidity. There is also a sense of richness that is slowly developing and that will broaden the wine over the next several months.',102,NULL,0,'Gouttes d\'Or Premier Cru',197241),
(290983,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Give this young Cabernet a good decant before you serve, because it\'s a big, brooding wine that needs some air to open up. Right out of the bottle, it\'s tannic and dry, and the blackberry and black currant flavors are buried under a blanket of astringency. But it\'s quite a good, well-made wine.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 149',196620),
(291007,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A ripe, full-bodied wine, the yellow peach and apricot flavors balanced with grapefruit, spice and a pear skin structure. There is a hint of vanilla from the wood, with a final, enticing floral character.',15,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar',196794),
(291036,218035,'other','Gewürztraminer-Riesling','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3t36GVQxTpKNaA1MrJAQmw_pb_600x600.png','A spectacular dessert wine from South America; probably the best we\'ve had to date. Amber in color, with intoxicating aromas of baked pineapple and orange liqueur. Caramel, toffee, burnt vanilla and more cruise on the palate, all pushed by perky acidity. Sensational flavor and balance. A hidden gem among the world\'s best sweeties. Imported by T.G.I.C. Importers.',24,NULL,0,'Late Harvest Botrytised',196713),
(291037,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Only 300 cases were made of this serious mountain wine. It\'s tough as nails now, filled with tannins and acids, and everything\'s shut down in the driest way. Deep down there is amazing fruit and authority. This 100% Cabernet will live for two decades, but if you must open it anytime soon, it needs serious decanting and the richest, most imperial foods.',50,NULL,0,'Highlands Estate Napa Mountain',196751),
(291112,217148,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Wow. This is one big, impressive Sauvignon Blanc. It\'s the grass and gooseberry, and the acidity. The wine hits the palate like a bomb, dry and crisp and explosive. Mid-palate, the fruit emerges, peaches, figs, melons, limes, kiwi. This is De Loach\'s first OFS Sauvignon and it\'s worthy of the designation.',20,NULL,0,'OFS',196642),
(291191,218426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/LA9-C1zqRsK7WQUxatPQPA_pb_x600.png','This Bordeaux blend is certainly an oaky wine. It\'s made in a fruit-forward style, and seems lusher, softer and more accessible than K-J\'s other new release, Highlands Estates Cabernets from Sonoma County. Of course, it\'s also more than four years old now. It\'s a really good wine, with a flashy opulence that makes it appealing.',95,NULL,0,'Stature',196751),
(291212,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A lush, delicious wine, and one of the better Cabernets to emerge from this promising Lake County appellation. Dry and rich in tannins, it offers deep, long flavors of blackberries, cherries and chocolate. Fully ready now.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 168',196620),
(291283,223183,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Smooth and sexy, this trilogy of Cabernet Sauvignon, Cabernet Franc and Merlot offers a wood-driven nose with eucalyptus, brown sugar, vanilla and chocolate, all tinged with spice. The flavors of dark berry, eucalyptus and earth, while more subdued, still manage to convey  strength, and lead to smooth tannins and chocolate on the finish. Imported by Broadbent Selections, Inc.',30,NULL,0,'Tilogy (Estate Reserve)',196689),
(291296,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A mineral wine that brings an austere character as well as fresh fruit. Apples, pears and lime zest are all there. Attractive, open and ready to drink.',35,NULL,0,'Beaune du Château Premier Cru',197241),
(291361,222668,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'A bit of horse funk opens up the nose, but it never overpowers. Some fresh herb notes add nuance to black pepper, dark berry and menthol flavors. Finishes warm and spicy. Despite 15% alcohol, this wine is nicely balanced, with dusty tannins. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',34,NULL,0,'Solitude',197456),
(291366,217702,'other','Merlot-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A delicious wine, loaded with cassis and kirsch liqueur. The complex nose offers tobacco and menthol in addition to the deep fruit, similar to the spice and tobacco on the fruity finish. A wine to drink over the near term. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',22,NULL,0,'Mill Race',196689),
(291383,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This is a big, powerful, ripe Cabernet, brimming with blackberry, black currant and cedar flavors. It\'s not shy, but bowls over the palate with potency. Not for the faint-hearted now, and should develop over the next six years.',22,NULL,0,'Lot 116',196620),
(291463,218035,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/bJzYZJLGQOGCcWEwxYTtOA_pb_x600.png','Angular on the nose, with earthy, semisharp red fruit aromas that are undoubtedly Pinot-related. The palate offers good depth and only slightly jagged acids, and the flavors of raspberry are snappy and just a bit herbal. Dry, toasty and endearing on the finish.',24,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(291482,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A wine that reflects the relative lightness of the reds in this vintage. It has a layer of tannins, but they don\'t suggest aging; they are more a base for the attractive raspberry and red plum flavor, freshened by the acidity.',50,NULL,0,'Marconnets Premier Cru',197241),
(291483,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'A lovely Zinfandel, dry and elegant and balanced. Yet it preserves Zin\'s briary, brambly character, with wild berry, currant, cola and pepper flavors. Really savory and a delight to drink.',20,NULL,0,'Cool Climate Vineyards',196642),
(291529,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/50Yw4QDvQ1aV6b_FJBkZ5Q_pb_600x600.png','Gold and pretty, with apricot and butterscotch on the fruity nose. Thick melon dripping with honey is the primary flavor component, while the ripe finish is sweet and satisfying, and not at all cloying. If you like sweet orange marmalade, this wine is for you. Imported by Banfi Vintners.',14,NULL,0,'Late Harvest Private Reserve',196852),
(291569,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A good, flavorful Pinot Noir that shows exceptionally ripe cherry and sassafras fruit, balanced with fine tannins. It\'s a little on the soft side. Drink now, with lamb and roasted potatoes.',24,NULL,0,'Open-top Vat Fermentation',196642),
(291581,219884,'other','Fernão Pires',NULL,'Full, soft wine, with fruit that is rich and gentle. The acidity is what keeps this broad wine together. The green apple and white berry fruits add texture, with just a touch of spice.',9,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Branco',196807),
(291615,217702,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'Much better than a bottle previously reviewed, this wine shows ample tobacco, earth, and slate to combine with its admittedly green flavors. Its structured like a tightrope, linear and strong, with more acidity than many Cabernets of its caliber. It will pair beautifully with a pot roast, and develop more complexity with age.',59,NULL,0,'Red',196689),
(291617,229221,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Starting to show some age with a rusty color at the rim. Black olive and earth dominate the mouth, although aromas of red berry and some woody notes of spice and pastry shine through. With smooth tannins and a nice mouthfeel, this is a solid wine. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',22,NULL,0,'Un Deux Trois',197445),
(291619,229222,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'With powerful aromas of tobacco and menthol this earthy wine definitely pleases, although a medicinal note detracts a bit. In the mouth, red berry is muted by forest floor, tobacco and mint, and the wine coats the palate with some gritty tannins. Finishes smooth, ending with mixed berry. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',16,NULL,0,'Titan',196689),
(291717,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A natural wine made from four grapes. The nose has an abundance of black fruit along with leather and dried herb notes, while the palate, although a bit hard and acidic, is also pretty well saturated. Grapey, generous and flavorful, but a little rough in the mouth.',11,NULL,0,'Urban Maule',196852),
(291752,217310,'other','Tinta Roriz','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hTzqkrQsTHSenXY62-lt1g_pb_x960.png','TR stands for Tinta Roriz, the dominant grape in this blended wine (with Touriga Nacional). It is smooth, polished, with a spice and mint character, juicy and fruity. The tannins may be dry, but they in no way inhibit the exuberant fruit.',8,NULL,0,'Vista TR',196677),
(291803,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Call it Chablis-like. This Chard is bone dry, crisp in citrusy acidity, and features stony, minerally flavors of Meyer lemons and limes. Try as a richer alternative to Pinot Grigio.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 115',196620),
(291844,222330,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Dark red in color, this Bordeaux blend offers sexy aromas of chocolate and cigar box, and has earthy flavors of forest floor, tobacco with a nice spice. Aside from a bulky feel in the mouth, it\'s got the whole package, including firm acidity and dry tannins. Imported by The Hess Collection.',18,NULL,0,'Grand Classique',197445),
(291851,229286,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A blend of almost equal parts Merlot, Cab Franc and Cab Sauvignon, this wine has nice cassis and tobacco notes on the nose that translate to the mouth, adding some spicy earth and tart berry. Big on the palate, with solid tannins to back it up, it picks up some lemony notes on the finish. Imported by Global Vineyard Importers.',25,NULL,0,'Calligraphy',197484),
(291857,229221,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This wine shows good extraction with dark color and flavors of charred meat and black fruit, but also has aromas of raspberry and a tinge of green to the plum. The juxtaposition works, although the wine could use a little more oomph midpalate. Imported by DC Imports LLC.',24,NULL,0,'Roland\'s Reserve',197445),
(291861,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A blend of Baga and Merlot, the Baga giving the tight juiciness, the Merlot rounding the wine out. The wine is fresh, fruity, packed with red berries, with an herbal edge and spice from wood.',11,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro',196794),
(291865,218426,'other','Meritage','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AgB3zXrRTvWrdj9lIUWrjw_pb_x960.png','A fine, dry Bordeaux blend that offers lots of value for the money. It shows full-bodied flavors of blackberries, black currants, herbs and cedar, with a spicy finish.',17,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196751),
(291923,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This is a big, very fruity Syrah. It\'s almost over the top, blasting the palate with blackberry and cherry jam, blueberry tart, black currant and chocolate flavors. But then the tannins kick in, offering structural balance. Drink now.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 144',196620),
(291943,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hAa4DZV-ShSC4jfbYiF5ww_pb_x600.png','Delicious, almost dry rosé, with spice, sweet strawberries and a texture of bright berry skins. There is some depth here, flavors that go right through the wine, finishing with vivid acidity.',8,NULL,0,'Casa de Lago Rosé',196807),
(291979,217839,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Intensely purple, with aromas of char, shoe polish, coffee, black fruits and herbs. Thick but balanced, with juicy, fresh-styled blackberry and dark plum flavors. Combines chocolate and herbal qualities on the finish. Zesty, driving, a little lemony and nice overall.',12,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(291991,217839,'other','Merlot','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/07/cdd-me-1.png','Like most Casillero varietals, this Merlot offers good concentration and a mix of berry fruit and light herbal aromas. The palate is lively, with good acidity and zesty red plum and pie cherry flavors. It\'s a little tangy throughout but on the plus side it\'s not overdone or heavy.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(291992,217265,'other','Meritage',NULL,'Fruit fans will love the explosive blackberry, cherry, raspberry and vanilla mocha flavors of this wine. On the other hand, it\'s a bit obvious, with no real subtlety. Defines the easy, ripe California style.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 161',196620),
(291995,229307,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This wine has an appealing, roasted quality to the dark berry flavors. A roasted game note mixes with berry in the nose,  and comes through again in the mouth. Medium-bodied, with good tannin and a sweet and tangy oak finish. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',17,NULL,0,'Reserve',196689),
(292068,227535,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Golden Kaan is known for their bargain-priced bottlings, and this wine shows the extra effort. Ruby-purple in color and medium in body, this wine has typical South African funk on the nose mixed with stewed fruit and a hint of tar. The mouth delivers stewed plummy fruit with pepper, and a nice, spicy finish. Imported by Golden Kaan USA.',14,NULL,0,'Reserve Selection',196839),
(292082,218228,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_bxoe6kpRVOBF0W2t9sYtg_pb_x960.png','Definitely a dark wine with heavy concentration. Aromas are foresty and rich, but also soft and soupy. The palate is quite heavy and full, with reduced black fruit and herbal flavors. So ripe that prune and raisin come up on the finish. Has its merits but also a few balance issues.',21,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Estate Single Vineyard',196886),
(292105,219884,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Creamy, green plum- and wood-flavored Chardonnay, clean, somewhat anonymous. Hints of citrus and acidity help keep the wine fresh, giving a final, easy crisp finish.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte Chardonnay',196807),
(292139,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This winery has generated buzz in California for its value wines, and this is certainly a nice Cabernet for the price. It\'s not the smoothest ride, but it\'s plenty ripe in flavor, with rich tannins and a dry finish.',10,NULL,0,'Lot 7',196620),
(292147,227535,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Creamy in the nose, with banana and oak aromas, and yellow fruits and straw in the mouth. Creamy and soft in the mouth, this is a simple yet enjoyable wine. Imported by Golden Kaan USA.',14,NULL,0,'Reserve Selection',196839),
(292210,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The coolness of the site and the vintage has yielded a young, tart wine that fans of big, fat Chards might find lean and austere. But it\'s a grand wine for Burgundy lovers. Acidity is high, and there\'s a stony minerality undergirding the citrus, wildflower and smoky oak flavors. This is one of those rare Chards that needs some time to come around. Best 2008–2011.',39,NULL,0,'La Cruz Vineyard',196639),
(292228,222507,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Heavy aromas of roasted berry lead to caramel, meat and berry flavors. Despite the dark flavors this wine is simple, although with good balance. Imported by Cape Wine Ventures.',12,NULL,0,'Our Founder\'s',197456),
(292264,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Soft, ripe wine, with easy flavors of juicy black berries, fresh acidity and sweet tannins. A wine with only a hint of dryness, which is ready to drink.',8,NULL,0,'Segada',196807),
(292265,217310,'other','Bical','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','Initially a tightly textured, apple and pear skin flavored wine. As it opens up, it shows creamy, fresh fruit, with pear and white currant freshness, finished with green walnuts and a burst of acidity.',9,NULL,0,'Galeria Branco',196677),
(292274,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Full-bodied, soft wine, with pleasant, open flavors of melon, lime and ripe white figs. There is sweetness, emphasizing the softness of the wine. Pleasant and drinkable now.',13,NULL,0,'Alvarinho-Chardonnay',196807),
(292294,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A best barrels blend of the winery\'s various vineyards, which are numerous throughout California, Niclaire shows a balance and elegance that prove Pinot doesn\'t have to come from a single vineyard to be great. The \'05 is a delicious wine, soft and gentle and rich in flavor, yet dry and balanced. It fills the mouth with cherry pie, cassis, cola, Asian spice and smoky oak flavors that last long on the finish. This is a real crowd-pleaser, but it\'s not an ager. Drink now.',75,NULL,0,'Cuvée Niclaire',196639),
(292306,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/LwMdHK4ERTKmIDuI5YezjA_pb_x600.png','Sweet, clean and melony to start, yet a bit tart and citrus-heavy to the taste. Definitely in balance, with solid if commonplace flavors of lemon, lime and green melon. Imported by Banfi Vintners.',9,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo',196852),
(292323,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/07/cdd-cs-1.png','For a huge-volume wine, it\'s what we\'d expect. Controlled oak results in aromas of coffee, vanilla, marshmallow and resin in addition to cassis and cherry, while the palate offers generic fruit flavors as well as vanilla and herbal notes. A bit puckery and scratchy, but keep in mind that annual production tops 1.3 million cases.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(292376,229362,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Though  the wine has aromas of roasted meat, dark berry, and clove, it lacks weight on the palate. Oak flavors overpower the fading berry fruit flavors. Drink up. Imported by Southern Starz,',20,NULL,0,'Limited Release',196689),
(292388,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Crisp, clean and clear Chardonnay, soft and attractive, the fruit on the citrus side, but with some red apple skin juice to make it richer.',24,NULL,0,'Bourgogne Chardonnay',197241),
(292389,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Fine, simple red Burgundy, with soft tannins, jellied raspberry flavors good broad texture. Obviously not for aging, but a pleasure to drink.',24,NULL,0,'Bourgogne Pinot Noir',197241),
(292424,223284,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Hits the fat and the lean of Sauvignon Blanc with both fig and grassy flavors. A well-balanced wine, it shows a smooth mouthfeel and a long finish. This is one to have with grilled fish.',14,NULL,0,'Private Collection',196689),
(292436,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A soft, clean, fruity wine, with spice and a fresh, aromatic character. The lemon and white fruit flavors are in an easy, apéritif style, with a lightly sweet aftertaste.',10,NULL,0,'Cabriz Colheita Seleccionada',196794),
(292437,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional','https://res.cloudinary.com/evino/image/upload/t_bottle_large,f_auto/v1/products/1649390-standing-front.jpg','A fresh, bone-dry rosé, packed with acidity, red currants and a touch of caramel. The wine is light, summery, good for apéritif or food.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte Rosé',196807),
(292439,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A fresh, slightly sweet rosé, that keeps crispness through its bright, breezy strawberry flavors. The wine is soft, crisp, clean, a summer rosé.',8,NULL,0,'Portada Rosé',196807),
(292454,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fKUwUaHPSKS8Lb-8200NkA_pb_x960.png','From Aliança\'s Alentejo Terrugem vineyard, this dense, tannin-packed wine has powerful flavors of dark fruits, a very dry backbone and layer upon layer of tarry, smoky tastes. Initially it overwhelms with its richness, but that softens and the acidity gives the wine a lifted vibrancy.',23,NULL,0,'Quinta da Terrugem',196677),
(292466,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Dry and tart, with fruit so thin it accentuates the alcohol, this wine shows how hard it is to produce a good, inexpensive Pinot Noir. It\'s properly silky. If only they could have figured out a way to boost the flavors.',10,NULL,0,'Lot 8',196620),
(292488,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Quite sharp in acidity, giving a bite of tartness to the dry flavors of cola, cherries, sandalwood and pepper. A good, silky Pinot for drinking now.',16,NULL,0,'Cool Coastal Vineyards',196642),
(292503,223183,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Earth and wood aromas open to a tart berry palate. The wine has a mildly creamy texture, but the fruit seems clipped with a slight green note. High acidity gives the wine an edgy feel and it closes a bit short, with more tart berry fruit.',18,NULL,0,'Old Bush Vines',196689),
(292507,222151,'other','White Blend',NULL,'The attractive opening notes of orange blossom and mild spice are quickly overwhelmed by an off-putting asparagus and sulfur note that just doesn\'t yield. Light on the palate, the wine finishes lean with a pronounced vegetal element. This producer has impressed us with other offerings, but this one misses the mark.',16,NULL,0,'Chameleon',196689),
(292517,219884,'other','Alvarinho','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/b_NPM_kvRuiNttiEMbKMaw_pb_300x300.png','Although it lacks the creamy crispness of Alavarinho from Vinho Verde, this certainly has the right lemon and cantaloup melon flavors. There is a lift and freshness to it, aided by the tight pear skin structure. The finish is a letdown, though, with a cardboard and green pea character.',11,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(292601,219884,'other','Fernão Pires',NULL,'A very soft, open style of wine. It has ripe white pear and spice flavors, but everything is muted. It is clean, fresh, with some lemon flavors just creeping in finally.',9,NULL,0,'Segada Branco',196807),
(292633,218426,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/z-PY-KodSdClra0AA0sBHQ_pb_x960.png','Only 500 cases were produced of this thick, tannic, complex wine from Sonoma County. It\'s cellarworthy and hard, dry and astringent now in dense cherry, cassis and mocha flavors that finish with wonderful length and harmony. You can drink it now, but you must adjust for the tannins. Otherwise, cellar until at least 2008.',40,NULL,0,'Highlands Estate Taylor Peak',196751),
(292659,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MrWbDNNxQRmlAb20rtfBww_pb_x600.png','This is what vineyard selection and winemaker intervention can do to enrich a wine.  Everything here is on steroids.  The fruit is deep and rich, the oak is smoky and spicy and the finish long and deep.  Pretty fancy stuff that might even improve with a few years in the cellar.',22,NULL,0,'Wild Ferment La Escultura Estate',196886),
(292669,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.alhamracellar.com/wp-content/uploads/7231614.png','Bacon and lavender are prominent on the meaty, slightly muddled nose, which unfolds gracefully if given lots and lots of time. Blackberry and some tannins up front, a fairly nice and buttery middle, and finally cola accents on the grapy, heavy, long finish. For years this was C&T;\'s top effort, before Almaviva.',40,NULL,0,'Private Reserve Don Melchor',196852),
(292671,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Will satisfy Chardophiles with its oaky, creamy flavors and notes of pineapples, lemons and limes. Finishes dry and crisp in acidity.',10,NULL,0,'Lot 101',196620),
(292712,228413,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Smoke, toast and red fruit flavors come together gracefully in this approachable Bordeaux blend. There are plenty of aromas and flavors to contemplate—think roasted lamb and black fruit—but overall the wine is one you can feel comfortable savoring with a big bowl of stew or a plate of cheese. The price is right, too.',20,NULL,0,'Tian',196689),
(292716,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/aNpjwkKiRmGgKfzdqV2_Iw_pb_600x600.png','A little softer than K-J\'s Camelot Highlands, but no less delicious, with similar lemon drop and custard flavors and a tinge of sweet, ripe pear. The mouthfeel is round, creamy and full-bodied, with a complex veneer of toasty oak.',30,NULL,0,'Seco Highlands Estate',196751),
(292736,217148,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Crisp and fruity, with lemon, lime, pineapple and spice flavors, brightened with mouth-cleansing acidity. Yet it\'s a bit too strong in those feline pyrazines that lend a green, unripe taste.',30,NULL,0,'Ritchie Vineyard',196642),
(292745,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3OMisWgFQzOohbmCKM8k8g_pb_x960.png','Partial barrel-fermentation shows in this wine\'s hints of vanilla and cream, which marry smoothly with grapefruit and melon fruit. The grapefruit shades toward pink, particularly on the pleasantly crisp finish.',29,NULL,0,'Terrunyo',196852),
(292748,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6iw-uaV1TZaIX7js6QQD-Q_pb_x600.png','Concha y Toro is making an effort to upgrade its entire lineup. This offering boasts copious weedy, chocolaty, black-currant aromas, followed by a soft, lush mouthfeel. It could use a bit more backbone, but this is a generously fruity wine ideal for early consumption.',29,NULL,0,'Terrunyo',196852),
(292749,218228,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.hatchmansfield.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Image1-ECHBW20B.png','A great price for a wine this rich and spicy. It\'s busting with ripe tropical fruit, peach, tangerine and pear notes, and spices, too. And it\'s dry, with just a hint of residual sugar to make the fruit round and forward. Turns really pretty on the polished, spicy finish.',10,NULL,0,'La Escultura Estate',196886),
(292751,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/rVk7J_ghSziUhA09t90ofQ_pb_x600.png','A refreshing wine, with nicely ripened fruit and exceptional balance, that\'s pleasant in every way and a super value, too.  The fruit goes beyond citrus into more deeply flavored apricot and pear, and modest sur lie aging adds creamy, buttery notes.  This is a lovely wine and one of the best values of the year in Sauvignon/Fume Blanc.',10,NULL,0,'La Escultura',196886),
(292753,218228,'other','Merlot','https://shop12458.sfstatic.io/upload_dir/shop/_thumbs/1875070917_El-Descanso-Merlot_HIGH.w610.h610.backdrop.png','Hooray for the fruit on this beauty!  Gobs of freshly crushed blackberries, blueberries, plums, espresso, black currants and vanilla are charming, and the flavors are every bit as lush.  Technically, it\'s bone dry, but it\'s one of those wines that tastes fruity sweet.  It has elegance and style that belie the value price. Plus, the tannins are soft as velvet',10,NULL,0,'El Decanso Estate',196886),
(292765,218426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/Jackson-Estate-Trace-Ridge-Cabernet-Sauvignon-Non-Vintage.png?itok=7bLPncQv','Dark, viscous and monumental, this Cabernet-based Bordeaux blend detonates on the palate with black currants, chocolate and cedar concentration, wrapped into the most perfect tannins. Outstanding, and should age for many years. Only 277 cases of this wine, which was grown on steep hillsides, were produced.',125,NULL,0,'Highland Estates Trace Ridge',196751),
(292831,218228,'other','Cabernet Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/snh5ReE0QOyx1Z7TofjCZQ_pb_x960.png','This is a very distinctive, even eccentric, Cab that must reflect its single-vineyard terroir.  The usual black-currant and blackberry notes are there, but the aroma is sharply dominated by an herbal streak, somewhat stalky or green, as if some of the grapes didn\'t ripen.  Tastes a little sharp.  Purists might want to age it for 3-5 years to see if it softens up.',30,NULL,0,'Don Maximiano Founder\'s Reserve',196886),
(292832,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.santaema.cl/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Cs_Detalle_.png','Boasts a reasonably complex bouquet of chocolate, cedar and weedy cassis, followed by a mellow, soft palate impression. The fruit is sweet and direct, just the kind of thing that would hit the spot with an impromptu meal of steak frites. No, there\'s not a lot of structure, but why age a wine that\'s so clearly made for immediate gratification?',9,NULL,0,'Estate Bottled',196857),
(292840,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/33IhbEETRayyFsYM0-l_lA_pb_x300.png','A gorgeous Cab that shows the density and concentration, but also the elegant structure, of a fine mountain vineyard. Dry and richly tannic, this 100% Cabernet has pinpoint flavors of currants, plums and cedar. Brilliant now, and should evolve through at least 2012.',70,NULL,0,'Highland Estates Trace Ridge',196751),
(292871,229431,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'The gripping, earthy flavors of this impressive Pinotage are true to the variety without frightening off fans of softer wine. Pinotage has a tendency toward angularity, but this wine, with its deep leather and coffee flavors and elegant minerality is accessible and, paired with meats like pork or grilled steak, will please palates overall. It needs to age though—at least 4 years.',24,NULL,0,'Hunting Family',196689),
(292945,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjje_nv_hawkeye_cabsauv_outshinery_cmyk.png?itok=TGVJBCtj','Shows the soft tannins and slight herbal quality of a top Alexander Valley Cab, along with low-yield mountain concentration of red and black currants, mocha and spice. Drink this polished, supple wine through 2012.',60,NULL,0,'Highland Estates Hawkeye Mountain',196751),
(292949,223590,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This rich, ruby-colored red goes in the softer, smoother direction for a Pinotage, making it more appealing to American palates. The dry, spicy Pinotage character is still present, but it\'s rounded by a softer, fuller blanket of pretty fruit. Simonsig gets it right and this wine will pair well with grilled meats or can be enjoyed on its own. Hold for aging. Imported by Quintessential Family of Wines, LLC.',30,NULL,0,'Redhill',196689),
(292987,217780,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/qn916y2oSuSGG0Yu_1KMlQ_pb_600x600.png','Reasonably solid and inviting on the nose, with clean fruit and a touch of oak. The palate is spritzy and jumpy, with sweet apple, pear and melon flavors. A totally average, easy-drinking wine, but in the end how basic do we want to go with our Chardonnay?',10,NULL,0,'Selected Terroir',196857),
(293084,229466,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Rich plum and cherry roused by a touch of spicy Pinotage and red fruit exuberance make this Merlot, Cabernet and Pinotage blend both elegant and adventurous. It has good structure and is hearty enough to hold its own against smoked meat and game dishes.',26,NULL,0,'Cape Fusion',196689),
(293172,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/33IhbEETRayyFsYM0-l_lA_pb_x300.png','Superb, opulent, just wonderful. Hard to exaggerate the beauty of this 100% Cabernet Sauvignon. Fantastically ripe and rich in black cherries, currants, sandalwood and spices, with a grounding streak of herbs. Beyond the flavors is the near-perfect structure, marked by smooth, complex tannins. Finishes sweet but completely dry, the paradox of a great wine. Drink now–2015.',70,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Trace Ridge',196751),
(293229,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'From the steep Sonoma slopes of Mount St. Helena comes this tannic, concentrated young 100% Cabernet. Dramatic in structure and flavor, with massively packed blackberries, dark chocolate and pain grillé. The wine was aged in 49% new oak, which adds smoky, spice overtones. Drink now and through 2013.',40,NULL,0,'Jackson Hills',196751),
(293237,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://s3.amazonaws.com/thewinespies-production/uploads/product/bottle_image/6845-78d5cac72d74b4e56846272baf4a1d6550e78145/large_bottle_image.jpg','Beautifully soft and limpid. So pretty and polished now, with ultrafine tannins framing ripe, dry flavors of black and red cherries, currants, chocolate, herbs and smoky sandalwood. Dramatic and opulent, this 100% Cab was aged in 40% new French oak.',80,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Raptor Peak',196751),
(293245,229482,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Subtle oak, strawberry, raspberry and mocha flavors come together in a rich swirl in this unique Pinotage. Juicy and smooth, with elegant tannins and a lingering finish, this is a very nice example of what South African Pinotage can achieve, and how it can please multiple palates.',15,NULL,0,'Broken Stone',196689),
(293288,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/rfOoZGyaSB6dm2-eRsesVQ_pb_x960.png','Beefy, burly wine, shot through with dry Dão tannins, dry and firm. The fruit is juicy, lightly rustic, with high acidity coming through its rich meat gravy flavors.',11,NULL,0,'Aliança Particular',196677),
(293293,218035,'other','Malbec','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/ZL8ZKI2cRqmeDwfciy8TWw_pb_x600.png','Licorice, mint and black plum aromas foreshadow somewhat tart, snappy fruit flavors. The wine has a good mouthfeel but registers a little short on depth of fruit and the sweetness that usually defines South American Malbec. Finishes with some vanilla but also acidic crispness. With 15% Cabernet Sauvignon.',12,NULL,0,'Classic Series',196713),
(293326,218426,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/Jackson-Estate-Trace-Ridge-Cabernet-Sauvignon-Non-Vintage.png?itok=7bLPncQv','Doesn\'t have quite the sheer ravishing power of the winery\'s Trace Ridge Cabernet, but this Cab-based Bordeaux blend is nuanced and possibly more complex and Bordeaux-like. The flavors are of currants, blackberries, cherries, anise and cedar, aged in 78% new French oak. Give it until 2011 to mellow.',75,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Trace Ridge',196751),
(293335,228413,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Cabernet and Pinotage give this a hearty edge, but balanced oak and vanilla flavors soften the punch. Add to the toast a mélange of blackberry, plum and currant flavors and the result is a classic wine with character.',16,NULL,0,'Akira',196689),
(293374,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AWqbAJ1bRbi81VcQtGMpEw_pb_x960.png','A fruity, juicy wine, all ripe raspberries and red plum skins. It is fresh, with a layer of dry tannins, but more fruit than structure.',8,NULL,0,'Aliança Foral',196677),
(293419,217265,'other','Garnacha',NULL,'This is nothing more than a few barrels of wine bottled by Hughes, a so-called “global vintner.” And like its Lot 128 brother, it is really good juice. Inky and floral, with blueberry and wild raspberry flavors. It\'s smooth, fresh, bold and finishes with mint and chocolate. Shows the positives of Campo de Borja\'s Garnacha.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 129',196620),
(293440,223582,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Cabernet Franc',NULL,'This alluring Cabernet Franc-Cabernet Sauvignon blend starts with aromas of black cherry, violets and black currant, leading into waves of black fruit and spice. Structured but smooth, it has a classic, ageable quality. Good minerality gives it an upright character. Delicious now, but definitely can be held.',30,NULL,0,'Donatus',196689),
(293441,217265,'other','Garnacha',NULL,'A fuller, more minty and deep Garnacha than Hughes\' Lot 129. This has standup, standout aromas followed by deep berry fruit flavors. It has plenty of body but keeps its balance, and the finish is thick and strong. A little rugged but really good by regional standards.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 128',196620),
(293447,223750,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Aromas of cigarbox, black fruit and spice are followed by blackberry, plum and pepper on the palate. Clean flavors, balanced tannins and minerality, and an overall easy-to-drink character recommend the blend. Pair with roasted meats, stews.',35,NULL,0,'Signal Rock',196689),
(293462,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Here\'s a tasty little country wine, rich in berry-cherry fruit and chocolate chip cookies. It\'s soft in tannins, and dry.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 27',196620),
(293476,218426,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Dark in color, with a black center, this is a big, intense, broodingly tannic 100% Merlot. The ripeness shows in the concentrated blackberry and black currant flavors that finish with a dusting of red currants, licorice and exotic Indian spices. Very good quality. Drink now–2012.',41,NULL,0,'Highands Estates Taylor Peak',196751),
(293508,217265,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Very soft, almost melted is the texture on this wine. Soft in both tannins and acids, which leaves the fruit and alcohol to star. The flavors, of blackberries, cherries, milk chocolate, plums and coffee, are rich, but the wine could use greater structure.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 24',196620),
(293510,223183,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Aromas of black currant, violet and pepper start this stylish Cabernet and Petit Verdot red from Warwick. On the palate, smooth, round and full-bodied flavors of vanilla, black cherry and cassis are complex but easy drinking. A delicious, chewy spice finish ends the sip. Pair with hearty cuisine like steaks, stews and roasted lamb.',15,NULL,0,'The First Lady',196689),
(293523,223005,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Named after a popular Afrikaner country dance, “straight arm,” this Pinotage, Touriga Nacional, Tannat, Grenache, Cabernet Sauvignon and Primitivo blend marries classic European flavors with South African spice. The nose offers blackberry, plum, cherry and pepper, and on the palate, like flavors are delivered in a structured, clean package that ends with a nutty, spicy spin.',20,NULL,0,'Solms Astor Langarm',196839),
(293542,229520,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This classic, masculine red starts with aromas of cedar, coffee and tobacco, followed by flavors of cigarbox, balsamic and spice. Expressive but smooth, the wine is one with which to unwind. Pair with duck, cheeses.',25,NULL,0,'Gentle Giant',197456),
(293550,223250,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Spicy plum and black currant aromas lead this stylish red blend. On the palate, savory black fruit and pepper flavors are poised and elegant, and not too big. Structured tannins and a spicy finish give it muscle, but overall it\'s a mannered wine with a touch of mischief at the end.',15,NULL,0,'Cape Roan',197557),
(293610,223506,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'This Shiraz speaks of its terroir, with its savory black pepper, plum and cassis nose and balanced black fruit, spice and cedar flavors. Full of ripe, rich fruit and tied together with an elegant spicy backbone. Pair with grilled meat or go spicy and try Asian or Mexican alongside.',19,NULL,0,'1685',197456),
(293640,223641,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Smoky, savory notes start this rich red blend from Spier. On the palate, vanilla, black fruit and spice flavors are delivered in a structured, layered package. Good weight and mouthfeel with a lingering cocoa and tobacco finish.',18,NULL,0,'Vintage Selection Malbec-Cabernet Franc-Petit Verdot',197456),
(293648,226799,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Black cherry, mocha and cola on the nose, followed by a balanced, bright array of red and black berries give this wine a fun, easy-drinking character. Good overall structure and length, with a smoky finish. The wine is a great everyday red choice.',9,NULL,0,'The Elements of Stonecross',197596),
(293719,223005,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of Shiraz, Mourvèdre, Grenache, Carignan and Viognier offers savory, spiced meat and citrus aromas and rich, spicy flavors of blackberry, pepper and cedar. Soft in style, the wine is well suited to ripe, soft cheeses and everything from game to poultry. Versatile and ageable.',30,NULL,0,'Solms Wijn de Caab Hiervandaan',196839),
(293847,217512,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Powerful and complex, this is solid and impressive, made from a selection of wines. It is dark, dense, full of blackberry fruit and dry tannins. The wood aging still shows in the spiciness, while the tight fruit flavors bring out the acidity. Drink this wine from 2016.',16,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas Selecção Enólogo',196663),
(293871,219884,'other','Alvarinho-Chardonnay',NULL,'Two complementary grapes produce this ripe wine that\'s full of citrus flavors and balanced with pear and peach. It\'s rounded and rich in its texture, with a touch of honey to go with the lemon acidity on the finish.',9,NULL,0,'Point West',196807),
(293927,217999,'other','Red Blend','https://campaniawines.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/Sirica-1.png','Sirica is a newly discovered grape variety that is said to have genetic ties to Teroldego, Syrah and Refosco Friulano. How it ended up in Campania is anyone\'s guess. Besides the beauty and purity of its cherry aroma, this bold red wine has been carefully embellished by spicy oak and chocolate tones. The finish is long, fresh and rich.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sirica',196908),
(293958,229582,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A light, bright and easygoing wine with clean notes of citrus, fresh-cut grass and lime zest. Lively acidity keeps the palate vibrant and refreshing, ending with a mouthwatering, tart green-plum flavor. Drink up.',18,NULL,0,'Nr 3',196793),
(293962,226846,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'An easygoing, approachable wine to be enjoyed now, this offers upfront notes of blackberry, underripe plum, cured meat and soft tar. A kiss of vanilla lingers through to the medium-length finish. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'The Winemaker\'s Reserve',196839),
(294040,218035,'other','Carmenère','https://www.vinello.de/media/image/d9/45/47/montes-limited-selection-red.png','There\'s no denying this wine\'s green character, which blends with aromas of hay, red berry and scratchiness. On the palate, it feels a bit syrupy, countered by acidity. It tastes savory, with sweet, chocolaty and barbecued flavors. It turns oakier on the finish.',15,NULL,0,'Limited Selection - Apalta Vineyard',196713),
(294085,217203,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Very juicy—intensely so—this is a wine dominated by red-berry flavor. It has a rustic edge with barnyard aromas softened by notes from oak aging. Acidity on the finish confirms the wine\'s inherent freshness.',15,NULL,0,'Pegos Claros',196685),
(294099,224480,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Forward fruit aromas of boysenberry and cherry are laced with accents of sweet smoke and oaky vanilla spice. These notes carry through to the medium-weight mouth, followed by a somewhat short yet clean finish. Drink now.',13,NULL,0,'Bush Vine',197445),
(294337,226862,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Bright notes of strawberry and raspberry are backed by suggestions of carnation and talcum powder on the nose and palate of this light, vibrant Pinot Noir. A fleeting flavor of watermelon rind comes and goes on the short finish.',15,NULL,0,'Unwooded',197599),
(294362,217512,'other','Arinto','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/XniE_rD_SKOSP6VwFyWZ0Q_pb_x960.png','Wood-aged Arinto in the right hands, as here, gives an opulently ripe wine that hints at the richness of Chardonnay. Yellow fruit, pear skin and a touch of toast are beautifully combined to give a full and complex wine that can age. Drink from 2014.',25,NULL,0,'Morgado de Santa Catherina Reserva',196663),
(294366,217203,'other','Alvarinho',NULL,'A superior Vinho Verde, elegant and full-bodied. The creamy texture is partnered with ripe apricot and pear fruits, a touch of green plum and a feeling of opulence along with the acidity. Drink now, or age a year.',19,NULL,0,'Toucas',196685),
(294662,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://campaniawines.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/dubl-rosato-1.jpg','Here\'s a pearl for sparkling wine lovers. This bubbly rosato is made from the hearty Aglianico grape, usually reserved for one of Italy\'s most austere and masculine red wines. Yet here the variety shows a delicate, soft side with notes of wild berry and creamy almond paste.',43,NULL,0,'DUBL',196908),
(294694,225668,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Green aromas and flavors take center stage on this wine, with assertive notes of bell pepper, asparagus, green bean, grass and flint. The palate is somewhat astringent and sharp, ending with a tart, saline finish.',17,NULL,0,'Life from Stone',196845),
(294760,217203,'other','Castelão',NULL,'Vines grown on sandy soil yield a wine that is accessible now. Full, soft and ripe with red berry fruits, the palate is marked by gentle tannins and an attractive burst of fruity acidity. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Dona Helena Colheita Tinto',196685),
(294907,217265,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Lots of ripe cherry and blackberry flavors in this soft, lush and fruity Merlot. Brisk tannins give it enough structure to accompany a nice barbecued steak. Or drink it with some great beef tacos.',18,NULL,0,'Lot 356',196620),
(294911,217999,'other','Falanghina','https://campaniawines.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/Bottiglie_DUBL-BRUT-FALANGHINA-e1467637226850-1.png','Made from Falanghina, a variety native to Campania, this sparkler shows heady aromas of white spring flowers and Golden Delicious apple. The palate is vivacious and refreshing, featuring apple and pear layered with hints of nut and pastry dough.',39,NULL,0,'Dubl Brut',196908),
(295019,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Full-bodied and ripe, this is a rich, generous wine that shows complexity as well as subtle fruitiness. A blend of Viosinho and Verdelho, it\'s full of tropical fruit flavors, with ample weight and concentration. Spicy accents, a dense texture and a fine, long-lasting finish are all part of this stylish wine.',18,NULL,0,'Andreza Branco',196685),
(295020,217999,'other','Aglianico',NULL,'Made from the native Aglianico, this rosé sparkler is a sheer delight. It has a lovely fragrance of cherry and hints of nut and baked bread. The refreshing palate delivers additional cherry notes, pastry cream and a hint of walnut.',43,NULL,0,'Dubl Rosé',196908),
(295032,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A big, ripe and spicy wine that is full of red fruit notes and gentle tannins. It is open and accessible, its fruit juiciness already a pleasure to taste. There is fresh acidity on the finish. Drink now through 2019.',15,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Catapereiro Escolha',196685),
(295210,217625,'other','Encruzado',NULL,'Made from Dão\'s signature Encruzado grape, this has ripe almonds, yellow fruit and a seductive perfumed character. It\'s a rounded wine, the acidity well integrated into the ripe character. Drink now, but could age a year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cabriz Branco',196794),
(295211,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'A soft, rounded melon and pear flavored wine. Very fruity, it is rich, smooth and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Monte da Cal Branco',196794),
(295267,217265,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A common, country-style wine, rich in cherries, cola and spices, with lusty tannins. It\'s lush and simple, but will rise to the occasion with a cheeseburger. The blend is Zinfandel, Petite Sirah and Graciano.',16,NULL,0,'Lot 362',196620),
(295272,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This simple Chardonnay delivers with buttered toast, butterscotch and pineapple-orange-mango juice flavors. It\'s on the soft side.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 324',196620),
(295304,217512,'other','Arinto',NULL,'Produced at the medieval Quinta da Romeira, this ripe, tropical-fruit flavored wine has richness and a smooth texture. Full-bodied and fruity, it shows minerality from the chalk soil as well as a bright, tight fruitiness and balancing acidity.',15,NULL,0,'Prova Régia Premium',196663),
(295344,222367,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This shows dark concentration, with dense aromas of sweet cherry, tobacco, prune and blackberry. On the palate, it delivers a ripe impression of sweetness and a soft, plush texture.',NULL,NULL,0,'Siray',197281),
(295352,217999,'other','Aglianico','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/lHkdxpcYS9iq53xMwKUEhQ_pb_600x600.png','Ros\'Aura is one of the most delightful rosatos to come from southern Italy. It\'s a concentrated bright pink color, with fresh aromas of wild berry and pink grapefruit.',15,NULL,0,'Ros\'Aura',196908),
(295412,217265,'other','G-S-M',NULL,'Good cherry, currant and cola fruit flavors in this Rhône-style blend. It has some brisk tannins and is soft and dry. Bring on the burgers.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 339',196620),
(295581,217310,'other','Baga','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KY_bjoP_S8KEjzBvJuxB1w_pb_x960.png ','With the French winemaking influence of consultant Pascal Chatonnet, this is a rich and rounded wine, bringing out some flavors of wood, while preserving much of the firm, structured character of the Baga grape. Just ready to drink, but worth aging.',28,NULL,0,'Quinta das Baceladas',196677),
(295588,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A fine Marin Pinot Noir, showing the dryness, zesty acidity and rich, deep red fruit that mark this cool, coastal county. Bigtime in raspberries, strawberries and cherries, it\'s complexed with subtle minerals, mushrooms and Indian spices. So elegant, with 13.5% alcohol, you can give it a chill in the fridge.',40,NULL,0,'Stubbs Vineyard',196642),
(295589,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fKUwUaHPSKS8Lb-8200NkA_pb_x960.png','A new reserva category from Quinta da Terrugem, this is perfumed with mint and solidly dense tannins. It has concentrated black fruits, very rich in style. It needs aging to bring out the beautiful fruit and structure.',29,NULL,0,'Quinta da Terrugem Reserva',196677),
(295722,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fiDjIQwbRNO0vMV0NSNe6w_pb_x960.png','A fascinating mix of Bordeaux and Portuguese grapes results in a wine that is both structured and attractively generous. Wood aging shows through although not excessively, the main character being the firm fruit tannins and black fruit concentration. Worth aging two more years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta da Pancas Reserva',196663),
(295767,222635,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This is complex and powerful, with its energy directed equally at the concentrated tannins and at the ripe damson and plum fruits. It\'s going to be a delicious wine—the wood element smoothing the firm edge. Age for at least five years.',100,NULL,0,'Epenots Premier Cru',197408),
(295822,217265,'other','Merlot',NULL,'Deeply concentrated on the nose with pure black fruit and whiffs of toast and wood, this Merlot packs a lot of bang for the buck. Full bodied and dry, it\'s mellow but bright, overflowing with cassis and black cherry flavors and a fresh, herbal finish.',7,NULL,0,'Frunza',196620),
(295846,223183,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'The mouthfeel of this wine is full and round despite lean flavors of tart tropical fruit and melon rind. The nose offers aromas of fresh herbs and green fruit that reappear on the finish. Drink now.',19,NULL,0,'Professor Black',196689),
(295986,227749,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This Chenin immediately draws you in with notes of baked apple, beeswax and softly toasted brioche. The rich, medium-weight mouth carries similar notes of spicy toast and ripe pear flavors. Full-flavored and easy to drink; enjoy now.',12,NULL,0,'The Den',197368),
(296100,223250,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'Dried fruit aromas of red plum mix with spicy notes of licorice root and woody spice, while the mouth shows more high-toned red fruit flavors. The tannins are soft and approachable with a dusty finish. Drink now.',30,NULL,0,'Renaissance',197557),
(296145,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/udbiO8fPQTq9JP9-F2cq2Q_pb_x960.png','Rich, ripe and juicy, this structured and fruity wine has warmth, ripe plum flavors and smooth tannins. It\'s generous, full-bodied, with an open feel to it. Ready to drink now.',NULL,NULL,0,'Herdade da Farizoa Grand Escolha',196663),
(296242,223005,'other','Viognier-Grenache Blanc',NULL,'An interesting wine, this blend offers a complex nose of ripe whole lychee and fresh pressed apple aromas countered by glimmers of beeswax and rose florals. More red apple unfolds in the round mouth, with a touch of sweet lime oil freshening up the finish.',35,NULL,0,'Amalie',196839),
(296294,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a taut wine, touched by yeast and warmed by ripe yellow fruit. Flavors of melon and spice from the new wood give it an open feel. It\'s ripe, already rounded and full bodied.',90,NULL,0,'Les Folatières Premier Cru',197254),
(296308,222635,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'For the moment, the tannins are still firm and the generous red fruits have not yet penetrated the surface. The acidity is present, like a line of brightness that cuts through this richly tannic wine. This is a potentially opulent wine.',90,NULL,0,'Santenots Premier Cru',197408),
(296320,222821,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Though the nose is a bit muted, assertive juicy black plum and muddled mulberry unfold in the round mouth. Firm tannins follow through to the dry, waxy finish. Try in another year or two, or give it a good long decant before drinking now.',20,NULL,0,'Aigle Noir',196689),
(296336,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Puckery sweet morello cherries scent this refreshing, medium-bodied Romanian Pinot Noir. On the palate, jammy red fruit is balanced by soft tannins and glimmers of granite, gravel and sun-dried hay. Not too shabby at $7.',7,NULL,0,'Frunza',196620),
(296363,217203,'other','Alvarinho',NULL,'Full, rich and creamy, a fine expression of the rich white fruit character of Alvarinho. It also preserves some of the crisp citrus Vinho Verde character, giving a balanced, full and structured character.',19,NULL,0,'Touquinheiras',196685),
(296369,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'The modern, high alcohol style marks this Chardonnay. It\'s superripe in orange, pear and yellow apricot flavors, with an elaborate coating of sweet new oak, with all of its caramel, honey and butterscotch elaborations. Flamboyant, and ready now with rich fare.',40,NULL,0,'La Reine',196642),
(296382,218426,'other','White Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3zgBRy6aSXi-pawIfNmjeg_pb_600x600.png','This has citrus, apricot and honey flavors brightened with crisp acidity. It turns a little sweet on the finish, but it\'s a lovely wine that should be versatile with a huge range of food.',15,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve Summation',196751),
(296420,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Browning in color and showing premature age, this big, oaky Chardonnay is at peak maturity and won\'t make it too far past 2011. In the meantime, there\'s fleshy, baked aromas and flavors of sweet pear, toast, buttery notes and resin.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 226',196620),
(296506,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/wOq6MEZ-TmKbNODdktHzfA_pb_x960.png','With vines that are located next to La Tâche, this vineyard is great. Powerful and complex, this has the right depth of flavor. It is finely endowed with brooding tannins and black fruit flavors. The texture and acidity on the finish promise this has considerable aging potential.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Clos Frantin Les Malconsorts Premier Cru',196775),
(296554,223334,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'A strong toasty streak lines the essence of this beautiful Chenin Blanc, adding character to the apple and pear fruit core. The mouthfeel is full and rich without being overdone thanks to the balanced acidity, while nuances of sweet spice, pie crust and wood-grilled Red Delicious all linger well into the long finish.',15,NULL,0,'Reserve',196839),
(296556,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Alvarinho away from the north of Portugal gives a much creamier style of wine and makes a fine partner with Chardonnay. So this is ripe, full-bodied, with tropical fruit flavors as well as kiwi. It has just the right acidity, well-balanced, worth aging another year.',NULL,NULL,0,'DFJ Alvarinho/Chardonnay',196807),
(296557,217310,'other','Touriga Nacional','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hTzqkrQsTHSenXY62-lt1g_pb_x960.png','From central Portugal, here is a dark, firm wine, perfumed with hints of violets and given depth of flavor by the year\'s wood aging. A warm, big-hearted wine with a solid core.',13,NULL,0,'Vista Reserva',196677),
(296589,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Big and fruity, this is very lively, balancing butteriness with green-fruit acidity. The wine is maturing quickly, its tension is fading into rich, wood-flavored fruitiness.',70,NULL,0,'Meursault Blagny Premier Cru',197254),
(296598,222635,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Big and firm, this is packed with red fruits and solid tannins. It has flavors of red berries and black fruits—the wood component still prominent. The acidity is gentle; but it does need to age for at least four years.',90,NULL,0,'Clos des Angles Premier Cru',197408),
(296628,223438,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A blend of 48% Chenin Blanc, 41% Chardonnay and 11% Viognier, this is an interesting white with slightly oxidized but rich notes of honeycomb, toasted hazelnut and baked apple thoughout. Medium weight with a touch of heat coming through on the long finish.',25,NULL,0,'Roulette Blanc',197368),
(296634,227749,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'There\'s a nice spicy character that appears throughout the nose and mouth of this wine, lifted by juicy black berry and plum fruit flavors. Medium weight with solid acidity and balanced alcohol. Drink now.',18,NULL,0,'Guillermo',197368),
(296686,223606,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The high-tone fruit aromas work here, lifting the otherwise dark and heady notes of mulled berries, cherry pie filling, cured meat and sweet smoke. Balanced and ready to drink now with medium weight and dusty tannins. The finish shows nice evolution from fruit to earthy tobacco and finally coffee.',33,NULL,0,'Penny Black',196689),
(296692,217504,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A very interesting blend composed of 50% Sangiovese, 22% Pinot Noir, 13% Nebbiolo, 7% Mourvèdre, 6% Barbera and 2% Shiraz. Nuances of leather and sweet spice mingle seamlessly with red cherry and fruit cake characteristics; the silky texture and soft tannins carry the earthy notes through the close.',36,NULL,0,'Hannibal',196793),
(296713,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/M5ZfaQZaTKqPwnWQxKuqLg_pb_x960.png','Bichot owns part of this small grand cru portion of Maréchaudes as well as the walled section of the premier cru section. This is dense, solid and powerful, and it demonstrates the dark character of the clay soil. A concentrated black-plum flavor is supported by firm, dry tannins, which makes this a serious, age-worthy wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos des Maréchaudes',196775),
(296714,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','An elegant wine, this has dark tannins and a sumptuous texture, which is smoothed by generous fruit and acidity. On the finish, a spice note and a dry structure promise that this will age well.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Château Gris Premier Cru',196775),
(296751,222367,'other','Cannonau',NULL,'Plump and round with ripe cherry and blackberry aromas, I Fiori is an easy wine to pair with honey-roasted ham or chicken in mushroom cream sauce. It shows balance and a mildly creamy texture.',NULL,NULL,0,'I Fiori',197281),
(296791,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/YWEk0NZxRiyoGMGZT7poBA_pb_x960.png','A rich and firmly structured wine, with intense tannins balanced by concentrated fruit. It shows the granite character of the Dão while also having spice and a full-bodied feel. Worth aging for another year.',11,NULL,0,'Reserva',196677),
(296829,222607,'other','Shiraz-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A soft, drinkable red with hints of sweet smoke and cured meat adding character to the mulberry and blackberry fruit flavors. Medium weight with low tannins and an easy finish. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Oak Lane',196689),
(296851,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Varietally sound on the nose but also scratchy and stemmy smelling, with a pickled element. The palate is tight and tart, with lean plum and red cherry flavors that coax out a gritty, citrusy, peppery finish.',15,NULL,0,'Lot 227',196620),
(296911,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AMBklm3WSkietnaXDMIfCw_pb_x960.png','This wine shows the structured side of Gevrey-Chambertin. The vineyard is situated at the opening of a small side valley, a location that allows the grapes to ripen slowly. This is elegant and structured, and it\'s full of solid tannins as well as cherry and red berry flavors. Age this for 7–8 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Lavaux Saint-Jacques Premier Cru',196775),
(296913,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Xj64b5SnRjyc-BPZV8_dhw_pb_x960.png','Close to the white grand crus of Chassagne-Montrachet, this wine is structured and weighty, and it offers juicy apricot and pear flavors. A citrus element cuts through the wood influence and the steely texture, which brings freshness to the ripe, rich mouthfeel.',NULL,NULL,0,'Vide Bourse Premier Cru',196775),
(296922,224517,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Composed of 40% Viognier, 39% Chenin Blanc and 21% Grenache Blanc, there\'s an attractive round richness to this wine. A toasty character spices up the fresh pear, melon and orange rind flavors, with a nutty accent lingering on the finish.',10,NULL,0,'The Wolftrap',197456),
(296928,217780,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/CS5CAKTqTDaPTVREgKt8EQ_pb_x960.png','Clean yet dilute on the bouquet, with touches of lime and grassiness. The palate, however, is kind of heavy and honeyed, a direct reflection of its warm Maipo roots. Tastes sweet and creamy but without much zesty fruit. Maybe a little too soft and candied, but still pretty good.',10,NULL,0,'Selected Terroir',196857),
(297014,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Crisp and elegant in feel, this has apricot and peach flavors that are balanced by the tight structure and the green-fruit-like acidity. The layers of toast have integrated with the ebullient fruit character and the taut, minerally finish. For aging 3–4 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Dents du Chien Premier Cru',197408),
(297017,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Round, opulent and generous, this wine has yellow-fruit flavors that are paired with lime-like acidity, creating a balanced feel. The toast note is still showing strongly, and it needs a few years to settle.',NULL,NULL,0,'Referts Premier Cru',197408),
(297029,223937,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'With 11,000 cases imported, this crisp, clean Steen should be easy to find and well worth the price. Light weight but filled with ripe pineapple and Key lime flavors accented by crushed white flowers. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Old Vines Steen',197368),
(297076,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Dominated by its tannins and a firm, structured character, this dark-colored wine is concentrated stuff. It has plenty of acidity that balances the solid, chunky plum fruits. Powerful, a big mouthful.',16,NULL,0,'Murzelo Reserva',196685),
(297138,222367,'other','Rosato',NULL,'This opens with a bright pink color and easy aromas of spring flower, peach, cranberry and grapefruit. It has a subtle impression of sweetness on the finish, followed by bright fruit flavors.',NULL,NULL,0,'Silenzi',197281),
(297152,223606,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Though it might be a bit direct and simple, this dessert wine is delicious and satisfying with decadent flavors of juicy peach, sweet spice and ginger bread drizzled with honey. The alcohol shows a bit after swallow, but the spicy notes take hold on the close.',23,NULL,0,'Treskilling Yellow',196689),
(297154,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Juicy, ripe wine, perfumed and the wood aging showing through. The wine is sweet, rich, the tannins well integrated into the powerful red berry fruits. There is a hint of maturity, with tobacco and spice flavors.',22,NULL,0,'Quinta da Veiga da Casa das Mouras Reserva',196685),
(297177,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/M5ZfaQZaTKqPwnWQxKuqLg_pb_x960.png','This Bichot monopole has produced a round wine that\'s full of attractive plum flavor. It\'s backbone is buried in the sumptuous texture. Age this for at least four years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos des Maréchaudes Premier Cru',196775),
(297183,217719,'other','Chenin Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/KlQexO11RPmogC2QkrlzEQ_pb_x960.png','Tropical fruit notes of pineapple and guava backed by accents of sweet grass and clementine citrus flesh out this white. Lively and slightly prickly on the palate.',16,NULL,0,'The Game Reserve',196845),
(297190,222686,'other','Pinotage-Merlot',NULL,'This blend of 70% Pinotage and 30% Merlot shows herbal notes of bramble and black plum skins alongside a rubbery accent. Medium weight with a soft, round mouth and a clean finish.',10,NULL,0,'Polkadraai',197491),
(297242,222635,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Mitans is one of the lesser-known premier crus in Volnay, and it has created a wine that shows the voluptuousness of Volnay. It has a smoky character, and it\'s laced with acidity and bright red fruit. It will benefit from 3–4 years of aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Mitans Premier Cru',197408),
(297248,222367,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Delicate and feminine, this rosé from Sardinia delivers clean aromas of raspberry, wild strawberry, white cherry and a touch of lemon zest. There\'s a mineral note at the back and the wine also boasts some of the herbal aromas that are so often associated with Mediterranean flavors.',NULL,NULL,0,'Silenzi',197281),
(297254,223606,'other','Chenin Blanc-Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This 65% Chenin Blanc - 35% Sauvignon Blanc blend is clean and fresh with flavors of green grass, hard nectarine and a touch of orange rind in the round mouth. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Blueish White',196689),
(297255,227749,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'A bit closed on the nose, it takes a while for notes of black cherry skins and rubber to appear in the bouquet. The mouth offers a bit more flavor, with a nice chocolate-covered cherry finish. Drink now.',12,NULL,0,'The Den',197368),
(297297,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Made from old vines (vinhas velhas), this wine has good concentration of green and citrus fruits. There is a tang of lime zest, giving a cool, fresh feel and acidity. Drink now, or keep a year.',14,NULL,0,'Lua Cheia em Vinhas Velhas Branco',196685),
(297301,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a superrich, smooth wine. The acidity is what keeps the ripe yellow-fruit flavors in order, and it has a lemon-like edge to the tropical mouthfeel. Age this for 3–4 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sous le Dos d\'Ane Premier Cru',197408),
(297309,224505,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Medium intense aromas of tangerine citrus and crushed yellow flowers transition to flavors of dried grass, red apple and a touch of mushroom powder. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Made With Organically Grown Grapes',196839),
(297350,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/YsvMCqEcSTeS2y3FhkzuYA_pb_x600.png','Standard berry, plum and herb aromas set up a gummy-feeling palate, with a berry flavor and a hint of fine herbs. It shows texture and a black olive flavor on the finish.',9,NULL,0,'Selected Terroir',196857),
(297369,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A really nice wine, showing the generosity and sheer sexiness that Pinot Noir can offer. With a silky mouthfeel, it has expansive flavors of raspberry and cherry jam, orange zest, vanilla, cinnamon and sandalwood. One of the best Pinots on the market at this price, and easy to find, with 20,000 cases produced.',15,NULL,0,'Heritage Reserve',196642),
(297370,219884,'other','Arinto',NULL,'Arinto, sometimes used in sparkling wine, creates a bright, crisp, lime-flavored wine. It is powered by its acidity and the apple skin texture, all the fruit coming right to the front.',11,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(297380,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/w5gFmpwYSkm9oo4_sgJHmQ_pb_x960.png','Rugiens,  which is named after its red soil, is located in the south of Pommard. Dense, structured and powerful, this is a brooding wine that has concentrated tannins and fruit that is offset by a tight line of acidity. This is a wine that demands aging.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Rugiens Premier Cru',196775),
(297452,223405,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A heady and intense red blend composed mostly of Cabernet Sauvignon and Shiraz with touches of Petit Verdot, Cabernet Franc and Malbec, this wine offers a seriously firm structure with gripping tannins and a palate loaded with black plum skin, forest berries, cigar leaf and a hint of rosemary twig. The finish is long and reminiscent of French press coffee; try after 2012.',20,NULL,0,'R M Nicholson',196689),
(297510,223676,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This Cab has all of the classic notes one would expect: rich dark berry fruit, black plum skin, cigar tobacco and black currant leaf are all front and center. The tannins are surprisingly firm and tightly structured, but the nuances of milk chocolate sauce and graham cracker crumb add decadence to the finish.',12,NULL,0,'Bergkelder Selection',196839),
(297517,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A wine that is currently closed, this shows hints of bright green- and white-fruit flavors. The toast influence and acidity cover this complex, potentially impressive selection. With its crisp finish and minerally texture, this has excellent aging potential.',NULL,NULL,0,'Chatenière Premier Cru',197408),
(297522,218426,'other','Red Blend','data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQAAAQABAAD/2wCEAAoHCBUWEhgWEhUYGBgYGhwcGBgYGRkYGBoaGBoa','A beautiful wine, supple and delicious. Classically dry and tannic, it shows fascinating, elusive blackberry, blueberry, currant and herb flavors, elaborated with sweet, smoky oak. Lots going on here, and it should develop nicely in the bottle over the next decade.',120,NULL,0,'Stature',196751),
(297576,222635,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a tight, currently closed wine, but it has the potential to exude intense fruit and balancing acidity. It has weight and a taut, minerally texture, and the finish is fresh and lively. It will age over the medium term.',NULL,NULL,0,'Grande Montagne Premier Cru',197408),
(297579,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Although this Pinot is captivatingly rich in raspberry and cherry pie filling, red currant and Dr. Pepper cola flavors, it also has fine acidity and smooth, complex tannins, and a lovely overlay of sweet, smoky oak. Good as it is, there\'s no reason why it shouldn\'t develop bottle complexity over the next six years.',59,NULL,0,'Sleepy Hollow Vineyard',196639),
(297668,222367,'other','Monica',NULL,'This expression of the indigenous Monica grape opens with flavors of sour fruit and cherry cola. Its easy informality is perfect for cocktail hour.',NULL,NULL,0,'I Fiori',197281),
(297705,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Full bodied and very round in character, this has rich pineapple and white fruits that are cut with grapefruit-like acidity. A touch of spice surfaces from having been wood aged. This could age for 2–3 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Bois Rosier',197404),
(297732,218426,'other','Chardonnay','https://media.danmurphys.com.au/dmo/product/161940-1.png?impolicy=PROD_MD','Very fine Chardonnay, marked by brisk, racy acidity and a steely tang to the lemon, lime, white peach and honeysuckle flavors. Very complex and lively, an alluring wine that will take a few years in the bottle.',25,NULL,0,'Jackson Hills',196751),
(297862,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/GlPIM3NJR8KhDsudzyljbw_pb_x960.png','Rich and broad, this is packed with dense fruit and tannins. It is ripe and full bodied, two qualities that are derived from the warm vineyard. The finish shows juicy acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Peuillets Premier Cru',196775),
(297915,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'The blend of Fernão Pires and Arinto produces a rich and creamy wine with pear, ripe apple and apricot flavors. A floral character gives extra piquancy.',12,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Catapereiro Branco',196685),
(297934,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'With toasty wood-aging flavors, this is a rich, spicy wine. It has a note of nutmeg to balance the citrus- and apricot-like acidity and the ripe depth of flavor.',24,NULL,0,'Clos Reyssie',197404),
(297935,217719,'other','Sparkling Blend','https://shop.grahambeck.com/storage/products/June2020/7x7M1wcLJ1LpFE17ugwA.png','A distinct note of honeycomb marries harmoniously with the pear and hard nectarine aromas. A nice creaminess fills the mouth, with green apple and citrus flavors, which finish on an appropriately toasty yet mouthwatering note. This already shows nice development; drink now.',55,NULL,0,'Cuvée Clive',196845),
(297937,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_1.png','This is a smoky, fragrant wine that offers dense fruit and firm tannins. It has the structure of a fine Gevrey and the concentration of the vintage. This is classic and worth aging for 4–5 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clos Prieur',196775),
(298090,223334,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Ken Forrester\'s Petit Pinotage is an accessible and easy-drinking wine from the notoriously love-it-or-hate-it grape that shows bright brambly forest berry and plum flesh flavors coupled with a touch of coffee-infused milk chocolate on the finish. Balanced and juicy, it\'s sure to please.',12,NULL,0,'Petit',196839),
(298093,223655,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Here\'s a straightforward but enjoyable Shiraz with notes of dark plum, cherry and strawberry on the nose and mouth. There\'s a touch of greenness on the palate augmented by firm, young tannins, but it all works out and fades smoothly on the finish.',14,NULL,0,'Mountainside',196689),
(298171,223676,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Soft toast and hazelnut aromas add character to the otherwise straightforward honeydew, pear and orange oil flavors of this value Chard. Medium weight with a round body but lifting acidity to keep things fresh and vibrant. Drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Bergkelder Selection',196839),
(298195,225996,'other','Chardonnay-Viognier',NULL,'Apple and citrus aromas mingle on the nose, with hints of steely minerality and just-dried grass. The medium-weight mouthfeel boasts flavors of underripe stone fruit and lemon zest, shifting to riper orange and pear flavors as the finish evolves.',10,NULL,0,'The Ruins',196845),
(298270,222933,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Round but lifted with racy pineapple-infused acidity in the mouth, this Chard offers ripe melon and red apple flavors to balance the serious cut. A hint of peach pit nuttiness stays through the finish.',18,NULL,0,'The Glass Collection',197420),
(298282,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Ripe and wood aged, full bodied and rounded, this is now mature. Its broad features are tempered by a shot of minerality and a steel note that add a crisp texture to the tropical fruits.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sélection',197404),
(298296,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A firmly structured, dry Cabernet whose thick mountain tannins frame classic Cabernet flavors of blackberries and cassis, elaborated with smoky new oak. Not showing its best now, but needs time. Try beyond 2014.',70,NULL,0,'Highland Estates Napa Mountain',196751),
(298341,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A serious, complex wine—this has dark, firm tannins that structure the flavors of dense black fruit, spice and herb. This intense wine needs to age for at least four years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Andreza Reserva',196685),
(298351,223584,'other','Sauvignon Blanc-Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Rich fruit aromas of yellow apple flesh, mealy pear and banana lead the bouquet, with a hint of grapefruit pith in the background. The palate is tangier and more lifted than the nose suggests, with bright flavors of green plum and citrus juice.',12,NULL,0,'Combination',196689),
(298353,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/4fVjSKYtQcSx_mOBWZtDOg_pb_x960.png','Rich, deliciously fruity and ripe, this combines warmth with a more mineral undertow that cuts through the palate, creating a wine that is refreshing and mouth-filling. It would be worth aging for two years or more.',20,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit',196775),
(298431,227479,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This red blend offers aromas of raspberry, mint and spice and savory flavors of cherry and blackberries. Integrated and full, with soft tannins and a spicy finish.',9,NULL,0,'Live-a-Little Really Ravishing Red Organic-Fairtrade',196839),
(298446,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'After an initial blast of cheesy, lactic oak, the nose settles on molasses and prune. This feels saturated and tough, with a steady drumming of hard tannins bolstering sweet, dark flavors of blackberry, bitter chocolate and peppercorn. A wine that\'s excellent for its power, it turns a bit raisiny on the finish. Drink now.',45,NULL,0,'Alfa Crux Red',196852),
(298452,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is a toast- and spice-laden wine that has richness and smooth, creamy fruit notes. It\'s balanced with firm acidity that adds to the vanilla and white fruit flavors. Delicious now, but it will age.',NULL,NULL,0,'Andreza Grande Reserva Branco',196685),
(298466,217719,'other','Sparkling Blend','https://images.wine.co.za/GetWineImage.ashx?ImageSize=large&IMAGEID=268007','Delicate accents of green apple flesh, juicy orange and peach pit fill out the nose and mouth of this attractive sparkler. The slightly aggressive carbonation keeps the palate fresh and mouthwatering, and a hint of baking spice graces the brisk finish.',25,NULL,0,'Brut Blanc de Blancs',196845),
(298513,217780,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/NwLDRoodQVKTz_KO2tEliA_pb_600x600.png','Herbal and loaded with tomato leaf on the nose, but that\'s mostly the first impression. The wine settles down to reveal black olive, berry and leather. The feel is smooth and silky, with nice tannins and flavors of herbs, vanilla, cream, plum and chocolate. Lengthy on the finish, with acidic snap throughout. Drink now through 2014.',84,NULL,0,'Rivalta',196857),
(298557,217265,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Thin, dry and earthy, and not showing much fruit. The tobacco, dried herb and pepper flavors are only modestly relieved by a trace of cherries.',18,NULL,0,'Lot 110',196620),
(298588,222525,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This value selection is a no-brainer, with medium tannins providing good structure to the ripe palate. Boysenberry and black currant flavors mingle with spicy accents of hoisin sauce, licorice and coffee bean. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Hands',196845),
(298607,221639,'other','Tempranillo',NULL,'Starts with dark, statuesque aromas led by mineral, leather and wood smoke. A powerful, intense wine with clean, rich flavors of black plum, chocolate and raisin. It\'s a touch on the sweet and chewy side, with some tannic bite and heat, but overall it\'s rock-solid and very nice. Drink now–2013.',31,NULL,0,'Spiga',196852),
(298691,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Full, ripe and creamy, this rolls mellifluously around the palate. Pear and plum flavors dominate along with the crisp edge of lime. The finish is just as rich and smooth.',18,NULL,0,'Domaine Saint-Martin',197404),
(298814,223005,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'Vibrantly effervescent and bursting with ripe, juicy strawberry and cherry fruit notes, this has a fine-sandpaper-like texture. It\'s an interesting selection that would pair well with barbecue or pulled-pork dishes.',20,NULL,0,'Solms Astor Cape Jazz Shiraz',196839),
(298824,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Spicy wine from the wood and from the ripe berry fruits. The acidity is light, a sideshow to the juicy fruit, flavors of nutmeg and red cherries and a fine kick of dry tannin.',8,NULL,0,'Monte Altentejano Tinto',196807),
(298890,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A solid and chunky wine, this balances a rich structure with ripe, rounded fruit. Acidity cuts through the complex texture to give a juicy, fragrant feel. It\'s worth aging another year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cuvée Prestige',197404),
(298933,222090,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Delicate aromas of white cherry and strawberry lead the nose and carry through onto the palate with a bit more intensity. There\'s texture to the mouthfeel, with flavors of red cherry and plum skin that stay through the medium-length finish.',15,NULL,0,'Kadette Dry Pinotage',197420),
(298934,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Taut and textured, yet ripe and soft, this has a nectarine flavor that\'s balanced by a note of fresh lime. The finish is easy, nervy and zingy.',14,NULL,0,'Domaine Chenevières',197404),
(298970,217335,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/7D_9gQsvSLG8gkVkPbrJTQ_pb_x960.png','A little gritty in texture, and the rawness is compounded by black pepper tartness. Yet there\'s a huge, succulent core of black cherry fruit, and the wine is perfectly dry and acidic. An interesting Pinot, one to stash in the cellar and see what happens.',56,NULL,0,'Graham Family Vineyard',196639),
(299003,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Firmly tannic, this is a solid, chunky wine. It\'s full of dark plum, black currant and cherry flavors that fill out the firm, dry structure. Concentrated while also fruity, it\'s worth aging for a year.',14,NULL,0,'Domaine Moulin à Vent',197404),
(299051,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Soft, smooth and buttery, this is full of ripe tropical fruits and bright, citrusy acidity. Ready to drink.',19,NULL,0,'Domaine de la Batie',197404),
(299052,226862,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Made from 70% Chardonnay and 30% Pinot Noir, this is clean yet nuanced, with subtle suggestions of strawberry hull and freshly picked herbs to the white peach and Key lime core. Medium weight, with a mouthwatering finish; drink now.',15,NULL,0,'Chardonnay-Pinot Noir',197599),
(299124,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This big, burly effort is structured and solidly textured. It has weight accompanying the blackberry flavor, with a firm character that demands aging over at least 18 months. The finish is still firm and concentrated.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Mont Chavy',197404),
(299165,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Ripe, soft and round, this is an accessible wine, with easy yellow-fruit flavors that lend a sweetly juicy character. The acidity just cuts through the warm feel to give the finish some lift.',NULL,NULL,0,'La Vignée',197241),
(299168,217719,'other','Sparkling Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/LJWydliHS0OyfHBhzltkQQ_pb_x960.png','Green plum, apple and lemon-rind aromas and flavors are at the center of this dry sparkler. It\'s clean and refreshing, with medium carbonation and a brisk, mouthwatering finish. Drink now.',25,NULL,0,'Brut Zero',196845),
(299250,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Firm tannins and its dark plum and blackberry fruits all point to a structured wine that has aging potential. It is ripe, with black cherry and spice notes that are balanced with acidity. Keep for one year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Chaponne',197404),
(299279,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Big, tannic and bold wine, this has ripe black fruits and sweet tannins, with a firm, mineral edge. Richness and structure combine to form a dense wine that should age for over three years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal Reserva',196685),
(299440,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A brisk, bright Chardonnay, made in the Testarossa style of ripe fruit and oakiness. What it lacks in subtlety it makes up for in the sheer power of tangerine, pineapple and tropical fruit flavors, elaborated with vanilla cream and caramelized oak.',20,NULL,0,'Cuvee Katelyn',196639),
(299467,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6FARI5McQhm8iB5wEsDYfA_pb_x960.png','There is power here, but it is hidden behind an exterior of sweet fruit. The black plum juice freshness fronts dark, dry tannins, a core of steel. The ripe fruit is already delicious, but those tannins shows this dense wine\'s aging potential.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Clos Frantin Clos de Vougeot',196775),
(299594,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'A little short in the finish and acidic, with some green, minty flavors. But there\'s enough raspberry and cherry fruit to satisfy, and the wine shows the balance and elegance associated with any Testarossa Pinot Noir.',25,NULL,0,'Henry\'s Blend',196639),
(299862,217625,'other','Bical',NULL,'Green plums, freshly sliced melon and some pineapple all come together in this fruit-salad-fresh wine. It is ripe, but retains plenty of crispness, a light structure of orange zest giving shape and piquancy.',9,NULL,0,'Q do E Encontro',196794),
(299872,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'From the Monte da Cal vineyard, this big, bold wine has firm tannins, tight acidity and exuberant black berry fruits. It has an open, juicy core around which those tannins wrap, leaving a wine that is so obviously food-friendly.',10,NULL,0,'Terra Plana',196794),
(299944,221639,'other','Tempranillo Blend',NULL,'Attractive background aromas like nutmeg and licorice are taken down a notch by front-running bramble and pickled notes, while the palate is hard, tannic and spunky as it delivers lively cherry, raspberry and chocolate flavors. A good wine with RDD pedigree, but also sort of grabby and rough, with coffee and pepper on the finish.',31,NULL,0,'Spiga',196852),
(300011,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'From the Bairrada vineyards of Quinta do Encontro, this is an intriguing blend of Merlot and the local Baga grape. It definitely has the Baga\'s dry, edgy structure, a very firm core of tannins. Around that the Merlot brings some richness and fruitcake flavors.',9,NULL,0,'Q do E Encontro',196794),
(300015,217625,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'For a wine at this price, this is an impressive performance. It is rich, finely structured, the juicy blackberry flavors filling the mouth. It may lack complexity, but the spice, tobacco and berry flavors are enjoyably drinkable.',7,NULL,0,'Cortello',196794),
(300148,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fiDjIQwbRNO0vMV0NSNe6w_pb_x960.png','This is beautiful, with smooth, polished tannins and a spice note from the wood aging. It is layered with black plum, chocolate and licorice flavors, along with structure. The fruit is rich and likely to come forward in the next 3–4 years.',30,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas Reserva',196663),
(300161,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A lively, juicy wine, with pepper, cinnamon and green herbs. The fruits are red berry and rhubarb, giving a wine that is both fruity and edged with rawness. The acidity is prominent, layering over the dry tannin core.',7,NULL,0,'Cortello',196794),
(300204,224641,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A full-bodied wave of savory spice and rich fruit. Aromas of tobacco, mint, cassis and mocha lead, followed by smooth, luscious flavors of plum, smoke, and tobacco. Ageable but delicious now, the wine has a soft character that makes it good for solo sipping. It also will pair nicely with steaks and soft cheeses.',51,NULL,0,'Liber II',197484),
(300226,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This is a firmly structured wine, but its black cherry flavor is marred by banana sweetness. Otherwise the wine is solid and tannic, with light acidity on the finish. Age for a year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Javernière',197404),
(300264,217625,'other','Rosé',NULL,'A blend of Touriga Nacional and Alfrocheiro grapes, this crisp, lightweight rosé shows tight cranberry acidity, layered with some caramel and it finishes dry and fresh.',9,NULL,0,'Cabriz',196794),
(300378,222420,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'An alluring, aromatic nose of apple, grapefruit and pineapple leads into creamy but crisp flavors of tropical fruit and citrus on the palate. Lively but complex, the wine offers a delicate minerality and food-friendly balance. Elegant and delicate, but big enough to handle more complex dishes.',15,NULL,0,'Finlayson Family Vineyards',196689),
(300402,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fKUwUaHPSKS8Lb-8200NkA_pb_x960.png','Firm and structured, this is a densely rich wine for aging. Firm tannins dominate its ripe black fruit, lending notes of spice, licorice and toast from the wood. It needs several years of aging to round out—give it four years at least.',69,NULL,0,'T Quinta da Terrugem',196677),
(300428,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Perfumed wine, reeking of candy shops and sweet fruits. There are lychee, spice, pear, a cornucopia of delights. Just a touch of acidity creates a wine that is designed more for apéritif than for food.',10,NULL,0,'Terra Plana Branco',196794),
(300433,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'As a fan of almost everything O. Fournier puts in the bottle, I\'d say this value-oriented wine needs work. For starters, it mixes Zinfandel-like blueberry fruit with green, weedy aromas. The palate holds onto that green essence while also tossing out rhubarb, tea and carob flavors. Lacks the ripeness and structure as it should have, even at this modest price.',14,NULL,0,'Urban Ribera Roble Red Wine',196852),
(300517,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Spicebox, red berry, pepper…all entice in the aroma of this more delicate, sophisticated red. On the plate, its gentle layers of warming spice, pepper, spice and cloves offer refined complexity. A beautiful, sultry sip that will pair well with cheeses, grilled meats, stew.',35,NULL,0,'Three Pines',196689),
(300518,218042,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'The nose on this red is soft and full of rounded spice and red berry fruit. Rich, balanced flavors of plum, black fruit and pepper are poised and backed by a good acidity. A classy Shiraz that will pair well with meat dishes and aged cheeses.',19,NULL,0,'Wolfkloof Limited Release',196845),
(300543,217512,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/XniE_rD_SKOSP6VwFyWZ0Q_pb_x960.png','Wood-aged, this is a ripe-textured wine that has rich flavors of yellow and white fruits and toast. It has concentrated, intense fruit that bursts in the mouth. Delicious and impressive, this could be aged for another two years.',25,NULL,0,'Morgado de Santa Catherina Reserva',196663),
(300630,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/lJEDr20rRh6TP21v0RpjoA_pb_x960.png','Full bodied and rich, this has a juicy core followed by firm, minerally tannins and intense acidity. Wood aging adds complexity to this impressive, ageworthy effort.',19,NULL,0,'Quinta da Garrida Reserva',196677),
(300728,217512,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-tQxWTN6Qo26fnE0VZR8AA_pb_x960.png','Densely tannic, this is also full of sweet berry fruits. Powerful and superripe, its fruit is beginning to integrate into the big, smoky, chocolaty structure. The finish shows both toast and juicy fruit notes. Keep for 3–4 years.',30,NULL,0,'Herdade da Farizoa Reserva',196663),
(300795,226799,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This lively, balanced Pinotage offers the vivid spice and rich banana and plum fruit for which Pinotage is known, in an exuberant, approachable package. Plum and red berry, tobacco smoke and warming spice offer big but elegant favors. Cellarworthy, but can be drunk now. Pair with lamb, game, spicy cuisine.',30,NULL,0,'Oak Matured',197596),
(300817,217265,'other','Tempranillo',NULL,'From an off vintage, this hits with piercing cherry and black olive aromas. It\'s powerful, almost astringent, with grating tannins that intensify as the wine unwinds. Brandied cherry, coffee and chocolate flavors set up a rowdy finish.',24,NULL,0,'Lot 264 Gran Reserva',196620),
(300826,217203,'other','Alvarinho',NULL,'This is a rich, full-bodied and impressive wine, with intense and complex flavors of apple and green fruit. The acidity meshes with the ripe fruit.',22,NULL,0,'Nostalgia',196685),
(300918,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Round and smooth, this has a weighty, full-bodied structure, with the Alvarinho adding a more crisp character. Pear and melon fruits are balanced by citrusy acidity.',10,NULL,0,'DFJ Alvarinho-Chardonnay',196807),
(300980,223676,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'This Chenin starts with aromas of vanilla, spice and honey, followed by upfront flavors of peaches, honey and spice. Fun but elegant, with a balanced freshness that keeps it clean on the tongue. Pair with creamy cheeses, fruit.',10,NULL,0,'Wooded',196839),
(300988,227426,'other','Merlot-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Brambleberry, pepper and smoke lead this distinctive red blend from Capaia. Red berries, pepper and spice have South African character, and are enlivened by good acidity and a minerally finish. A refreshing but savory everyday red; pair with lamb or game.',21,NULL,0,'Blue Grove Hill',197920),
(300989,224641,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Cloves, black fruit and vanilla spice on the nose are followed by a brooding array of tobacco, spice, red berry and vanilla on the palate. Full-bodied but smooth, with a lingering, savory finish. Pair with steak, lamb or aged cheeses.',51,NULL,0,'Liber I',197484),
(301215,219884,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/OvXeDJN0QNSo1IQm6uJoSg_pb_x600.png','Profiting from the exceptional 2009 vintage, this is rich and full bodied, yet it retains elegance. Black fruits dominate the firm tannins, lending a juicy character to the ripe texture. The finish is suave and fruity.',10,NULL,0,'Casa do Lago Grande Reserva',196807),
(301221,217310,'other','Portuguese White','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/ojYu0uCQQAaFixeEaYAm9Q_pb_x960.png','Rich and ripe, this has pear, peach and quince fruits that are rounded out by wood aging. It has a floral character that balances the richness. It will age for another two years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta da Garrida Reserva Branco',196677),
(301226,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is very aromatic, with lively acidity, a soft and creamy texture, and a rounded yellow-fruit flavor that\'s balanced by a citrus note. It is elegant, rich and worth aging for another year.',19,NULL,0,'Toucas',196685),
(301251,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Shows the crisp elegance and clean balance this bottling is known for, with ripe citrus, apricot, tropical fruit and mineral flavors, accented by rich new oak. It\'s fun to play with this Chard, let it warm up in the glass and see how it changes over the course of a dinner. That\'s the mark of a great table wine.',39,NULL,0,'Bien Nacido Vineyard Elder Series',196639),
(301264,217335,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This regional bottling has been a strong suit of Testarossa over the years, a best-barrel blend from their far-flung coastal empire of vineyards. It\'s very rich in apricot, pineapple, honeysuckle and smoky oak flavors, and finishes dry and spicy. Shows an elegant complexity that should develop over the next six years.',55,NULL,0,'Diana\'s Reserve',196639),
(301330,217512,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'Portugal\'s national grape offers a richly grounded wine, with dark tannins, black plum fruit and tight acidity. The texture is dusty, and the wood aging just showing through on the finish.',30,NULL,0,'Quinta de Pancas Reserva',196663),
(301404,223676,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A fresh, green nose of grass, herbs and asparagus leads on this mouthfilling white. Flavors of citrus, tropical fruit and melon are punctuated by earthy spice and herbs. A lengthy aftertaste adds to the appeal. An interesting, distinctive Sauvignon Blanc.',18,NULL,0,'Unfiltered',196839),
(301494,222346,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A savory nose with hints of balsamic and smoke, balanced by cassis and cedar, start this wine out right. In the mouth, it\'s complex and assertive, with flavors of anise, spice and plum. Pronounced tannins need some time to age, but overall the wine is excellent now.',37,NULL,0,'Classique',196689),
(301520,218426,'other','Red Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/5OmkO9TiRX2mhWO1EYVjGg_pb_x600.png','A bit sharp and green in tannins, this nevertheless provides plenty of cherry, blackberry, black pepper and baking spice flavors to pair with barbecue. The blend is Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Zinfandel.',15,NULL,0,'Summation',196751),
(301523,217203,'other','Siria',NULL,'Made from the Códega do Larinho grape (also called Síria), this is a refreshingly rich wine. It\'s full in the mouth yet it retains its natural freshness, with a touch of pepper, tangy acidity and great depth of flavor. The finish bears notes of citrus, pear and green apple.',15,NULL,0,'Andreza Códega do Larinho',196685),
(301533,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'This is a dark wine, with an intense, dry structure and seemingly sweet fruit. It has a dense herb flavor, with notes of black plum, spice and bitter chocolate. Keep for a year.',NULL,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias Samora',196685),
(301627,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Simple and fruity, this has berry flavors that mingle with floral acidity, soft tannins and a rounded texture. Ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Paradis',197404),
(301838,218228,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MTHIoePMQOSpxVORHYWm5A_pb_600x600.png','Very nice on the nose, with lime, celery and semisour pickle aromas. There is plenty of character to this round, generous single-vineyard SB from Casablanca. The palate is snappy and citric, while the finish is full of ripe grapefruit and other subtle green notes. A very good wine that borders on excellence. For the money, it\'s a green-light special.',17,NULL,0,'Single Vineyard',196886),
(301855,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/3OMisWgFQzOohbmCKM8k8g_pb_x960.png','Terrunyo is arguably Chile\'s best SB. This vintage gets going with a touch of green bean but also plenty of passion fruit and pink grapefruit. The palate is ripe, crystal-clear and tangy, and the passion fruit and citrus flavors really drive it home. Expect a racy wine with dynamic pineapple and grapefruit as its cornerstones.',29,NULL,0,'Terrunyo El Triángulo Vineyard Block: 28',196852),
(301870,226799,'other','Chenin Blanc-Chardonnay',NULL,'Floral aromas with a touch of citrus lead in this assertive white blend. The flavors‚Äîvanilla, fresh fruit, spice, are wrapped in a wave of smooth oak. Honey and spice add character. An elegant wine good for pairing with salad and poultry dishes.',11,NULL,0,'Stonecross',197596),
(301873,223641,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This Cabernet offers candied plum, smoke, pepper and vanilla on the nose, and on the palate, a lively red berry, pepper and tobacco mélange. Moderate tannins and friendly fruit give it an approachable edge. Pair with beef or pasta.',9,NULL,0,'Savanha',197456),
(302001,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Big and spicy, this has notes of ripe black fruit and raisin, with a tarry edge and smooth tannins. It has an intense structure and a dry core, with a spice note and a touch of pepper from the alcohol.',NULL,NULL,0,'Companhia das Lezírias',196685),
(302133,223861,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Fresh, fruity and charming, this rosé offers full-bodied flavors of strawberry and spice that are balanced and complex. A step above the typical flirty rosé, the wine gives style and substance and will handle heartier dishes—think Moroccan tagine or grilled, spiced fish.',19,NULL,0,'Juanita Rosé',196845),
(302512,218569,'other','Muscat',NULL,'The winery\'s philosophy is, if you\'re going to make a dessert wine, why not make it fabulously sweet instead of boringly off-dry? With 17.5% residual sugar, this indeed hits the limit of the sweetness scale. Yet it\'s superbly balanced with acidity, giving a refreshing balance to the intense apricot jam, lemon drop, candied ginger, pineapple crème brûlée and vanilla custard flavors. A tremendous success for a California dessert wine.',40,NULL,0,'Late Harvest',196626),
(302571,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This wine benefits from the great, forward fruits of the 2006 vintage, giving red berry and spice flavors. It is ripe, charming and deliciously fruity, with a jammy, rounded aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine des Sablons',197404),
(302663,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Named after one of the proponents of Saint-Amour wines, this is appropriately serious and rich, with tight tannins and acidity. Underneath the structure, the red currant fruits promise some freshness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Louis Dailly',197404),
(302849,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'A lovely nose of cedar, pepper and berry is followed by flavors of smoke, pepper and energetic fruit in this big red. A touch aggressive on first taste, the wine is rounded by good acidity and elegant spice layers.',35,NULL,0,'Twin Peak Vineyard Unfined and Unfiltered',196689),
(303074,217999,'other','Greco','https://static.xtrawine.com/Global/Images/XW/products/wines/21924_FeudiSanGregorioDublBrutGrecoDiTufo_2016_3.png?h=720','The impressive natural structure and staying power of Greco make this a creamy and sophisticated metodo classico sparkling wine, with aromas of honey, pear and Golden Delicious apple.',43,NULL,0,'DUBL Brut Greco',196908),
(303154,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This is serious, complex and age worthy. It balances wood-aged toast with peach, apricot and crisp lime-juice flavors. From one of Bairrada\'s top estates, this is worth keeping for 3–4 years.',28,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Encontro I',196794),
(303251,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/LwE0vWAVRrGBl0C5kzMrhg_pb_x960.png','From the far northeast region of Tras-os-Montes, this is an attractively fruity wine. It has a core of tannins that are a fine complement to the blueberry and damson fruits.',NULL,NULL,0,'Terra Boa',196677),
(303270,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This nice drinking Chard offers plenty of bang for the buck. It\'s dry and creamy, with oak-infused pear, peach and green apple fruit flavors that finish in a swirl of dusty spices.',13,NULL,0,'Lot 59',196620),
(303322,218035,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/61uvD5mSRiOPFyvfstAi8w_pb_x960.png','This is a perfectly nice Sauvignon Blanc from stand-alone vineyards in Zapallar. The nose features a varietal aroma of white pepper and a piquant hint of green. The acid-driven palate bears lime, tangerine and bell pepper flavors.',30,NULL,0,'Outer Limits Beyond Frontiers Zappallar Vineyard',196713),
(303327,217999,'other','Aglianico',NULL,'Native Aglianico grapes give this metodo classico sparkling wine its pretty pink color. Aromas recall wild berry, stone fruit and pink grapefruit. The quality of the perlage is steady, bright and tonic.',43,NULL,0,'DUBL Rosé Brut',196908),
(303339,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/AWqbAJ1bRbi81VcQtGMpEw_pb_x960.png','Spice and red plum flavors dominate this fruity, forward effort. It has some tannins, but they seem lost in the wine\'s easy character. For drinking over the next two years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Foral',196677),
(303363,218042,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Young, bright berry aromas lead on this appealing red. Balanced red fruit, minerals and a touch of spice are friendly and appealing, though not terribly complex. A great everyday red.',18,NULL,0,'Limited Release Wolfkloof',196845),
(303473,228198,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Clean, minerally, but with a spin of spice, the nose on this Chenin suggests fun. On the palate, a good balance of acid and body showcases the wine\'s citrus and honey flavors. Over all, a great everyday white.',10,NULL,0,'Cape White',197456),
(303529,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Crisp and herbaceous, this is a green-fruited wine that\'s light on the palate, offering delightful refreshing acidity. This is very fruity and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Clemens Reserva',196685),
(303531,217310,'other','Tinta Roriz','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hTzqkrQsTHSenXY62-lt1g_pb_x960.png','Lightweight, with smooth red fruit and acidity, this is soft and round. The berry fruit neatly merges with the gentle tannins.',NULL,NULL,0,'Vista',196677),
(303534,217148,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'This shows the combo of a cool vintage and deft winemaking. It\'s impressively deep in citrus, fig and pepper flavors, with just a touch of oak that adds a nice, smoky edge. With high acidity, it really gets those tastebuds whistling. Best of all, the wine achieves the Holy Grail: low alcohol, only 13%, and bone dryness.',22,NULL,0,'O.F.S.',196642),
(303569,223676,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Fleur du Cap\'s consistently good quality shows again in this classy Chardonnay. Fresh Chardonnay fruit and a touch of minerality on the nose are followed by solid, medium-bodied fruit and spice. The finish is long and luscious. A solid everyday choice.',18,NULL,0,'Unfiltered',196839),
(303608,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'This aromatic white is laden with toast and white fruit notes. It is rich and smooth, the toast character is well-blended with the melon, pear and lime flavors. Its fruitiness makes it attractive. It should be aged for at least two years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Branco Reserva',196794),
(303616,219700,'other','Chardonnay','https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ8dTSoLPuVk2u6eZmpioxsNRB5-Ksm1pYCD5m6-nw-3UkdePFboxPlTpbL4yOso69quA&usqp=CAU','Tasca d\'Almerita produces one of southern Italy\'s finest metodo classico sparklers. Made from Chardonnay ripened under the Sicilian sun, this is creamy, rich and long, redolent of apricot, toasted almond and honey.',56,NULL,0,'Almerita Extra Brut',196776),
(303627,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Produced only in top vintages, this is a ripe, wood-aged wine. The fragrant aromas of its fruit are balanced by toast and spice. It is warm, ripe and complex, a wine that could age for another 2–3 years.',28,NULL,0,'Monte da Cal Vinha de Saturno',196794),
(303634,217203,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Light and fragrant, this has pear and lemon flavors. It\'s ripe, soft and ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Dona Helena Branco',196685),
(303638,217310,'other','Rosé','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/hTzqkrQsTHSenXY62-lt1g_pb_x960.png','Ripe and soft, this is made from Tinta Roriz. It is rich and full bodied, with its rounded strawberry fruit leaving just enough room on the palate for crispness. Screwcap.',NULL,NULL,0,'Vista',196677),
(303647,219884,'other','Shiraz','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/fSQKgHmlTkeahORJ1YBazQ_pb_x960.png','Dark plums and  bitter chocolate on this wine along with powerful structure and tannins. It is ripe, spicy and finely perfumed with full black fruits. The tannins are boosted by wood aging, rounding it out and giving it extra richness.',16,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte Shiraz',196807),
(303701,217625,'other','Port',NULL,'This is a finely balanced LBV with structure complementing the luscious black-fruit and raisin flavors. The wine is rich and densely textured, very smooth and unctuous. Big tannins suggest that the wine could age.',20,NULL,0,'Quinta das Tecedeiras LBV Late Bottled Vintage',196794),
(303786,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'With its crisp spine of acidity, this wine clearly comes from a cool climate. The flavors show long hang-time notes of ripe pineapples and pears. There\'s too much oak for balance, given the dominating blast of caramel, but the wine will appeal to many for the price.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 58',196620),
(303802,217625,'other','Bical',NULL,'This is a lightly wood-aged wine, with melon and pear flavors that are rounded by a toast character. Taut orange zest and lime notes balance this softness. The aftertaste is fragrant, crisp and warm.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta do Encontro Q do E ',196794),
(303845,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Ripe and fruity, this bears a red berry flavor and a dry structure. It has weight, richness and a smooth finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Azul Portugal',196685),
(303847,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'This is a floral, aromatic and dry rosé, full of red currant fruit and refreshing acidity. It\'s a great apéritif wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Samora',196685),
(303921,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Black currants and plums dominate this ripe, soft, open wine. There are delicious flavors of dark chocolate, spice and bacon, which add to the fruit. The tannins are subservient, lending support but not dominant.',NULL,NULL,0,'Tinta Roriz-Merlot',196807),
(303930,217203,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Soft, with strawberry flavors and only light acidity, this has a caramel burst that surfaces on the finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Dona Helena',196685),
(304012,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A firm, tannic wine with elegant structure. The red fruits from the Merlot are a great foil for the tannins of the Touriga Franca. Even at five years, this is still fruit dominated, although the wood and spice element is well integrated.',NULL,NULL,0,'Merlot-Touriga Franca',196807),
(304096,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'An impressive, dense wine, this is a wood-aged, smooth blend of Aragonez and Castelão grapes. This has ripe tannins and fruit, and a rich blend of blackberries and dark plums.',7,NULL,0,'Berço do Infante',196794),
(304148,217512,'other','Arinto',NULL,'Pure Arinto from the Lisbon region, this wood-aged wine is delicious and Chardonnay-like in its richness, with great swathes of apples and cream flavors, layered with toast. This is a great advertisement for a neglected region in Portugal\'s viticulture.',14,NULL,0,'Morgado Santa Catherina',196663),
(304187,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'Perfumed, soft, easy wine, showing the juicy, fresh side of the two grapes. The fruits are more red than black, open and ripe, but still with youthful exuberance and great freshness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Touriga Nacional e Touriga Franca',196807),
(304192,219884,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An unexpected combination perhaps, but it works to give a fresh, flavorful wine, with soft tannins, juicy fruit and flavors of red cherries and vanilla. Not complex, and ready to drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Tinta Roriz and Merlot',196807),
(304193,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A big, burly, juicy wine, focusing on powerful red fruits and layers of acidity. The tannins are dense, but the fruit is more dominant. There are smoky flavors, spiked with licorice and blueberries. Caladoc is a cross between Malbec and Grenache, developed in France, rarely planted.',NULL,NULL,0,'Caladoc-Alicante Boushet',196807),
(304292,219700,'other','Sparkling Blend','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0620/5145/1073/products/Tenuta-Regaleali-Almerita-Rose-2017_600x.png?v=1676557910','This historic Sicilian producer offers two sparkling wines, of which this superfriendly and enjoyable rosé is the more affordable bottling. It opens with toasty, creamy aromas of wild berry and stone fruit. The finish is foamy, rich and fresh.',56,NULL,0,'Almerita Brut Rosé',196776),
(304529,219884,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Fresh green-apple aromas and some ripe, mango flavors, this is well rounded, showing some acidity, but more of open, fresh fruits. This is a wine that will be perfect to drink over the next few months.',NULL,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano',196807),
(304533,217719,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/w6sdvUoZT3SMaa7qEmQ-tQ_pb_300x300.png','Soft spice and blackberry on the nose are followed by rich, balanced layers of mint, toast and berry. The wine has a minerality that adds a fresh note to the mix. A big wine but not overly complex, this is a Cabernet for spicy dishes and beef stew. Imported by GBW, LLC.',17,NULL,0,'Gamekeeper\'s Reserve',196845),
(304610,217512,'other','Arinto',NULL,'The vineyards of Quinta da Romeira in cool-climate Bucelas are the source of this elegant, fragrant wine. It has fine acidity, and apple and pear fruits. The Arinto grape provides a lift of freshness on the finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Prova Régia',196663),
(304694,217148,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Comes down on the lean, hard, Chablis-like side of Chardonnay, with a steely spine of minerals and tangy acidity. This provides an elegant infrastructure to the subtle pineapple, green apple and lime zest flavors.',45,NULL,0,'Porter Bass Vineyard',196642),
(304731,229466,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Smoke, spice and rustic herbs lead on the nose of this assertive blend. On the palate a touch of South African smoke and alkaline flavors adds to the earthy feel of the wine, but pairing it with roasted meat or game will create a compelling meal.',35,NULL,0,'Bell Tower',196689),
(304829,217512,'other','Siria','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/df-X1OYWTV6PoT8DBYsRnw_pb_x960.png','This tangy, lemon-scented wine has a fine citrus flavor and a mineral touch due to its vineyard\'s high altitude. It is zesty and bright in character, with fresh final acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo',196663),
(304861,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'There\'s no doubting this is a rich wine. It\'s flamboyant in jammy cherry, boysenberry and cola flavors, while oak adds pronounced char and vanilla. It\'s the most expensive wine ever released by the winery, but tasty as it is, it\'s sweet and simple. Tasted four times.',85,NULL,0,'Sonoma Stage Vineyard',196642),
(304869,218569,'other','Zinfandel','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/8ISmZM4XQF-OyPfMw77OJg_pb_600x600.png','This is a terrific Zinfandel, offering berry, cherry, mocha, spice and cedar flavors that come wrapped in briary tannins. It\'s technically dry, but with a satisfying honeyed note.',50,NULL,0,'Forchini Vineyard South Knoll',196626),
(304902,217512,'other','Touriga Nacional',NULL,'Ripe, smooth, velvet textured wine, layering dark chocolate, black plum skins, dense tannins and a big, solid structure. It tastes powerful from the ripe tannins and big fruit, finishing with fresh acidity.',14,NULL,0,'Quinta do Cardo Special Selection',196663),
(304915,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The vineyard has championed Pinot Noir in this unlikely location in inland Mendocino County, and now De Loach successfully takes up the cause. Their \'06 is gently soft, silky and dry, with deep flavors of cherries, currants, raspberries and chocolate, finished with a fine layer of oaky vanilla.',45,NULL,0,'Masut Vineyard',196642),
(304988,221639,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This is dense, lusty and attractive from the beginning, with rich black-fruit, coconut, tobacco and pine aromas. It feels pure and deep, with ribald acids that keep the pulse up and push blackberry, plum and savory cured-meat flavors. The finish remains savory and saucy. Drink this Cabernet Franc-Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot blend now–2017.',45,NULL,0,'Alfa Centauri Cabernet Sauvignon-Cabernet Franc-Merlot',196852),
(305100,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'A simple fruity red wine, with spice, red-berry fruit flavors, lively acidity and some stalky tannins. This is great quaffing wine, all red fruits and freshness.',9,NULL,0,'Monte Alentejano Trincadeira and Aragonez',196807),
(305110,219884,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'It is curious how the Cabernet, presumably ripe, tastes austere. It is young, and the tannins will certainly soften, but this is a hard wine at the moment, all edges. Blueberries and cranberries are the dominant fruits, while the wood shows as toastiness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Tinta Roriz-Cabernet Sauvignon',196807),
(305218,217719,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Dusty, red berry aromas introduce this blend packed with soft, red berry fruit and a hint of rubber typical of Pinotage. Approachable and fun. Imported by GBW, LLC.',17,NULL,0,'The William Barrel Selection',196845),
(305286,220798,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'From its own estate, this Louis Latour wine is a ripe, strawberry- and juicy plum-flavored wine, sustained by a well- judged dry layer of tannins. It is sweet, the acidity showing through in the red fruits.',50,NULL,0,'Domaine Latour',197254),
(305331,229431,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 40% Cabernet and 60% Pinotage is not for the faint-hearted, with its bold aromas and flavors of spice and spiky fruit. The Cabernet takes the edge off the Pinotage without changing its nature, making this a great wine for pairing with a big plate of ribs or a spicy ethnic dish.',15,NULL,0,'Lindsay\'s Whimsy Cape Blend',196689),
(305421,217625,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'An earthy, rustic blend of Aragonez and Castelão grapes, soft and ripe, touched with black figs and plum skins. For a hearty stew, this is certainly a fine wine, but there\'s nothing sophisticated about it.',5,NULL,0,'Sul South',196794),
(305428,218426,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/axrUM40PRUmebjEtlsj1bg_pb_x600.png','From the Los Alamos region, this young, firm Pinot wants a little time in the bottle to mellow. Tasted in January, it\'s unresolved in tannins, fresh acidity, oak (76% new) and primary cherry and raspberry fruit. Should be a very fine wine sometime toward 2011.',30,NULL,0,'Highlands Estates Los Robles',196751),
(305600,222477,'other','Riesling',NULL,'This wine has freshly picked apple aromas and nice flavors of peach and mango with some varietal petrol thrown in. There\'s even a bit of slate, although not as concentrated as some better versions. It also has enough sugar to give it a bit of sweetness and body, but not enough acidity to balance it out. All in all good.',17,NULL,0,'Rhine',196839),
(305648,218426,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Here\'s a good buy in a big, rich, decadently delicious Syrah. Soft and dry, with refined tannins, it offers flavors of currants, blackberries, cherries, chocolate, licorice, Dr. Pepper cola, black pepper and spices. Easy to like, yet complex.',25,NULL,0,'Grand Reserve',196751),
(305699,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'With its distinctive enameled, flowered bottle, this sets out to be a fun party wine. It succeeds with its fresh, flowery, open fruit, enhanced by vanilla, spice and green apple flavors.',7,NULL,0,'Chardonnay',197404),
(305702,222448,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The tannins and the black currant flavors leave no doubt about the varietal origin of this straightforward, well-made, fresh wine.',6,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon',197404),
(305708,223231,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'A beautiful example of 100% Pinotage. Gorgeous aromas of cassis, black berry and plum abound from this deep red wine. Firmly structured but approachable with the potential to age gracefully another three to five years. Unsweetened cocoa and concentrated dark fruit linger through the lengthy finish.',NULL,NULL,0,'Diesel',196689),
(305985,221639,'other','Torrontés',NULL,'The ultimate patio/terrace wine has been found, and it\'s Urban from O. Fournier. True as can be, with lychee, acacia and green melon aromas and flavors, this wine is plump but refreshing, with honest Cafayate character. Maybe the best under-$10 white wine being made in Argentina.',8,NULL,0,'Urban',196852),
(305992,221639,'other','Malbec-Tempranillo',NULL,'The bringing together of Malbec and Tempranillo works like a charm here. There\'s a touch of complexity to the fruit-forward nose, and better depth than what most under-$10 red varietals offer. Look for sweet, smooth raspberry and plum flavors with a tasty, balanced finish.',8,NULL,0,'Urban Uco Blend',196852),
(306140,217335,'other','Syrah',NULL,'This is quite a luscious Syrah, soft, smooth, complex and layered, showing qualities of both warm and cool climates. From the cool end of the spectrum comes a lively acidity and not a trace of overripeness. The riper notes of blackberries, cassis, gingersnap cookie and licorice are delicious, enriched by smoky oak. Drink now and for a few years.',49,NULL,0,'Thompson Vineyard',196639),
(306187,222090,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Luscious, full-bodied and sophisticated, this red blend starts with aromas of blackberry, anise and spice, followed by black frit, cedar, mocha and spice flavors. Elegant and complex, with a long, spicy finish.',45,NULL,0,'Paul Sauer',197420),
(306286,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This pale-colored wine is light in texture, with a sheer, silk and satin, airy mouthfeel that reminds you of tea. It\'s also very acidic, and filled with youthfully immature fruit and spice. Brings to mind certain great Burgundies on release. It should be exciting to age this wine past 2008.',54,NULL,0,'Schultze Family Vineyard',196639),
(306550,219700,'other','Grillo','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/JnVI32TpTD6m0Igj0aj4cA_pb_x600.png','Fruit for this pristine white wines comes from old, head-trained vines on the tiny island of Mozia off the southern coast of Sicily. Packed tight with archeological remains, the island is managed by the Whitaker Foundation and this wine is part of a larger project to revive ancient viticulture and winemaking traditions. It\'s an excellent story and a wonderful wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Whitaker Mozia',196776),
(306638,224337,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A subdued, classic spice nose leads this impressive Bordeaux blend from powerhouse producer Ernie Els. The wine is structured but soft, vibrant but restrained—in short, an exceptional balance of leathery spice, plum and blackberry juiciness and delicate minerality. Very pretty but with a backbone, this wine can age for added elegance.',93,NULL,0,'Limited Release',196689),
(306879,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/106n41ISQ56brPdSN4OSBQ_pb_600x600.png','Some of the best-bred Carmenères in the world are grown in Peumo, and a star example is this saturated, minty wine with medium-weight tannins and a long finish. It\'s lush, powerful and along the way you taste pepper, chocolate, berries and sunshine.',36,NULL,0,'Terrunyo',196852),
(306976,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'This wine has the solid tannins the mountain is known for, and ripe flavors of blackberries, currants, cherries and chocolate, enriched with new oak. At twenty bucks, and with a low production, it\'s a stunning value. With real elegance and even ageworthiness, it\'s one of the best at its price point available now.',20,NULL,0,'Lot 47',196620),
(306985,228295,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Fresh meets floral in this elegant blend. On the nose, there\'s perky citrus and delicate flowers. The flavors are an excellent balance of minerality and fruit, with a rich, round but delicate overall character that\'s intriguing and unfolds on the tongue. The finish is clean and cool. A versatile, sophisticated white.',30,NULL,0,'White Wine',197368),
(307042,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/6iw-uaV1TZaIX7js6QQD-Q_pb_x960.png','From an okay vintage, Concha y Toro did a great job with its \'04 Terrunyo Cab. The wine is sturdy and offers a top-dog nose of mineral, dark fruit, mushroom and toasty oak. The palate features textbook cassis, blackberry and chocolate flavors, and the finish is touched up herbs and black olive. Best in late 2008 and throughout \'09. Imported by Excelsior Wine & Spirits.',36,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Block Las Terrazas',196852),
(307049,222690,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Cigar, spice, cinnamon and plum entices on the nose of this deeply colored blend. Full-bodied and firmly structured, the offers ripe blackberry and cassis flavors that will further integrate and mellow with aging. The finish is smooth and lingering.',32,NULL,0,'Reserve',196878),
(307074,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This well-crafted single-vineyard wine, offers immediate pleasure. We\'re talking about intense cherry liqueur, raspberry, cola and root beer flavors that are opulently ripe, although the wine itself is correctly dry. Light and silky, with crisp acidity and a lingering aftertaste. Drink now.',54,NULL,0,'Elder Series Bien Nacido Vineyard',196639),
(307110,218043,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Like most of the wines from Neil Ellis, this Sauvignion Blanc has moxy and elegance wrapped into one. Intense ripe fruit and lemon in the nose and on the palate give the wine a bold character, but good minerality adds a pretty restraint to the final product. An assertive, exciting wine that will pair well with dishes of the same ilk.',28,NULL,0,'Vineyard Selection',196839),
(307184,217839,'other','Syrah',NULL,'From “old” Syrah vines planted all of 15 years ago, this is a meaty and spicy wine that carries clove and licorice aromas in front of a full-bodied palate that houses black fruit, fennel and chocolate. Good acidity ensures that it flows across the tongue with snap and no overt heaviness.',36,NULL,0,'Terrunyo',196852),
(307253,227832,'other','Rosé',NULL,'Avondale wines are consistently elegant and poised, and this rosé blend follows that style. A pretty, subtle nose of red berry and tropical fruit is followed by a crisp, flinty offering of strawberry and red berry flavors. The wine dances on the palate and finishes clean. A great wine for the price.',12,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon',197445),
(307254,227975,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This medium-body blend of Sauvignon, Chenin Blanc and Semillon offers tropical fruit flavors on the nose and the palate, along with a strain of spicy, toasted oak. There\'s dimension but still a dry, clean character on the palate and finish. Pair with seafood dishes.',17,NULL,0,'The Old Man\'s Blend',197456),
(307261,218042,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Ripe, round aromas of melon and pineapple lead into a crisp, fresh and slightly flinty SB. This has length and complexity but is still light and clean. Its poised balance of minerality and appealing fruit makes it good for pairing or enjoying alone.',17,NULL,0,'Limited Release Retreat',196845),
(307283,221639,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The big brother and precursor to B Crux, this wine has 70% Tempranillo, 20% Malbec and 10% Merlot. It\'s a big, chewy sweet wine with a lot of character as well as some heavy oak and heat toward the end. Since it\'s the very first wine from O. Fournier, and because 2001 was an average year, expect even better offerings in 2002 and \'03.',42,NULL,0,'A Crux',196852),
(307292,218046,'other','Pinotage','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/eWCUhQ5AQ6W9wl6QlILAhQ_pb_x600.png','An odd but not unbecoming note of book paper starts off the nose of cooked meat and red fruit peels. The tart red fruit and char is basic and balanced on the palate, finishing with a wisp of bitter chocolate.',17,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar',196839),
(307296,222448,'other','Merlot',NULL,'A touch oaky, with burnt sugar, mint and lemon aromas. It is firm and tannic, with proper acids; the peppy palate has good blackberry and cherry fruit, and the finish is ripe. Starts fast but loses some of its appeal as the tannins mount.',10,NULL,0,'Cuvée Prestige Reserve',197404),
(307297,223107,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A faint herbal note ribbons around creamy vanilla, currant and plum skin flavors. The tannins are snug and mouthcoating, carrying out to the herbal finish.',25,NULL,0,'Warrant Estate Wine',197545),
(307365,222448,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Early aromas of clove and spice give way to chunky berry fruit and some grassy notes. The palate bursts forward with juicy fruit and full tannins, and the finish is reasonably long. Snappy and simple, with a forward attitude.',10,NULL,0,'Cuvée Prestige Reserve',197404),
(307369,229307,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Shiraz',NULL,'Sweet and sour fruit, not unlike stewed rhubarb, colors the nose and palate. Although it is a little watery, peppery tannins pick up the slack. Closes with eucalyptus, char and bitter herbs.',16,NULL,0,'Basket Pressed',196689),
(307379,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'A wine that starts bright, and then reveals a more bitter, austere side. The tannins move forwards, hiding the cherry fruit flavors. That makes for a complex wine, the acidity offering a fresh respite.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cuvée Jean Descombes',197404),
(307408,217719,'other','Pinotage','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/2788/1238/products/DelheimPinotagerose_1200x1200.jpg?v=1678663923','A fresh and fruity red berry nose leads into a combo of crisp acidity and subdued berry fruit on this elegant rosé. Good, versatile food wine at a great price.',10,NULL,0,'Rosé',196845),
(307432,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Lots of oak on the nose, and for that matter, throughout. The wine tastes of lemon, vanilla and wood resin, while the creamy finish deals even more oak. Texture and richness are not a problem, but the wood runs roughshod over the mild, base-level fruit.',10,NULL,0,'Cuvée Prestige Reserve',197404),
(307438,223107,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'With 91% Cabernet Franc, this wine displays strong, vegetal, reedy aromas and flavors. There is red plum and cedar laid out over supportive acidity and tannins, but the finish is of bitter eucalyptus.',13,NULL,0,'Estate Wine - Cabernet Franc/Merlot',197545),
(307442,229307,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Opens with black cherry, toast and dark chocolate aromas. Followed by green herbs and grass that chase the tight, well-oaked fruit on the palate. Comes off as eucalyptus on the cherry-chocolate finish.',16,NULL,0,'Basket Pressed',196689),
(307477,223692,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Named after the creature that has been seen near this South African winery, this blend of Cabernet, Merlot and Cabernet Franc offers confident aromas of berry and spice. On the palate, it is supple and elegant with a touch of chocolate and oak sweetness that adds character. Overall, it\'s subtle and soft with a shot of minerality that recommends it to food pairing. The finish is lingering but gentle.',20,NULL,0,'Xanache',197599),
(307505,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'The ungainly name refers to older vines from this celebrated vineyard, and the wine does possess a distinguished balance. The pure cherry kirsch flavors are perfectly integrated into the oak, acid and tannic structure, with an elegantly silky texture. The result is pure Pinot pleasure. Should hold well over the next six years.',54,NULL,0,'Bien Nacido Vineyard Elder Series',196639),
(307525,217839,'other','Carmenère','https://conchaytoro.com/content/uploads/2018/07/cdd-me-1.png','A very ripe and ready style of Carmenère. The big berry aromas mixed with spice and herbs are just what you need to get into the juicy, forward palate of plum and blackberry. Round in the mouth, not tannic, yet still a force to reckon with. For $10 this is a lot of wine. Imported by Excelsior Wine & Spirits.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo',196852),
(307546,217702,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'91% Cabernet Sauvignon, plus Merlot and Cabernet Franc, Vergelegen\'s ultrapremium cuvée is tightly structured, harmoniously balanced, and built to age, although it has a greener flavor profile than many modern wines—bell pepper and bramble aromas and green bean flavors—there is still plenty of underlying cassis, tobacco and chocolate to make this a keeper. Polished tannins lead to a long, powerful finish.',145,NULL,0,'V',196689),
(307614,217265,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A really good Merlot-based blend, rich in cherry, blackberry, anise and smoky oak flavors, and shows a sophistication that\'s elegant enough to pair with fine food. Should be easy to find, with 7,000 cases.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 48 Meritage',196620),
(307623,217265,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'Dry and high-alcohol voluptuous, with appealingly forward cherry, blackberry and cola flavors, and a complex, spicy finish. The rich tannins make it perfect with flank steak and short ribs.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 43',196620),
(307647,217719,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'A classic South African SB, with dancing acidity, tropical fruit and pear flavors and a touch of rounded, wooded spice. The wine has complexity but is fresh and friendly. Pair with grilled fish or chicken. Imported by GBW, LLC.',15,NULL,0,'Varietal Collection',196845),
(307675,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Soft, but with an edge of dusty tannins, this wine has bright forward jammy red fruits that fill the mouth easily. It is open, fresh and, finally, almost sweet.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Sablons',197404),
(307682,217839,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'As a whole this is a mixed bag of dark fruit, creamy oak and chocolate, which makes it a New World Shiraz in every way, shape and form. The nose is creamy and ripe, and so is the chunky, broad, fruit-rich palate. It\'s a fruitball, no doubt, but a balanced one with proper acidity and tannins. Imported by Excelsior Wine & Spirits.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(307687,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From the Bouchard domaine, this wine is soft and ripe. There is some structure and firm acidity, but that\'s secondary to the luscious flavors that roll around the mouth. The wood broadens but also gives extra complexity to the wine.',84,NULL,0,'Les Gouttes d\'Or Premier Cru',197241),
(307694,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Chenevottes is situated high up on the Chassagne-Montrachet slope, above the grand cru vineyards. With its fat, ripe butter and coconut milk character, this wine offers an immediately appealing style. But there is a hint of ageability in its layers of serious wood and structure.',49,NULL,0,'Les Chenevottes Premier Cru',197254),
(307730,223391,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Bright, vibrant aromas of red berry and flowers leads on this rosé. Its easygoing, fresh and fruity character will pair well with almost any food, and good minerality ensures it\'s not too sweet.',12,NULL,0,'Rosé',196839),
(307741,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Blagny is a small hamlet just up the hill from Les Perrières. This is a cooler spot, and the wine shows this with its structure and flavors of fresh green fruits over generous portions of wood. A wine that should age for more than 5 years.',48,NULL,0,'Château de Blagny Meursault Blagny Premier Cru',197254),
(307752,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Ripe, open and packed with melon and tropical fruit flavors, this wine is already showing enticing drinkability. Its fresh, ripe fruits is layered with some mineral character and an under-cushion of wood.',65,NULL,0,'Cailleret Premier Cru',197254),
(307757,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/IRF_lbU0SLyMyVsl91epGg_pb_x960.png','For a so-called value wine, there\'s an awful lot of toast and oak on this baby. But that\'s okay, because despite the wine\'s almondy, sugary aromas and flavors, it has the body and acidity to handle it all. And along the way there are flavors of mango, orange and green banana as well as modest but present citrus zest. A big-production wine (270,000 cases) that satisfies.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo Reserve',196852),
(307785,222607,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Dry, minerally and crisp citrus flavors give this well priced wine a simple but striking appeal. Waves of lemon and grapefruit are lifted by a snap of acidity that leaves the finish clean on the tongue.',8,NULL,0,'Oak Lane Chenin Blanc Sauvignon Blanc',196689),
(307801,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'High up on the slope, the Sous le Puits vineyard has produced a ripe, open, buttery wine that is full of generous, opulent fruit. It is packed with pineapple, tropical fruit and lime flavors, along with a hint of caramel and almonds. Ready to drink now.',49,NULL,0,'Sous le Puits Premier Cru',197254),
(307808,217265,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'On opening, the oak on this Carneros Chard was overwhelming in smoke and char, giving the pear, Meyer lemon and kiwi flavors a woody undertow. As it breathes, it softens and unifies, but it\'s still a Hulk of a wine.',12,NULL,0,'Lot 57',196620),
(307811,223506,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Bursting with a nose of lemon and grapefruit, this fresh, lively wine offers good, mouthpuckering Sauvignon Blanc fruit with a racy, clean finish. Food friendly and affordable, it\'s simple but good.',12,NULL,0,'Reserve Collection',197456),
(307813,223909,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'A very pretty, balanced nose of fresh fruit and flowers, and a flavor profile of good, balanced strawberry fruit and acidity make this wine suitable for everyday drinking and pairing with salads, poultry and fresh fruit. Not terribly complex but tasty for this price. Imported by Cape Wine Ventures, LLC.',8,NULL,0,'Rosé',196839),
(307835,218228,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/u-pEznmeRyi8_pNj9ZIJPQ_pb_x600.png','A heavy whiff of balsam wood and dried leaves accents the brambly berry aromas that make up the bouquet. The feel is fairly snappy and curt, with red-berry fruit notes carrying a modest herbal touch. Finishes dry and firm, with a final blast of oak. Has power but runs a bit herbal and rough.',21,NULL,0,'Max Reserva',196886),
(307838,223593,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Fresh aromas of strawberry and toasty spice lead on this friendly rosé from Juno. On the palate, it\'s soft and subtle, with vibrant fruit flavors and a delicate finish. A great everyday wine that will pair especially well with seafood and summer fare.',10,NULL,0,'Cape Maidens Rosé',197456),
(307852,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A soft, open wine with some vanilla flavors emphasizing the opulence of Meursault. The wine is ready to drink now.',65,NULL,0,'Goutte d\'Or Premier Cru',197254),
(307872,218035,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Carmenère','https://www.vinello.de/media/image/d9/45/47/montes-limited-selection-red.png','Burnt coffee, leaves and herbal aromas give the wine an awkward bouquet. There is big-time oak, and it creates a creamy, unctuous mouthfeel and resiny marshmallow flavors. It has its berry foundation, size and weight, but it seems candied, simple and overoaked.',16,NULL,0,'Limited Selection Apalta Vineyard',196713),
(307892,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A lively, fresh and relatively light wine, showing the soft and easy side of Charmes. It is ready to drink but without the opulence of some wines from this vineyard.',80,NULL,0,'Charmes Premier Cru',197241),
(307900,222525,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Tart and bright and not terribly complex, this is nonetheless a good value. There\'s minerality and spice there too, which spicy grilled lamb or beef will enhance.',10,NULL,0,'Paddock',196845),
(307952,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Despite the prestigious Yountville appellation, this Cabernet disappoints. It\'s harsh and sweet, with medicinal flavors of cherries.',14,NULL,0,'Lot 35',196620),
(308021,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/zkXw45mESWmSWDK6cjPEbw_pb_x960.png','Very concentrated and closed up, like a coil. The intense green fruit is followed by plum skins. Crispness, dry but fresh, comes alongside a powerful explosion of flavors.',65,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Vaudésirs Grand Cru',196775),
(308036,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/cOV036xxToGm9rIRy0RQew_pb_x960.png','Weighty, full-bodied, full of ripe yellow fruits. Here\'s a wine that is going to be a powerhouse, packed with intense flavors, touched by wood and a crisp edge. The aftertaste leaves minerality along with the ripe fruit.',65,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Blanchots Grand Cru',196775),
(308069,217999,'other','Fiano','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/X0tNqLXNSgq4-o0HFLIy5Q_pb_x960.png','This Fiano-based wine offers the generous pear and peach aromas often associated with this native grape from Campania plus its trademark structure and caressing consistency (it is oak aged for six months). But what sets it apart is the elegant manner in which these elements are brought together.',42,NULL,0,'Campanaro',196908),
(308376,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'While there is some unfortunate banana flavor, the rest of this wine is attractive. It has juicy black berry flavors, an edge of citrus and final lively acidity.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine de Grand Croix',197404),
(308386,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Very mineral to start, only opening up slowly to offer a wonderful line of pure fruit. The texture is important—apple skin freshness dominant, along with spicy wood. This is for medium-term aging—4–5 years.',79,NULL,0,'Les Perrières Premier Cru',197241),
(308388,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://web-common.vivino.com/assets/bottleShot/fallback_2.png','There is an important element of wood here, along with a ripe, creamy texture. By contrast, the structure is mineral, lifted with grapefruit flavors. The wood supports this fruit, giving a complete, mouth filling wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Perrières Premier Cru',196775),
(308407,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'The banana aromas are off-putting in this light, juicy wine. Although there are tannins, they are not enough to make sense of the simple, jammy fruit.',NULL,NULL,0,'La Trinquée',197404),
(308424,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A very mineral–textured wine, with a stark contrast of ripe yellow fruits, sweet vanilla and an open final flavor. The wine is certainly packed with flavors, dense, the steely edge likely to soften over the next 2–3 years.',65,NULL,0,'La Garenne Premier Cru',197254),
(308427,220716,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Densely textured wine, its complex fruit and spice character offering currants, quince and green plums to go with the wood element. The wine layers fruit and a powerful dose of acidity, giving an edge to richness, never losing sight of freshness.',79,NULL,0,'Les Genevrières Premier Cru',197241),
(308461,217203,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'With six years\' aging, this is a delicious, soft and mature wine. The fruit and acidity have been subsumed into a balsam and spice flavored wine, with a touch of mint and sweet chocolate. It is delicious now, not for aging further.',20,NULL,0,'Casa das Mouras Reserva',196685),
(308464,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A rounded wine, with a counterpoint of apple skin texture, the fruit flavors offering acidity as well as green plums. The texture is plush, velvet, delicious.',69,NULL,0,'Charmes Premier Cru',197254),
(308609,217425,'other','Gamay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/PNzB2oEqQY-VtevwyxkMKg_pb_x960.png','A wine that shows perhaps too much tannin for a Nouveau, and will probably be more accessible next year. It has a tight side, with the acidity fitting well into the ripe plum flavors.',13,NULL,0,'Beaujolais Villages Nouveau',196775),
(308611,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'This has weight and some rich fruit. On top of this are ripe tannins, bananas and black cherry flavors. The acidity is present but balanced.',11,NULL,0,'Beaujolais Villages Nouveau',197404),
(308637,219700,'other','Red Blend','https://www.totalwine.com/dynamic/490x/media/sys_master/twmmedia/h31/h35/14936416845854.png','This delicious Sicilian blend of Merlot, Syrah, Cabernet Sauvignon and Nero d\'Avola offers a pretty aromatic ensemble of ripe fruit, spice and leather. There are distinct notes of blackberry and prune and the wine tastes soft and opulent in the mouth.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sallier de la Tour',196776),
(308674,217839,'other','Sauvignon Blanc','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Nd8xOoEQRCapbFkcthM8_w_pb_x960.png','We haven\'t seen anything labeled Trio for years, but the return of this Concha y Toro brand seems solid. Aromas of orange blossom, lime and other green fruits are good, while flavors of citrus, grapefruit and cucumber are fresh and appealing. A good but standard wine that is lifted by a touch of green herb and brine.',14,NULL,0,'Trio Reserva',196852),
(308679,224534,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This Bradgate blend of Chenin and Sauvignon Blanc offers food-friendly aromas and flavors of lemon spice, pepper and slate. It\'s zippy but fruity, with a spicy character that will pair well with like foods—think Asian spice. The Chenin offers roundness, while the SB gives citric, clean flavors. A nice match.',10,NULL,0,'Chenin Blanc - Sauvignon Blanc',196689),
(308684,226846,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a friendly, New World- style Chardonnay, with flavors of toast, oak and spice and decent complexity. Assertive and upfront, it\'s a good everyday white for fans of whites with pronounced flavors.',11,NULL,0,'The Winemaster\'s Reserve',196839),
(308685,226846,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A minerally, grassy nose leads on this white blend of 51% Sauvignon Blanc, 25% Chenin and 23% Chardonnay. Intense flavors of honey, almond and spice blend well with a citric, zingy edge. Some tropical fruit curviness rounds the whole thing out. A unique and stylish sip.',10,NULL,0,'Lyric',196839),
(308772,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/cOV036xxToGm9rIRy0RQew_pb_x960.png','There is a fine steely, mineral character to the wine that parallels the ripe yellow fruit, toast and quince jelly flavors. The ensemble is rich, but maintains the true cool-climate character of Chablis.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Blanchots Premier Cru',196775),
(308776,219884,'other','Touriga Nacional Blend','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_959i6B8TzyEfTkv7R4law_pb_x600.png','There was once a belief that Pinot Noir and Touriga Nacional were related, although DNA tests have now disproved it. Putting the two together gives a big, smooth wine, the tannins of the Touriga rounded and softened by the hearty Pinot Noir red fruits.',25,NULL,0,'Consensus Pinot Noir-Touriga Nacional',196807),
(308855,220716,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Tough and defiantly tannic, a hard-edged wine that gives a powerful dry texture. The fruit is less obvious, but has a potential to offer red fruits and fresh acidity. This does need aging, over 4–5 years.',NULL,NULL,0,'Les Porrets Premier Cru',197241),
(308965,217425,'other','Pinot Noir','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/M5ZfaQZaTKqPwnWQxKuqLg_pb_x960.png','There is good weight here. Its richness and fruits offer light red plum textures, a dry tannic character as well as some good power. Complexity and sweetness both promote a concentrated wine.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Clos des Maréchaudes',196775),
(308998,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://www.saq.com/media/catalog/product/1/4/14796020-1_1635452128.png?quality=80&fit=bounds&height=&width=','This is a wine that has lightness and freshness as dominant characters. Yes, there is fine green fruit, with a backbone structure of white currants, but the acidity, well supported by wood, is what gives the wine shape and a vivid, fresh aftertaste.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine du Pavillon Premier Cru Clos des Mouches',196775),
(309074,217265,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A bit sweet and candied on the nose, palate and finish, but good if you like creamy, sweet, vanilla notes in your Cabernet. The feel is sort of soft and soupy, while flavors of candied, gummy red berry and prune maintain enough vitality to bring things home. A lot like a cherry-cola ice cream float.',13,NULL,0,'The Flying Winemaker',196620),
(309392,217780,'other','Carmenère','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/Rzvg7SXFTsaUMPUDXKyf9g_pb_x600.png','Opens with generic red fruit and candy aromas, but the palate is overtly acidic, which causes a sourness to go with candied, medicinal berry fruit flavors. After the tartness subsides, there\'s regular red fruit notes left over.',12,NULL,0,'Barrel Select Reserve',196857),
(309410,218512,'other','Nero d\'Avola',NULL,'Here\'s an easygoing (and well-priced) Nero d\'Avola with fresh tones of cherry, blueberry and white almond. It\'s a compact and simple wine that would pair well with informal stay-home meals.',11,NULL,0,'Poggio Bidini',196773),
(309414,218512,'other','Syrah',NULL,'The wine has a slightly awkward note of burnt biscuit behind more satisfactory aromas of soft, sweet cherry, rose petal, tobacco and leather. The mouthfeel is edgy and sharp with a spice-driven finish.',13,NULL,0,'Poggio Bidini',196773),
(309814,219884,'other','Trincadeira',NULL,'A black, solid wine, spiced heavily with wood but still showing blackberry flavors, textured with plum skins. The wine feels warm and ripe, finishing with black cherries and lingering softness.',13,NULL,0,'Grand\'Arte',196807),
(309889,218042,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This is an extremely appealing, accessible Pinotage—instantly likeable and elegant. On the nose, heady aromas of chocolate and plum; on the palate, lush, velvety, soft tannins and substantial structure. Not sure you\'ll like Pinotage? Give this one a shot. With food, it will be even better.',18,NULL,0,'Phanto Ridge',196845),
(309893,222367,'other','Nuragus',NULL,'The sun-drenched island of Sardinia is gaining an excellent reputation for extremely food-friendly white wines. With stone fruit, honey and floral tones, this is a perfect example; pair well with seafood.',NULL,NULL,0,'Sàlnico',197281),
(309895,222367,'other','Vermentino',NULL,'The nose is almost neutral save for subtle notes of white stone, honey and pear. But on the palate, the wine proves itself, thanks to its smooth and silky consistency.',14,NULL,0,'Crabilis',197281),
(309949,224555,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This is unique not only because it\'s the first such blend to be produced in South Africa (Syrah-Mourvèdre-Grenache) but also because of its exotic palate of dark chocolate, plum and spice flavors. The wine is fun and vibrant but also elegant and complex enough to stand on its own in the glass, and it still exhibits the measured restraint for which the French, and many South African wines, are known. Imported by Terlato Wines International.',NULL,NULL,0,'SMG',196839),
(309956,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/cOV036xxToGm9rIRy0RQew_pb_x960.png','Closed up and firm with a hint of vanilla, honey and refined acidity. There is some crispness here, green apples and a plum skin character. This is going to be serious Chardonnay; the minerality already in evidence.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Bougnons Premier Cru',196775),
(309958,217425,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/F9li_iPeQXeoNqb6F9hJPg_pb_x960.png','This is definitely young, but the fresh fruit is already very apparent. There\'s a lifted, vibrant apple character that opens in the mouth to give yellow fruits with a finish of steel and gun flint sharpness.',NULL,NULL,0,'Domaine Long-Depaquit Les Lys Premier Cru',196775),
(310034,223130,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The Nieuwould family has farmed at Cederberg for five generations—hence the name. This top Cabernet from the estate vineyards comes from old vines, giving huge concentration and elegance. Aged for 18 months in wood, this intense, berry- dominated wine also shows big, dry fruit tannins, and should age for a good 10 years.',49,NULL,0,'Five Generations',197547),
(310082,222821,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'The second vintage from this joint venture between Remhoogte owner Murray Boustred and new partner Michel Rolland. This blend includes Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon and Pinotage. It is an impressively perfumed wine that gets away from the juicy Pinotage flavors and goes for a densely packed, woody taste, with great black plum flavors.',45,NULL,0,'Bonne Nouvelle',196689),
(310083,222821,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'The estate wine from Remhoogte in which Michel Rolland is both consultant and partner. This Bordeaux Blend is serious stuff with dry tannins that promise good aging. There is some Pinotage in the blend, but it is hardly noticeable; the main flavors come from the textured cassis of Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon.',28,NULL,0,'Estate Wine',196689),
(310084,223183,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'The Winemakers Guild is a grouping of South African winemakers and members who can submit wines for approval and release under the Guild name. This impressive 2004 Cabernet is still very young, firmly under the control of fine tannins, but showing ripe but structured dark plums and herbs underneath.',60,NULL,0,'Winemaker Guild Blend',196689),
(310112,225668,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'From its wax seal, its older vintage (this is the current release) and its name, expect interesting things. You won\'t be disappointed. The wines come from a small parcel of land on the estate that was long considered too poor to plant. Native yeasts, whole berry fermentation and no filtering—that\'s the methode ancienne part. There are just 20 barrels of poised, elegant wine with huge depth of flavor, black cherries and dense tannins blending well together.',52,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon Methode Ancienne',196845),
(310188,223791,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A classic Bordeaux blend, dominated by 60% Cabernet Sauvignon, Premiere Selection is a ripe wine, layered with sweet fruit dominating firm tannins. Despite those tannins, the big fruit flavors mean the wine is ready to drink now.',35,NULL,0,'Premiere Selection',196839),
(310276,229307,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'If any proof were needed that South African wines are stylistically as close to Europe as they can be to California, it would be in this wine. With its tight structure, mineral fruit character and enclosed layer of cassis fruits, this is as Bordeaux as it gets outside southwest France.',67,NULL,0,'Limited Release',196689),
(310283,222331,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A very pure line of blackberry and dark cherry flavors distinguish this wine. It is certainly structured—underneath the fruit there are plenty of fruit and wood tannins—but the ripe fruit flavors dominate. Based on fruit from the Jonkershoek valley, this shows a fine minerally side, compliments of the granite subsoil.',27,NULL,0,'Stark',196689),
(310294,227664,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'From one of the Cape\'s coolest wine regions, this Marlbrook, grown in Constantia, has great structure and dry tannins that reveal cassis fruit underneath. It is very dry at present, a sign of aging potential, but also means it will be a great accompaniment to rich meat dishes. Not imported.',NULL,NULL,0,'Marlbrook',197609),
(310295,217625,'other','Portuguese White',NULL,'Made from the vineyards of Casa de Santar, this is the result of an exercise in old-style white wine making, but without the oxidation. The wine is full, rich, maybe not as fruity as more modern-style whites, but with considerable complexity of new wood, almonds, spice and a touch of honey.',NULL,NULL,0,'Casa de Santar Vinha do Contador',196794),
(310363,225668,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'The is the first vintage of this Bordeaux blend, after 10 years of planning and waiting. But the wine is excellent—there\'s plenty of juicy fruit, dry wood and tannin, along with chocolate and plenty of firm berry flavors.',30,NULL,0,'The Work of Time',196845),
(310370,222544,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'At first smell this seems to be maturing fast, with cedar and pencil shaving aromas. But in fact the tannins are still firm and dry, the ripe black fruit is all there, and it will certainly improve for a few years yet. But it is ready to drink now. A restrained, elegant wine overall. Not imported.',NULL,NULL,0,'Estate',196689),
(310448,218046,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A ripe plum and black cherry-flavored wine that shows wood tannins from aging in small French oak barrels. This blend of Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot and Shiraz (hence the name Triptych) is full-blooded, dense and very rich. Not imported.',NULL,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar Triptych',196839),
(310450,223265,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'One of South Africa\'s best with Chenin, Bruwer Raats has hit another home run with this unwooded wine. It kicks off with perfumed citrus aromas, then lets fly with lively almond-tinged flavors of orange and peach. Vibrant in the mouth with beautifully matching acidity, this is a wine that calls for food, but can certainly be enjoyed alone.',13,NULL,0,'Original',197456),
(310456,223284,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A very herbal wine, with sage and thyme flavors. There are solid, dry tannins that mask the black fruits and red berry tastes. This is a wine that obviously needs time to develop, promising a serious, tannin-layered style.',NULL,NULL,0,'Private Collection',196689),
(310458,227664,'other','White Blend',NULL,'From the historic Constantia Valley comes this beautiful blend of Sémillon, Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc and Muscat. Broad aromas of peachy tropical fruit are brushed with grass and toast notes that add complexity, leading to a round, medium-bodied wine that is sculpted with a dry, grassy feel. Tropical fruit and green-bean flavors play cat and mouse, finishing with grapefuit.',20,NULL,0,'Marlbrook',197609),
(310541,225668,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Whole-berry fermentation in open-top fermenters allows fermentation to take place slowly and gently. That\'s the basis behind this open, generous wine, which has great black fruit flavor, good intensity and soft, ripe tannins.',22,NULL,0,'Whole Berry Cabernet Sauvignon',196845),
(310545,222331,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A single-vineyard wine from land high in the dramatic Jonkershoek valley, this is an intriguingly perfumed wine that still shows a fine sense of structure. The fruit is certainly ripe—it is 14.5% alcohol—but that is lost in the balance with acidity and fine black currant flavors.',42,NULL,0,'Condé',196689),
(310623,223590,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A spicy, forward and fruity wine that maintains ample balance. It shows red fruits, spice and dry tannins. This is fresh, elegant and ready to drink now.',18,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon',196689),
(310688,218046,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A very intense, perfumed wine, with great blackberry and spice flavors. Ripe and juicy, it has soft tannins and a firm, dry layer from wood aging. Big and concentrated, this wine is ready to drink now. Not imported.',NULL,NULL,0,'Reserve',196839),
(310751,223506,'other','Chardonnay-Semillon',NULL,'Like biting into a peach, this bargain-buster has intense peach and yellow fruit flavors with a dry, pithy edge. Touches of butter and spice suggest oak, while grassy notes and acid give it backbone. Beyond an aperitif, this wine has the stuffing to stand up to many a chicken dish.',9,NULL,0,'Le Pavillon',197456),
(310835,229222,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Fans of old-style Tuscan wines, take note. This easy-to-like wine has plummy-cherry fruit flavors wrapped in a leathery skin. Some barnyard and cola are apparent on the nose, while sweet tannins coat the palate. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',16,NULL,0,'Bellevue Estate',196689),
(310953,228459,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Light gold, this has a touch of oak to the nose, adding sweetness to aromas of tropical fruit. Rounder and fuller than unoaked Chenins, with a touch of sweetness from the oak, this nevertheless has good acidity propping up yellow fruit flavors touched with spice.',12,NULL,0,'Premium Select',196839),
(310982,228459,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Rounded in the mouth, with decent balance, this has nice fruit and spice, even if the impression is not lasting. Citrus pith, oak spice and a touch of petrol surround tropical fruit flavors. Finish is brief. Imported by American Wine Distributors.',12,NULL,0,'Premium Select',196839),
(310999,217839,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'The newest addition to the Terrunyo line is a single-vineyard Shiraz with high alcohol, ripe fruit and varietal correctness. The nose has some wild game and spice alongside big black-fruit aromas. The palate, meanwhile, is ripe as can be, with upbeat tannins and acidity. Huge but balanced. A winner. Imported by Banfi Vintners.',28,NULL,0,'Terrunyo Block 34',196852),
(311023,222428,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'From a famed Stellenbosch estate comes another fantastic vintage of the Estate red. A blend of Cabernet (53%) and Shiraz (33%), with Merlot picking up the slack, this awesome wine shows all that the Stellenbosch region can be. Nearly black in color, the nose is awash with clove, cinnamon and coffee notes that donï¿½t overpower the dark, plummy fruit. Its rich mouthfeel is loaded with dark plum and cassis flavors and sprinkled coffee grounds, ending in a long, earthy finish. Drink now and over the next 8 years. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',46,NULL,0,'Estate Wine',196689),
(311097,224352,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This Cab-dominant Bordeaux blend opens slowly, eventually showing blueberry, pastry, and cedar aromas. Tobacco and earth take the stage in the mouth, along with more blueberry and pie crust. The smooth, evolved tannins offer a seamless mouthfeel; will continue to evolve over the next five years. Imported by Maisons Marques & Domaines USA.',30,NULL,0,'Rubicon',196689),
(311110,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Chocolate, cigar leaf and plum fruit aromas lead to a big, full-bodied wine with great balance and plenty of ripe tannins. Kirsch, black currant and spice flavors are plenty deep; tobacco shines through on the long, smooth finish. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',35,NULL,0,'Condé',196689),
(311179,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An interesting blend of Nerello Mascalese (from 600 meters above sea level) and Merlot that sees 12 months of oak. Toasted notes are embellished with granite, resin, tobacco and forest berry; nice, linear and supple in the mouth. Drink now. Imported by A.V. Imports Inc.',14,NULL,0,'Terre d\'Agala',196776),
(311185,223633,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Has dominant stably, earthy aromas and flavors. While not a fruity wine, it still has a beautiful mouthfeel, creamy, yet with good acidity. Finishes spicy and long. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',36,NULL,0,'Gouverneurs',197609),
(311186,222331,'other','Syrah',NULL,'Not as complex as the Condé, this wine still has rich, plummy fruit matched with sexy oak. The oak shows as chocolate and vanilla on the nose. Full, with a barely noticeable 15% alcohol, the palate offers dry tannins and just enough acidity. The dark fruit flavors have hints  of spice, and pick up herbal notes on the finish. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',26,NULL,0,'Stark',196689),
(311249,218228,'other','Cabernet Blend',NULL,'The Chadwicks have hit the big time with this superb Cabernet-dominated blend. The bouquet of black cherry, charcoal, plum and tree bark is sensational, while the cassis, cherry and tobacco flavors sing on the palate. Lots of fruit, power and balance, with a touch of earthiness.',100,NULL,0,'Viñedo Chadwick',196886),
(311291,227535,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Golden Kaan\'s best wine to date, this competes with some of South Africa\'s much pricier wines. There are cola, balsam, coffee and mixed berry aromas, while the mouthfeel is creamy, with  dry tannins. On the palate, the wine picks up some earthy flavors in addition to mixed berry, and has good length on the finish. Imported by Golden Kaan USA.',14,NULL,0,'Reserve Selection',196839),
(311299,222421,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'From Charles Back comes another play on a Rhône wine, although this has Grenache and Carignan in addition to the Shiraz and Viognier. A tight nose of ripe, red fruit leads to a jammy, plum-filled palate layered with chocolate, oak spice and vanilla. Rich and dark, with a round mouthfeel, it finishes with spice and a little warmth. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',18,NULL,0,'Goat-Roti',197456),
(311304,229221,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Oak is a key player in this wine, caressing purple-fruit aromas with vanilla and spice. Full-bodied and vibrant in the mouth, with moderate acid and tannins, the oak lends a hint of spice to young plum and sour cherry flavors. A warm, smoky finish of lemon-rubbed leather lingers on the palate. Will improve over two years. Imported by DC Imports LLC.',22,NULL,0,'Roland\'s Reserve',197445),
(311334,222421,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'This inky purple wine offers aromas of carob and smoke. Chunky, with a hint of sweetness and solid tannins, this wine nevertheless has spiky acids that show through and call for food. Flavors of plum, carob and vanilla are rich, finishing with overripe prune. Imported by Vineyard Brands.',13,NULL,0,'Goats do Roam in Villages',197456),
(311337,219700,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'This is a golden-hued Chardonnay that sees seven months of French oak with a rich, creamy quality that is not always easy to read. The aromas span from exotic fruit to Parmigiano cheese rind, but the mouthfeel is jazzy and cool. Imported by Winebow.',29,NULL,0,'Chardonnay',196776),
(311372,226846,'other','White Blend',NULL,'A blend of four white grapes, this semisweet white has pineapple and citrus aromas mixed with menthol. In the mouth it\'s creamy, with  flavors of white fruits, nuts, menthol and flowers. Enjoy with mild curry dishes. Imported by Dreyfus, Ashby & Co.',11,NULL,0,'Stein',196839),
(311432,217839,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MbUwLPqCSx2JVTjMgvesmg_pb_x600.png','Nice and full on the nose, with a bit of subtle oak that yields smoke, bacon, coffee and mocha aromas. Red plum and sweet berry fruit lead to a smooth finish. Good and in proportion, if a touch raw and woody. Imported by Banfi Vintners.',9,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo',196852),
(311479,217839,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Hard to believe that this Chilean icon is now in its 17th year. We recall back in the early \'90s when it was just getting going at well under $20 a bottle. With this wine look for potent, almost buttery oak propping up ripe berry fruit. In the folds are notes of tobacco, earth, mineral and mushroom. Tannic on the tail, with some overt wood that needs to find its place. Hold of at least a year.',47,NULL,0,'Don Melchor Vintage 17',196852),
(311530,223130,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Half Merlot, 15% Pinotage, and the remainder Ruby Cabernet (a cross between Cab Sauvignon and Carignan), this wine has nice structure backed by refined tannins. A creamy nose of vanilla and cassis touched with mint leads to a full mouth of dark berry, coffee, balsam and barnyard. Has enough body to pair well with assorted cheeses. Imported by Global Vineyard Importers.',20,NULL,0,'Cederberger',197547),
(311537,228411,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'From an area formerly known for wheat and tobacco comes this co-op produced premium wine. This Pinotage is inky-purple in color with fresh, grapy whiffs of dark berry and spice, with lemony overtones. Full-bodied and creamy in the mouth, it has flavors of spice, purple fruit and straw with a lemony-citrus finish. Imported by Hemingway & Hale.',14,NULL,0,'Indalo',197368),
(311539,229221,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'There is some peanut shell to the nose, but also banana and citrus. Medium-full in the mouth, the wine is smooth, with citrus flavors tempered by spice and nut. Picks up some lime on the sweet finish. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',12,NULL,0,'Estate',197445),
(311552,217148,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://bremerswineandliquor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/deloach-vineyards-cabernet-sauvignon.png','Made in a ripe style, this Cab bursts with jammy black currant, plum and coffee flavors that finish rich and sweet. But it\'s also got a firm texture, with fine-grained tannins and a keen edge of acidity. The result is a balanced and stylish Cab that should hold for at least seven years.',30,NULL,0,'OFS',196642),
(311600,228408,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Super clean and fresh, with pineapple, pink grapefruit and ample minerality. Quite snappy and tasty, with mostly tropical fruit flavors and grassy notes. Graceful, with a light to medium palate feel. Imported by Hemingway and Hale.',23,NULL,0,'Vintner\'s Reserve',196793),
(311666,223438,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'An interesting, medium-weight red and a sort of Cape-o-neuf de Pape--comprised of four Rhone grapes.  It\'s ripe and juicy, with dark berry fruit accented by menthol and mint notes. The close of this nicely-fruited blend shows classy drier, slightly metallic Grenache notes.',28,NULL,0,'Roulette',197368),
(311723,218042,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Smooth and even, this is  grapy and pretty soft. Chocolate and caramel notes accent the ripe berry fruit. It\'s a refined take on the low-acid easy drinker--think of it as an upscale quaff. Finishes gently with good length.',20,NULL,0,'Prospect Hill',196845),
(311739,223183,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A fun wine, with plenty of plum and berry flavors cloaked in oak, with a hint of earth to add interest. Quaffable for its smooth mouthfeel and moderate tannins, the nose has a hint of sour cherry. A Pinotage,  Cabernet and Merlot blend. Imported by Broadbent Selections, Inc.',25,NULL,0,'Three Cape Ladies Cape Blend',196689),
(311786,227975,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Ripe, full, and decidedly different from the lean, rather sharp style currently in vogue. The mild, tropical fruit and grapefruit flavors show good intensity. It\'s an interesting change of pace, low-acid though satisfying, in a softer style. Imported by 57 Main Street Wine Co.',13,NULL,0,'Darling Hills Road',197456),
(311807,222607,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Tart apple is the main player in the mouth. Zesty and ripe, the 85% Chenin Blanc is beginning to show nutty flavors, too. A good bargain from Beau Joubert\'s second label. Imported by DC Imports LLC.',8,NULL,0,'Oak Lane Chenin Blanc-Sauvignon Blanc',196689),
(311852,217780,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/_6NbTxQYQTCFUQeF0ICxOA_pb_600x600.png','A Cab/Merlot blend that\'s ripe and alluring, with easygoing but still power-packed aromatics. Flavors of cassis, black cherry and raisin are full-bore, and the chocolaty finish scores. Balanced and correct. Imported by T.G.I.C. Importers.',11,NULL,0,'60/40 Barrel Select',196857),
(311879,229362,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Smooth and simple, this wine comes on strong with dark red berry flavors then fades quickly. Solid tannins and a bit of sweetness add to the mouthfeel, but aromas of red berry and clay are marred by the smell of band-aid.',15,NULL,0,'Hidden Agenda',196689),
(311942,226846,'other','Riesling',NULL,'Light and taut, with bright acidity underlying grass and mineral aromas and flavors, plus kerosene hints. The light lemon and grape flavors are appealing. An attractive, inexpensive white for sipping or light dining. Imported by Dreyfus, Ashby & Co.',10,NULL,0,'Paarl',196839),
(311949,220442,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Lots of tight oak results in aromas of resin, mint and burnt grass. Runs a bit light and tart, given all that oak. The flavors are of raspberry and cranberry with an artificial vanilla sweetness and full tannins. Imported by A.V. Imports Inc.',18,NULL,0,'Terra D\'Agala',196776),
(312040,227240,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Tomato leaf and red fruit aromas lift from this 80/20 blend. Despite the young age, it\'s starting to rust at the rim. The wine is on the soft side, creamy and smooth, with with flavors of red berry, vanilla, and green leaf.',9,NULL,0,'Merlot/Pinotage',196839),
(312243,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Soft, light and fresh, this wine has attractive acidity as well as crisp, green flavors. There\'s a touch of vanilla which broadens it out. It\'s a solid, ready-to-drink wine.',6,NULL,0,'Cépage',197404),
(312249,217310,'other','Portuguese Red','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/vkSBoEDWRBSn8dJ3dfUzsA_pb_x960.png','A soft, simple, pleasurably fruit wine, which has flavors of dried berries and perfumed violets. Fresh and ripe, it is ready to drink.',NULL,NULL,0,'Alabastro',196677),
(312436,219700,'other','Nerello Mascalese','https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0620/5145/1073/products/Tenuta-Regaleali-Regaleali-Le-Rose.png?v=1679307626','A beautifully luminous rosé with a peach-raspberry hue made from Nerello Mascalese (vinified white) that sees contact with Nero d\'Avola skins for color. The pretty aromas include raspberry, strawberry and stone fruit and the wine\'s freshness and structure is reminiscent of rosés from southern France.',12,NULL,0,'Le Rose',196776),
(312508,217512,'other','Portuguese Red',NULL,'With its well-integrated scents of cedar, plum and tobacco, this is a medium-weight wine whose hallmark is its balance. Vanilla and dried spices meld nicely with cherry and plum fruit, finishing smooth, with modest tannins. Drink now-2008.',14,NULL,0,'Cado',196663),
(312526,222693,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Backsberg\'s top offerings, its Babylons Toren range, are impressive, showing a focus, quality and style not seen before. This is suave, with vibrant pineapple, mango and apple aromas and flavors, and ample French oak. The texture is very good—a positive tension between rich and zingy notes.',25,NULL,0,'Babylons Toren',197445),
(312565,218035,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Gold in color, this blend of 50% Riesling and 50% Gewürztraminer is packed with apricot, peach and honey notes along with walnut and peanut hints. It\'s rich and fruity, with marzipan and other sugary flavors. Modest acidity suggests it should be consumed soon.',18,NULL,0,'Late Harvest',196713),
(312637,222693,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Achieves a fine, balance of tangy and rich elements. Grapefruit, fig and vanilla aromas and flavors abound, with a lovely tension. The texture is great, and tart citrus notes linger on the long finish. Not the zingiest, nor the weightiest, but an excellent all-around Sauvignon Blanc.',15,NULL,0,'John Martin',197445),
(312642,222668,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Opaque and very dense on the nose with deep, focused, black plum and berry fruit. Toasty oak is nicely melded with the strong fruit, adding smoke and tobacco notes. A chewy mouthfeel and long dark finish complete the package. Should improve through 2006, and hold well beyond that.',28,NULL,0,'Beacon',197456),
(312657,218035,'other','Merlot-Cabernet Franc',NULL,'Big and forward, with spicy, pungent aromas and also a softening hint of bread dough. The palate features snappy red fruit with drying oak in support. The tannic structure holds its own but doesn\'t rise up too much. A weighty, driving wine.',20,NULL,0,'Alpha',196713),
(312768,217839,'other','Chardonnay','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/mVnqafVsTv26grHSG7tXUA_pb_600x600.png','Creamy and plump; this is a fine bargain-priced Chard, one with character and balance. Sure, there are the telltale pear and banana flavors, but on the back it offers subtle apple notes prior to a light, casual finish.',10,NULL,0,'Casillero del Diablo',196852),
(312929,218035,'other','Malbec',NULL,'Rarely does one get celery from the nose of a Montes wine, but in this case it\'s there. The mouth, meanwhile, is expectedly sweet, with blackberry and a touch of rubber. The wine improves with airing, but it\'s not a prime-timer.',10,NULL,0,'Reserve Oak Aged',196713),
(312981,218046,'other','Shiraz','https://www.vinello.eu/media/image/cc/ff/01/cathedral-cellar-shiraz-kwv.png','Scents of sawdust, kiln-dried wood and scorched oak bring the lumberyard to life. There\'s some coffee and licorice at this wine\'s core, plus a beam of lemony acidity that helps keep it balanced. This is definitely a wine for oakophiles.',15,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar',196839),
(312988,223258,'other','Port',NULL,'This squat-bottled offering shows a rich and dense stewed fruit, dried plum and raisin platform. The fruit\'s up front, with attractive nut and smoke accents showing as this opens up in the glass. Even in feel, not overly dense or heavy, and accessible now.',20,NULL,0,'Cape Vintage Port',197445),
(313075,223183,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Offers interesting Oriental spice, leather, popcorn and earth notes over deep cassis fruit. Full and smooth, with excellent balance and an espresso-dark finish. Perhaps oak-heavy, but delicious in weight and style not unlike some very good modern-style Graves.',32,NULL,0,'Estate Reserve',196689),
(313080,222693,'other','Viognier',NULL,'This tasty Viognier hits all the right notes, presenting very appealing honeysuckle-spice aromas and flavors. It\'s not heavy or sappy, and good acidity supports the fruit. Finishes long and with a very nice blend of spice and mineral notes.',25,NULL,0,'Babylons Toren',197445),
(313104,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/-ehAWOyaS2q7-6X-LaRriw_pb_x600.png','Mainly from Rutherford, a beautiful wine. Opens with alluring aromas of blackcurrant and cassis and the lilting perfume of new French oak, with its smoky vanillins. In the mouth, supple and polished, long on Cabernet flavor, with rich, sumptuous tannins. The tannins are already melted, making it drinkable now.',40,NULL,0,'Great Estates',196751),
(313251,217999,'other','White Blend',NULL,'The name of the wine and the grape is Falanghina. It was well liked by Pliny, Horace and Virgil—and who could argue with them? Clean and fresh, this rendition opens with pineapple, banana, citrus and pear scents. The palate displays vibrant acidity, excellent balance, medium body and a velvety mouthfeel. The finish is long and echoes the opening notes. Editors\' Choice.',15,NULL,0,'Falanghina Sannio',196908),
(313259,223506,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Another strong showing by Boschendahl, the 1999 Sauvignon Blanc offers grapefruit, smoke and melon aromas. The supple palate has a good acid spine, plus apple-vanilla accents—perhaps from the 15% Chardonnay in the blend. Finishes long, with a slight peppery note. Best Buy.',12,NULL,0,'Grande Cuvée',197456),
(313273,223258,'other','Morio Muskat',NULL,'Bright, focused classic orange-apricot Muscat aromas and flavors shine in this fortified wine from Paarl. Though light in feel, it shows a little heat—no surprise with its 18% alcohol. Refreshing very cold from the nose right through the tangy citrus-spice close.',15,NULL,0,'Jerepico',197445),
(313364,222693,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot',NULL,'Opaque and hard to read, with deep, toasty, menthol-tinged oak over dark and dense fruit. Built for the cellar. Taut structure and firm   tannins here demand keeping both the wine until 2006–7.',15,NULL,0,'Klein Babylons Toren',197445),
(313377,223391,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A touch buttery on the nose at first, this wine quickly shows mango, vanilla and toast aromas. Big in the mouth, but with a firm line of acidity to hold it in check, the warm flavors of tropical fruits are backed by plenty of toasty, spicy oak. An intense finish is magnified by a dash of lasting acidity.',38,NULL,0,'Barrel Fermented',196839),
(313383,223633,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A subtle, elegant nose displays cassis, soy, vanilla and green bean aromas. Many of Groot Constantia\'s wines, including this one, have a silky mouthfeel, with just the right amount of oak balancing the soft tannins and acidity. Mixed berry, bell pepper and tobacco flavors continue through a decently long finish.',32,NULL,0,'Gouverneurs Reserve',197609),
(313439,218046,'other','Merlot','https://images.vivino.com/thumbs/MAc_29R4SoKJlao6F4fZhA_pb_x600.png','With its dried fruit, leather and mint scents, this lean wine could easily be mistaken for a modest Bordeaux. The tart cherry flavors on the lithe palate bear tobacco accents. Closes tart and dry, with a cocoa note.',15,NULL,0,'Cathedral Cellar',196839),
(313606,220798,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'A rich, lush melange of fruit and nuts, with sinuous, almost unctuous flavors that twine around the palate like a snake. Long, fascinating finish, elegantly balanced and precise.',55,NULL,0,'Les Referts Premier Cru',197254),
(313616,222448,'other','Gamay',NULL,'Fruity and fresh, this wine is as packed with grapes and cherries as a wine can be, yet still picks up hints of plum and chocolate on the finish, imparting added complexity. Duboeuf, the largest producer of Beaujolais, seems to have struck gold in this vintage; if you can\'t find this Morgon, try one of the other crus. And look for the domaine wines Duboeuf commercializes when they are released.',12,NULL,0,'Grand Cuvée Flower label',197404),
(313669,227775,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Not your average Shiraz, this has touches of tobacco, eraser and mineral to the rasberry and dark berry fruit aromas. More plummy in the mouth, with spicy pepper and layered oak and acidity to match the still young tannins. Leave it on its side for a couple years, or give it at least an hour in a decanter. Imported by Cape Classics.',20,NULL,0,'Zondernaam',196689),
(313673,223231,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Pinotage aromas of woodsmoke and sour cherry segue into Bordeaux scents of dried tobacco and cassis. This blend of 45% Pinotage with the rest Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot juxtaposes the former\'s vibrant fruit with structured tannin and brown leaf flavors. Smooth, incorporating high acidity, the oak still needs time to fully integrate.',20,NULL,0,'Cape Blend',196689),
(313678,218043,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Nearly black, this big wine smells like dark berries dipped in vanilla cream, with a hint of barnyard. The barnyard carries to the palate, where it\'s joined by leather and blackberry. Tannins start off smooth, but develop plenty of grip with time. Warm throughout, this is one that should be decanted a few hours before serving.',43,NULL,0,'Vineyard Selection',196839),
(313684,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon','https://www.kj.com/sites/default/files/styles/bottle_desktop/public/bottle-shots/kjvr-cab-sauv-nv_1.png?itok=wZZFpV5e','Very aromatic, showing a complex nose of cherry, spice, smoked and raw meat, and tobacco. The flavors are copious, too, with strong black cherry, licorice and tobacco elements. Balance and structure are beautiful here, and the coffee-chocolate finish has very good length, showing spice and blueberry accents. Lovely already, it will be better in four years and will drink well to 2010.',100,NULL,0,'Elite',196751),
(313747,218426,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Big mountain fruit here throws powerful aromas of ripe plum, thyme and bacon, while full-scale oaking yields maple aromas, vanilla flavors, and coffee on the finish. The wood element is a little weighty at this point, but there\'s solid fruit to support it.',45,NULL,0,'Buckeye Vyd',196751),
(313768,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'A bouquet of full, sweet fruit with attractive spice and earth accents and a rich creamy mouthfeel make this large-scale wine a real winner. Despite its plush qualities it has structure and some tannins to resolve. Already delicious, this should shine in three years. Cellar Selection.',30,NULL,0,'Pelletti Ranch',196642),
(313773,217148,'other','Zinfandel',NULL,'“Black is Black” went the old song, and this Zin does too, with blackberries, black-pepper and dark-chocolate aromas and flavors galore. An impressive wine that shows full mouthfeel, and a long finish with dusty tannins. Editors\' Choice.',30,NULL,0,'Barbieri Ranch',196642),
(313815,227505,'other','Viognier',NULL,'Toasty vanilla meets peach, apricot, and honeysuckle in a classic Viognier nose. Round in the mouth, with moderate acidity, the melon and peach flavors are brushed aside by toasty, buttery oak. Give the oak another six months to a year, then try with potato gnocchi slathered in a rich alfredo sauce. Imported by Cape Classics.',20,NULL,0,'Cape of Good Hope',197456),
(313818,227775,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Flavors of white stone fruits, peach pit and spicy oak are a surprise after a modest nose of melon. The finish carries more of the oak-spice flavors and alcoholic warmth, while the acidity seems high for this medium-bodied wine.',20,NULL,0,'Zondernaam',196689),
(313881,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Light floral and sweet herb aromas open to a mouthful of grapefruit and mineral flavors in this clean, crisp but not sharp white. The finish is tangy and bright, with stony notes. All in all an enjoyable and refreshing light Chardonnay, with some complexity and style.',12,NULL,0,'Les Mures',197404),
(313910,228459,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Dry, chalky tannins frame this woody wine with modest aromas of berry, earth and leather. The finish shows a hint of lemon and more leather, but the wood overpowers the dark berry fruit in the mouth.',12,NULL,0,'Premium Select',196839),
(313921,222448,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'From a warm area of France—the hefty body and overt sweetness virtually announce “Pays d\'Oc white.” Melon and lemon notes spread across the chewy palate. A heavy dose of candy-store sugar is partially balanced by a brisk tang on the finish.',9,NULL,0,'Milenage',197404),
(313945,222421,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Banana and popcorn vie on the nose before continuing in the mouth, where oak offers dusty vanilla flavors along with white citrus. Medium-bodied, this wine has plenty of acidity, giving it a tart finish with more popcorn flavors.',14,NULL,0,'Goat Door',197456),
(313950,222421,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Young and purple, with dark plummy fruit aromas tempered by smoke, this is another cleverly named wine from The Goats do Roam line of Charles Back. It\'s smooth, simple and easy to drink, with straightforward grape and plum flavors.',14,NULL,0,'Bored Doe',197456),
(313956,217335,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Deep, rich and spicy, and with a vineyard-driven flavor that shouldn\'t be taken lightly (it\'s from the well-regarded Sleepy Hollow and Pisoni vineyards). This is full-bodied, full-force Pinot with high alcohol (14.7%) that nonetheless maintains a semblance of balance. Cinnamon and nutmeg nuances add to the vibrant core of first-class raspberry/cherry fruit. Heft is both its bane and its beauty.',50,NULL,0,'Cuvée Niclaire Reserve',196639),
(313980,228459,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Has sweet white fruit aromas, like peaches that have been sitting in the sun too long. Citrusy in the mouth, with a medium body but a flat feel. Finishes with a hint of spice.',15,NULL,0,'Vineyards Specific',196839),
(314079,217148,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'This shows winemaker Greg LaFollette\'s master touch in the way he\'s balanced the wine and kept it harmonious. It\'s a huge mouthful of cherry pie and cassis flavor, with the most delicate notes of raspberries, toasted meringue and vanilla, subtlely spiced and dry. A gorgeous Pinot Noir that superbly combines power with elegance.',45,NULL,0,'30th Anniversary Cuvee',196642),
(314494,229862,'other','Pinot Noir',NULL,'Lightweight but flavorful with sweet vanilla accents supporting the red fruit character. A touch of popcorn toast appears in the bouquet, while the finish exhibits sweet cola spice.',26,NULL,0,'Minelli',196689),
(314495,229863,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'With only 20 cases imported, this will be a tough find but it\'s certainly well worth the hunt. This high-end Pinotage is lush and creamy, the oak-driven notes of dark chocolate and smoky cigar spice fusing seamlessly with the damson plum and dark berry preserve fruit center. Though dense and powerful, the long finish is surprisingly vibrant and spicy all at once.',75,NULL,0,'Reserve',197428),
(314537,229909,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Green plum skins, bitter lime pith, hay and pepper all dominate the nose with barely a hint of ripe fruit to be found. The mouth, however, offers a bit more ripeness to the lime and plum flavors, fleshing out the medium-weight mouth and adding depth to the wine.',12,NULL,0,'Terra D\'Aria',197484),
(314547,229863,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'With a satiny texture and softened tannins, this is a well-balanced Pinotage that\'s ready for enjoyment now. Brambly dark berry, Asian spice and sweet mesquite smoke all abound on the nose and mouth, while the long finish carries the charred woody edge even further.',55,NULL,0,'Private Cellar',197428),
(314567,229863,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Though sweeter aromas of melon, dried peach and apricot abound in the bouquet, the prominent acidity lifts the mouth and provides vibrancy to the rich fruit flavors on the palate. Woody spice and a touch of tannic astringency adds a nice texture to the finish. Drink now or through 2012.',40,NULL,0,'Private Cellar Barrel Fermented',197428),
(314596,229976,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Straightforward and easy to drink with a red fruit core of plum and cherry flavors accented by notes of black currant leaf and tea leaves. Low tannins assist in the approachable structure, and the finish is clean and juicy.',12,NULL,0,'Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot-Malbec-Petit Verdot',197557),
(314614,229863,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'The touch of oak that\'s promised on the label is delivered with subtle hints of almond and dusty spice. Otherwise, the wine is fresh and lively with assertive and zippy notes of green plum and underripe tropical fruit, all of which carry through to the mouthwatering finish. Drink now.',30,NULL,0,'Touch of Oak',197428),
(314615,229830,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Spiced meat, tomato leaf and stemmy black fruit overwhelm this wine, which might unfortunately be a bit past its prime. 69% Merlot, 27% Cabernet Franc and 4% Cabernet Sauvignon.',30,NULL,0,'The Oak Valley Blend',197462),
(314617,229909,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'There are a lot of different elements going on here, with aromas of black fruit mixing with nuances of sweet smoke and a touch of leather. Balanced and full in the mouth with moderate tannins and a solid finish. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Music by D\'Aria',197484),
(314623,230003,'other','Rhône-style Red Blend',NULL,'The SGMV (Shiraz-Grenache-Mourvèdre-Viognier) is a crowd-pleasing style of wine with a very attractive price tag. Mocha hits you first on the nose, with secondary scents of forest floor, licorice root, bramble and boysenberry unfolding shortly after. The mouth is creamy and lush and transitions into a beautiful sweet spice-infused finish.',15,NULL,0,'SGMV',197445),
(314654,230052,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'The name doesn\'t mislead or disappoint with intense mocha aromas and flavors paired with raspberry sauce and sweet spice flavors. This is a crowd-pleasing style of Pinotage with a texture like crushed satin, medium tannins and a lush but not overly opulent mouthfeel.',18,NULL,0,'Cappuccino',197445),
(314656,229976,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Fruity and herbal all at once with aromas of kirsch and black cherry competing with notes of wet forest floor and wild game. Lightweight and drinkable with a clean, fruit-driven finish.',12,NULL,0,'Shiraz-Cinsaut-Mourvèdre',197557),
(314757,230167,'other','Shiraz-Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'The alcohol is a bit too noticeable here, but overall this is a straightforward wine with nice mocha and spicy oak accents to the wild berry and red plum fruit frame. Drink now.',30,NULL,0,'Strawberry Fields',196839),
(314774,230184,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Light and easy with a great lift to the green plum, hard guava and banana notes. Lively but not overly zippy or mouth-puckering on the finish. Drink now.',9,NULL,0,'Collection',197368),
(314782,230184,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Dark berries and a touch of woody spice lead the way on the nose of this friendly Pinotage. As you settle in to the velvety texture, sultry tannins wrap around your tongue and mingle with the juicy plum and peppery spice flavors. Ready to drink now.',10,NULL,0,'Collection',197368),
(314851,230278,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'This Chenin Blanc-based sparkler is attractively light and approachable, with a fruity mélange of peach, pear and lychee aromas and flavors that are jazzed up by hints of sweet grass and pineapple-like acidity. Ripe and lively, it has brisk carbonation and a clean finish.',11,NULL,0,'Star Tree Brut Sparkling Wine',198115),
(314854,230282,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Toast and fresh hay aromas immediately waft from the glass, with supporting notes of red apple and spiced orange peel. Round and full in the mouth, it has good mousse and a soft honeyed accent that carries through onto the finish.',28,NULL,0,'Philip Jonker The Ring Blanc de Blancs Brut',196845),
(314859,230290,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'Cedar, savory balsamic, blueberry and cherry lead on this vibrant red blend from Bilton. Lots of spice, crushed herbs and berry on the palate. A touch of chocolate in the finish adds depth.',NULL,NULL,0,'Matt Black',196689),
(314873,230305,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Accents of crushed violets add interest to the wild strawberry, blackberry and plum fruit core. Mouthwatering and clean, this has dusty tannins and medium acidity that provide a nice structure.',10,NULL,0,'Wild Wine',196839),
(314916,230349,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Medium-intense spice and game aromas inflect the ripe forest-berry and cherry fruits. This is accessible and easy, with low tannins and a clean finish.',11,NULL,0,'Bain\'s Way',197445),
(314918,230349,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Bright and easy, this has direct aromas and flavors of red cherry and raspberry. It\'s light in weight, with low tannins and a short but clean finish. Drink now.',11,NULL,0,'Bain\'s Way',197445),
(314919,230278,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'This sparkler is sweet but attractive and balanced, with a lovely lychee, peach and rose water aromatic profile. The carbonation is not overly assertive, and the acidity is brisk enough to keep the finish from coming off as cloyingly sweet.',11,NULL,0,'Star Tree Cuvée Brulsand Doux Sparkling Wine',198115),
(314924,230357,'other','Rosé',NULL,'This is so intense and fruit forward, the aromas are almost like those of Fruit Roll-Ups. Notes of strawberry, raspberry and peach abound on the nose and palate, with good acidic lift that just balances all of that fruity sweetness.',12,NULL,0,'Provenance Shiraz',197428),
(315012,230448,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Crisp aromas and flavors of clove, mint, red berries and tobacco give this Shiraz a food-friendly but complex character. The minerally backbone, combined with the savory spicebox layers, offers Old World elegance with a South African twist. Ageable and a good pairing for grilled meats, filets.',48,NULL,0,'Kalkveld Hall of Enon Small Berry Pick',196845),
(315036,230477,'other','White Blend',NULL,'This approachable, fruity quaff starts with crisp citrus and tropical fruit on the nose, leading into fresh, fun, fruity flavors backed by a lively, minerally kick. Some spice on the finish gives it extra oomph. Not terribly complex, but definitely exciting.',11,NULL,0,'Celebration',197456),
(315066,230516,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Lemon, pineapple and spice aromas, followed by flavors of crisp citrus and rounded gooseberry mean this wine can pair with myriad dishes. A deft, elegant touch—with the trademark Elgin freshness and minerality—keeps the fruit from heaviness. A fun, clean wine with food pairing character.',13,NULL,0,'The Vineyards',197462),
(315067,230517,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Honeysuckle, spice and lime on the nose lead into juicy flavors of citrus and pineapple on the palate. A balanced combination of spicy oak, minerals and fresh fruit, the wine is both fun and unfolding. The Chenin Blanc and Viognier both have a prominent place here, but neither overpowers.',35,NULL,0,'Saskia',197456),
(315279,230707,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This is a beautiful Bordeaux blend, offering the kind of classic poise and exotic flair that South Africans are so good at delivering. On the nose, soft mint, chocolate, cedar and black currant beckon, and on the palate, spice and minerality mingle with the earthier elements. The structure is good, and there\'s ample complexity, but the wine is still approachable.',52,NULL,0,'Ingenium Reserve',196689),
(315438,230832,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'This is a friendly, mainstream approach to Pinotage that makes a lot of sense; with its balanced flavors of pepper, red berry and spice it has exotic appeal but is still easy to drink. The price is reasonable, making it a fun pick for ethnic dishes or grilled meats.',10,NULL,0,'Elephant',196839),
(315486,230832,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'A soft, delicate nose of spice and mocha lead on this approachable Cab from South Africa. Simple flavors of berry and tobacco and an overall integrated character make it an easy choice for everyday sipping. Could use some structure and complexity but for the price, it\'s a good buy.',10,NULL,0,'Lion',196839),
(315527,230916,'other','Sparkling Blend',NULL,'Yeasty to start, with moderate yellow fruit aromas that transfer to a soft and creamy mouthfeel. A bit too soft, though, with low acidity letting the wine get flabby. 90% Chardonnay, 10% Chenin Blanc.',19,NULL,0,'Blanc de Blanc Brut',197599),
(315551,230290,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'Rich, savory and smooth, this Bordeaux blend offers complex aromas of leather, cloves, tobacco and cedar followed by integrated layers of tobacco, cinnamon, cloves and spice. Elegant and structured, with a big, lingering finish. A beautiful example of how to marry Old and New World styles.',40,NULL,0,'Sir Percy Classic Blend',196689),
(315613,231004,'other','White Blend',NULL,'Curvy, full and luscious but underpinned with a fresh acidity that gives the wine balance, this white blend from Tulbagh Mountain has a creamy fruit and spice character that is both delicious and unique. The wine finishes with length but is clean. Could handle richer dishes but is still delicate enough to augment lighter fare.',29,NULL,0,'TMV White',197456),
(315686,231075,'other','Pinotage',NULL,'Fresh aromas of strawberry and lemon are followed in flavor on the palate of this poised and balanced rosé. A touch of oak adds spice and dimension. Overall, it\'s delicate and delicious with good acidity. A very pretty wine at a good price.',16,NULL,0,'Rosé',197420),
(315687,230864,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Zippy, grassy aromas with a touch of floral sweetness typify the nose of this wine, while on the palate, good acidity and fresh flavors are balanced by a round, complex mouthfeel. A fun Sauvignon Blanc with added character, it will pair with everything from a marinated seafood salad to richer poultry dishes.',33,NULL,0,'Single Vineyard',197484),
(315801,231004,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Fresh, clean and spicy minerality typifies this Shiraz.  Leather and berry on the nose leads to a well structured combination of flinty and rich flavors on the palate. A good South African Shiraz with its own indigenous character.',25,NULL,0,'TMV',197456),
(315843,230832,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Underneath the lively tropical fruit and grassiness, a creamy, smooth undertone balances the whole. The wine is a touch green in the nose and there are hints of it on the palate, but the rounded mouthfeel and body help to keep it in check. A simple but tasty everyday wine.',10,NULL,0,'Rhino',196839),
(316056,231354,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'This Cabernet Sauvignon-Merlot-Cabernet Franc blend is full-bodied and rich, with sweet fruit overflowing an impressive structure that seems effortless. It is near maturity, possibly benefiting from a few more years in the cellar, but those generous, full-power flavors could well be enjoyed now. Until this 2001 vintage, this wine was labeled as Reserve.',35,NULL,0,'Estate Wine',196689),
(316101,230916,'other','Chardonnay',NULL,'Nice Chard fruit has just enough oak on the nose, leading to a smooth, creamy mouth with tropical and white stone fruits whetted with mint and oak. Despite the fruitiness, this is dry, with plenty of spicy oak on the finish. Imported by wine@34south.',19,NULL,0,'Premium',197599),
(316108,230916,'other','Bordeaux-style Red Blend',NULL,'A Bordeaux blend, with 60% Cabernet Sauvignon, 16% Cabernet Franc and 24% Merlot, supposedly named because a passing Bulgarian described the wine as Magia (magical). In fact, it is in an elegant style, not hugely intense, but with good berry flavors, some herbal character and a sweet, juicy finish.',27,NULL,0,'Magia',197599),
(316145,231431,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'Don\'t let the screwcap fool you: this wine has quality written all over it. Twelve months in mostly American oak yields graham cracker and lemon aromas, with young blackberry and herbs supporting. Oak again shows in the mouth, supporting dark fruit flavors. It will be interesting to see how the big tannins age under screwcap, as this wine has years to go. Imported by Pasternak Wine Imports.',40,NULL,0,'Dark Horse',196839),
(316155,231441,'other','Chenin Blanc',NULL,'Not known for whites, Anura has crafted a very nice Chenin. This golden-hued wine exudes aromas of cooked peanuts, soy dumplings and Asian spices, all wrapped in toasty oak. Nutty and toasty in the mouth, with flavors of olive oil and spice coating moderate white stone fruit. The full, creamy mouthfeel borders on bulky. Imported by DC Imports LLC.',18,NULL,0,'Private Cellar',197445),
(316164,231441,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'A huge wine, clocking in at 15% alcohol, this liqueur-like offering has aromas of plum, mint, cinnamon and hints of  lemon. Warm, with sweet blackberry flavors to match the moderate tannins, it borders on raisiny, with plenty of oak-driven spice, and more heat on the finish. Imported by DC Imports LLC.',30,NULL,0,'Private Cellar Syrah-Mourvèdre',197445),
(316245,231514,'other','Red Blend',NULL,'This blend of 51% Cabernet Sauvignon, 38% Pinotage, and the remainder Merlot has nice aromas of balsam, red fruit, and spice. But the palate is heavy and chunky, with the 14% alcohol showing through. Sour cherry and dark berry flavors dominate, but are marred by band-aid flavors.',30,NULL,0,'Nikela',196689),
(316371,231632,'other','Sauvignon Blanc',NULL,'Tasty Sauvignon, with grass, grapefruit and slate elements in nice balance. It\'s crisp without being sharp, as too many are, and just slightly tangy on the tongue. An attractive wine with a spicy satisfying finish.',12,NULL,0,'JB',196689),
(316388,231647,'other','Sémillon',NULL,'Delicious and full bodied with fine depth of flavor and excellent texture. Ample oak compliments dry pear, herb-tinged fruit aromas and flavors. Most Chardonnays, don\'t offer this elegance, structure, or food-friendliness. Will cellar well for 4–8 years.',25,NULL,0,'Reserve',196689),
(316465,231728,'other','Shiraz',NULL,'This lightweight, juicy, organically farmed South African wine has a coffee edge to its tart berry fruit. Even on the palate, it turns harder on the finish with edgy, metallic tannins—too much for the weight and density of fruit.',12,NULL,0,'Cape Soleil',197456),
(316523,231354,'other','Port',NULL,'Tasty but very dark, even black, with a dense oak veneer over its solid fruit core. The ripe crushed blackberry and blueberry fruit and nutty accents work hard to come forward. Structured and tannic now, but should improve and open a bit more through 2006. This might really sing with less overbearing dark, toasty oak.',30,NULL,0,'Old Cape Colony',196689),
(316567,231431,'other','Cabernet Sauvignon',NULL,'Earthy red berry aromas lead to nice flavors of dark berry, leather and barnyard. Full and ripe in the mouth, with plenty of acidity and chalky tannins. Finishes hot, with a metallic feel.',40,NULL,0,'The Music Room',196839);
